insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 12, 'And he hath confirmed his words, which he spake against us, and against our judges that judged us, by bringing upon us a great evil: for under the whole heaven hath not been done as hath been done upon Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 13, 'As it is written in the law of Moses, all this evil is come upon us: yet made we not our prayer before the LORD our God, that we might turn from our iniquities, and understand thy truth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 14, 'Therefore hath the LORD watched upon the evil, and brought it upon us: for the LORD our God is righteous in all his works which he doeth: for we obeyed not his voice.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 15, 'And now, O Lord our God, that hast brought thy people forth out of the land of Egypt with a mighty hand, and hast gotten thee renown, as at this day; we have sinned, we have done wickedly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 16, 'O Lord, according to all thy righteousness, I beseech thee, let thine anger and thy fury be turned away from thy city Jerusalem, thy holy mountain: because for our sins, and for the iniquities of our fathers, Jerusalem and thy people are become a reproach to all that are about us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 17, 'Now therefore, O our God, hear the prayer of thy servant, and his supplications, and cause thy face to shine upon thy sanctuary that is desolate, for the Lord''s sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 18, 'O my God, incline thine ear, and hear; open thine eyes, and behold our desolations, and the city which is called by thy name: for we do not present our supplications before thee for our righteousnesses, but for thy great mercies.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 19, 'O Lord, hear; O Lord, forgive; O Lord, hearken and do; defer not, for thine own sake, O my God: for thy city and thy people are called by thy name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 20, 'And whiles I was speaking, and praying, and confessing my sin and the sin of my people Israel, and presenting my supplication before the LORD my God for the holy mountain of my God;'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 21, 'Yea, whiles I was speaking in prayer, even the man Gabriel, whom I had seen in the vision at the beginning, being caused to fly swiftly, touched me about the time of the evening oblation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 22, 'And he informed me, and talked with me, and said, O Daniel, I am now come forth to give thee skill and understanding.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 23, 'At the beginning of thy supplications the commandment came forth, and I am come to shew thee; for thou art greatly beloved: therefore understand the matter, and consider the vision.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 24, 'Seventy weeks are determined upon thy people and upon thy holy city, to finish the transgression, and to make an end of sins, and to make reconciliation for iniquity, and to bring in everlasting righteousness, and to seal up the vision and prophecy, and to anoint the most Holy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 25, 'Know therefore and understand, that from the going forth of the commandment to restore and to build Jerusalem unto the Messiah the Prince shall be seven weeks, and threescore and two weeks: the street shall be built again, and the wall, even in troublous times.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 26, 'And after threescore and two weeks shall Messiah be cut off, but not for himself: and the people of the prince that shall come shall destroy the city and the sanctuary; and the end thereof shall be with a flood, and unto the end of the war desolations are determined.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 9, 27, 'And he shall confirm the covenant with many for one week: and in the midst of the week he shall cause the sacrifice and the oblation to cease, and for the overspreading of abominations he shall make it desolate, even until the consummation, and that determined shall be poured upon the desolate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 1, 'In the third year of Cyrus king of Persia a thing was revealed unto Daniel, whose name was called Belteshazzar; and the thing was true, but the time appointed was long: and he understood the thing, and had understanding of the vision.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 2, 'In those days I Daniel was mourning three full weeks.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 3, 'I ate no pleasant bread, neither came flesh nor wine in my mouth, neither did I anoint myself at all, till three whole weeks were fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 4, 'And in the four and twentieth day of the first month, as I was by the side of the great river, which is Hiddekel;'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 5, 'Then I lifted up mine eyes, and looked, and behold a certain man clothed in linen, whose loins were girded with fine gold of Uphaz:'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 6, 'His body also was like the beryl, and his face as the appearance of lightning, and his eyes as lamps of fire, and his arms and his feet like in colour to polished brass, and the voice of his words like the voice of a multitude.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 7, 'And I Daniel alone saw the vision: for the men that were with me saw not the vision; but a great quaking fell upon them, so that they fled to hide themselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 8, 'Therefore I was left alone, and saw this great vision, and there remained no strength in me: for my comeliness was turned in me into corruption, and I retained no strength.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 9, 'Yet heard I the voice of his words: and when I heard the voice of his words, then was I in a deep sleep on my face, and my face toward the ground.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 10, 'And, behold, an hand touched me, which set me upon my knees and upon the palms of my hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 11, 'And he said unto me, O Daniel, a man greatly beloved, understand the words that I speak unto thee, and stand upright: for unto thee am I now sent. And when he had spoken this word unto me, I stood trembling.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 12, 'Then said he unto me, Fear not, Daniel: for from the first day that thou didst set thine heart to understand, and to chasten thyself before thy God, thy words were heard, and I am come for thy words.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 13, 'But the prince of the kingdom of Persia withstood me one and twenty days: but, lo, Michael, one of the chief princes, came to help me; and I remained there with the kings of Persia.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 14, 'Now I am come to make thee understand what shall befall thy people in the latter days: for yet the vision is for many days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 15, 'And when he had spoken such words unto me, I set my face toward the ground, and I became dumb.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 16, 'And, behold, one like the similitude of the sons of men touched my lips: then I opened my mouth, and spake, and said unto him that stood before me, O my lord, by the vision my sorrows are turned upon me, and I have retained no strength.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 17, 'For how can the servant of this my lord talk with this my lord? for as for me, straightway there remained no strength in me, neither is there breath left in me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 18, 'Then there came again and touched me one like the appearance of a man, and he strengthened me,'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 19, 'And said, O man greatly beloved, fear not: peace be unto thee, be strong, yea, be strong. And when he had spoken unto me, I was strengthened, and said, Let my lord speak; for thou hast strengthened me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 20, 'Then said he, Knowest thou wherefore I come unto thee? and now will I return to fight with the prince of Persia: and when I am gone forth, lo, the prince of Grecia shall come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 10, 21, 'But I will shew thee that which is noted in the scripture of truth: and there is none that holdeth with me in these things, but Michael your prince.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 1, 'Also I in the first year of Darius the Mede, even I, stood to confirm and to strengthen him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 2, 'And now will I shew thee the truth. Behold, there shall stand up yet three kings in Persia; and the fourth shall be far richer than they all: and by his strength through his riches he shall stir up all against the realm of Grecia.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 3, 'And a mighty king shall stand up, that shall rule with great dominion, and do according to his will.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 4, 'And when he shall stand up, his kingdom shall be broken, and shall be divided toward the four winds of heaven; and not to his posterity, nor according to his dominion which he ruled: for his kingdom shall be plucked up, even for others beside those.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 5, 'And the king of the south shall be strong, and one of his princes; and he shall be strong above him, and have dominion; his dominion shall be a great dominion.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 6, 'And in the end of years they shall join themselves together; for the king''s daughter of the south shall come to the king of the north to make an agreement: but she shall not retain the power of the arm; neither shall he stand, nor his arm: but she shall be given up, and they that brought her, and he that begat her, and he that strengthened her in these times.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 7, 'But out of a branch of her roots shall one stand up in his estate, which shall come with an army, and shall enter into the fortress of the king of the north, and shall deal against them, and shall prevail:'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 8, 'And shall also carry captives into Egypt their gods, with their princes, and with their precious vessels of silver and of gold; and he shall continue more years than the king of the north.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 9, 'So the king of the south shall come into his kingdom, and shall return into his own land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 10, 'But his sons shall be stirred up, and shall assemble a multitude of great forces: and one shall certainly come, and overflow, and pass through: then shall he return, and be stirred up, even to his fortress.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 11, 'And the king of the south shall be moved with choler, and shall come forth and fight with him, even with the king of the north: and he shall set forth a great multitude; but the multitude shall be given into his hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 12, 'And when he hath taken away the multitude, his heart shall be lifted up; and he shall cast down many ten thousands: but he shall not be strengthened by it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 13, 'For the king of the north shall return, and shall set forth a multitude greater than the former, and shall certainly come after certain years with a great army and with much riches.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 14, 'And in those times there shall many stand up against the king of the south: also the robbers of thy people shall exalt themselves to establish the vision; but they shall fall.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 15, 'So the king of the north shall come, and cast up a mount, and take the most fenced cities: and the arms of the south shall not withstand, neither his chosen people, neither shall there be any strength to withstand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 16, 'But he that cometh against him shall do according to his own will, and none shall stand before him: and he shall stand in the glorious land, which by his hand shall be consumed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 17, 'He shall also set his face to enter with the strength of his whole kingdom, and upright ones with him; thus shall he do: and he shall give him the daughter of women, corrupting her: but she shall not stand on his side, neither be for him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 18, 'After this shall he turn his face unto the isles, and shall take many: but a prince for his own behalf shall cause the reproach offered by him to cease; without his own reproach he shall cause it to turn upon him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 19, 'Then he shall turn his face toward the fort of his own land: but he shall stumble and fall, and not be found.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 20, 'Then shall stand up in his estate a raiser of taxes in the glory of the kingdom: but within few days he shall be destroyed, neither in anger, nor in battle.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 21, 'And in his estate shall stand up a vile person, to whom they shall not give the honour of the kingdom: but he shall come in peaceably, and obtain the kingdom by flatteries.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 22, 'And with the arms of a flood shall they be overflown from before him, and shall be broken; yea, also the prince of the covenant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 23, 'And after the league made with him he shall work deceitfully: for he shall come up, and shall become strong with a small people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 24, 'He shall enter peaceably even upon the fattest places of the province; and he shall do that which his fathers have not done, nor his fathers'' fathers; he shall scatter among them the prey, and spoil, and riches: yea, and he shall forecast his devices against the strong holds, even for a time.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 25, 'And he shall stir up his power and his courage against the king of the south with a great army; and the king of the south shall be stirred up to battle with a very great and mighty army; but he shall not stand: for they shall forecast devices against him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 26, 'Yea, they that feed of the portion of his meat shall destroy him, and his army shall overflow: and many shall fall down slain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 27, 'And both these kings'' hearts shall be to do mischief, and they shall speak lies at one table; but it shall not prosper: for yet the end shall be at the time appointed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 28, 'Then shall he return into his land with great riches; and his heart shall be against the holy covenant; and he shall do exploits, and return to his own land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 29, 'At the time appointed he shall return, and come toward the south; but it shall not be as the former, or as the latter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 30, 'For the ships of Chittim shall come against him: therefore he shall be grieved, and return, and have indignation against the holy covenant: so shall he do; he shall even return, and have intelligence with them that forsake the holy covenant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 31, 'And arms shall stand on his part, and they shall pollute the sanctuary of strength, and shall take away the daily sacrifice, and they shall place the abomination that maketh desolate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 32, 'And such as do wickedly against the covenant shall he corrupt by flatteries: but the people that do know their God shall be strong, and do exploits.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 33, 'And they that understand among the people shall instruct many: yet they shall fall by the sword, and by flame, by captivity, and by spoil, many days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 34, 'Now when they shall fall, they shall be holpen with a little help: but many shall cleave to them with flatteries.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 35, 'And some of them of understanding shall fall, to try them, and to purge, and to make them white, even to the time of the end: because it is yet for a time appointed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 36, 'And the king shall do according to his will; and he shall exalt himself, and magnify himself above every god, and shall speak marvellous things against the God of gods, and shall prosper till the indignation be accomplished: for that that is determined shall be done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 37, 'Neither shall he regard the God of his fathers, nor the desire of women, nor regard any god: for he shall magnify himself above all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 38, 'But in his estate shall he honour the God of forces: and a god whom his fathers knew not shall he honour with gold, and silver, and with precious stones, and pleasant things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 39, 'Thus shall he do in the most strong holds with a strange god, whom he shall acknowledge and increase with glory: and he shall cause them to rule over many, and shall divide the land for gain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 40, 'And at the time of the end shall the king of the south push at him: and the king of the north shall come against him like a whirlwind, with chariots, and with horsemen, and with many ships; and he shall enter into the countries, and shall overflow and pass over.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 41, 'He shall enter also into the glorious land, and many countries shall be overthrown: but these shall escape out of his hand, even Edom, and Moab, and the chief of the children of Ammon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 42, 'He shall stretch forth his hand also upon the countries: and the land of Egypt shall not escape.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 43, 'But he shall have power over the treasures of gold and of silver, and over all the precious things of Egypt: and the Libyans and the Ethiopians shall be at his steps.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 44, 'But tidings out of the east and out of the north shall trouble him: therefore he shall go forth with great fury to destroy, and utterly to make away many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 11, 45, 'And he shall plant the tabernacles of his palace between the seas in the glorious holy mountain; yet he shall come to his end, and none shall help him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 1, 'And at that time shall Michael stand up, the great prince which standeth for the children of thy people: and there shall be a time of trouble, such as never was since there was a nation even to that same time: and at that time thy people shall be delivered, every one that shall be found written in the book.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 2, 'And many of them that sleep in the dust of the earth shall awake, some to everlasting life, and some to shame and everlasting contempt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 3, 'And they that be wise shall shine as the brightness of the firmament; and they that turn many to righteousness as the stars for ever and ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 4, 'But thou, O Daniel, shut up the words, and seal the book, even to the time of the end: many shall run to and fro, and knowledge shall be increased.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 5, 'Then I Daniel looked, and, behold, there stood other two, the one on this side of the bank of the river, and the other on that side of the bank of the river.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 6, 'And one said to the man clothed in linen, which was upon the waters of the river, How long shall it be to the end of these wonders?'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 7, 'And I heard the man clothed in linen, which was upon the waters of the river, when he held up his right hand and his left hand unto heaven, and sware by him that liveth for ever that it shall be for a time, times, and an half; and when he shall have accomplished to scatter the power of the holy people, all these things shall be finished.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 8, 'And I heard, but I understood not: then said I, O my Lord, what shall be the end of these things?'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 9, 'And he said, Go thy way, Daniel: for the words are closed up and sealed till the time of the end.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 10, 'Many shall be purified, and made white, and tried; but the wicked shall do wickedly: and none of the wicked shall understand; but the wise shall understand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 11, 'And from the time that the daily sacrifice shall be taken away, and the abomination that maketh desolate set up, there shall be a thousand two hundred and ninety days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 12, 'Blessed is he that waiteth, and cometh to the thousand three hundred and five and thirty days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Daniel', 27, 12, 13, 'But go thou thy way till the end be: for thou shalt rest, and stand in thy lot at the end of the days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 1, 'The word of the LORD that came unto Hosea, the son of Beeri, in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 2, 'The beginning of the word of the LORD by Hosea. And the LORD said to Hosea, Go, take unto thee a wife of whoredoms and children of whoredoms: for the land hath committed great whoredom, departing from the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 3, 'So he went and took Gomer the daughter of Diblaim; which conceived, and bare him a son.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 4, 'And the LORD said unto him, Call his name Jezreel; for yet a little while, and I will avenge the blood of Jezreel upon the house of Jehu, and will cause to cease the kingdom of the house of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 5, 'And it shall come to pass at that day, that I will break the bow of Israel in the valley of Jezreel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 6, 'And she conceived again, and bare a daughter. And God said unto him, Call her name Loruhamah: for I will no more have mercy upon the house of Israel; but I will utterly take them away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 7, 'But I will have mercy upon the house of Judah, and will save them by the LORD their God, and will not save them by bow, nor by sword, nor by battle, by horses, nor by horsemen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 8, 'Now when she had weaned Loruhamah, she conceived, and bare a son.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 9, 'Then said God, Call his name Loammi: for ye are not my people, and I will not be your God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 10, 'Yet the number of the children of Israel shall be as the sand of the sea, which cannot be measured nor numbered; and it shall come to pass, that in the place where it was said unto them, Ye are not my people, there it shall be said unto them, Ye are the sons of the living God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 1, 11, 'Then shall the children of Judah and the children of Israel be gathered together, and appoint themselves one head, and they shall come up out of the land: for great shall be the day of Jezreel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 1, 'Say ye unto your brethren, Ammi; and to your sisters, Ruhamah.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 2, 'Plead with your mother, plead: for she is not my wife, neither am I her husband: let her therefore put away her whoredoms out of her sight, and her adulteries from between her breasts;'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 3, 'Lest I strip her naked, and set her as in the day that she was born, and make her as a wilderness, and set her like a dry land, and slay her with thirst.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 4, 'And I will not have mercy upon her children; for they be the children of whoredoms.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 5, 'For their mother hath played the harlot: she that conceived them hath done shamefully: for she said, I will go after my lovers, that give me my bread and my water, my wool and my flax, mine oil and my drink.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 6, 'Therefore, behold, I will hedge up thy way with thorns, and make a wall, that she shall not find her paths.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 7, 'And she shall follow after her lovers, but she shall not overtake them; and she shall seek them, but shall not find them: then shall she say, I will go and return to my first husband; for then was it better with me than now.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 8, 'For she did not know that I gave her corn, and wine, and oil, and multiplied her silver and gold, which they prepared for Baal.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 9, 'Therefore will I return, and take away my corn in the time thereof, and my wine in the season thereof, and will recover my wool and my flax given to cover her nakedness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 10, 'And now will I discover her lewdness in the sight of her lovers, and none shall deliver her out of mine hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 11, 'I will also cause all her mirth to cease, her feast days, her new moons, and her sabbaths, and all her solemn feasts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 12, 'And I will destroy her vines and her fig trees, whereof she hath said, These are my rewards that my lovers have given me: and I will make them a forest, and the beasts of the field shall eat them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 13, 'And I will visit upon her the days of Baalim, wherein she burned incense to them, and she decked herself with her earrings and her jewels, and she went after her lovers, and forgat me, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 14, 'Therefore, behold, I will allure her, and bring her into the wilderness, and speak comfortably unto her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 15, 'And I will give her her vineyards from thence, and the valley of Achor for a door of hope: and she shall sing there, as in the days of her youth, and as in the day when she came up out of the land of Egypt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 16, 'And it shall be at that day, saith the LORD, that thou shalt call me Ishi; and shalt call me no more Baali.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 17, 'For I will take away the names of Baalim out of her mouth, and they shall no more be remembered by their name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 18, 'And in that day will I make a covenant for them with the beasts of the field, and with the fowls of heaven, and with the creeping things of the ground: and I will break the bow and the sword and the battle out of the earth, and will make them to lie down safely.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 19, 'And I will betroth thee unto me for ever; yea, I will betroth thee unto me in righteousness, and in judgment, and in lovingkindness, and in mercies.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 20, 'I will even betroth thee unto me in faithfulness: and thou shalt know the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 21, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, I will hear, saith the LORD, I will hear the heavens, and they shall hear the earth;'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 22, 'And the earth shall hear the corn, and the wine, and the oil; and they shall hear Jezreel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 2, 23, 'And I will sow her unto me in the earth; and I will have mercy upon her that had not obtained mercy; and I will say to them which were not my people, Thou art my people; and they shall say, Thou art my God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 3, 1, 'Then said the LORD unto me, Go yet, love a woman beloved of her friend, yet an adulteress, according to the love of the LORD toward the children of Israel, who look to other gods, and love flagons of wine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 3, 2, 'So I bought her to me for fifteen pieces of silver, and for an homer of barley, and an half homer of barley:'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 3, 3, 'And I said unto her, Thou shalt abide for me many days; thou shalt not play the harlot, and thou shalt not be for another man: so will I also be for thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 3, 4, 'For the children of Israel shall abide many days without a king, and without a prince, and without a sacrifice, and without an image, and without an ephod, and without teraphim:'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 3, 5, 'Afterward shall the children of Israel return, and seek the LORD their God, and David their king; and shall fear the LORD and his goodness in the latter days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 1, 'Hear the word of the LORD, ye children of Israel: for the LORD hath a controversy with the inhabitants of the land, because there is no truth, nor mercy, nor knowledge of God in the land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 2, 'By swearing, and lying, and killing, and stealing, and committing adultery, they break out, and blood toucheth blood.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 3, 'Therefore shall the land mourn, and every one that dwelleth therein shall languish, with the beasts of the field, and with the fowls of heaven; yea, the fishes of the sea also shall be taken away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 4, 'Yet let no man strive, nor reprove another: for thy people are as they that strive with the priest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 5, 'Therefore shalt thou fall in the day, and the prophet also shall fall with thee in the night, and I will destroy thy mother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 6, 'My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge: because thou hast rejected knowledge, I will also reject thee, that thou shalt be no priest to me: seeing thou hast forgotten the law of thy God, I will also forget thy children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 7, 'As they were increased, so they sinned against me: therefore will I change their glory into shame.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 8, 'They eat up the sin of my people, and they set their heart on their iniquity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 9, 'And there shall be, like people, like priest: and I will punish them for their ways, and reward them their doings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 10, 'For they shall eat, and not have enough: they shall commit whoredom, and shall not increase: because they have left off to take heed to the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 11, 'Whoredom and wine and new wine take away the heart.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 12, 'My people ask counsel at their stocks, and their staff declareth unto them: for the spirit of whoredoms hath caused them to err, and they have gone a whoring from under their God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 13, 'They sacrifice upon the tops of the mountains, and burn incense upon the hills, under oaks and poplars and elms, because the shadow thereof is good: therefore your daughters shall commit whoredom, and your spouses shall commit adultery.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 14, 'I will not punish your daughters when they commit whoredom, nor your spouses when they commit adultery: for themselves are separated with whores, and they sacrifice with harlots: therefore the people that doth not understand shall fall.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 15, 'Though thou, Israel, play the harlot, yet let not Judah offend; and come not ye unto Gilgal, neither go ye up to Bethaven, nor swear, The LORD liveth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 16, 'For Israel slideth back as a backsliding heifer: now the LORD will feed them as a lamb in a large place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 17, 'Ephraim is joined to idols: let him alone.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 18, 'Their drink is sour: they have committed whoredom continually: her rulers with shame do love, Give ye.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 4, 19, 'The wind hath bound her up in her wings, and they shall be ashamed because of their sacrifices.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 1, 'Hear ye this, O priests; and hearken, ye house of Israel; and give ye ear, O house of the king; for judgment is toward you, because ye have been a snare on Mizpah, and a net spread upon Tabor.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 2, 'And the revolters are profound to make slaughter, though I have been a rebuker of them all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 3, 'I know Ephraim, and Israel is not hid from me: for now, O Ephraim, thou committest whoredom, and Israel is defiled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 4, 'They will not frame their doings to turn unto their God: for the spirit of whoredoms is in the midst of them, and they have not known the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 5, 'And the pride of Israel doth testify to his face: therefore shall Israel and Ephraim fall in their iniquity; Judah also shall fall with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 6, 'They shall go with their flocks and with their herds to seek the LORD; but they shall not find him; he hath withdrawn himself from them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 7, 'They have dealt treacherously against the LORD: for they have begotten strange children: now shall a month devour them with their portions.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 8, 'Blow ye the cornet in Gibeah, and the trumpet in Ramah: cry aloud at Bethaven, after thee, O Benjamin.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 9, 'Ephraim shall be desolate in the day of rebuke: among the tribes of Israel have I made known that which shall surely be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 10, 'The princes of Judah were like them that remove the bound: therefore I will pour out my wrath upon them like water.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 11, 'Ephraim is oppressed and broken in judgment, because he willingly walked after the commandment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 12, 'Therefore will I be unto Ephraim as a moth, and to the house of Judah as rottenness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 13, 'When Ephraim saw his sickness, and Judah saw his wound, then went Ephraim to the Assyrian, and sent to king Jareb: yet could he not heal you, nor cure you of your wound.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 14, 'For I will be unto Ephraim as a lion, and as a young lion to the house of Judah: I, even I, will tear and go away; I will take away, and none shall rescue him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 5, 15, 'I will go and return to my place, till they acknowledge their offence, and seek my face: in their affliction they will seek me early.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 1, 'Come, and let us return unto the LORD: for he hath torn, and he will heal us; he hath smitten, and he will bind us up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 2, 'After two days will he revive us: in the third day he will raise us up, and we shall live in his sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 3, 'Then shall we know, if we follow on to know the LORD: his going forth is prepared as the morning; and he shall come unto us as the rain, as the latter and former rain unto the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 4, 'O Ephraim, what shall I do unto thee? O Judah, what shall I do unto thee? for your goodness is as a morning cloud, and as the early dew it goeth away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 5, 'Therefore have I hewed them by the prophets; I have slain them by the words of my mouth: and thy judgments are as the light that goeth forth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 6, 'For I desired mercy, and not sacrifice; and the knowledge of God more than burnt offerings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 7, 'But they like men have transgressed the covenant: there have they dealt treacherously against me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 8, 'Gilead is a city of them that work iniquity, and is polluted with blood.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 9, 'And as troops of robbers wait for a man, so the company of priests murder in the way by consent: for they commit lewdness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 10, 'I have seen an horrible thing in the house of Israel: there is the whoredom of Ephraim, Israel is defiled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 6, 11, 'Also, O Judah, he hath set an harvest for thee, when I returned the captivity of my people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 1, 'When I would have healed Israel, then the iniquity of Ephraim was discovered, and the wickedness of Samaria: for they commit falsehood; and the thief cometh in, and the troop of robbers spoileth without.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 2, 'And they consider not in their hearts that I remember all their wickedness: now their own doings have beset them about; they are before my face.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 3, 'They make the king glad with their wickedness, and the princes with their lies.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 4, 'They are all adulterers, as an oven heated by the baker, who ceaseth from raising after he hath kneaded the dough, until it be leavened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 5, 'In the day of our king the princes have made him sick with bottles of wine; he stretched out his hand with scorners.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 6, 'For they have made ready their heart like an oven, whiles they lie in wait: their baker sleepeth all the night; in the morning it burneth as a flaming fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 7, 'They are all hot as an oven, and have devoured their judges; all their kings are fallen: there is none among them that calleth unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 8, 'Ephraim, he hath mixed himself among the people; Ephraim is a cake not turned.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 9, 'Strangers have devoured his strength, and he knoweth it not: yea, gray hairs are here and there upon him, yet he knoweth not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 10, 'And the pride of Israel testifieth to his face: and they do not return to the LORD their God, nor seek him for all this.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 11, 'Ephraim also is like a silly dove without heart: they call to Egypt, they go to Assyria.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 12, 'When they shall go, I will spread my net upon them; I will bring them down as the fowls of the heaven; I will chastise them, as their congregation hath heard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 13, 'Woe unto them! for they have fled from me: destruction unto them! because they have transgressed against me: though I have redeemed them, yet they have spoken lies against me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 14, 'And they have not cried unto me with their heart, when they howled upon their beds: they assemble themselves for corn and wine, and they rebel against me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 15, 'Though I have bound and strengthened their arms, yet do they imagine mischief against me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 7, 16, 'They return, but not to the most High: they are like a deceitful bow: their princes shall fall by the sword for the rage of their tongue: this shall be their derision in the land of Egypt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 1, 'Set the trumpet to thy mouth. He shall come as an eagle against the house of the LORD, because they have transgressed my covenant, and trespassed against my law.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 2, 'Israel shall cry unto me, My God, we know thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 3, 'Israel hath cast off the thing that is good: the enemy shall pursue him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 4, 'They have set up kings, but not by me: they have made princes, and I knew it not: of their silver and their gold have they made them idols, that they may be cut off.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 5, 'Thy calf, O Samaria, hath cast thee off; mine anger is kindled against them: how long will it be ere they attain to innocency?'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 6, 'For from Israel was it also: the workman made it; therefore it is not God: but the calf of Samaria shall be broken in pieces.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 7, 'For they have sown the wind, and they shall reap the whirlwind: it hath no stalk: the bud shall yield no meal: if so be it yield, the strangers shall swallow it up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 8, 'Israel is swallowed up: now shall they be among the Gentiles as a vessel wherein is no pleasure.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 9, 'For they are gone up to Assyria, a wild ass alone by himself: Ephraim hath hired lovers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 10, 'Yea, though they have hired among the nations, now will I gather them, and they shall sorrow a little for the burden of the king of princes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 11, 'Because Ephraim hath made many altars to sin, altars shall be unto him to sin.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 12, 'I have written to him the great things of my law, but they were counted as a strange thing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 13, 'They sacrifice flesh for the sacrifices of mine offerings, and eat it; but the LORD accepteth them not; now will he remember their iniquity, and visit their sins: they shall return to Egypt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 8, 14, 'For Israel hath forgotten his Maker, and buildeth temples; and Judah hath multiplied fenced cities: but I will send a fire upon his cities, and it shall devour the palaces thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 1, 'Rejoice not, O Israel, for joy, as other people: for thou hast gone a whoring from thy God, thou hast loved a reward upon every cornfloor.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 2, 'The floor and the winepress shall not feed them, and the new wine shall fail in her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 3, 'They shall not dwell in the LORD''S land; but Ephraim shall return to Egypt, and they shall eat unclean things in Assyria.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 4, 'They shall not offer wine offerings to the LORD, neither shall they be pleasing unto him: their sacrifices shall be unto them as the bread of mourners; all that eat thereof shall be polluted: for their bread for their soul shall not come into the house of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 5, 'What will ye do in the solemn day, and in the day of the feast of the LORD?'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 6, 'For, lo, they are gone because of destruction: Egypt shall gather them up, Memphis shall bury them: the pleasant places for their silver, nettles shall possess them: thorns shall be in their tabernacles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 7, 'The days of visitation are come, the days of recompence are come; Israel shall know it: the prophet is a fool, the spiritual man is mad, for the multitude of thine iniquity, and the great hatred.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 8, 'The watchman of Ephraim was with my God: but the prophet is a snare of a fowler in all his ways, and hatred in the house of his God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 9, 'They have deeply corrupted themselves, as in the days of Gibeah: therefore he will remember their iniquity, he will visit their sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 10, 'I found Israel like grapes in the wilderness; I saw your fathers as the firstripe in the fig tree at her first time: but they went to Baalpeor, and separated themselves unto that shame; and their abominations were according as they loved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 11, 'As for Ephraim, their glory shall fly away like a bird, from the birth, and from the womb, and from the conception.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 12, 'Though they bring up their children, yet will I bereave them, that there shall not be a man left: yea, woe also to them when I depart from them!'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 13, 'Ephraim, as I saw Tyrus, is planted in a pleasant place: but Ephraim shall bring forth his children to the murderer.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 14, 'Give them, O LORD: what wilt thou give? give them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 15, 'All their wickedness is in Gilgal: for there I hated them: for the wickedness of their doings I will drive them out of mine house, I will love them no more: all their princes are revolters.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 16, 'Ephraim is smitten, their root is dried up, they shall bear no fruit: yea, though they bring forth, yet will I slay even the beloved fruit of their womb.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 9, 17, 'My God will cast them away, because they did not hearken unto him: and they shall be wanderers among the nations.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 1, 'Israel is an empty vine, he bringeth forth fruit unto himself: according to the multitude of his fruit he hath increased the altars; according to the goodness of his land they have made goodly images.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 2, 'Their heart is divided; now shall they be found faulty: he shall break down their altars, he shall spoil their images.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 3, 'For now they shall say, We have no king, because we feared not the LORD; what then should a king do to us?'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 4, 'They have spoken words, swearing falsely in making a covenant: thus judgment springeth up as hemlock in the furrows of the field.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 5, 'The inhabitants of Samaria shall fear because of the calves of Bethaven: for the people thereof shall mourn over it, and the priests thereof that rejoiced on it, for the glory thereof, because it is departed from it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 6, 'It shall be also carried unto Assyria for a present to king Jareb: Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 7, 'As for Samaria, her king is cut off as the foam upon the water.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 8, 'The high places also of Aven, the sin of Israel, shall be destroyed: the thorn and the thistle shall come up on their altars; and they shall say to the mountains, Cover us; and to the hills, Fall on us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 9, 'O Israel, thou hast sinned from the days of Gibeah: there they stood: the battle in Gibeah against the children of iniquity did not overtake them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 10, 'It is in my desire that I should chastise them; and the people shall be gathered against them, when they shall bind themselves in their two furrows.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 11, 'And Ephraim is as an heifer that is taught, and loveth to tread out the corn; but I passed over upon her fair neck: I will make Ephraim to ride; Judah shall plow, and Jacob shall break his clods.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 12, 'Sow to yourselves in righteousness, reap in mercy; break up your fallow ground: for it is time to seek the LORD, till he come and rain righteousness upon you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 13, 'Ye have plowed wickedness, ye have reaped iniquity; ye have eaten the fruit of lies: because thou didst trust in thy way, in the multitude of thy mighty men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 14, 'Therefore shall a tumult arise among thy people, and all thy fortresses shall be spoiled, as Shalman spoiled Betharbel in the day of battle: the mother was dashed in pieces upon her children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 10, 15, 'So shall Bethel do unto you because of your great wickedness: in a morning shall the king of Israel utterly be cut off.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 1, 'When Israel was a child, then I loved him, and called my son out of Egypt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 2, 'As they called them, so they went from them: they sacrificed unto Baalim, and burned incense to graven images.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 3, 'I taught Ephraim also to go, taking them by their arms; but they knew not that I healed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 4, 'I drew them with cords of a man, with bands of love: and I was to them as they that take off the yoke on their jaws, and I laid meat unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 5, 'He shall not return into the land of Egypt, but the Assyrian shall be his king, because they refused to return.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 6, 'And the sword shall abide on his cities, and shall consume his branches, and devour them, because of their own counsels.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 7, 'And my people are bent to backsliding from me: though they called them to the most High, none at all would exalt him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 8, 'How shall I give thee up, Ephraim? how shall I deliver thee, Israel? how shall I make thee as Admah? how shall I set thee as Zeboim? mine heart is turned within me, my repentings are kindled together.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 9, 'I will not execute the fierceness of mine anger, I will not return to destroy Ephraim: for I am God, and not man; the Holy One in the midst of thee: and I will not enter into the city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 10, 'They shall walk after the LORD: he shall roar like a lion: when he shall roar, then the children shall tremble from the west.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 11, 'They shall tremble as a bird out of Egypt, and as a dove out of the land of Assyria: and I will place them in their houses, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 11, 12, 'Ephraim compasseth me about with lies, and the house of Israel with deceit: but Judah yet ruleth with God, and is faithful with the saints.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 1, 'Ephraim feedeth on wind, and followeth after the east wind: he daily increaseth lies and desolation; and they do make a covenant with the Assyrians, and oil is carried into Egypt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 2, 'The LORD hath also a controversy with Judah, and will punish Jacob according to his ways; according to his doings will he recompense him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 3, 'He took his brother by the heel in the womb, and by his strength he had power with God:'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 4, 'Yea, he had power over the angel, and prevailed: he wept, and made supplication unto him: he found him in Bethel, and there he spake with us;'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 5, 'Even the LORD God of hosts; the LORD is his memorial.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 6, 'Therefore turn thou to thy God: keep mercy and judgment, and wait on thy God continually.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 7, 'He is a merchant, the balances of deceit are in his hand: he loveth to oppress.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 8, 'And Ephraim said, Yet I am become rich, I have found me out substance: in all my labours they shall find none iniquity in me that were sin.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 9, 'And I that am the LORD thy God from the land of Egypt will yet make thee to dwell in tabernacles, as in the days of the solemn feast.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 10, 'I have also spoken by the prophets, and I have multiplied visions, and used similitudes, by the ministry of the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 11, 'Is there iniquity in Gilead? surely they are vanity: they sacrifice bullocks in Gilgal; yea, their altars are as heaps in the furrows of the fields.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 12, 'And Jacob fled into the country of Syria, and Israel served for a wife, and for a wife he kept sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 13, 'And by a prophet the LORD brought Israel out of Egypt, and by a prophet was he preserved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 12, 14, 'Ephraim provoked him to anger most bitterly: therefore shall he leave his blood upon him, and his reproach shall his Lord return unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 1, 'When Ephraim spake trembling, he exalted himself in Israel; but when he offended in Baal, he died.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 2, 'And now they sin more and more, and have made them molten images of their silver, and idols according to their own understanding, all of it the work of the craftsmen: they say of them, Let the men that sacrifice kiss the calves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 3, 'Therefore they shall be as the morning cloud, and as the early dew that passeth away, as the chaff that is driven with the whirlwind out of the floor, and as the smoke out of the chimney.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 4, 'Yet I am the LORD thy God from the land of Egypt, and thou shalt know no god but me: for there is no saviour beside me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 5, 'I did know thee in the wilderness, in the land of great drought.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 6, 'According to their pasture, so were they filled; they were filled, and their heart was exalted; therefore have they forgotten me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 7, 'Therefore I will be unto them as a lion: as a leopard by the way will I observe them:'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 8, 'I will meet them as a bear that is bereaved of her whelps, and will rend the caul of their heart, and there will I devour them like a lion: the wild beast shall tear them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 9, 'O Israel, thou hast destroyed thyself; but in me is thine help.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 10, 'I will be thy king: where is any other that may save thee in all thy cities? and thy judges of whom thou saidst, Give me a king and princes?'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 11, 'I gave thee a king in mine anger, and took him away in my wrath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 12, 'The iniquity of Ephraim is bound up; his sin is hid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 13, 'The sorrows of a travailing woman shall come upon him: he is an unwise son; for he should not stay long in the place of the breaking forth of children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 14, 'I will ransom them from the power of the grave; I will redeem them from death: O death, I will be thy plagues; O grave, I will be thy destruction: repentance shall be hid from mine eyes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 15, 'Though he be fruitful among his brethren, an east wind shall come, the wind of the LORD shall come up from the wilderness, and his spring shall become dry, and his fountain shall be dried up: he shall spoil the treasure of all pleasant vessels.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 13, 16, 'Samaria shall become desolate; for she hath rebelled against her God: they shall fall by the sword: their infants shall be dashed in pieces, and their women with child shall be ripped up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 1, 'O Israel, return unto the LORD thy God; for thou hast fallen by thine iniquity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 2, 'Take with you words, and turn to the LORD: say unto him, Take away all iniquity, and receive us graciously: so will we render the calves of our lips.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 3, 'Asshur shall not save us; we will not ride upon horses: neither will we say any more to the work of our hands, Ye are our gods: for in thee the fatherless findeth mercy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 4, 'I will heal their backsliding, I will love them freely: for mine anger is turned away from him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 5, 'I will be as the dew unto Israel: he shall grow as the lily, and cast forth his roots as Lebanon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 6, 'His branches shall spread, and his beauty shall be as the olive tree, and his smell as Lebanon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 7, 'They that dwell under his shadow shall return; they shall revive as the corn, and grow as the vine: the scent thereof shall be as the wine of Lebanon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 8, 'Ephraim shall say, What have I to do any more with idols? I have heard him, and observed him: I am like a green fir tree. From me is thy fruit found.'),
  ('KJV', 'Hosea', 28, 14, 9, 'Who is wise, and he shall understand these things? prudent, and he shall know them? for the ways of the LORD are right, and the just shall walk in them: but the transgressors shall fall therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 1, 'The word of the LORD that came to Joel the son of Pethuel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 2, 'Hear this, ye old men, and give ear, all ye inhabitants of the land. Hath this been in your days, or even in the days of your fathers?'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 3, 'Tell ye your children of it, and let your children tell their children, and their children another generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 4, 'That which the palmerworm hath left hath the locust eaten; and that which the locust hath left hath the cankerworm eaten; and that which the cankerworm hath left hath the caterpiller eaten.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 5, 'Awake, ye drunkards, and weep; and howl, all ye drinkers of wine, because of the new wine; for it is cut off from your mouth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 6, 'For a nation is come up upon my land, strong, and without number, whose teeth are the teeth of a lion, and he hath the cheek teeth of a great lion.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 7, 'He hath laid my vine waste, and barked my fig tree: he hath made it clean bare, and cast it away; the branches thereof are made white.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 8, 'Lament like a virgin girded with sackcloth for the husband of her youth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 9, 'The meat offering and the drink offering is cut off from the house of the LORD; the priests, the LORD''S ministers, mourn.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 10, 'The field is wasted, the land mourneth; for the corn is wasted: the new wine is dried up, the oil languisheth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 11, 'Be ye ashamed, O ye husbandmen; howl, O ye vinedressers, for the wheat and for the barley; because the harvest of the field is perished.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 12, 'The vine is dried up, and the fig tree languisheth; the pomegranate tree, the palm tree also, and the apple tree, even all the trees of the field, are withered: because joy is withered away from the sons of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 13, 'Gird yourselves, and lament, ye priests: howl, ye ministers of the altar: come, lie all night in sackcloth, ye ministers of my God: for the meat offering and the drink offering is withholden from the house of your God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 14, 'Sanctify ye a fast, call a solemn assembly, gather the elders and all the inhabitants of the land into the house of the LORD your God, and cry unto the LORD,'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 15, 'Alas for the day! for the day of the LORD is at hand, and as a destruction from the Almighty shall it come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 16, 'Is not the meat cut off before our eyes, yea, joy and gladness from the house of our God?'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 17, 'The seed is rotten under their clods, the garners are laid desolate, the barns are broken down; for the corn is withered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 18, 'How do the beasts groan! the herds of cattle are perplexed, because they have no pasture; yea, the flocks of sheep are made desolate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 19, 'O LORD, to thee will I cry: for the fire hath devoured the pastures of the wilderness, and the flame hath burned all the trees of the field.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 1, 20, 'The beasts of the field cry also unto thee: for the rivers of waters are dried up, and the fire hath devoured the pastures of the wilderness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 1, 'Blow ye the trumpet in Zion, and sound an alarm in my holy mountain: let all the inhabitants of the land tremble: for the day of the LORD cometh, for it is nigh at hand;'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 2, 'A day of darkness and of gloominess, a day of clouds and of thick darkness, as the morning spread upon the mountains: a great people and a strong; there hath not been ever the like, neither shall be any more after it, even to the years of many generations.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 3, 'A fire devoureth before them; and behind them a flame burneth: the land is as the garden of Eden before them, and behind them a desolate wilderness; yea, and nothing shall escape them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 4, 'The appearance of them is as the appearance of horses; and as horsemen, so shall they run.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 5, 'Like the noise of chariots on the tops of mountains shall they leap, like the noise of a flame of fire that devoureth the stubble, as a strong people set in battle array.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 6, 'Before their face the people shall be much pained: all faces shall gather blackness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 7, 'They shall run like mighty men; they shall climb the wall like men of war; and they shall march every one on his ways, and they shall not break their ranks:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 8, 'Neither shall one thrust another; they shall walk every one in his path: and when they fall upon the sword, they shall not be wounded.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 9, 'They shall run to and fro in the city; they shall run upon the wall, they shall climb up upon the houses; they shall enter in at the windows like a thief.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 10, 'The earth shall quake before them; the heavens shall tremble: the sun and the moon shall be dark, and the stars shall withdraw their shining:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 11, 'And the LORD shall utter his voice before his army: for his camp is very great: for he is strong that executeth his word: for the day of the LORD is great and very terrible; and who can abide it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 12, 'Therefore also now, saith the LORD, turn ye even to me with all your heart, and with fasting, and with weeping, and with mourning:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 13, 'And rend your heart, and not your garments, and turn unto the LORD your God: for he is gracious and merciful, slow to anger, and of great kindness, and repenteth him of the evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 14, 'Who knoweth if he will return and repent, and leave a blessing behind him; even a meat offering and a drink offering unto the LORD your God?'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 15, 'Blow the trumpet in Zion, sanctify a fast, call a solemn assembly:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 16, 'Gather the people, sanctify the congregation, assemble the elders, gather the children, and those that suck the breasts: let the bridegroom go forth of his chamber, and the bride out of her closet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 17, 'Let the priests, the ministers of the LORD, weep between the porch and the altar, and let them say, Spare thy people, O LORD, and give not thine heritage to reproach, that the heathen should rule over them: wherefore should they say among the people, Where is their God?'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 18, 'Then will the LORD be jealous for his land, and pity his people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 19, 'Yea, the LORD will answer and say unto his people, Behold, I will send you corn, and wine, and oil, and ye shall be satisfied therewith: and I will no more make you a reproach among the heathen:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 20, 'But I will remove far off from you the northern army, and will drive him into a land barren and desolate, with his face toward the east sea, and his hinder part toward the utmost sea, and his stink shall come up, and his ill savour shall come up, because he hath done great things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 21, 'Fear not, O land; be glad and rejoice: for the LORD will do great things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 22, 'Be not afraid, ye beasts of the field: for the pastures of the wilderness do spring, for the tree beareth her fruit, the fig tree and the vine do yield their strength.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 23, 'Be glad then, ye children of Zion, and rejoice in the LORD your God: for he hath given you the former rain moderately, and he will cause to come down for you the rain, the former rain, and the latter rain in the first month.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 24, 'And the floors shall be full of wheat, and the fats shall overflow with wine and oil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 25, 'And I will restore to you the years that the locust hath eaten, the cankerworm, and the caterpiller, and the palmerworm, my great army which I sent among you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 26, 'And ye shall eat in plenty, and be satisfied, and praise the name of the LORD your God, that hath dealt wondrously with you: and my people shall never be ashamed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 27, 'And ye shall know that I am in the midst of Israel, and that I am the LORD your God, and none else: and my people shall never be ashamed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 28, 'And it shall come to pass afterward, that I will pour out my spirit upon all flesh; and your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, your old men shall dream dreams, your young men shall see visions:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 29, 'And also upon the servants and upon the handmaids in those days will I pour out my spirit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 30, 'And I will shew wonders in the heavens and in the earth, blood, and fire, and pillars of smoke.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 31, 'The sun shall be turned into darkness, and the moon into blood, before the great and the terrible day of the LORD come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 2, 32, 'And it shall come to pass, that whosoever shall call on the name of the LORD shall be delivered: for in mount Zion and in Jerusalem shall be deliverance, as the LORD hath said, and in the remnant whom the LORD shall call.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 1, 'For, behold, in those days, and in that time, when I shall bring again the captivity of Judah and Jerusalem,'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 2, 'I will also gather all nations, and will bring them down into the valley of Jehoshaphat, and will plead with them there for my people and for my heritage Israel, whom they have scattered among the nations, and parted my land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 3, 'And they have cast lots for my people; and have given a boy for an harlot, and sold a girl for wine, that they might drink.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 4, 'Yea, and what have ye to do with me, O Tyre, and Zidon, and all the coasts of Palestine? will ye render me a recompence? and if ye recompense me, swiftly and speedily will I return your recompence upon your own head;'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 5, 'Because ye have taken my silver and my gold, and have carried into your temples my goodly pleasant things:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 6, 'The children also of Judah and the children of Jerusalem have ye sold unto the Grecians, that ye might remove them far from their border.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 7, 'Behold, I will raise them out of the place whither ye have sold them, and will return your recompence upon your own head:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 8, 'And I will sell your sons and your daughters into the hand of the children of Judah, and they shall sell them to the Sabeans, to a people far off: for the LORD hath spoken it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 9, 'Proclaim ye this among the Gentiles; Prepare war, wake up the mighty men, let all the men of war draw near; let them come up:'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 10, 'Beat your plowshares into swords, and your pruninghooks into spears: let the weak say, I am strong.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 11, 'Assemble yourselves, and come, all ye heathen, and gather yourselves together round about: thither cause thy mighty ones to come down, O LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 12, 'Let the heathen be wakened, and come up to the valley of Jehoshaphat: for there will I sit to judge all the heathen round about.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 13, 'Put ye in the sickle, for the harvest is ripe: come, get you down; for the press is full, the fats overflow; for their wickedness is great.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 14, 'Multitudes, multitudes in the valley of decision: for the day of the LORD is near in the valley of decision.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 15, 'The sun and the moon shall be darkened, and the stars shall withdraw their shining.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 16, 'The LORD also shall roar out of Zion, and utter his voice from Jerusalem; and the heavens and the earth shall shake: but the LORD will be the hope of his people, and the strength of the children of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 17, 'So shall ye know that I am the LORD your God dwelling in Zion, my holy mountain: then shall Jerusalem be holy, and there shall no strangers pass through her any more.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 18, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that the mountains shall drop down new wine, and the hills shall flow with milk, and all the rivers of Judah shall flow with waters, and a fountain shall come forth of the house of the LORD, and shall water the valley of Shittim.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 19, 'Egypt shall be a desolation, and Edom shall be a desolate wilderness, for the violence against the children of Judah, because they have shed innocent blood in their land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 20, 'But Judah shall dwell for ever, and Jerusalem from generation to generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Joel', 29, 3, 21, 'For I will cleanse their blood that I have not cleansed: for the LORD dwelleth in Zion.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 1, 'The words of Amos, who was among the herdmen of Tekoa, which he saw concerning Israel in the days of Uzziah king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam the son of Joash king of Israel, two years before the earthquake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 2, 'And he said, The LORD will roar from Zion, and utter his voice from Jerusalem; and the habitations of the shepherds shall mourn, and the top of Carmel shall wither.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 3, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Damascus, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they have threshed Gilead with threshing instruments of iron:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 4, 'But I will send a fire into the house of Hazael, which shall devour the palaces of Benhadad.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 5, 'I will break also the bar of Damascus, and cut off the inhabitant from the plain of Aven, and him that holdeth the sceptre from the house of Eden: and the people of Syria shall go into captivity unto Kir, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 6, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Gaza, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they carried away captive the whole captivity, to deliver them up to Edom:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 7, 'But I will send a fire on the wall of Gaza, which shall devour the palaces thereof:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 8, 'And I will cut off the inhabitant from Ashdod, and him that holdeth the sceptre from Ashkelon, and I will turn mine hand against Ekron: and the remnant of the Philistines shall perish, saith the Lord GOD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 9, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Tyrus, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they delivered up the whole captivity to Edom, and remembered not the brotherly covenant:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 10, 'But I will send a fire on the wall of Tyrus, which shall devour the palaces thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 11, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Edom, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because he did pursue his brother with the sword, and did cast off all pity, and his anger did tear perpetually, and he kept his wrath for ever:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 12, 'But I will send a fire upon Teman, which shall devour the palaces of Bozrah.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 13, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of the children of Ammon, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they have ripped up the women with child of Gilead, that they might enlarge their border:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 14, 'But I will kindle a fire in the wall of Rabbah, and it shall devour the palaces thereof, with shouting in the day of battle, with a tempest in the day of the whirlwind:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 1, 15, 'And their king shall go into captivity, he and his princes together, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 1, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Moab, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because he burned the bones of the king of Edom into lime:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 2, 'But I will send a fire upon Moab, and it shall devour the palaces of Kerioth: and Moab shall die with tumult, with shouting, and with the sound of the trumpet:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 3, 'And I will cut off the judge from the midst thereof, and will slay all the princes thereof with him, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 4, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Judah, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they have despised the law of the LORD, and have not kept his commandments, and their lies caused them to err, after the which their fathers have walked:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 5, 'But I will send a fire upon Judah, and it shall devour the palaces of Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 6, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Israel, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because they sold the righteous for silver, and the poor for a pair of shoes;'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 7, 'That pant after the dust of the earth on the head of the poor, and turn aside the way of the meek: and a man and his father will go in unto the same maid, to profane my holy name:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 8, 'And they lay themselves down upon clothes laid to pledge by every altar, and they drink the wine of the condemned in the house of their god.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 9, 'Yet destroyed I the Amorite before them, whose height was like the height of the cedars, and he was strong as the oaks; yet I destroyed his fruit from above, and his roots from beneath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 10, 'Also I brought you up from the land of Egypt, and led you forty years through the wilderness, to possess the land of the Amorite.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 11, 'And I raised up of your sons for prophets, and of your young men for Nazarites. Is it not even thus, O ye children of Israel? saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 12, 'But ye gave the Nazarites wine to drink; and commanded the prophets, saying, Prophesy not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 13, 'Behold, I am pressed under you, as a cart is pressed that is full of sheaves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 14, 'Therefore the flight shall perish from the swift, and the strong shall not strengthen his force, neither shall the mighty deliver himself:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 15, 'Neither shall he stand that handleth the bow; and he that is swift of foot shall not deliver himself: neither shall he that rideth the horse deliver himself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 2, 16, 'And he that is courageous among the mighty shall flee away naked in that day, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 1, 'Hear this word that the LORD hath spoken against you, O children of Israel, against the whole family which I brought up from the land of Egypt, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 2, 'You only have I known of all the families of the earth: therefore I will punish you for all your iniquities.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 3, 'Can two walk together, except they be agreed?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 4, 'Will a lion roar in the forest, when he hath no prey? will a young lion cry out of his den, if he have taken nothing?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 5, 'Can a bird fall in a snare upon the earth, where no gin is for him? shall one take up a snare from the earth, and have taken nothing at all?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 6, 'Shall a trumpet be blown in the city, and the people not be afraid? shall there be evil in a city, and the LORD hath not done it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 7, 'Surely the Lord GOD will do nothing, but he revealeth his secret unto his servants the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 8, 'The lion hath roared, who will not fear? the Lord GOD hath spoken, who can but prophesy?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 9, 'Publish in the palaces at Ashdod, and in the palaces in the land of Egypt, and say, Assemble yourselves upon the mountains of Samaria, and behold the great tumults in the midst thereof, and the oppressed in the midst thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 10, 'For they know not to do right, saith the LORD, who store up violence and robbery in their palaces.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 11, 'Therefore thus saith the Lord GOD; An adversary there shall be even round about the land; and he shall bring down thy strength from thee, and thy palaces shall be spoiled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 12, 'Thus saith the LORD; As the shepherd taketh out of the mouth of the lion two legs, or a piece of an ear; so shall the children of Israel be taken out that dwell in Samaria in the corner of a bed, and in Damascus in a couch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 13, 'Hear ye, and testify in the house of Jacob, saith the Lord GOD, the God of hosts,'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 14, 'That in the day that I shall visit the transgressions of Israel upon him I will also visit the altars of Bethel: and the horns of the altar shall be cut off, and fall to the ground.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 3, 15, 'And I will smite the winter house with the summer house; and the houses of ivory shall perish, and the great houses shall have an end, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 1, 'Hear this word, ye kine of Bashan, that are in the mountain of Samaria, which oppress the poor, which crush the needy, which say to their masters, Bring, and let us drink.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 2, 'The Lord GOD hath sworn by his holiness, that, lo, the days shall come upon you, that he will take you away with hooks, and your posterity with fishhooks.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 3, 'And ye shall go out at the breaches, every cow at that which is before her; and ye shall cast them into the palace, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 4, 'Come to Bethel, and transgress; at Gilgal multiply transgression; and bring your sacrifices every morning, and your tithes after three years:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 5, 'And offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving with leaven, and proclaim and publish the free offerings: for this liketh you, O ye children of Israel, saith the Lord GOD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 6, 'And I also have given you cleanness of teeth in all your cities, and want of bread in all your places: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 7, 'And also I have withholden the rain from you, when there were yet three months to the harvest: and I caused it to rain upon one city, and caused it not to rain upon another city: one piece was rained upon, and the piece whereupon it rained not withered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 8, 'So two or three cities wandered unto one city, to drink water; but they were not satisfied: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 9, 'I have smitten you with blasting and mildew: when your gardens and your vineyards and your fig trees and your olive trees increased, the palmerworm devoured them: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 10, 'I have sent among you the pestilence after the manner of Egypt: your young men have I slain with the sword, and have taken away your horses; and I have made the stink of your camps to come up unto your nostrils: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 11, 'I have overthrown some of you, as God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah, and ye were as a firebrand plucked out of the burning: yet have ye not returned unto me, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 12, 'Therefore thus will I do unto thee, O Israel: and because I will do this unto thee, prepare to meet thy God, O Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 4, 13, 'For, lo, he that formeth the mountains, and createth the wind, and declareth unto man what is his thought, that maketh the morning darkness, and treadeth upon the high places of the earth, The LORD, The God of hosts, is his name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 1, 'Hear ye this word which I take up against you, even a lamentation, O house of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 2, 'The virgin of Israel is fallen; she shall no more rise: she is forsaken upon her land; there is none to raise her up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 3, 'For thus saith the Lord GOD; The city that went out by a thousand shall leave an hundred, and that which went forth by an hundred shall leave ten, to the house of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 4, 'For thus saith the LORD unto the house of Israel, Seek ye me, and ye shall live:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 5, 'But seek not Bethel, nor enter into Gilgal, and pass not to Beersheba: for Gilgal shall surely go into captivity, and Bethel shall come to nought.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 6, 'Seek the LORD, and ye shall live; lest he break out like fire in the house of Joseph, and devour it, and there be none to quench it in Bethel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 7, 'Ye who turn judgment to wormwood, and leave off righteousness in the earth,'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 8, 'Seek him that maketh the seven stars and Orion, and turneth the shadow of death into the morning, and maketh the day dark with night: that calleth for the waters of the sea, and poureth them out upon the face of the earth: The LORD is his name:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 9, 'That strengtheneth the spoiled against the strong, so that the spoiled shall come against the fortress.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 10, 'They hate him that rebuketh in the gate, and they abhor him that speaketh uprightly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 11, 'Forasmuch therefore as your treading is upon the poor, and ye take from him burdens of wheat: ye have built houses of hewn stone, but ye shall not dwell in them; ye have planted pleasant vineyards, but ye shall not drink wine of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 12, 'For I know your manifold transgressions and your mighty sins: they afflict the just, they take a bribe, and they turn aside the poor in the gate from their right.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 13, 'Therefore the prudent shall keep silence in that time; for it is an evil time.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 14, 'Seek good, and not evil, that ye may live: and so the LORD, the God of hosts, shall be with you, as ye have spoken.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 15, 'Hate the evil, and love the good, and establish judgment in the gate: it may be that the LORD God of hosts will be gracious unto the remnant of Joseph.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 16, 'Therefore the LORD, the God of hosts, the Lord, saith thus; Wailing shall be in all streets; and they shall say in all the highways, Alas! alas! and they shall call the husbandman to mourning, and such as are skilful of lamentation to wailing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 17, 'And in all vineyards shall be wailing: for I will pass through thee, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 18, 'Woe unto you that desire the day of the LORD! to what end is it for you? the day of the LORD is darkness, and not light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 19, 'As if a man did flee from a lion, and a bear met him; or went into the house, and leaned his hand on the wall, and a serpent bit him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 20, 'Shall not the day of the LORD be darkness, and not light? even very dark, and no brightness in it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 21, 'I hate, I despise your feast days, and I will not smell in your solemn assemblies.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 22, 'Though ye offer me burnt offerings and your meat offerings, I will not accept them: neither will I regard the peace offerings of your fat beasts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 23, 'Take thou away from me the noise of thy songs; for I will not hear the melody of thy viols.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 24, 'But let judgment run down as waters, and righteousness as a mighty stream.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 25, 'Have ye offered unto me sacrifices and offerings in the wilderness forty years, O house of Israel?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 26, 'But ye have borne the tabernacle of your Moloch and Chiun your images, the star of your god, which ye made to yourselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 5, 27, 'Therefore will I cause you to go into captivity beyond Damascus, saith the LORD, whose name is The God of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 1, 'Woe to them that are at ease in Zion, and trust in the mountain of Samaria, which are named chief of the nations, to whom the house of Israel came!'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 2, 'Pass ye unto Calneh, and see; and from thence go ye to Hamath the great: then go down to Gath of the Philistines: be they better than these kingdoms? or their border greater than your border?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 3, 'Ye that put far away the evil day, and cause the seat of violence to come near;'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 4, 'That lie upon beds of ivory, and stretch themselves upon their couches, and eat the lambs out of the flock, and the calves out of the midst of the stall;'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 5, 'That chant to the sound of the viol, and invent to themselves instruments of musick, like David;'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 6, 'That drink wine in bowls, and anoint themselves with the chief ointments: but they are not grieved for the affliction of Joseph.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 7, 'Therefore now shall they go captive with the first that go captive, and the banquet of them that stretched themselves shall be removed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 8, 'The Lord GOD hath sworn by himself, saith the LORD the God of hosts, I abhor the excellency of Jacob, and hate his palaces: therefore will I deliver up the city with all that is therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 9, 'And it shall come to pass, if there remain ten men in one house, that they shall die.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 10, 'And a man''s uncle shall take him up, and he that burneth him, to bring out the bones out of the house, and shall say unto him that is by the sides of the house, Is there yet any with thee? and he shall say, No. Then shall he say, Hold thy tongue: for we may not make mention of the name of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 11, 'For, behold, the LORD commandeth, and he will smite the great house with breaches, and the little house with clefts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 12, 'Shall horses run upon the rock? will one plow there with oxen? for ye have turned judgment into gall, and the fruit of righteousness into hemlock:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 13, 'Ye which rejoice in a thing of nought, which say, Have we not taken to us horns by our own strength?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 6, 14, 'But, behold, I will raise up against you a nation, O house of Israel, saith the LORD the God of hosts; and they shall afflict you from the entering in of Hemath unto the river of the wilderness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 1, 'Thus hath the Lord GOD shewed unto me; and, behold, he formed grasshoppers in the beginning of the shooting up of the latter growth; and, lo, it was the latter growth after the king''s mowings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 2, 'And it came to pass, that when they had made an end of eating the grass of the land, then I said, O Lord GOD, forgive, I beseech thee: by whom shall Jacob arise? for he is small.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 3, 'The LORD repented for this: It shall not be, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 4, 'Thus hath the Lord GOD shewed unto me: and, behold, the Lord GOD called to contend by fire, and it devoured the great deep, and did eat up a part.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 5, 'Then said I, O Lord GOD, cease, I beseech thee: by whom shall Jacob arise? for he is small.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 6, 'The LORD repented for this: This also shall not be, saith the Lord GOD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 7, 'Thus he shewed me: and, behold, the Lord stood upon a wall made by a plumbline, with a plumbline in his hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 8, 'And the LORD said unto me, Amos, what seest thou? And I said, A plumbline. Then said the Lord, Behold, I will set a plumbline in the midst of my people Israel: I will not again pass by them any more:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 9, 'And the high places of Isaac shall be desolate, and the sanctuaries of Israel shall be laid waste; and I will rise against the house of Jeroboam with the sword.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 10, 'Then Amaziah the priest of Bethel sent to Jeroboam king of Israel, saying, Amos hath conspired against thee in the midst of the house of Israel: the land is not able to bear all his words.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 11, 'For thus Amos saith, Jeroboam shall die by the sword, and Israel shall surely be led away captive out of their own land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 12, 'Also Amaziah said unto Amos, O thou seer, go, flee thee away into the land of Judah, and there eat bread, and prophesy there:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 13, 'But prophesy not again any more at Bethel: for it is the king''s chapel, and it is the king''s court.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 14, 'Then answered Amos, and said to Amaziah, I was no prophet, neither was I a prophet''s son; but I was an herdman, and a gatherer of sycomore fruit:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 15, 'And the LORD took me as I followed the flock, and the LORD said unto me, Go, prophesy unto my people Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 16, 'Now therefore hear thou the word of the LORD: Thou sayest, Prophesy not against Israel, and drop not thy word against the house of Isaac.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 7, 17, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD; Thy wife shall be an harlot in the city, and thy sons and thy daughters shall fall by the sword, and thy land shall be divided by line; and thou shalt die in a polluted land: and Israel shall surely go into captivity forth of his land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 1, 'Thus hath the Lord GOD shewed unto me: and behold a basket of summer fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 2, 'And he said, Amos, what seest thou? And I said, A basket of summer fruit. Then said the LORD unto me, The end is come upon my people of Israel; I will not again pass by them any more.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 3, 'And the songs of the temple shall be howlings in that day, saith the Lord GOD: there shall be many dead bodies in every place; they shall cast them forth with silence.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 4, 'Hear this, O ye that swallow up the needy, even to make the poor of the land to fail,'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 5, 'Saying, When will the new moon be gone, that we may sell corn? and the sabbath, that we may set forth wheat, making the ephah small, and the shekel great, and falsifying the balances by deceit?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 6, 'That we may buy the poor for silver, and the needy for a pair of shoes; yea, and sell the refuse of the wheat?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 7, 'The LORD hath sworn by the excellency of Jacob, Surely I will never forget any of their works.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 8, 'Shall not the land tremble for this, and every one mourn that dwelleth therein? and it shall rise up wholly as a flood; and it shall be cast out and drowned, as by the flood of Egypt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 9, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the Lord GOD, that I will cause the sun to go down at noon, and I will darken the earth in the clear day:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 10, 'And I will turn your feasts into mourning, and all your songs into lamentation; and I will bring up sackcloth upon all loins, and baldness upon every head; and I will make it as the mourning of an only son, and the end thereof as a bitter day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 11, 'Behold, the days come, saith the Lord GOD, that I will send a famine in the land, not a famine of bread, nor a thirst for water, but of hearing the words of the LORD:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 12, 'And they shall wander from sea to sea, and from the north even to the east, they shall run to and fro to seek the word of the LORD, and shall not find it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 13, 'In that day shall the fair virgins and young men faint for thirst.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 8, 14, 'They that swear by the sin of Samaria, and say, Thy god, O Dan, liveth; and, The manner of Beersheba liveth; even they shall fall, and never rise up again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 1, 'I saw the Lord standing upon the altar: and he said, Smite the lintel of the door, that the posts may shake: and cut them in the head, all of them; and I will slay the last of them with the sword: he that fleeth of them shall not flee away, and he that escapeth of them shall not be delivered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 2, 'Though they dig into hell, thence shall mine hand take them; though they climb up to heaven, thence will I bring them down:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 3, 'And though they hide themselves in the top of Carmel, I will search and take them out thence; and though they be hid from my sight in the bottom of the sea, thence will I command the serpent, and he shall bite them:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 4, 'And though they go into captivity before their enemies, thence will I command the sword, and it shall slay them: and I will set mine eyes upon them for evil, and not for good.')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 5, 'And the Lord GOD of hosts is he that toucheth the land, and it shall melt, and all that dwell therein shall mourn: and it shall rise up wholly like a flood; and shall be drowned, as by the flood of Egypt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 6, 'It is he that buildeth his stories in the heaven, and hath founded his troop in the earth; he that calleth for the waters of the sea, and poureth them out upon the face of the earth: The LORD is his name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 7, 'Are ye not as children of the Ethiopians unto me, O children of Israel? saith the LORD. Have not I brought up Israel out of the land of Egypt? and the Philistines from Caphtor, and the Syrians from Kir?'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 8, 'Behold, the eyes of the Lord GOD are upon the sinful kingdom, and I will destroy it from off the face of the earth; saving that I will not utterly destroy the house of Jacob, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 9, 'For, lo, I will command, and I will sift the house of Israel among all nations, like as corn is sifted in a sieve, yet shall not the least grain fall upon the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 10, 'All the sinners of my people shall die by the sword, which say, The evil shall not overtake nor prevent us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 11, 'In that day will I raise up the tabernacle of David that is fallen, and close up the breaches thereof; and I will raise up his ruins, and I will build it as in the days of old:'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 12, 'That they may possess the remnant of Edom, and of all the heathen, which are called by my name, saith the LORD that doeth this.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 13, 'Behold, the days come, saith the LORD, that the plowman shall overtake the reaper, and the treader of grapes him that soweth seed; and the mountains shall drop sweet wine, and all the hills shall melt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 14, 'And I will bring again the captivity of my people of Israel, and they shall build the waste cities, and inhabit them; and they shall plant vineyards, and drink the wine thereof; they shall also make gardens, and eat the fruit of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Amos', 30, 9, 15, 'And I will plant them upon their land, and they shall no more be pulled up out of their land which I have given them, saith the LORD thy God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 1, 'The vision of Obadiah. Thus saith the Lord GOD concerning Edom; We have heard a rumour from the LORD, and an ambassador is sent among the heathen, Arise ye, and let us rise up against her in battle.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 2, 'Behold, I have made thee small among the heathen: thou art greatly despised.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 3, 'The pride of thine heart hath deceived thee, thou that dwellest in the clefts of the rock, whose habitation is high; that saith in his heart, Who shall bring me down to the ground?'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 4, 'Though thou exalt thyself as the eagle, and though thou set thy nest among the stars, thence will I bring thee down, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 5, 'If thieves came to thee, if robbers by night, (how art thou cut off!) would they not have stolen till they had enough? if the grapegatherers came to thee, would they not leave some grapes?'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 6, 'How are the things of Esau searched out! how are his hidden things sought up!'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 7, 'All the men of thy confederacy have brought thee even to the border: the men that were at peace with thee have deceived thee, and prevailed against thee; they that eat thy bread have laid a wound under thee: there is none understanding in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 8, 'Shall I not in that day, saith the LORD, even destroy the wise men out of Edom, and understanding out of the mount of Esau?'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 9, 'And thy mighty men, O Teman, shall be dismayed, to the end that every one of the mount of Esau may be cut off by slaughter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 10, 'For thy violence against thy brother Jacob shame shall cover thee, and thou shalt be cut off for ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 11, 'In the day that thou stoodest on the other side, in the day that the strangers carried away captive his forces, and foreigners entered into his gates, and cast lots upon Jerusalem, even thou wast as one of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 12, 'But thou shouldest not have looked on the day of thy brother in the day that he became a stranger; neither shouldest thou have rejoiced over the children of Judah in the day of their destruction; neither shouldest thou have spoken proudly in the day of distress.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 13, 'Thou shouldest not have entered into the gate of my people in the day of their calamity; yea, thou shouldest not have looked on their affliction in the day of their calamity, nor have laid hands on their substance in the day of their calamity;'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 14, 'Neither shouldest thou have stood in the crossway, to cut off those of his that did escape; neither shouldest thou have delivered up those of his that did remain in the day of distress.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 15, 'For the day of the LORD is near upon all the heathen: as thou hast done, it shall be done unto thee: thy reward shall return upon thine own head.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 16, 'For as ye have drunk upon my holy mountain, so shall all the heathen drink continually, yea, they shall drink, and they shall swallow down, and they shall be as though they had not been.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 17, 'But upon mount Zion shall be deliverance, and there shall be holiness; and the house of Jacob shall possess their possessions.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 18, 'And the house of Jacob shall be a fire, and the house of Joseph a flame, and the house of Esau for stubble, and they shall kindle in them, and devour them; and there shall not be any remaining of the house of Esau; for the LORD hath spoken it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 19, 'And they of the south shall possess the mount of Esau; and they of the plain the Philistines: and they shall possess the fields of Ephraim, and the fields of Samaria: and Benjamin shall possess Gilead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 20, 'And the captivity of this host of the children of Israel shall possess that of the Canaanites, even unto Zarephath; and the captivity of Jerusalem, which is in Sepharad, shall possess the cities of the south.'),
  ('KJV', 'Obadiah', 31, 1, 21, 'And saviours shall come up on mount Zion to judge the mount of Esau; and the kingdom shall be the LORD''S.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 1, 'Now the word of the LORD came unto Jonah the son of Amittai, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 2, 'Arise, go to Nineveh, that great city, and cry against it; for their wickedness is come up before me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 3, 'But Jonah rose up to flee unto Tarshish from the presence of the LORD, and went down to Joppa; and he found a ship going to Tarshish: so he paid the fare thereof, and went down into it, to go with them unto Tarshish from the presence of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 4, 'But the LORD sent out a great wind into the sea, and there was a mighty tempest in the sea, so that the ship was like to be broken.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 5, 'Then the mariners were afraid, and cried every man unto his god, and cast forth the wares that were in the ship into the sea, to lighten it of them. But Jonah was gone down into the sides of the ship; and he lay, and was fast asleep.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 6, 'So the shipmaster came to him, and said unto him, What meanest thou, O sleeper? arise, call upon thy God, if so be that God will think upon us, that we perish not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 7, 'And they said every one to his fellow, Come, and let us cast lots, that we may know for whose cause this evil is upon us. So they cast lots, and the lot fell upon Jonah.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 8, 'Then said they unto him, Tell us, we pray thee, for whose cause this evil is upon us; What is thine occupation? and whence comest thou? what is thy country? and of what people art thou?'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 9, 'And he said unto them, I am an Hebrew; and I fear the LORD, the God of heaven, which hath made the sea and the dry land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 10, 'Then were the men exceedingly afraid, and said unto him, Why hast thou done this? For the men knew that he fled from the presence of the LORD, because he had told them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 11, 'Then said they unto him, What shall we do unto thee, that the sea may be calm unto us? for the sea wrought, and was tempestuous.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 12, 'And he said unto them, Take me up, and cast me forth into the sea; so shall the sea be calm unto you: for I know that for my sake this great tempest is upon you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 13, 'Nevertheless the men rowed hard to bring it to the land; but they could not: for the sea wrought, and was tempestuous against them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 14, 'Wherefore they cried unto the LORD, and said, We beseech thee, O LORD, we beseech thee, let us not perish for this man''s life, and lay not upon us innocent blood: for thou, O LORD, hast done as it pleased thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 15, 'So they took up Jonah, and cast him forth into the sea: and the sea ceased from her raging.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 16, 'Then the men feared the LORD exceedingly, and offered a sacrifice unto the LORD, and made vows.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 1, 17, 'Now the LORD had prepared a great fish to swallow up Jonah. And Jonah was in the belly of the fish three days and three nights.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 1, 'Then Jonah prayed unto the LORD his God out of the fish''s belly,'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 2, 'And said, I cried by reason of mine affliction unto the LORD, and he heard me; out of the belly of hell cried I, and thou heardest my voice.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 3, 'For thou hadst cast me into the deep, in the midst of the seas; and the floods compassed me about: all thy billows and thy waves passed over me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 4, 'Then I said, I am cast out of thy sight; yet I will look again toward thy holy temple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 5, 'The waters compassed me about, even to the soul: the depth closed me round about, the weeds were wrapped about my head.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 6, 'I went down to the bottoms of the mountains; the earth with her bars was about me for ever: yet hast thou brought up my life from corruption, O LORD my God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 7, 'When my soul fainted within me I remembered the LORD: and my prayer came in unto thee, into thine holy temple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 8, 'They that observe lying vanities forsake their own mercy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 9, 'But I will sacrifice unto thee with the voice of thanksgiving; I will pay that that I have vowed. Salvation is of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 2, 10, 'And the LORD spake unto the fish, and it vomited out Jonah upon the dry land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 1, 'And the word of the LORD came unto Jonah the second time, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 2, 'Arise, go unto Nineveh, that great city, and preach unto it the preaching that I bid thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 3, 'So Jonah arose, and went unto Nineveh, according to the word of the LORD. Now Nineveh was an exceeding great city of three days'' journey.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 4, 'And Jonah began to enter into the city a day''s journey, and he cried, and said, Yet forty days, and Nineveh shall be overthrown.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 5, 'So the people of Nineveh believed God, and proclaimed a fast, and put on sackcloth, from the greatest of them even to the least of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 6, 'For word came unto the king of Nineveh, and he arose from his throne, and he laid his robe from him, and covered him with sackcloth, and sat in ashes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 7, 'And he caused it to be proclaimed and published through Nineveh by the decree of the king and his nobles, saying, Let neither man nor beast, herd nor flock, taste any thing: let them not feed, nor drink water:'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 8, 'But let man and beast be covered with sackcloth, and cry mightily unto God: yea, let them turn every one from his evil way, and from the violence that is in their hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 9, 'Who can tell if God will turn and repent, and turn away from his fierce anger, that we perish not?'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 3, 10, 'And God saw their works, that they turned from their evil way; and God repented of the evil, that he had said that he would do unto them; and he did it not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 1, 'But it displeased Jonah exceedingly, and he was very angry.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 2, 'And he prayed unto the LORD, and said, I pray thee, O LORD, was not this my saying, when I was yet in my country? Therefore I fled before unto Tarshish: for I knew that thou art a gracious God, and merciful, slow to anger, and of great kindness, and repentest thee of the evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 3, 'Therefore now, O LORD, take, I beseech thee, my life from me; for it is better for me to die than to live.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 4, 'Then said the LORD, Doest thou well to be angry?'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 5, 'So Jonah went out of the city, and sat on the east side of the city, and there made him a booth, and sat under it in the shadow, till he might see what would become of the city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 6, 'And the LORD God prepared a gourd, and made it to come up over Jonah, that it might be a shadow over his head, to deliver him from his grief. So Jonah was exceeding glad of the gourd.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 7, 'But God prepared a worm when the morning rose the next day, and it smote the gourd that it withered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 8, 'And it came to pass, when the sun did arise, that God prepared a vehement east wind; and the sun beat upon the head of Jonah, that he fainted, and wished in himself to die, and said, It is better for me to die than to live.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 9, 'And God said to Jonah, Doest thou well to be angry for the gourd? And he said, I do well to be angry, even unto death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 10, 'Then said the LORD, Thou hast had pity on the gourd, for the which thou hast not laboured, neither madest it grow; which came up in a night, and perished in a night:'),
  ('KJV', 'Jonah', 32, 4, 11, 'And should not I spare Nineveh, that great city, wherein are more than sixscore thousand persons that cannot discern between their right hand and their left hand; and also much cattle?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 1, 'The word of the LORD that came to Micah the Morasthite in the days of Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah, which he saw concerning Samaria and Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 2, 'Hear, all ye people; hearken, O earth, and all that therein is: and let the Lord GOD be witness against you, the Lord from his holy temple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 3, 'For, behold, the LORD cometh forth out of his place, and will come down, and tread upon the high places of the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 4, 'And the mountains shall be molten under him, and the valleys shall be cleft, as wax before the fire, and as the waters that are poured down a steep place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 5, 'For the transgression of Jacob is all this, and for the sins of the house of Israel. What is the transgression of Jacob? is it not Samaria? and what are the high places of Judah? are they not Jerusalem?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 6, 'Therefore I will make Samaria as an heap of the field, and as plantings of a vineyard: and I will pour down the stones thereof into the valley, and I will discover the foundations thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 7, 'And all the graven images thereof shall be beaten to pieces, and all the hires thereof shall be burned with the fire, and all the idols thereof will I lay desolate: for she gathered it of the hire of an harlot, and they shall return to the hire of an harlot.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 8, 'Therefore I will wail and howl, I will go stripped and naked: I will make a wailing like the dragons, and mourning as the owls.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 9, 'For her wound is incurable; for it is come unto Judah; he is come unto the gate of my people, even to Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 10, 'Declare ye it not at Gath, weep ye not at all: in the house of Aphrah roll thyself in the dust.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 11, 'Pass ye away, thou inhabitant of Saphir, having thy shame naked: the inhabitant of Zaanan came not forth in the mourning of Bethezel; he shall receive of you his standing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 12, 'For the inhabitant of Maroth waited carefully for good: but evil came down from the LORD unto the gate of Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 13, 'O thou inhabitant of Lachish, bind the chariot to the swift beast: she is the beginning of the sin to the daughter of Zion: for the transgressions of Israel were found in thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 14, 'Therefore shalt thou give presents to Moreshethgath: the houses of Achzib shall be a lie to the kings of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 15, 'Yet will I bring an heir unto thee, O inhabitant of Mareshah: he shall come unto Adullam the glory of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 1, 16, 'Make thee bald, and poll thee for thy delicate children; enlarge thy baldness as the eagle; for they are gone into captivity from thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 1, 'Woe to them that devise iniquity, and work evil upon their beds! when the morning is light, they practise it, because it is in the power of their hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 2, 'And they covet fields, and take them by violence; and houses, and take them away: so they oppress a man and his house, even a man and his heritage.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 3, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD; Behold, against this family do I devise an evil, from which ye shall not remove your necks; neither shall ye go haughtily: for this time is evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 4, 'In that day shall one take up a parable against you, and lament with a doleful lamentation, and say, We be utterly spoiled: he hath changed the portion of my people: how hath he removed it from me! turning away he hath divided our fields.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 5, 'Therefore thou shalt have none that shall cast a cord by lot in the congregation of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 6, 'Prophesy ye not, say they to them that prophesy: they shall not prophesy to them, that they shall not take shame.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 7, 'O thou that art named the house of Jacob, is the spirit of the LORD straitened? are these his doings? do not my words do good to him that walketh uprightly?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 8, 'Even of late my people is risen up as an enemy: ye pull off the robe with the garment from them that pass by securely as men averse from war.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 9, 'The women of my people have ye cast out from their pleasant houses; from their children have ye taken away my glory for ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 10, 'Arise ye, and depart; for this is not your rest: because it is polluted, it shall destroy you, even with a sore destruction.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 11, 'If a man walking in the spirit and falsehood do lie, saying, I will prophesy unto thee of wine and of strong drink; he shall even be the prophet of this people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 12, 'I will surely assemble, O Jacob, all of thee; I will surely gather the remnant of Israel; I will put them together as the sheep of Bozrah, as the flock in the midst of their fold: they shall make great noise by reason of the multitude of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 2, 13, 'The breaker is come up before them: they have broken up, and have passed through the gate, and are gone out by it: and their king shall pass before them, and the LORD on the head of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 1, 'And I said, Hear, I pray you, O heads of Jacob, and ye princes of the house of Israel; Is it not for you to know judgment?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 2, 'Who hate the good, and love the evil; who pluck off their skin from off them, and their flesh from off their bones;'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 3, 'Who also eat the flesh of my people, and flay their skin from off them; and they break their bones, and chop them in pieces, as for the pot, and as flesh within the caldron.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 4, 'Then shall they cry unto the LORD, but he will not hear them: he will even hide his face from them at that time, as they have behaved themselves ill in their doings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 5, 'Thus saith the LORD concerning the prophets that make my people err, that bite with their teeth, and cry, Peace; and he that putteth not into their mouths, they even prepare war against him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 6, 'Therefore night shall be unto you, that ye shall not have a vision; and it shall be dark unto you, that ye shall not divine; and the sun shall go down over the prophets, and the day shall be dark over them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 7, 'Then shall the seers be ashamed, and the diviners confounded: yea, they shall all cover their lips; for there is no answer of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 8, 'But truly I am full of power by the spirit of the LORD, and of judgment, and of might, to declare unto Jacob his transgression, and to Israel his sin.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 9, 'Hear this, I pray you, ye heads of the house of Jacob, and princes of the house of Israel, that abhor judgment, and pervert all equity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 10, 'They build up Zion with blood, and Jerusalem with iniquity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 11, 'The heads thereof judge for reward, and the priests thereof teach for hire, and the prophets thereof divine for money: yet will they lean upon the LORD, and say, Is not the LORD among us? none evil can come upon us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 3, 12, 'Therefore shall Zion for your sake be plowed as a field, and Jerusalem shall become heaps, and the mountain of the house as the high places of the forest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 1, 'But in the last days it shall come to pass, that the mountain of the house of the LORD shall be established in the top of the mountains, and it shall be exalted above the hills; and people shall flow unto it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 2, 'And many nations shall come, and say, Come, and let us go up to the mountain of the LORD, and to the house of the God of Jacob; and he will teach us of his ways, and we will walk in his paths: for the law shall go forth of Zion, and the word of the LORD from Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 3, 'And he shall judge among many people, and rebuke strong nations afar off; and they shall beat their swords into plowshares, and their spears into pruninghooks: nation shall not lift up a sword against nation, neither shall they learn war any more.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 4, 'But they shall sit every man under his vine and under his fig tree; and none shall make them afraid: for the mouth of the LORD of hosts hath spoken it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 5, 'For all people will walk every one in the name of his god, and we will walk in the name of the LORD our God for ever and ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 6, 'In that day, saith the LORD, will I assemble her that halteth, and I will gather her that is driven out, and her that I have afflicted;'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 7, 'And I will make her that halted a remnant, and her that was cast far off a strong nation: and the LORD shall reign over them in mount Zion from henceforth, even for ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 8, 'And thou, O tower of the flock, the strong hold of the daughter of Zion, unto thee shall it come, even the first dominion; the kingdom shall come to the daughter of Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 9, 'Now why dost thou cry out aloud? is there no king in thee? is thy counsellor perished? for pangs have taken thee as a woman in travail.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 10, 'Be in pain, and labour to bring forth, O daughter of Zion, like a woman in travail: for now shalt thou go forth out of the city, and thou shalt dwell in the field, and thou shalt go even to Babylon; there shalt thou be delivered; there the LORD shall redeem thee from the hand of thine enemies.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 11, 'Now also many nations are gathered against thee, that say, Let her be defiled, and let our eye look upon Zion.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 12, 'But they know not the thoughts of the LORD, neither understand they his counsel: for he shall gather them as the sheaves into the floor.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 4, 13, 'Arise and thresh, O daughter of Zion: for I will make thine horn iron, and I will make thy hoofs brass: and thou shalt beat in pieces many people: and I will consecrate their gain unto the LORD, and their substance unto the Lord of the whole earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 1, 'Now gather thyself in troops, O daughter of troops: he hath laid siege against us: they shall smite the judge of Israel with a rod upon the cheek.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 2, 'But thou, Bethlehem Ephratah, though thou be little among the thousands of Judah, yet out of thee shall he come forth unto me that is to be ruler in Israel; whose goings forth have been from of old, from everlasting.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 3, 'Therefore will he give them up, until the time that she which travaileth hath brought forth: then the remnant of his brethren shall return unto the children of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 4, 'And he shall stand and feed in the strength of the LORD, in the majesty of the name of the LORD his God; and they shall abide: for now shall he be great unto the ends of the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 5, 'And this man shall be the peace, when the Assyrian shall come into our land: and when he shall tread in our palaces, then shall we raise against him seven shepherds, and eight principal men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 6, 'And they shall waste the land of Assyria with the sword, and the land of Nimrod in the entrances thereof: thus shall he deliver us from the Assyrian, when he cometh into our land, and when he treadeth within our borders.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 7, 'And the remnant of Jacob shall be in the midst of many people as a dew from the LORD, as the showers upon the grass, that tarrieth not for man, nor waiteth for the sons of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 8, 'And the remnant of Jacob shall be among the Gentiles in the midst of many people as a lion among the beasts of the forest, as a young lion among the flocks of sheep: who, if he go through, both treadeth down, and teareth in pieces, and none can deliver.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 9, 'Thine hand shall be lifted up upon thine adversaries, and all thine enemies shall be cut off.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 10, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the LORD, that I will cut off thy horses out of the midst of thee, and I will destroy thy chariots:'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 11, 'And I will cut off the cities of thy land, and throw down all thy strong holds:'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 12, 'And I will cut off witchcrafts out of thine hand; and thou shalt have no more soothsayers:'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 13, 'Thy graven images also will I cut off, and thy standing images out of the midst of thee; and thou shalt no more worship the work of thine hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 14, 'And I will pluck up thy groves out of the midst of thee: so will I destroy thy cities.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 5, 15, 'And I will execute vengeance in anger and fury upon the heathen, such as they have not heard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 1, 'Hear ye now what the LORD saith; Arise, contend thou before the mountains, and let the hills hear thy voice.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 2, 'Hear ye, O mountains, the LORD''S controversy, and ye strong foundations of the earth: for the LORD hath a controversy with his people, and he will plead with Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 3, 'O my people, what have I done unto thee? and wherein have I wearied thee? testify against me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 4, 'For I brought thee up out of the land of Egypt, and redeemed thee out of the house of servants; and I sent before thee Moses, Aaron, and Miriam.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 5, 'O my people, remember now what Balak king of Moab consulted, and what Balaam the son of Beor answered him from Shittim unto Gilgal; that ye may know the righteousness of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 6, 'Wherewith shall I come before the LORD, and bow myself before the high God? shall I come before him with burnt offerings, with calves of a year old?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 7, 'Will the LORD be pleased with thousands of rams, or with ten thousands of rivers of oil? shall I give my firstborn for my transgression, the fruit of my body for the sin of my soul?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 8, 'He hath shewed thee, O man, what is good; and what doth the LORD require of thee, but to do justly, and to love mercy, and to walk humbly with thy God?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 9, 'The LORD''S voice crieth unto the city, and the man of wisdom shall see thy name: hear ye the rod, and who hath appointed it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 10, 'Are there yet the treasures of wickedness in the house of the wicked, and the scant measure that is abominable?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 11, 'Shall I count them pure with the wicked balances, and with the bag of deceitful weights?'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 12, 'For the rich men thereof are full of violence, and the inhabitants thereof have spoken lies, and their tongue is deceitful in their mouth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 13, 'Therefore also will I make thee sick in smiting thee, in making thee desolate because of thy sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 14, 'Thou shalt eat, but not be satisfied; and thy casting down shall be in the midst of thee; and thou shalt take hold, but shalt not deliver; and that which thou deliverest will I give up to the sword.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 15, 'Thou shalt sow, but thou shalt not reap; thou shalt tread the olives, but thou shalt not anoint thee with oil; and sweet wine, but shalt not drink wine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 6, 16, 'For the statutes of Omri are kept, and all the works of the house of Ahab, and ye walk in their counsels; that I should make thee a desolation, and the inhabitants thereof an hissing: therefore ye shall bear the reproach of my people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 1, 'Woe is me! for I am as when they have gathered the summer fruits, as the grapegleanings of the vintage: there is no cluster to eat: my soul desired the firstripe fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 2, 'The good man is perished out of the earth: and there is none upright among men: they all lie in wait for blood; they hunt every man his brother with a net.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 3, 'That they may do evil with both hands earnestly, the prince asketh, and the judge asketh for a reward; and the great man, he uttereth his mischievous desire: so they wrap it up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 4, 'The best of them is as a brier: the most upright is sharper than a thorn hedge: the day of thy watchmen and thy visitation cometh; now shall be their perplexity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 5, 'Trust ye not in a friend, put ye not confidence in a guide: keep the doors of thy mouth from her that lieth in thy bosom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 6, 'For the son dishonoureth the father, the daughter riseth up against her mother, the daughter in law against her mother in law; a man''s enemies are the men of his own house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 7, 'Therefore I will look unto the LORD; I will wait for the God of my salvation: my God will hear me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 8, 'Rejoice not against me, O mine enemy: when I fall, I shall arise; when I sit in darkness, the LORD shall be a light unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 9, 'I will bear the indignation of the LORD, because I have sinned against him, until he plead my cause, and execute judgment for me: he will bring me forth to the light, and I shall behold his righteousness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 10, 'Then she that is mine enemy shall see it, and shame shall cover her which said unto me, Where is the LORD thy God? mine eyes shall behold her: now shall she be trodden down as the mire of the streets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 11, 'In the day that thy walls are to be built, in that day shall the decree be far removed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 12, 'In that day also he shall come even to thee from Assyria, and from the fortified cities, and from the fortress even to the river, and from sea to sea, and from mountain to mountain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 13, 'Notwithstanding the land shall be desolate because of them that dwell therein, for the fruit of their doings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 14, 'Feed thy people with thy rod, the flock of thine heritage, which dwell solitarily in the wood, in the midst of Carmel: let them feed in Bashan and Gilead, as in the days of old.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 15, 'According to the days of thy coming out of the land of Egypt will I shew unto him marvellous things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 16, 'The nations shall see and be confounded at all their might: they shall lay their hand upon their mouth, their ears shall be deaf.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 17, 'They shall lick the dust like a serpent, they shall move out of their holes like worms of the earth: they shall be afraid of the LORD our God, and shall fear because of thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 18, 'Who is a God like unto thee, that pardoneth iniquity, and passeth by the transgression of the remnant of his heritage? he retaineth not his anger for ever, because he delighteth in mercy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 19, 'He will turn again, he will have compassion upon us; he will subdue our iniquities; and thou wilt cast all their sins into the depths of the sea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Micah', 33, 7, 20, 'Thou wilt perform the truth to Jacob, and the mercy to Abraham, which thou hast sworn unto our fathers from the days of old.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 1, 'The burden of Nineveh. The book of the vision of Nahum the Elkoshite.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 2, 'God is jealous, and the LORD revengeth; the LORD revengeth, and is furious; the LORD will take vengeance on his adversaries, and he reserveth wrath for his enemies.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 3, 'The LORD is slow to anger, and great in power, and will not at all acquit the wicked: the LORD hath his way in the whirlwind and in the storm, and the clouds are the dust of his feet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 4, 'He rebuketh the sea, and maketh it dry, and drieth up all the rivers: Bashan languisheth, and Carmel, and the flower of Lebanon languisheth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 5, 'The mountains quake at him, and the hills melt, and the earth is burned at his presence, yea, the world, and all that dwell therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 6, 'Who can stand before his indignation? and who can abide in the fierceness of his anger? his fury is poured out like fire, and the rocks are thrown down by him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 7, 'The LORD is good, a strong hold in the day of trouble; and he knoweth them that trust in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 8, 'But with an overrunning flood he will make an utter end of the place thereof, and darkness shall pursue his enemies.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 9, 'What do ye imagine against the LORD? he will make an utter end: affliction shall not rise up the second time.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 10, 'For while they be folden together as thorns, and while they are drunken as drunkards, they shall be devoured as stubble fully dry.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 11, 'There is one come out of thee, that imagineth evil against the LORD, a wicked counsellor.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 12, 'Thus saith the LORD; Though they be quiet, and likewise many, yet thus shall they be cut down, when he shall pass through. Though I have afflicted thee, I will afflict thee no more.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 13, 'For now will I break his yoke from off thee, and will burst thy bonds in sunder.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 14, 'And the LORD hath given a commandment concerning thee, that no more of thy name be sown: out of the house of thy gods will I cut off the graven image and the molten image: I will make thy grave; for thou art vile.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 1, 15, 'Behold upon the mountains the feet of him that bringeth good tidings, that publisheth peace! O Judah, keep thy solemn feasts, perform thy vows: for the wicked shall no more pass through thee; he is utterly cut off.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 1, 'He that dasheth in pieces is come up before thy face: keep the munition, watch the way, make thy loins strong, fortify thy power mightily.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 2, 'For the LORD hath turned away the excellency of Jacob, as the excellency of Israel: for the emptiers have emptied them out, and marred their vine branches.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 3, 'The shield of his mighty men is made red, the valiant men are in scarlet: the chariots shall be with flaming torches in the day of his preparation, and the fir trees shall be terribly shaken.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 4, 'The chariots shall rage in the streets, they shall justle one against another in the broad ways: they shall seem like torches, they shall run like the lightnings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 5, 'He shall recount his worthies: they shall stumble in their walk; they shall make haste to the wall thereof, and the defence shall be prepared.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 6, 'The gates of the rivers shall be opened, and the palace shall be dissolved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 7, 'And Huzzab shall be led away captive, she shall be brought up, and her maids shall lead her as with the voice of doves, tabering upon their breasts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 8, 'But Nineveh is of old like a pool of water: yet they shall flee away. Stand, stand, shall they cry; but none shall look back.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 9, 'Take ye the spoil of silver, take the spoil of gold: for there is none end of the store and glory out of all the pleasant furniture.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 10, 'She is empty, and void, and waste: and the heart melteth, and the knees smite together, and much pain is in all loins, and the faces of them all gather blackness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 11, 'Where is the dwelling of the lions, and the feedingplace of the young lions, where the lion, even the old lion, walked, and the lion''s whelp, and none made them afraid?'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 12, 'The lion did tear in pieces enough for his whelps, and strangled for his lionesses, and filled his holes with prey, and his dens with ravin.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 2, 13, 'Behold, I am against thee, saith the LORD of hosts, and I will burn her chariots in the smoke, and the sword shall devour thy young lions: and I will cut off thy prey from the earth, and the voice of thy messengers shall no more be heard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 1, 'Woe to the bloody city! it is all full of lies and robbery; the prey departeth not;'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 2, 'The noise of a whip, and the noise of the rattling of the wheels, and of the pransing horses, and of the jumping chariots.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 3, 'The horseman lifteth up both the bright sword and the glittering spear: and there is a multitude of slain, and a great number of carcases; and there is none end of their corpses; they stumble upon their corpses:'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 4, 'Because of the multitude of the whoredoms of the wellfavoured harlot, the mistress of witchcrafts, that selleth nations through her whoredoms, and families through her witchcrafts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 5, 'Behold, I am against thee, saith the LORD of hosts; and I will discover thy skirts upon thy face, and I will shew the nations thy nakedness, and the kingdoms thy shame.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 6, 'And I will cast abominable filth upon thee, and make thee vile, and will set thee as a gazingstock.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 7, 'And it shall come to pass, that all they that look upon thee shall flee from thee, and say, Nineveh is laid waste: who will bemoan her? whence shall I seek comforters for thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 8, 'Art thou better than populous No, that was situate among the rivers, that had the waters round about it, whose rampart was the sea, and her wall was from the sea?'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 9, 'Ethiopia and Egypt were her strength, and it was infinite; Put and Lubim were thy helpers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 10, 'Yet was she carried away, she went into captivity: her young children also were dashed in pieces at the top of all the streets: and they cast lots for her honourable men, and all her great men were bound in chains.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 11, 'Thou also shalt be drunken: thou shalt be hid, thou also shalt seek strength because of the enemy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 12, 'All thy strong holds shall be like fig trees with the firstripe figs: if they be shaken, they shall even fall into the mouth of the eater.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 13, 'Behold, thy people in the midst of thee are women: the gates of thy land shall be set wide open unto thine enemies: the fire shall devour thy bars.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 14, 'Draw thee waters for the siege, fortify thy strong holds: go into clay, and tread the morter, make strong the brickkiln.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 15, 'There shall the fire devour thee; the sword shall cut thee off, it shall eat thee up like the cankerworm: make thyself many as the cankerworm, make thyself many as the locusts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 16, 'Thou hast multiplied thy merchants above the stars of heaven: the cankerworm spoileth, and flieth away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 17, 'Thy crowned are as the locusts, and thy captains as the great grasshoppers, which camp in the hedges in the cold day, but when the sun ariseth they flee away, and their place is not known where they are.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 18, 'Thy shepherds slumber, O king of Assyria: thy nobles shall dwell in the dust: thy people is scattered upon the mountains, and no man gathereth them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Nahum', 34, 3, 19, 'There is no healing of thy bruise; thy wound is grievous: all that hear the bruit of thee shall clap the hands over thee: for upon whom hath not thy wickedness passed continually?'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 1, 'The burden which Habakkuk the prophet did see.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 2, 'O LORD, how long shall I cry, and thou wilt not hear! even cry out unto thee of violence, and thou wilt not save!'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 3, 'Why dost thou shew me iniquity, and cause me to behold grievance? for spoiling and violence are before me: and there are that raise up strife and contention.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 4, 'Therefore the law is slacked, and judgment doth never go forth: for the wicked doth compass about the righteous; therefore wrong judgment proceedeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 5, 'Behold ye among the heathen, and regard, and wonder marvellously: for I will work a work in your days, which ye will not believe, though it be told you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 6, 'For, lo, I raise up the Chaldeans, that bitter and hasty nation, which shall march through the breadth of the land, to possess the dwellingplaces that are not theirs.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 7, 'They are terrible and dreadful: their judgment and their dignity shall proceed of themselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 8, 'Their horses also are swifter than the leopards, and are more fierce than the evening wolves: and their horsemen shall spread themselves, and their horsemen shall come from far; they shall fly as the eagle that hasteth to eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 9, 'They shall come all for violence: their faces shall sup up as the east wind, and they shall gather the captivity as the sand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 10, 'And they shall scoff at the kings, and the princes shall be a scorn unto them: they shall deride every strong hold; for they shall heap dust, and take it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 11, 'Then shall his mind change, and he shall pass over, and offend, imputing this his power unto his god.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 12, 'Art thou not from everlasting, O LORD my God, mine Holy One? we shall not die. O LORD, thou hast ordained them for judgment; and, O mighty God, thou hast established them for correction.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 13, 'Thou art of purer eyes than to behold evil, and canst not look on iniquity: wherefore lookest thou upon them that deal treacherously, and holdest thy tongue when the wicked devoureth the man that is more righteous than he?'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 14, 'And makest men as the fishes of the sea, as the creeping things, that have no ruler over them?'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 15, 'They take up all of them with the angle, they catch them in their net, and gather them in their drag: therefore they rejoice and are glad.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 16, 'Therefore they sacrifice unto their net, and burn incense unto their drag; because by them their portion is fat, and their meat plenteous.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 1, 17, 'Shall they therefore empty their net, and not spare continually to slay the nations?'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 1, 'I will stand upon my watch, and set me upon the tower, and will watch to see what he will say unto me, and what I shall answer when I am reproved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 2, 'And the LORD answered me, and said, Write the vision, and make it plain upon tables, that he may run that readeth it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 3, 'For the vision is yet for an appointed time, but at the end it shall speak, and not lie: though it tarry, wait for it; because it will surely come, it will not tarry.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 4, 'Behold, his soul which is lifted up is not upright in him: but the just shall live by his faith.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 5, 'Yea also, because he transgresseth by wine, he is a proud man, neither keepeth at home, who enlargeth his desire as hell, and is as death, and cannot be satisfied, but gathereth unto him all nations, and heapeth unto him all people:'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 6, 'Shall not all these take up a parable against him, and a taunting proverb against him, and say, Woe to him that increaseth that which is not his! how long? and to him that ladeth himself with thick clay!'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 7, 'Shall they not rise up suddenly that shall bite thee, and awake that shall vex thee, and thou shalt be for booties unto them?'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 8, 'Because thou hast spoiled many nations, all the remnant of the people shall spoil thee; because of men''s blood, and for the violence of the land, of the city, and of all that dwell therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 9, 'Woe to him that coveteth an evil covetousness to his house, that he may set his nest on high, that he may be delivered from the power of evil!'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 10, 'Thou hast consulted shame to thy house by cutting off many people, and hast sinned against thy soul.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 11, 'For the stone shall cry out of the wall, and the beam out of the timber shall answer it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 12, 'Woe to him that buildeth a town with blood, and stablisheth a city by iniquity!'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 13, 'Behold, is it not of the LORD of hosts that the people shall labour in the very fire, and the people shall weary themselves for very vanity?'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 14, 'For the earth shall be filled with the knowledge of the glory of the LORD, as the waters cover the sea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 15, 'Woe unto him that giveth his neighbour drink, that puttest thy bottle to him, and makest him drunken also, that thou mayest look on their nakedness!'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 16, 'Thou art filled with shame for glory: drink thou also, and let thy foreskin be uncovered: the cup of the LORD''S right hand shall be turned unto thee, and shameful spewing shall be on thy glory.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 17, 'For the violence of Lebanon shall cover thee, and the spoil of beasts, which made them afraid, because of men''s blood, and for the violence of the land, of the city, and of all that dwell therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 18, 'What profiteth the graven image that the maker thereof hath graven it; the molten image, and a teacher of lies, that the maker of his work trusteth therein, to make dumb idols?'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 19, 'Woe unto him that saith to the wood, Awake; to the dumb stone, Arise, it shall teach! Behold, it is laid over with gold and silver, and there is no breath at all in the midst of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 2, 20, 'But the LORD is in his holy temple: let all the earth keep silence before him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 1, 'A prayer of Habakkuk the prophet upon Shigionoth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 2, 'O LORD, I have heard thy speech, and was afraid: O LORD, revive thy work in the midst of the years, in the midst of the years make known; in wrath remember mercy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 3, 'God came from Teman, and the Holy One from mount Paran. Selah. His glory covered the heavens, and the earth was full of his praise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 4, 'And his brightness was as the light; he had horns coming out of his hand: and there was the hiding of his power.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 5, 'Before him went the pestilence, and burning coals went forth at his feet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 6, 'He stood, and measured the earth: he beheld, and drove asunder the nations; and the everlasting mountains were scattered, the perpetual hills did bow: his ways are everlasting.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 7, 'I saw the tents of Cushan in affliction: and the curtains of the land of Midian did tremble.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 8, 'Was the LORD displeased against the rivers? was thine anger against the rivers? was thy wrath against the sea, that thou didst ride upon thine horses and thy chariots of salvation?'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 9, 'Thy bow was made quite naked, according to the oaths of the tribes, even thy word. Selah. Thou didst cleave the earth with rivers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 10, 'The mountains saw thee, and they trembled: the overflowing of the water passed by: the deep uttered his voice, and lifted up his hands on high.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 11, 'The sun and moon stood still in their habitation: at the light of thine arrows they went, and at the shining of thy glittering spear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 12, 'Thou didst march through the land in indignation, thou didst thresh the heathen in anger.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 13, 'Thou wentest forth for the salvation of thy people, even for salvation with thine anointed; thou woundedst the head out of the house of the wicked, by discovering the foundation unto the neck. Selah.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 14, 'Thou didst strike through with his staves the head of his villages: they came out as a whirlwind to scatter me: their rejoicing was as to devour the poor secretly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 15, 'Thou didst walk through the sea with thine horses, through the heap of great waters.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 16, 'When I heard, my belly trembled; my lips quivered at the voice: rottenness entered into my bones, and I trembled in myself, that I might rest in the day of trouble: when he cometh up unto the people, he will invade them with his troops.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 17, 'Although the fig tree shall not blossom, neither shall fruit be in the vines; the labour of the olive shall fail, and the fields shall yield no meat; the flock shall be cut off from the fold, and there shall be no herd in the stalls:'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 18, 'Yet I will rejoice in the LORD, I will joy in the God of my salvation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Habakkuk', 35, 3, 19, 'The LORD God is my strength, and he will make my feet like hinds'' feet, and he will make me to walk upon mine high places. To the chief singer on my stringed instruments.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 1, 'The word of the LORD which came unto Zephaniah the son of Cushi, the son of Gedaliah, the son of Amariah, the son of Hizkiah, in the days of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 2, 'I will utterly consume all things from off the land, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 3, 'I will consume man and beast; I will consume the fowls of the heaven, and the fishes of the sea, and the stumblingblocks with the wicked; and I will cut off man from off the land, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 4, 'I will also stretch out mine hand upon Judah, and upon all the inhabitants of Jerusalem; and I will cut off the remnant of Baal from this place, and the name of the Chemarims with the priests;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 5, 'And them that worship the host of heaven upon the housetops; and them that worship and that swear by the LORD, and that swear by Malcham;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 6, 'And them that are turned back from the LORD; and those that have not sought the LORD, nor enquired for him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 7, 'Hold thy peace at the presence of the Lord GOD: for the day of the LORD is at hand: for the LORD hath prepared a sacrifice, he hath bid his guests.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 8, 'And it shall come to pass in the day of the LORD''S sacrifice, that I will punish the princes, and the king''s children, and all such as are clothed with strange apparel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 9, 'In the same day also will I punish all those that leap on the threshold, which fill their masters'' houses with violence and deceit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 10, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the LORD, that there shall be the noise of a cry from the fish gate, and an howling from the second, and a great crashing from the hills.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 11, 'Howl, ye inhabitants of Maktesh, for all the merchant people are cut down; all they that bear silver are cut off.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 12, 'And it shall come to pass at that time, that I will search Jerusalem with candles, and punish the men that are settled on their lees: that say in their heart, The LORD will not do good, neither will he do evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 13, 'Therefore their goods shall become a booty, and their houses a desolation: they shall also build houses, but not inhabit them; and they shall plant vineyards, but not drink the wine thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 14, 'The great day of the LORD is near, it is near, and hasteth greatly, even the voice of the day of the LORD: the mighty man shall cry there bitterly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 15, 'That day is a day of wrath, a day of trouble and distress, a day of wasteness and desolation, a day of darkness and gloominess, a day of clouds and thick darkness,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 16, 'A day of the trumpet and alarm against the fenced cities, and against the high towers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 17, 'And I will bring distress upon men, that they shall walk like blind men, because they have sinned against the LORD: and their blood shall be poured out as dust, and their flesh as the dung.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 1, 18, 'Neither their silver nor their gold shall be able to deliver them in the day of the LORD''S wrath; but the whole land shall be devoured by the fire of his jealousy: for he shall make even a speedy riddance of all them that dwell in the land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 1, 'Gather yourselves together, yea, gather together, O nation not desired;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 2, 'Before the decree bring forth, before the day pass as the chaff, before the fierce anger of the LORD come upon you, before the day of the LORD''S anger come upon you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 3, 'Seek ye the LORD, all ye meek of the earth, which have wrought his judgment; seek righteousness, seek meekness: it may be ye shall be hid in the day of the LORD''S anger.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 4, 'For Gaza shall be forsaken, and Ashkelon a desolation: they shall drive out Ashdod at the noon day, and Ekron shall be rooted up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 5, 'Woe unto the inhabitants of the sea coast, the nation of the Cherethites! the word of the LORD is against you; O Canaan, the land of the Philistines, I will even destroy thee, that there shall be no inhabitant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 6, 'And the sea coast shall be dwellings and cottages for shepherds, and folds for flocks.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 7, 'And the coast shall be for the remnant of the house of Judah; they shall feed thereupon: in the houses of Ashkelon shall they lie down in the evening: for the LORD their God shall visit them, and turn away their captivity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 8, 'I have heard the reproach of Moab, and the revilings of the children of Ammon, whereby they have reproached my people, and magnified themselves against their border.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 9, 'Therefore as I live, saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel, Surely Moab shall be as Sodom, and the children of Ammon as Gomorrah, even the breeding of nettles, and saltpits, and a perpetual desolation: the residue of my people shall spoil them, and the remnant of my people shall possess them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 10, 'This shall they have for their pride, because they have reproached and magnified themselves against the people of the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 11, 'The LORD will be terrible unto them: for he will famish all the gods of the earth; and men shall worship him, every one from his place, even all the isles of the heathen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 12, 'Ye Ethiopians also, ye shall be slain by my sword.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 13, 'And he will stretch out his hand against the north, and destroy Assyria; and will make Nineveh a desolation, and dry like a wilderness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 14, 'And flocks shall lie down in the midst of her, all the beasts of the nations: both the cormorant and the bittern shall lodge in the upper lintels of it; their voice shall sing in the windows; desolation shall be in the thresholds: for he shall uncover the cedar work.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 2, 15, 'This is the rejoicing city that dwelt carelessly, that said in her heart, I am, and there is none beside me: how is she become a desolation, a place for beasts to lie down in! every one that passeth by her shall hiss, and wag his hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 1, 'Woe to her that is filthy and polluted, to the oppressing city!'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 2, 'She obeyed not the voice; she received not correction; she trusted not in the LORD; she drew not near to her God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 3, 'Her princes within her are roaring lions; her judges are evening wolves; they gnaw not the bones till the morrow.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 4, 'Her prophets are light and treacherous persons: her priests have polluted the sanctuary, they have done violence to the law.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 5, 'The just LORD is in the midst thereof; he will not do iniquity: every morning doth he bring his judgment to light, he faileth not; but the unjust knoweth no shame.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 6, 'I have cut off the nations: their towers are desolate; I made their streets waste, that none passeth by: their cities are destroyed, so that there is no man, that there is none inhabitant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 7, 'I said, Surely thou wilt fear me, thou wilt receive instruction; so their dwelling should not be cut off, howsoever I punished them: but they rose early, and corrupted all their doings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 8, 'Therefore wait ye upon me, saith the LORD, until the day that I rise up to the prey: for my determination is to gather the nations, that I may assemble the kingdoms, to pour upon them mine indignation, even all my fierce anger: for all the earth shall be devoured with the fire of my jealousy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 9, 'For then will I turn to the people a pure language, that they may all call upon the name of the LORD, to serve him with one consent.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 10, 'From beyond the rivers of Ethiopia my suppliants, even the daughter of my dispersed, shall bring mine offering.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 11, 'In that day shalt thou not be ashamed for all thy doings, wherein thou hast transgressed against me: for then I will take away out of the midst of thee them that rejoice in thy pride, and thou shalt no more be haughty because of my holy mountain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 12, 'I will also leave in the midst of thee an afflicted and poor people, and they shall trust in the name of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 13, 'The remnant of Israel shall not do iniquity, nor speak lies; neither shall a deceitful tongue be found in their mouth: for they shall feed and lie down, and none shall make them afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 14, 'Sing, O daughter of Zion; shout, O Israel; be glad and rejoice with all the heart, O daughter of Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 15, 'The LORD hath taken away thy judgments, he hath cast out thine enemy: the king of Israel, even the LORD, is in the midst of thee: thou shalt not see evil any more.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 16, 'In that day it shall be said to Jerusalem, Fear thou not: and to Zion, Let not thine hands be slack.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 17, 'The LORD thy God in the midst of thee is mighty; he will save, he will rejoice over thee with joy; he will rest in his love, he will joy over thee with singing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 18, 'I will gather them that are sorrowful for the solemn assembly, who are of thee, to whom the reproach of it was a burden.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 19, 'Behold, at that time I will undo all that afflict thee: and I will save her that halteth, and gather her that was driven out; and I will get them praise and fame in every land where they have been put to shame.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zephaniah', 36, 3, 20, 'At that time will I bring you again, even in the time that I gather you: for I will make you a name and a praise among all people of the earth, when I turn back your captivity before your eyes, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 1, 'In the second year of Darius the king, in the sixth month, in the first day of the month, came the word of the LORD by Haggai the prophet unto Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to Joshua the son of Josedech, the high priest, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 2, 'Thus speaketh the LORD of hosts, saying, This people say, The time is not come, the time that the LORD''S house should be built.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 3, 'Then came the word of the LORD by Haggai the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 4, 'Is it time for you, O ye, to dwell in your cieled houses, and this house lie waste?'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 5, 'Now therefore thus saith the LORD of hosts; Consider your ways.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 6, 'Ye have sown much, and bring in little; ye eat, but ye have not enough; ye drink, but ye are not filled with drink; ye clothe you, but there is none warm; and he that earneth wages earneth wages to put it into a bag with holes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 7, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Consider your ways.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 8, 'Go up to the mountain, and bring wood, and build the house; and I will take pleasure in it, and I will be glorified, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 9, 'Ye looked for much, and, lo, it came to little; and when ye brought it home, I did blow upon it. Why? saith the LORD of hosts. Because of mine house that is waste, and ye run every man unto his own house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 10, 'Therefore the heaven over you is stayed from dew, and the earth is stayed from her fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 11, 'And I called for a drought upon the land, and upon the mountains, and upon the corn, and upon the new wine, and upon the oil, and upon that which the ground bringeth forth, and upon men, and upon cattle, and upon all the labour of the hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 12, 'Then Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Joshua the son of Josedech, the high priest, with all the remnant of the people, obeyed the voice of the LORD their God, and the words of Haggai the prophet, as the LORD their God had sent him, and the people did fear before the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 13, 'Then spake Haggai the LORD''S messenger in the LORD''S message unto the people, saying, I am with you, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 14, 'And the LORD stirred up the spirit of Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and the spirit of Joshua the son of Josedech, the high priest, and the spirit of all the remnant of the people; and they came and did work in the house of the LORD of hosts, their God,'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 1, 15, 'In the four and twentieth day of the sixth month, in the second year of Darius the king.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 1, 'In the seventh month, in the one and twentieth day of the month, came the word of the LORD by the prophet Haggai, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 2, 'Speak now to Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to Joshua the son of Josedech, the high priest, and to the residue of the people, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 3, 'Who is left among you that saw this house in her first glory? and how do ye see it now? is it not in your eyes in comparison of it as nothing?'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 4, 'Yet now be strong, O Zerubbabel, saith the LORD; and be strong, O Joshua, son of Josedech, the high priest; and be strong, all ye people of the land, saith the LORD, and work: for I am with you, saith the LORD of hosts:'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 5, 'According to the word that I covenanted with you when ye came out of Egypt, so my spirit remaineth among you: fear ye not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 6, 'For thus saith the LORD of hosts; Yet once, it is a little while, and I will shake the heavens, and the earth, and the sea, and the dry land;'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 7, 'And I will shake all nations, and the desire of all nations shall come: and I will fill this house with glory, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 8, 'The silver is mine, and the gold is mine, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 9, 'The glory of this latter house shall be greater than of the former, saith the LORD of hosts: and in this place will I give peace, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 10, 'In the four and twentieth day of the ninth month, in the second year of Darius, came the word of the LORD by Haggai the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 11, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Ask now the priests concerning the law, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 12, 'If one bear holy flesh in the skirt of his garment, and with his skirt do touch bread, or pottage, or wine, or oil, or any meat, shall it be holy? And the priests answered and said, No.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 13, 'Then said Haggai, If one that is unclean by a dead body touch any of these, shall it be unclean? And the priests answered and said, It shall be unclean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 14, 'Then answered Haggai, and said, So is this people, and so is this nation before me, saith the LORD; and so is every work of their hands; and that which they offer there is unclean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 15, 'And now, I pray you, consider from this day and upward, from before a stone was laid upon a stone in the temple of the LORD:'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 16, 'Since those days were, when one came to an heap of twenty measures, there were but ten: when one came to the pressfat for to draw out fifty vessels out of the press, there were but twenty.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 17, 'I smote you with blasting and with mildew and with hail in all the labours of your hands; yet ye turned not to me, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 18, 'Consider now from this day and upward, from the four and twentieth day of the ninth month, even from the day that the foundation of the LORD''S temple was laid, consider it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 19, 'Is the seed yet in the barn? yea, as yet the vine, and the fig tree, and the pomegranate, and the olive tree, hath not brought forth: from this day will I bless you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 20, 'And again the word of the LORD came unto Haggai in the four and twentieth day of the month, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 21, 'Speak to Zerubbabel, governor of Judah, saying, I will shake the heavens and the earth;'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 22, 'And I will overthrow the throne of kingdoms, and I will destroy the strength of the kingdoms of the heathen; and I will overthrow the chariots, and those that ride in them; and the horses and their riders shall come down, every one by the sword of his brother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Haggai', 37, 2, 23, 'In that day, saith the LORD of hosts, will I take thee, O Zerubbabel, my servant, the son of Shealtiel, saith the LORD, and will make thee as a signet: for I have chosen thee, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 1, 'In the eighth month, in the second year of Darius, came the word of the LORD unto Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, the son of Iddo the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 2, 'The LORD hath been sore displeased with your fathers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 3, 'Therefore say thou unto them, Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Turn ye unto me, saith the LORD of hosts, and I will turn unto you, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 4, 'Be ye not as your fathers, unto whom the former prophets have cried, saying, Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Turn ye now from your evil ways, and from your evil doings: but they did not hear, nor hearken unto me, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 5, 'Your fathers, where are they? and the prophets, do they live for ever?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 6, 'But my words and my statutes, which I commanded my servants the prophets, did they not take hold of your fathers? and they returned and said, Like as the LORD of hosts thought to do unto us, according to our ways, and according to our doings, so hath he dealt with us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 7, 'Upon the four and twentieth day of the eleventh month, which is the month Sebat, in the second year of Darius, came the word of the LORD unto Zechariah, the son of Berechiah, the son of Iddo the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 8, 'I saw by night, and behold a man riding upon a red horse, and he stood among the myrtle trees that were in the bottom; and behind him were there red horses, speckled, and white.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 9, 'Then said I, O my lord, what are these? And the angel that talked with me said unto me, I will shew thee what these be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 10, 'And the man that stood among the myrtle trees answered and said, These are they whom the LORD hath sent to walk to and fro through the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 11, 'And they answered the angel of the LORD that stood among the myrtle trees, and said, We have walked to and fro through the earth, and, behold, all the earth sitteth still, and is at rest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 12, 'Then the angel of the LORD answered and said, O LORD of hosts, how long wilt thou not have mercy on Jerusalem and on the cities of Judah, against which thou hast had indignation these threescore and ten years?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 13, 'And the LORD answered the angel that talked with me with good words and comfortable words.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 14, 'So the angel that communed with me said unto me, Cry thou, saying, Thus saith the LORD of hosts; I am jealous for Jerusalem and for Zion with a great jealousy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 15, 'And I am very sore displeased with the heathen that are at ease: for I was but a little displeased, and they helped forward the affliction.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 16, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD; I am returned to Jerusalem with mercies: my house shall be built in it, saith the LORD of hosts, and a line shall be stretched forth upon Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 17, 'Cry yet, saying, Thus saith the LORD of hosts; My cities through prosperity shall yet be spread abroad; and the LORD shall yet comfort Zion, and shall yet choose Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 18, 'Then lifted I up mine eyes, and saw, and behold four horns.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 19, 'And I said unto the angel that talked with me, What be these? And he answered me, These are the horns which have scattered Judah, Israel, and Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 20, 'And the LORD shewed me four carpenters.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 1, 21, 'Then said I, What come these to do? And he spake, saying, These are the horns which have scattered Judah, so that no man did lift up his head: but these are come to fray them, to cast out the horns of the Gentiles, which lifted up their horn over the land of Judah to scatter it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 1, 'I lifted up mine eyes again, and looked, and behold a man with a measuring line in his hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 2, 'Then said I, Whither goest thou? And he said unto me, To measure Jerusalem, to see what is the breadth thereof, and what is the length thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 3, 'And, behold, the angel that talked with me went forth, and another angel went out to meet him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 4, 'And said unto him, Run, speak to this young man, saying, Jerusalem shall be inhabited as towns without walls for the multitude of men and cattle therein:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 5, 'For I, saith the LORD, will be unto her a wall of fire round about, and will be the glory in the midst of her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 6, 'Ho, ho, come forth, and flee from the land of the north, saith the LORD: for I have spread you abroad as the four winds of the heaven, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 7, 'Deliver thyself, O Zion, that dwellest with the daughter of Babylon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 8, 'For thus saith the LORD of hosts; After the glory hath he sent me unto the nations which spoiled you: for he that toucheth you toucheth the apple of his eye.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 9, 'For, behold, I will shake mine hand upon them, and they shall be a spoil to their servants: and ye shall know that the LORD of hosts hath sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 10, 'Sing and rejoice, O daughter of Zion: for, lo, I come, and I will dwell in the midst of thee, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 11, 'And many nations shall be joined to the LORD in that day, and shall be my people: and I will dwell in the midst of thee, and thou shalt know that the LORD of hosts hath sent me unto thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 12, 'And the LORD shall inherit Judah his portion in the holy land, and shall choose Jerusalem again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 2, 13, 'Be silent, O all flesh, before the LORD: for he is raised up out of his holy habitation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 1, 'And he shewed me Joshua the high priest standing before the angel of the LORD, and Satan standing at his right hand to resist him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 2, 'And the LORD said unto Satan, The LORD rebuke thee, O Satan; even the LORD that hath chosen Jerusalem rebuke thee: is not this a brand plucked out of the fire?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 3, 'Now Joshua was clothed with filthy garments, and stood before the angel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 4, 'And he answered and spake unto those that stood before him, saying, Take away the filthy garments from him. And unto him he said, Behold, I have caused thine iniquity to pass from thee, and I will clothe thee with change of raiment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 5, 'And I said, Let them set a fair mitre upon his head. So they set a fair mitre upon his head, and clothed him with garments. And the angel of the LORD stood by.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 6, 'And the angel of the LORD protested unto Joshua, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 7, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; If thou wilt walk in my ways, and if thou wilt keep my charge, then thou shalt also judge my house, and shalt also keep my courts, and I will give thee places to walk among these that stand by.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 8, 'Hear now, O Joshua the high priest, thou, and thy fellows that sit before thee: for they are men wondered at: for, behold, I will bring forth my servant the BRANCH.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 9, 'For behold the stone that I have laid before Joshua; upon one stone shall be seven eyes: behold, I will engrave the graving thereof, saith the LORD of hosts, and I will remove the iniquity of that land in one day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 3, 10, 'In that day, saith the LORD of hosts, shall ye call every man his neighbour under the vine and under the fig tree.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 1, 'And the angel that talked with me came again, and waked me, as a man that is wakened out of his sleep,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 2, 'And said unto me, What seest thou? And I said, I have looked, and behold a candlestick all of gold, with a bowl upon the top of it, and his seven lamps thereon, and seven pipes to the seven lamps, which are upon the top thereof:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 3, 'And two olive trees by it, one upon the right side of the bowl, and the other upon the left side thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 4, 'So I answered and spake to the angel that talked with me, saying, What are these, my lord?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 5, 'Then the angel that talked with me answered and said unto me, Knowest thou not what these be? And I said, No, my lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 6, 'Then he answered and spake unto me, saying, This is the word of the LORD unto Zerubbabel, saying, Not by might, nor by power, but by my spirit, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 7, 'Who art thou, O great mountain? before Zerubbabel thou shalt become a plain: and he shall bring forth the headstone thereof with shoutings, crying, Grace, grace unto it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 8, 'Moreover the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 9, 'The hands of Zerubbabel have laid the foundation of this house; his hands shall also finish it; and thou shalt know that the LORD of hosts hath sent me unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 10, 'For who hath despised the day of small things? for they shall rejoice, and shall see the plummet in the hand of Zerubbabel with those seven; they are the eyes of the LORD, which run to and fro through the whole earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 11, 'Then answered I, and said unto him, What are these two olive trees upon the right side of the candlestick and upon the left side thereof?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 12, 'And I answered again, and said unto him, What be these two olive branches which through the two golden pipes empty the golden oil out of themselves?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 13, 'And he answered me and said, Knowest thou not what these be? And I said, No, my lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 4, 14, 'Then said he, These are the two anointed ones, that stand by the Lord of the whole earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 1, 'Then I turned, and lifted up mine eyes, and looked, and behold a flying roll.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 2, 'And he said unto me, What seest thou? And I answered, I see a flying roll; the length thereof is twenty cubits, and the breadth thereof ten cubits.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 3, 'Then said he unto me, This is the curse that goeth forth over the face of the whole earth: for every one that stealeth shall be cut off as on this side according to it; and every one that sweareth shall be cut off as on that side according to it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 4, 'I will bring it forth, saith the LORD of hosts, and it shall enter into the house of the thief, and into the house of him that sweareth falsely by my name: and it shall remain in the midst of his house, and shall consume it with the timber thereof and the stones thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 5, 'Then the angel that talked with me went forth, and said unto me, Lift up now thine eyes, and see what is this that goeth forth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 6, 'And I said, What is it? And he said, This is an ephah that goeth forth. He said moreover, This is their resemblance through all the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 7, 'And, behold, there was lifted up a talent of lead: and this is a woman that sitteth in the midst of the ephah.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 8, 'And he said, This is wickedness. And he cast it into the midst of the ephah; and he cast the weight of lead upon the mouth thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 9, 'Then lifted I up mine eyes, and looked, and, behold, there came out two women, and the wind was in their wings; for they had wings like the wings of a stork: and they lifted up the ephah between the earth and the heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 10, 'Then said I to the angel that talked with me, Whither do these bear the ephah?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 5, 11, 'And he said unto me, To build it an house in the land of Shinar: and it shall be established, and set there upon her own base.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 1, 'And I turned, and lifted up mine eyes, and looked, and, behold, there came four chariots out from between two mountains; and the mountains were mountains of brass.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 2, 'In the first chariot were red horses; and in the second chariot black horses;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 3, 'And in the third chariot white horses; and in the fourth chariot grisled and bay horses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 4, 'Then I answered and said unto the angel that talked with me, What are these, my lord?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 5, 'And the angel answered and said unto me, These are the four spirits of the heavens, which go forth from standing before the Lord of all the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 6, 'The black horses which are therein go forth into the north country; and the white go forth after them; and the grisled go forth toward the south country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 7, 'And the bay went forth, and sought to go that they might walk to and fro through the earth: and he said, Get you hence, walk to and fro through the earth. So they walked to and fro through the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 8, 'Then cried he upon me, and spake unto me, saying, Behold, these that go toward the north country have quieted my spirit in the north country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 9, 'And the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 10, 'Take of them of the captivity, even of Heldai, of Tobijah, and of Jedaiah, which are come from Babylon, and come thou the same day, and go into the house of Josiah the son of Zephaniah;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 11, 'Then take silver and gold, and make crowns, and set them upon the head of Joshua the son of Josedech, the high priest;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 12, 'And speak unto him, saying, Thus speaketh the LORD of hosts, saying, Behold the man whose name is The BRANCH; and he shall grow up out of his place, and he shall build the temple of the LORD:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 13, 'Even he shall build the temple of the LORD; and he shall bear the glory, and shall sit and rule upon his throne; and he shall be a priest upon his throne: and the counsel of peace shall be between them both.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 14, 'And the crowns shall be to Helem, and to Tobijah, and to Jedaiah, and to Hen the son of Zephaniah, for a memorial in the temple of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 6, 15, 'And they that are far off shall come and build in the temple of the LORD, and ye shall know that the LORD of hosts hath sent me unto you. And this shall come to pass, if ye will diligently obey the voice of the LORD your God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 1, 'And it came to pass in the fourth year of king Darius, that the word of the LORD came unto Zechariah in the fourth day of the ninth month, even in Chisleu;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 2, 'When they had sent unto the house of God Sherezer and Regemmelech, and their men, to pray before the LORD,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 3, 'And to speak unto the priests which were in the house of the LORD of hosts, and to the prophets, saying, Should I weep in the fifth month, separating myself, as I have done these so many years?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 4, 'Then came the word of the LORD of hosts unto me, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 5, 'Speak unto all the people of the land, and to the priests, saying, When ye fasted and mourned in the fifth and seventh month, even those seventy years, did ye at all fast unto me, even to me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 6, 'And when ye did eat, and when ye did drink, did not ye eat for yourselves, and drink for yourselves?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 7, 'Should ye not hear the words which the LORD hath cried by the former prophets, when Jerusalem was inhabited and in prosperity, and the cities thereof round about her, when men inhabited the south and the plain?'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 8, 'And the word of the LORD came unto Zechariah, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 9, 'Thus speaketh the LORD of hosts, saying, Execute true judgment, and shew mercy and compassions every man to his brother:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 10, 'And oppress not the widow, nor the fatherless, the stranger, nor the poor; and let none of you imagine evil against his brother in your heart.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 11, 'But they refused to hearken, and pulled away the shoulder, and stopped their ears, that they should not hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 12, 'Yea, they made their hearts as an adamant stone, lest they should hear the law, and the words which the LORD of hosts hath sent in his spirit by the former prophets: therefore came a great wrath from the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 13, 'Therefore it is come to pass, that as he cried, and they would not hear; so they cried, and I would not hear, saith the LORD of hosts:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 7, 14, 'But I scattered them with a whirlwind among all the nations whom they knew not. Thus the land was desolate after them, that no man passed through nor returned: for they laid the pleasant land desolate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 1, 'Again the word of the LORD of hosts came to me, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 2, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; I was jealous for Zion with great jealousy, and I was jealous for her with great fury.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 3, 'Thus saith the LORD; I am returned unto Zion, and will dwell in the midst of Jerusalem: and Jerusalem shall be called a city of truth; and the mountain of the LORD of hosts the holy mountain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 4, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; There shall yet old men and old women dwell in the streets of Jerusalem, and every man with his staff in his hand for very age.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 5, 'And the streets of the city shall be full of boys and girls playing in the streets thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 6, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; If it be marvellous in the eyes of the remnant of this people in these days, should it also be marvellous in mine eyes? saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 7, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Behold, I will save my people from the east country, and from the west country;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 8, 'And I will bring them, and they shall dwell in the midst of Jerusalem: and they shall be my people, and I will be their God, in truth and in righteousness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 9, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Let your hands be strong, ye that hear in these days these words by the mouth of the prophets, which were in the day that the foundation of the house of the LORD of hosts was laid, that the temple might be built.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 10, 'For before these days there was no hire for man, nor any hire for beast; neither was there any peace to him that went out or came in because of the affliction: for I set all men every one against his neighbour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 11, 'But now I will not be unto the residue of this people as in the former days, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 12, 'For the seed shall be prosperous; the vine shall give her fruit, and the ground shall give her increase, and the heavens shall give their dew; and I will cause the remnant of this people to possess all these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 13, 'And it shall come to pass, that as ye were a curse among the heathen, O house of Judah, and house of Israel; so will I save you, and ye shall be a blessing: fear not, but let your hands be strong.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 14, 'For thus saith the LORD of hosts; As I thought to punish you, when your fathers provoked me to wrath, saith the LORD of hosts, and I repented not:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 15, 'So again have I thought in these days to do well unto Jerusalem and to the house of Judah: fear ye not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 16, 'These are the things that ye shall do; Speak ye every man the truth to his neighbour; execute the judgment of truth and peace in your gates:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 17, 'And let none of you imagine evil in your hearts against his neighbour; and love no false oath: for all these are things that I hate, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 18, 'And the word of the LORD of hosts came unto me, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 19, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; The fast of the fourth month, and the fast of the fifth, and the fast of the seventh, and the fast of the tenth, shall be to the house of Judah joy and gladness, and cheerful feasts; therefore love the truth and peace.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 20, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; It shall yet come to pass, that there shall come people, and the inhabitants of many cities:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 21, 'And the inhabitants of one city shall go to another, saying, Let us go speedily to pray before the LORD, and to seek the LORD of hosts: I will go also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 22, 'Yea, many people and strong nations shall come to seek the LORD of hosts in Jerusalem, and to pray before the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 8, 23, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; In those days it shall come to pass, that ten men shall take hold out of all languages of the nations, even shall take hold of the skirt of him that is a Jew, saying, We will go with you: for we have heard that God is with you.')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 1, 'The burden of the word of the LORD in the land of Hadrach, and Damascus shall be the rest thereof: when the eyes of man, as of all the tribes of Israel, shall be toward the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 2, 'And Hamath also shall border thereby; Tyrus, and Zidon, though it be very wise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 3, 'And Tyrus did build herself a strong hold, and heaped up silver as the dust, and fine gold as the mire of the streets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 4, 'Behold, the Lord will cast her out, and he will smite her power in the sea; and she shall be devoured with fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 5, 'Ashkelon shall see it, and fear; Gaza also shall see it, and be very sorrowful, and Ekron; for her expectation shall be ashamed; and the king shall perish from Gaza, and Ashkelon shall not be inhabited.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 6, 'And a bastard shall dwell in Ashdod, and I will cut off the pride of the Philistines.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 7, 'And I will take away his blood out of his mouth, and his abominations from between his teeth: but he that remaineth, even he, shall be for our God, and he shall be as a governor in Judah, and Ekron as a Jebusite.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 8, 'And I will encamp about mine house because of the army, because of him that passeth by, and because of him that returneth: and no oppressor shall pass through them any more: for now have I seen with mine eyes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 9, 'Rejoice greatly, O daughter of Zion; shout, O daughter of Jerusalem: behold, thy King cometh unto thee: he is just, and having salvation; lowly, and riding upon an ass, and upon a colt the foal of an ass.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 10, 'And I will cut off the chariot from Ephraim, and the horse from Jerusalem, and the battle bow shall be cut off: and he shall speak peace unto the heathen: and his dominion shall be from sea even to sea, and from the river even to the ends of the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 11, 'As for thee also, by the blood of thy covenant I have sent forth thy prisoners out of the pit wherein is no water.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 12, 'Turn you to the strong hold, ye prisoners of hope: even to day do I declare that I will render double unto thee;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 13, 'When I have bent Judah for me, filled the bow with Ephraim, and raised up thy sons, O Zion, against thy sons, O Greece, and made thee as the sword of a mighty man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 14, 'And the LORD shall be seen over them, and his arrow shall go forth as the lightning: and the Lord GOD shall blow the trumpet, and shall go with whirlwinds of the south.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 15, 'The LORD of hosts shall defend them; and they shall devour, and subdue with sling stones; and they shall drink, and make a noise as through wine; and they shall be filled like bowls, and as the corners of the altar.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 16, 'And the LORD their God shall save them in that day as the flock of his people: for they shall be as the stones of a crown, lifted up as an ensign upon his land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 9, 17, 'For how great is his goodness, and how great is his beauty! corn shall make the young men cheerful, and new wine the maids.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 1, 'Ask ye of the LORD rain in the time of the latter rain; so the LORD shall make bright clouds, and give them showers of rain, to every one grass in the field.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 2, 'For the idols have spoken vanity, and the diviners have seen a lie, and have told false dreams; they comfort in vain: therefore they went their way as a flock, they were troubled, because there was no shepherd.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 3, 'Mine anger was kindled against the shepherds, and I punished the goats: for the LORD of hosts hath visited his flock the house of Judah, and hath made them as his goodly horse in the battle.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 4, 'Out of him came forth the corner, out of him the nail, out of him the battle bow, out of him every oppressor together.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 5, 'And they shall be as mighty men, which tread down their enemies in the mire of the streets in the battle: and they shall fight, because the LORD is with them, and the riders on horses shall be confounded.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 6, 'And I will strengthen the house of Judah, and I will save the house of Joseph, and I will bring them again to place them; for I have mercy upon them: and they shall be as though I had not cast them off: for I am the LORD their God, and will hear them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 7, 'And they of Ephraim shall be like a mighty man, and their heart shall rejoice as through wine: yea, their children shall see it, and be glad; their heart shall rejoice in the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 8, 'I will hiss for them, and gather them; for I have redeemed them: and they shall increase as they have increased.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 9, 'And I will sow them among the people: and they shall remember me in far countries; and they shall live with their children, and turn again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 10, 'I will bring them again also out of the land of Egypt, and gather them out of Assyria; and I will bring them into the land of Gilead and Lebanon; and place shall not be found for them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 11, 'And he shall pass through the sea with affliction, and shall smite the waves in the sea, and all the deeps of the river shall dry up: and the pride of Assyria shall be brought down, and the sceptre of Egypt shall depart away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 10, 12, 'And I will strengthen them in the LORD; and they shall walk up and down in his name, saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 1, 'Open thy doors, O Lebanon, that the fire may devour thy cedars.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 2, 'Howl, fir tree; for the cedar is fallen; because the mighty are spoiled: howl, O ye oaks of Bashan; for the forest of the vintage is come down.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 3, 'There is a voice of the howling of the shepherds; for their glory is spoiled: a voice of the roaring of young lions; for the pride of Jordan is spoiled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 4, 'Thus saith the LORD my God; Feed the flock of the slaughter;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 5, 'Whose possessors slay them, and hold themselves not guilty: and they that sell them say, Blessed be the LORD; for I am rich: and their own shepherds pity them not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 6, 'For I will no more pity the inhabitants of the land, saith the LORD: but, lo, I will deliver the men every one into his neighbour''s hand, and into the hand of his king: and they shall smite the land, and out of their hand I will not deliver them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 7, 'And I will feed the flock of slaughter, even you, O poor of the flock. And I took unto me two staves; the one I called Beauty, and the other I called Bands; and I fed the flock.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 8, 'Three shepherds also I cut off in one month; and my soul lothed them, and their soul also abhorred me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 9, 'Then said I, I will not feed you: that that dieth, let it die; and that that is to be cut off, let it be cut off; and let the rest eat every one the flesh of another.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 10, 'And I took my staff, even Beauty, and cut it asunder, that I might break my covenant which I had made with all the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 11, 'And it was broken in that day: and so the poor of the flock that waited upon me knew that it was the word of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 12, 'And I said unto them, If ye think good, give me my price; and if not, forbear. So they weighed for my price thirty pieces of silver.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 13, 'And the LORD said unto me, Cast it unto the potter: a goodly price that I was prised at of them. And I took the thirty pieces of silver, and cast them to the potter in the house of the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 14, 'Then I cut asunder mine other staff, even Bands, that I might break the brotherhood between Judah and Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 15, 'And the LORD said unto me, Take unto thee yet the instruments of a foolish shepherd.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 16, 'For, lo, I will raise up a shepherd in the land, which shall not visit those that be cut off, neither shall seek the young one, nor heal that that is broken, nor feed that that standeth still: but he shall eat the flesh of the fat, and tear their claws in pieces.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 11, 17, 'Woe to the idol shepherd that leaveth the flock! the sword shall be upon his arm, and upon his right eye: his arm shall be clean dried up, and his right eye shall be utterly darkened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 1, 'The burden of the word of the LORD for Israel, saith the LORD, which stretcheth forth the heavens, and layeth the foundation of the earth, and formeth the spirit of man within him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 2, 'Behold, I will make Jerusalem a cup of trembling unto all the people round about, when they shall be in the siege both against Judah and against Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 3, 'And in that day will I make Jerusalem a burdensome stone for all people: all that burden themselves with it shall be cut in pieces, though all the people of the earth be gathered together against it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 4, 'In that day, saith the LORD, I will smite every horse with astonishment, and his rider with madness: and I will open mine eyes upon the house of Judah, and will smite every horse of the people with blindness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 5, 'And the governors of Judah shall say in their heart, The inhabitants of Jerusalem shall be my strength in the LORD of hosts their God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 6, 'In that day will I make the governors of Judah like an hearth of fire among the wood, and like a torch of fire in a sheaf; and they shall devour all the people round about, on the right hand and on the left: and Jerusalem shall be inhabited again in her own place, even in Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 7, 'The LORD also shall save the tents of Judah first, that the glory of the house of David and the glory of the inhabitants of Jerusalem do not magnify themselves against Judah.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 8, 'In that day shall the LORD defend the inhabitants of Jerusalem; and he that is feeble among them at that day shall be as David; and the house of David shall be as God, as the angel of the LORD before them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 9, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that I will seek to destroy all the nations that come against Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 10, 'And I will pour upon the house of David, and upon the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the spirit of grace and of supplications: and they shall look upon me whom they have pierced, and they shall mourn for him, as one mourneth for his only son, and shall be in bitterness for him, as one that is in bitterness for his firstborn.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 11, 'In that day shall there be a great mourning in Jerusalem, as the mourning of Hadadrimmon in the valley of Megiddon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 12, 'And the land shall mourn, every family apart; the family of the house of David apart, and their wives apart; the family of the house of Nathan apart, and their wives apart;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 13, 'The family of the house of Levi apart, and their wives apart; the family of Shimei apart, and their wives apart;'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 12, 14, 'All the families that remain, every family apart, and their wives apart.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 1, 'In that day there shall be a fountain opened to the house of David and to the inhabitants of Jerusalem for sin and for uncleanness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 2, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the LORD of hosts, that I will cut off the names of the idols out of the land, and they shall no more be remembered: and also I will cause the prophets and the unclean spirit to pass out of the land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 3, 'And it shall come to pass, that when any shall yet prophesy, then his father and his mother that begat him shall say unto him, Thou shalt not live; for thou speakest lies in the name of the LORD: and his father and his mother that begat him shall thrust him through when he prophesieth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 4, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that the prophets shall be ashamed every one of his vision, when he hath prophesied; neither shall they wear a rough garment to deceive:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 5, 'But he shall say, I am no prophet, I am an husbandman; for man taught me to keep cattle from my youth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 6, 'And one shall say unto him, What are these wounds in thine hands? Then he shall answer, Those with which I was wounded in the house of my friends.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 7, 'Awake, O sword, against my shepherd, and against the man that is my fellow, saith the LORD of hosts: smite the shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered: and I will turn mine hand upon the little ones.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 8, 'And it shall come to pass, that in all the land, saith the LORD, two parts therein shall be cut off and die; but the third shall be left therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 13, 9, 'And I will bring the third part through the fire, and will refine them as silver is refined, and will try them as gold is tried: they shall call on my name, and I will hear them: I will say, It is my people: and they shall say, The LORD is my God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 1, 'Behold, the day of the LORD cometh, and thy spoil shall be divided in the midst of thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 2, 'For I will gather all nations against Jerusalem to battle; and the city shall be taken, and the houses rifled, and the women ravished; and half of the city shall go forth into captivity, and the residue of the people shall not be cut off from the city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 3, 'Then shall the LORD go forth, and fight against those nations, as when he fought in the day of battle.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 4, 'And his feet shall stand in that day upon the mount of Olives, which is before Jerusalem on the east, and the mount of Olives shall cleave in the midst thereof toward the east and toward the west, and there shall be a very great valley; and half of the mountain shall remove toward the north, and half of it toward the south.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 5, 'And ye shall flee to the valley of the mountains; for the valley of the mountains shall reach unto Azal: yea, ye shall flee, like as ye fled from before the earthquake in the days of Uzziah king of Judah: and the LORD my God shall come, and all the saints with thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 6, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that the light shall not be clear, nor dark:'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 7, 'But it shall be one day which shall be known to the LORD, not day, nor night: but it shall come to pass, that at evening time it shall be light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 8, 'And it shall be in that day, that living waters shall go out from Jerusalem; half of them toward the former sea, and half of them toward the hinder sea: in summer and in winter shall it be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 9, 'And the LORD shall be king over all the earth: in that day shall there be one LORD, and his name one.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 10, 'All the land shall be turned as a plain from Geba to Rimmon south of Jerusalem: and it shall be lifted up, and inhabited in her place, from Benjamin''s gate unto the place of the first gate, unto the corner gate, and from the tower of Hananeel unto the king''s winepresses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 11, 'And men shall dwell in it, and there shall be no more utter destruction; but Jerusalem shall be safely inhabited.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 12, 'And this shall be the plague wherewith the LORD will smite all the people that have fought against Jerusalem; Their flesh shall consume away while they stand upon their feet, and their eyes shall consume away in their holes, and their tongue shall consume away in their mouth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 13, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that a great tumult from the LORD shall be among them; and they shall lay hold every one on the hand of his neighbour, and his hand shall rise up against the hand of his neighbour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 14, 'And Judah also shall fight at Jerusalem; and the wealth of all the heathen round about shall be gathered together, gold, and silver, and apparel, in great abundance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 15, 'And so shall be the plague of the horse, of the mule, of the camel, and of the ass, and of all the beasts that shall be in these tents, as this plague.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 16, 'And it shall come to pass, that every one that is left of all the nations which came against Jerusalem shall even go up from year to year to worship the King, the LORD of hosts, and to keep the feast of tabernacles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 17, 'And it shall be, that whoso will not come up of all the families of the earth unto Jerusalem to worship the King, the LORD of hosts, even upon them shall be no rain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 18, 'And if the family of Egypt go not up, and come not, that have no rain; there shall be the plague, wherewith the LORD will smite the heathen that come not up to keep the feast of tabernacles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 19, 'This shall be the punishment of Egypt, and the punishment of all nations that come not up to keep the feast of tabernacles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 20, 'In that day shall there be upon the bells of the horses, HOLINESS UNTO THE LORD; and the pots in the LORD''S house shall be like the bowls before the altar.'),
  ('KJV', 'Zechariah', 38, 14, 21, 'Yea, every pot in Jerusalem and in Judah shall be holiness unto the LORD of hosts: and all they that sacrifice shall come and take of them, and seethe therein: and in that day there shall be no more the Canaanite in the house of the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 1, 'The burden of the word of the LORD to Israel by Malachi.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 2, 'I have loved you, saith the LORD. Yet ye say, Wherein hast thou loved us? Was not Esau Jacob''s brother? saith the LORD: yet I loved Jacob,'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 3, 'And I hated Esau, and laid his mountains and his heritage waste for the dragons of the wilderness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 4, 'Whereas Edom saith, We are impoverished, but we will return and build the desolate places; thus saith the LORD of hosts, They shall build, but I will throw down; and they shall call them, The border of wickedness, and, The people against whom the LORD hath indignation for ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 5, 'And your eyes shall see, and ye shall say, The LORD will be magnified from the border of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 6, 'A son honoureth his father, and a servant his master: if then I be a father, where is mine honour? and if I be a master, where is my fear? saith the LORD of hosts unto you, O priests, that despise my name. And ye say, Wherein have we despised thy name?'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 7, 'Ye offer polluted bread upon mine altar; and ye say, Wherein have we polluted thee? In that ye say, The table of the LORD is contemptible.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 8, 'And if ye offer the blind for sacrifice, is it not evil? and if ye offer the lame and sick, is it not evil? offer it now unto thy governor; will he be pleased with thee, or accept thy person? saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 9, 'And now, I pray you, beseech God that he will be gracious unto us: this hath been by your means: will he regard your persons? saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 10, 'Who is there even among you that would shut the doors for nought? neither do ye kindle fire on mine altar for nought. I have no pleasure in you, saith the LORD of hosts, neither will I accept an offering at your hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 11, 'For from the rising of the sun even unto the going down of the same my name shall be great among the Gentiles; and in every place incense shall be offered unto my name, and a pure offering: for my name shall be great among the heathen, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 12, 'But ye have profaned it, in that ye say, The table of the LORD is polluted; and the fruit thereof, even his meat, is contemptible.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 13, 'Ye said also, Behold, what a weariness is it! and ye have snuffed at it, saith the LORD of hosts; and ye brought that which was torn, and the lame, and the sick; thus ye brought an offering: should I accept this of your hand? saith the LORD.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 1, 14, 'But cursed be the deceiver, which hath in his flock a male, and voweth, and sacrificeth unto the Lord a corrupt thing: for I am a great King, saith the LORD of hosts, and my name is dreadful among the heathen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 1, 'And now, O ye priests, this commandment is for you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 2, 'If ye will not hear, and if ye will not lay it to heart, to give glory unto my name, saith the LORD of hosts, I will even send a curse upon you, and I will curse your blessings: yea, I have cursed them already, because ye do not lay it to heart.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 3, 'Behold, I will corrupt your seed, and spread dung upon your faces, even the dung of your solemn feasts; and one shall take you away with it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 4, 'And ye shall know that I have sent this commandment unto you, that my covenant might be with Levi, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 5, 'My covenant was with him of life and peace; and I gave them to him for the fear wherewith he feared me, and was afraid before my name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 6, 'The law of truth was in his mouth, and iniquity was not found in his lips: he walked with me in peace and equity, and did turn many away from iniquity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 7, 'For the priest''s lips should keep knowledge, and they should seek the law at his mouth: for he is the messenger of the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 8, 'But ye are departed out of the way; ye have caused many to stumble at the law; ye have corrupted the covenant of Levi, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 9, 'Therefore have I also made you contemptible and base before all the people, according as ye have not kept my ways, but have been partial in the law.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 10, 'Have we not all one father? hath not one God created us? why do we deal treacherously every man against his brother, by profaning the covenant of our fathers?'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 11, 'Judah hath dealt treacherously, and an abomination is committed in Israel and in Jerusalem; for Judah hath profaned the holiness of the LORD which he loved, and hath married the daughter of a strange god.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 12, 'The LORD will cut off the man that doeth this, the master and the scholar, out of the tabernacles of Jacob, and him that offereth an offering unto the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 13, 'And this have ye done again, covering the altar of the LORD with tears, with weeping, and with crying out, insomuch that he regardeth not the offering any more, or receiveth it with good will at your hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 14, 'Yet ye say, Wherefore? Because the LORD hath been witness between thee and the wife of thy youth, against whom thou hast dealt treacherously: yet is she thy companion, and the wife of thy covenant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 15, 'And did not he make one? Yet had he the residue of the spirit. And wherefore one? That he might seek a godly seed. Therefore take heed to your spirit, and let none deal treacherously against the wife of his youth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 16, 'For the LORD, the God of Israel, saith that he hateth putting away: for one covereth violence with his garment, saith the LORD of hosts: therefore take heed to your spirit, that ye deal not treacherously.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 2, 17, 'Ye have wearied the LORD with your words. Yet ye say, Wherein have we wearied him? When ye say, Every one that doeth evil is good in the sight of the LORD, and he delighteth in them; or, Where is the God of judgment?'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 1, 'Behold, I will send my messenger, and he shall prepare the way before me: and the Lord, whom ye seek, shall suddenly come to his temple, even the messenger of the covenant, whom ye delight in: behold, he shall come, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 2, 'But who may abide the day of his coming? and who shall stand when he appeareth? for he is like a refiner''s fire, and like fullers'' soap:'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 3, 'And he shall sit as a refiner and purifier of silver: and he shall purify the sons of Levi, and purge them as gold and silver, that they may offer unto the LORD an offering in righteousness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 4, 'Then shall the offering of Judah and Jerusalem be pleasant unto the LORD, as in the days of old, and as in former years.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 5, 'And I will come near to you to judgment; and I will be a swift witness against the sorcerers, and against the adulterers, and against false swearers, and against those that oppress the hireling in his wages, the widow, and the fatherless, and that turn aside the stranger from his right, and fear not me, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 6, 'For I am the LORD, I change not; therefore ye sons of Jacob are not consumed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 7, 'Even from the days of your fathers ye are gone away from mine ordinances, and have not kept them. Return unto me, and I will return unto you, saith the LORD of hosts. But ye said, Wherein shall we return?'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 8, 'Will a man rob God? Yet ye have robbed me. But ye say, Wherein have we robbed thee? In tithes and offerings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 9, 'Ye are cursed with a curse: for ye have robbed me, even this whole nation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 10, 'Bring ye all the tithes into the storehouse, that there may be meat in mine house, and prove me now herewith, saith the LORD of hosts, if I will not open you the windows of heaven, and pour you out a blessing, that there shall not be room enough to receive it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 11, 'And I will rebuke the devourer for your sakes, and he shall not destroy the fruits of your ground; neither shall your vine cast her fruit before the time in the field, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 12, 'And all nations shall call you blessed: for ye shall be a delightsome land, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 13, 'Your words have been stout against me, saith the LORD. Yet ye say, What have we spoken so much against thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 14, 'Ye have said, It is vain to serve God: and what profit is it that we have kept his ordinance, and that we have walked mournfully before the LORD of hosts?'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 15, 'And now we call the proud happy; yea, they that work wickedness are set up; yea, they that tempt God are even delivered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 16, 'Then they that feared the LORD spake often one to another: and the LORD hearkened, and heard it, and a book of remembrance was written before him for them that feared the LORD, and that thought upon his name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 17, 'And they shall be mine, saith the LORD of hosts, in that day when I make up my jewels; and I will spare them, as a man spareth his own son that serveth him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 3, 18, 'Then shall ye return, and discern between the righteous and the wicked, between him that serveth God and him that serveth him not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 4, 1, 'For, behold, the day cometh, that shall burn as an oven; and all the proud, yea, and all that do wickedly, shall be stubble: and the day that cometh shall burn them up, saith the LORD of hosts, that it shall leave them neither root nor branch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 4, 2, 'But unto you that fear my name shall the Sun of righteousness arise with healing in his wings; and ye shall go forth, and grow up as calves of the stall.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 4, 3, 'And ye shall tread down the wicked; for they shall be ashes under the soles of your feet in the day that I shall do this, saith the LORD of hosts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 4, 4, 'Remember ye the law of Moses my servant, which I commanded unto him in Horeb for all Israel, with the statutes and judgments.'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 4, 5, 'Behold, I will send you Elijah the prophet before the coming of the great and dreadful day of the LORD:'),
  ('KJV', 'Malachi', 39, 4, 6, 'And he shall turn the heart of the fathers to the children, and the heart of the children to their fathers, lest I come and smite the earth with a curse.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 1, 'The book of the generation of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 2, 'Abraham begat Isaac; and Isaac begat Jacob; and Jacob begat Judas and his brethren;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 3, 'And Judas begat Phares and Zara of Thamar; and Phares begat Esrom; and Esrom begat Aram;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 4, 'And Aram begat Aminadab; and Aminadab begat Naasson; and Naasson begat Salmon;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 5, 'And Salmon begat Booz of Rachab; and Booz begat Obed of Ruth; and Obed begat Jesse;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 6, 'And Jesse begat David the king; and David the king begat Solomon of her that had been the wife of Urias;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 7, 'And Solomon begat Roboam; and Roboam begat Abia; and Abia begat Asa;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 8, 'And Asa begat Josaphat; and Josaphat begat Joram; and Joram begat Ozias;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 9, 'And Ozias begat Joatham; and Joatham begat Achaz; and Achaz begat Ezekias;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 10, 'And Ezekias begat Manasses; and Manasses begat Amon; and Amon begat Josias;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 11, 'And Josias begat Jechonias and his brethren, about the time they were carried away to Babylon:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 12, 'And after they were brought to Babylon, Jechonias begat Salathiel; and Salathiel begat Zorobabel;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 13, 'And Zorobabel begat Abiud; and Abiud begat Eliakim; and Eliakim begat Azor;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 14, 'And Azor begat Sadoc; and Sadoc begat Achim; and Achim begat Eliud;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 15, 'And Eliud begat Eleazar; and Eleazar begat Matthan; and Matthan begat Jacob;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 16, 'And Jacob begat Joseph the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 17, 'So all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen generations; and from David until the carrying away into Babylon are fourteen generations; and from the carrying away into Babylon unto Christ are fourteen generations.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 18, 'Now the birth of Jesus Christ was on this wise: When as his mother Mary was espoused to Joseph, before they came together, she was found with child of the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 19, 'Then Joseph her husband, being a just man, and not willing to make her a publick example, was minded to put her away privily.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 20, 'But while he thought on these things, behold, the angel of the Lord appeared unto him in a dream, saying, Joseph, thou son of David, fear not to take unto thee Mary thy wife: for that which is conceived in her is of the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 21, 'And she shall bring forth a son, and thou shalt call his name JESUS: for he shall save his people from their sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 22, 'Now all this was done, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 23, 'Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel, which being interpreted is, God with us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 24, 'Then Joseph being raised from sleep did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him, and took unto him his wife:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 1, 25, 'And knew her not till she had brought forth her firstborn son: and he called his name JESUS.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 1, 'Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judaea in the days of Herod the king, behold, there came wise men from the east to Jerusalem,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 2, 'Saying, Where is he that is born King of the Jews? for we have seen his star in the east, and are come to worship him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 3, 'When Herod the king had heard these things, he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 4, 'And when he had gathered all the chief priests and scribes of the people together, he demanded of them where Christ should be born.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 5, 'And they said unto him, In Bethlehem of Judaea: for thus it is written by the prophet,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 6, 'And thou Bethlehem, in the land of Juda, art not the least among the princes of Juda: for out of thee shall come a Governor, that shall rule my people Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 7, 'Then Herod, when he had privily called the wise men, enquired of them diligently what time the star appeared.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 8, 'And he sent them to Bethlehem, and said, Go and search diligently for the young child; and when ye have found him, bring me word again, that I may come and worship him also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 9, 'When they had heard the king, they departed; and, lo, the star, which they saw in the east, went before them, till it came and stood over where the young child was.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 10, 'When they saw the star, they rejoiced with exceeding great joy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 11, 'And when they were come into the house, they saw the young child with Mary his mother, and fell down, and worshipped him: and when they had opened their treasures, they presented unto him gifts; gold, and frankincense, and myrrh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 12, 'And being warned of God in a dream that they should not return to Herod, they departed into their own country another way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 13, 'And when they were departed, behold, the angel of the Lord appeareth to Joseph in a dream, saying, Arise, and take the young child and his mother, and flee into Egypt, and be thou there until I bring thee word: for Herod will seek the young child to destroy him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 14, 'When he arose, he took the young child and his mother by night, and departed into Egypt:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 15, 'And was there until the death of Herod: that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet, saying, Out of Egypt have I called my son.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 16, 'Then Herod, when he saw that he was mocked of the wise men, was exceeding wroth, and sent forth, and slew all the children that were in Bethlehem, and in all the coasts thereof, from two years old and under, according to the time which he had diligently enquired of the wise men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 17, 'Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremy the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 18, 'In Rama was there a voice heard, lamentation, and weeping, and great mourning, Rachel weeping for her children, and would not be comforted, because they are not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 19, 'But when Herod was dead, behold, an angel of the Lord appeareth in a dream to Joseph in Egypt,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 20, 'Saying, Arise, and take the young child and his mother, and go into the land of Israel: for they are dead which sought the young child''s life.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 21, 'And he arose, and took the young child and his mother, and came into the land of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 22, 'But when he heard that Archelaus did reign in Judaea in the room of his father Herod, he was afraid to go thither: notwithstanding, being warned of God in a dream, he turned aside into the parts of Galilee:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 2, 23, 'And he came and dwelt in a city called Nazareth: that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophets, He shall be called a Nazarene.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 1, 'In those days came John the Baptist, preaching in the wilderness of Judaea,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 2, 'And saying, Repent ye: for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 3, 'For this is he that was spoken of by the prophet Esaias, saying, The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 4, 'And the same John had his raiment of camel''s hair, and a leathern girdle about his loins; and his meat was locusts and wild honey.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 5, 'Then went out to him Jerusalem, and all Judaea, and all the region round about Jordan,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 6, 'And were baptized of him in Jordan, confessing their sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 7, 'But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees come to his baptism, he said unto them, O generation of vipers, who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 8, 'Bring forth therefore fruits meet for repentance:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 9, 'And think not to say within yourselves, We have Abraham to our father: for I say unto you, that God is able of these stones to raise up children unto Abraham.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 10, 'And now also the axe is laid unto the root of the trees: therefore every tree which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 11, 'I indeed baptize you with water unto repentance: but he that cometh after me is mightier than I, whose shoes I am not worthy to bear: he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost, and with fire:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 12, 'Whose fan is in his hand, and he will throughly purge his floor, and gather his wheat into the garner; but he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 13, 'Then cometh Jesus from Galilee to Jordan unto John, to be baptized of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 14, 'But John forbad him, saying, I have need to be baptized of thee, and comest thou to me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 15, 'And Jesus answering said unto him, Suffer it to be so now: for thus it becometh us to fulfil all righteousness. Then he suffered him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 16, 'And Jesus, when he was baptized, went up straightway out of the water: and, lo, the heavens were opened unto him, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove, and lighting upon him:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 3, 17, 'And lo a voice from heaven, saying, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 1, 'Then was Jesus led up of the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted of the devil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 2, 'And when he had fasted forty days and forty nights, he was afterward an hungred.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 3, 'And when the tempter came to him, he said, If thou be the Son of God, command that these stones be made bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 4, 'But he answered and said, It is written, Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceedeth out of the mouth of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 5, 'Then the devil taketh him up into the holy city, and setteth him on a pinnacle of the temple,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 6, 'And saith unto him, If thou be the Son of God, cast thyself down: for it is written, He shall give his angels charge concerning thee: and in their hands they shall bear thee up, lest at any time thou dash thy foot against a stone.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 7, 'Jesus said unto him, It is written again, Thou shalt not tempt the Lord thy God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 8, 'Again, the devil taketh him up into an exceeding high mountain, and sheweth him all the kingdoms of the world, and the glory of them;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 9, 'And saith unto him, All these things will I give thee, if thou wilt fall down and worship me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 10, 'Then saith Jesus unto him, Get thee hence, Satan: for it is written, Thou shalt worship the Lord thy God, and him only shalt thou serve.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 11, 'Then the devil leaveth him, and, behold, angels came and ministered unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 12, 'Now when Jesus had heard that John was cast into prison, he departed into Galilee;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 13, 'And leaving Nazareth, he came and dwelt in Capernaum, which is upon the sea coast, in the borders of Zabulon and Nephthalim:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 14, 'That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Esaias the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 15, 'The land of Zabulon, and the land of Nephthalim, by the way of the sea, beyond Jordan, Galilee of the Gentiles;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 16, 'The people which sat in darkness saw great light; and to them which sat in the region and shadow of death light is sprung up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 17, 'From that time Jesus began to preach, and to say, Repent: for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 18, 'And Jesus, walking by the sea of Galilee, saw two brethren, Simon called Peter, and Andrew his brother, casting a net into the sea: for they were fishers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 19, 'And he saith unto them, Follow me, and I will make you fishers of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 20, 'And they straightway left their nets, and followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 21, 'And going on from thence, he saw other two brethren, James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother, in a ship with Zebedee their father, mending their nets; and he called them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 22, 'And they immediately left the ship and their father, and followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 23, 'And Jesus went about all Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, and preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing all manner of sickness and all manner of disease among the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 24, 'And his fame went throughout all Syria: and they brought unto him all sick people that were taken with divers diseases and torments, and those which were possessed with devils, and those which were lunatick, and those that had the palsy; and he healed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 4, 25, 'And there followed him great multitudes of people from Galilee, and from Decapolis, and from Jerusalem, and from Judaea, and from beyond Jordan.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 1, 'And seeing the multitudes, he went up into a mountain: and when he was set, his disciples came unto him:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 2, 'And he opened his mouth, and taught them, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 3, 'Blessed are the poor in spirit: for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 4, 'Blessed are they that mourn: for they shall be comforted.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 5, 'Blessed are the meek: for they shall inherit the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 6, 'Blessed are they which do hunger and thirst after righteousness: for they shall be filled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 7, 'Blessed are the merciful: for they shall obtain mercy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 8, 'Blessed are the pure in heart: for they shall see God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 9, 'Blessed are the peacemakers: for they shall be called the children of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 10, 'Blessed are they which are persecuted for righteousness'' sake: for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 11, 'Blessed are ye, when men shall revile you, and persecute you, and shall say all manner of evil against you falsely, for my sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 12, 'Rejoice, and be exceeding glad: for great is your reward in heaven: for so persecuted they the prophets which were before you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 13, 'Ye are the salt of the earth: but if the salt have lost his savour, wherewith shall it be salted? it is thenceforth good for nothing, but to be cast out, and to be trodden under foot of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 14, 'Ye are the light of the world. A city that is set on an hill cannot be hid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 15, 'Neither do men light a candle, and put it under a bushel, but on a candlestick; and it giveth light unto all that are in the house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 16, 'Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 17, 'Think not that I am come to destroy the law, or the prophets: I am not come to destroy, but to fulfil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 18, 'For verily I say unto you, Till heaven and earth pass, one jot or one tittle shall in no wise pass from the law, till all be fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 19, 'Whosoever therefore shall break one of these least commandments, and shall teach men so, he shall be called the least in the kingdom of heaven: but whosoever shall do and teach them, the same shall be called great in the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 20, 'For I say unto you, That except your righteousness shall exceed the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, ye shall in no case enter into the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 21, 'Ye have heard that it was said by them of old time, Thou shalt not kill; and whosoever shall kill shall be in danger of the judgment:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 22, 'But I say unto you, That whosoever is angry with his brother without a cause shall be in danger of the judgment: and whosoever shall say to his brother, Raca, shall be in danger of the council: but whosoever shall say, Thou fool, shall be in danger of hell fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 23, 'Therefore if thou bring thy gift to the altar, and there rememberest that thy brother hath ought against thee;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 24, 'Leave there thy gift before the altar, and go thy way; first be reconciled to thy brother, and then come and offer thy gift.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 25, 'Agree with thine adversary quickly, whiles thou art in the way with him; lest at any time the adversary deliver thee to the judge, and the judge deliver thee to the officer, and thou be cast into prison.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 26, 'Verily I say unto thee, Thou shalt by no means come out thence, till thou hast paid the uttermost farthing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 27, 'Ye have heard that it was said by them of old time, Thou shalt not commit adultery:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 28, 'But I say unto you, That whosoever looketh on a woman to lust after her hath committed adultery with her already in his heart.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 29, 'And if thy right eye offend thee, pluck it out, and cast it from thee: for it is profitable for thee that one of thy members should perish, and not that thy whole body should be cast into hell.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 30, 'And if thy right hand offend thee, cut it off, and cast it from thee: for it is profitable for thee that one of thy members should perish, and not that thy whole body should be cast into hell.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 31, 'It hath been said, Whosoever shall put away his wife, let him give her a writing of divorcement:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 32, 'But I say unto you, That whosoever shall put away his wife, saving for the cause of fornication, causeth her to commit adultery: and whosoever shall marry her that is divorced committeth adultery.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 33, 'Again, ye have heard that it hath been said by them of old time, Thou shalt not forswear thyself, but shalt perform unto the Lord thine oaths:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 34, 'But I say unto you, Swear not at all; neither by heaven; for it is God''s throne:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 35, 'Nor by the earth; for it is his footstool: neither by Jerusalem; for it is the city of the great King.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 36, 'Neither shalt thou swear by thy head, because thou canst not make one hair white or black.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 37, 'But let your communication be, Yea, yea; Nay, nay: for whatsoever is more than these cometh of evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 38, 'Ye have heard that it hath been said, An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 39, 'But I say unto you, That ye resist not evil: but whosoever shall smite thee on thy right cheek, turn to him the other also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 40, 'And if any man will sue thee at the law, and take away thy coat, let him have thy cloke also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 41, 'And whosoever shall compel thee to go a mile, go with him twain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 42, 'Give to him that asketh thee, and from him that would borrow of thee turn not thou away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 43, 'Ye have heard that it hath been said, Thou shalt love thy neighbour, and hate thine enemy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 44, 'But I say unto you, Love your enemies, bless them that curse you, do good to them that hate you, and pray for them which despitefully use you, and persecute you;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 45, 'That ye may be the children of your Father which is in heaven: for he maketh his sun to rise on the evil and on the good, and sendeth rain on the just and on the unjust.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 46, 'For if ye love them which love you, what reward have ye? do not even the publicans the same?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 47, 'And if ye salute your brethren only, what do ye more than others? do not even the publicans so?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 5, 48, 'Be ye therefore perfect, even as your Father which is in heaven is perfect.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 1, 'Take heed that ye do not your alms before men, to be seen of them: otherwise ye have no reward of your Father which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 2, 'Therefore when thou doest thine alms, do not sound a trumpet before thee, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, that they may have glory of men. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 3, 'But when thou doest alms, let not thy left hand know what thy right hand doeth:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 4, 'That thine alms may be in secret: and thy Father which seeth in secret himself shall reward thee openly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 5, 'And when thou prayest, thou shalt not be as the hypocrites are: for they love to pray standing in the synagogues and in the corners of the streets, that they may be seen of men. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 6, 'But thou, when thou prayest, enter into thy closet, and when thou hast shut thy door, pray to thy Father which is in secret; and thy Father which seeth in secret shall reward thee openly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 7, 'But when ye pray, use not vain repetitions, as the heathen do: for they think that they shall be heard for their much speaking.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 8, 'Be not ye therefore like unto them: for your Father knoweth what things ye have need of, before ye ask him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 9, 'After this manner therefore pray ye: Our Father which art in heaven, Hallowed be thy name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 10, 'Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done in earth, as it is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 11, 'Give us this day our daily bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 12, 'And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 13, 'And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil: For thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory, for ever. Amen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 14, 'For if ye forgive men their trespasses, your heavenly Father will also forgive you:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 15, 'But if ye forgive not men their trespasses, neither will your Father forgive your trespasses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 16, 'Moreover when ye fast, be not, as the hypocrites, of a sad countenance: for they disfigure their faces, that they may appear unto men to fast. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 17, 'But thou, when thou fastest, anoint thine head, and wash thy face;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 18, 'That thou appear not unto men to fast, but unto thy Father which is in secret: and thy Father, which seeth in secret, shall reward thee openly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 19, 'Lay not up for yourselves treasures upon earth, where moth and rust doth corrupt, and where thieves break through and steal:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 20, 'But lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust doth corrupt, and where thieves do not break through nor steal:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 21, 'For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 22, 'The light of the body is the eye: if therefore thine eye be single, thy whole body shall be full of light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 23, 'But if thine eye be evil, thy whole body shall be full of darkness. If therefore the light that is in thee be darkness, how great is that darkness!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 24, 'No man can serve two masters: for either he will hate the one, and love the other; or else he will hold to the one, and despise the other. Ye cannot serve God and mammon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 25, 'Therefore I say unto you, Take no thought for your life, what ye shall eat, or what ye shall drink; nor yet for your body, what ye shall put on. Is not the life more than meat, and the body than raiment?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 26, 'Behold the fowls of the air: for they sow not, neither do they reap, nor gather into barns; yet your heavenly Father feedeth them. Are ye not much better than they?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 27, 'Which of you by taking thought can add one cubit unto his stature?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 28, 'And why take ye thought for raiment? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow; they toil not, neither do they spin:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 29, 'And yet I say unto you, That even Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 30, 'Wherefore, if God so clothe the grass of the field, which to day is, and to morrow is cast into the oven, shall he not much more clothe you, O ye of little faith?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 31, 'Therefore take no thought, saying, What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink? or, Wherewithal shall we be clothed?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 32, '(For after all these things do the Gentiles seek:) for your heavenly Father knoweth that ye have need of all these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 33, 'But seek ye first the kingdom of God, and his righteousness; and all these things shall be added unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 6, 34, 'Take therefore no thought for the morrow: for the morrow shall take thought for the things of itself. Sufficient unto the day is the evil thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 1, 'Judge not, that ye be not judged.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 2, 'For with what judgment ye judge, ye shall be judged: and with what measure ye mete, it shall be measured to you again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 3, 'And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother''s eye, but considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 4, 'Or how wilt thou say to thy brother, Let me pull out the mote out of thine eye; and, behold, a beam is in thine own eye?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 5, 'Thou hypocrite, first cast out the beam out of thine own eye; and then shalt thou see clearly to cast out the mote out of thy brother''s eye.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 6, 'Give not that which is holy unto the dogs, neither cast ye your pearls before swine, lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 7, 'Ask, and it shall be given you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 8, 'For every one that asketh receiveth; and he that seeketh findeth; and to him that knocketh it shall be opened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 9, 'Or what man is there of you, whom if his son ask bread, will he give him a stone?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 10, 'Or if he ask a fish, will he give him a serpent?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 11, 'If ye then, being evil, know how to give good gifts unto your children, how much more shall your Father which is in heaven give good things to them that ask him?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 12, 'Therefore all things whatsoever ye would that men should do to you, do ye even so to them: for this is the law and the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 13, 'Enter ye in at the strait gate: for wide is the gate, and broad is the way, that leadeth to destruction, and many there be which go in thereat:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 14, 'Because strait is the gate, and narrow is the way, which leadeth unto life, and few there be that find it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 15, 'Beware of false prophets, which come to you in sheep''s clothing, but inwardly they are ravening wolves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 16, 'Ye shall know them by their fruits. Do men gather grapes of thorns, or figs of thistles?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 17, 'Even so every good tree bringeth forth good fruit; but a corrupt tree bringeth forth evil fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 18, 'A good tree cannot bring forth evil fruit, neither can a corrupt tree bring forth good fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 19, 'Every tree that bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 20, 'Wherefore by their fruits ye shall know them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 21, 'Not every one that saith unto me, Lord, Lord, shall enter into the kingdom of heaven; but he that doeth the will of my Father which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 22, 'Many will say to me in that day, Lord, Lord, have we not prophesied in thy name? and in thy name have cast out devils? and in thy name done many wonderful works?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 23, 'And then will I profess unto them, I never knew you: depart from me, ye that work iniquity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 24, 'Therefore whosoever heareth these sayings of mine, and doeth them, I will liken him unto a wise man, which built his house upon a rock:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 25, 'And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell not: for it was founded upon a rock.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 26, 'And every one that heareth these sayings of mine, and doeth them not, shall be likened unto a foolish man, which built his house upon the sand:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 27, 'And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell: and great was the fall of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 28, 'And it came to pass, when Jesus had ended these sayings, the people were astonished at his doctrine:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 7, 29, 'For he taught them as one having authority, and not as the scribes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 1, 'When he was come down from the mountain, great multitudes followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 2, 'And, behold, there came a leper and worshipped him, saying, Lord, if thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 3, 'And Jesus put forth his hand, and touched him, saying, I will; be thou clean. And immediately his leprosy was cleansed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 4, 'And Jesus saith unto him, See thou tell no man; but go thy way, shew thyself to the priest, and offer the gift that Moses commanded, for a testimony unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 5, 'And when Jesus was entered into Capernaum, there came unto him a centurion, beseeching him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 6, 'And saying, Lord, my servant lieth at home sick of the palsy, grievously tormented.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 7, 'And Jesus saith unto him, I will come and heal him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 8, 'The centurion answered and said, Lord, I am not worthy that thou shouldest come under my roof: but speak the word only, and my servant shall be healed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 9, 'For I am a man under authority, having soldiers under me: and I say to this man, Go, and he goeth; and to another, Come, and he cometh; and to my servant, Do this, and he doeth it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 10, 'When Jesus heard it, he marvelled, and said to them that followed, Verily I say unto you, I have not found so great faith, no, not in Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 11, 'And I say unto you, That many shall come from the east and west, and shall sit down with Abraham, and Isaac, and Jacob, in the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 12, 'But the children of the kingdom shall be cast out into outer darkness: there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 13, 'And Jesus said unto the centurion, Go thy way; and as thou hast believed, so be it done unto thee. And his servant was healed in the selfsame hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 14, 'And when Jesus was come into Peter''s house, he saw his wife''s mother laid, and sick of a fever.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 15, 'And he touched her hand, and the fever left her: and she arose, and ministered unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 16, 'When the even was come, they brought unto him many that were possessed with devils: and he cast out the spirits with his word, and healed all that were sick:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 17, 'That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Esaias the prophet, saying, Himself took our infirmities, and bare our sicknesses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 18, 'Now when Jesus saw great multitudes about him, he gave commandment to depart unto the other side.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 19, 'And a certain scribe came, and said unto him, Master, I will follow thee whithersoever thou goest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 20, 'And Jesus saith unto him, The foxes have holes, and the birds of the air have nests; but the Son of man hath not where to lay his head.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 21, 'And another of his disciples said unto him, Lord, suffer me first to go and bury my father.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 22, 'But Jesus said unto him, Follow me; and let the dead bury their dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 23, 'And when he was entered into a ship, his disciples followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 24, 'And, behold, there arose a great tempest in the sea, insomuch that the ship was covered with the waves: but he was asleep.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 25, 'And his disciples came to him, and awoke him, saying, Lord, save us: we perish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 26, 'And he saith unto them, Why are ye fearful, O ye of little faith? Then he arose, and rebuked the winds and the sea; and there was a great calm.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 27, 'But the men marvelled, saying, What manner of man is this, that even the winds and the sea obey him!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 28, 'And when he was come to the other side into the country of the Gergesenes, there met him two possessed with devils, coming out of the tombs, exceeding fierce, so that no man might pass by that way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 29, 'And, behold, they cried out, saying, What have we to do with thee, Jesus, thou Son of God? art thou come hither to torment us before the time?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 30, 'And there was a good way off from them an herd of many swine feeding.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 31, 'So the devils besought him, saying, If thou cast us out, suffer us to go away into the herd of swine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 32, 'And he said unto them, Go. And when they were come out, they went into the herd of swine: and, behold, the whole herd of swine ran violently down a steep place into the sea, and perished in the waters.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 33, 'And they that kept them fled, and went their ways into the city, and told every thing, and what was befallen to the possessed of the devils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 8, 34, 'And, behold, the whole city came out to meet Jesus: and when they saw him, they besought him that he would depart out of their coasts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 1, 'And he entered into a ship, and passed over, and came into his own city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 2, 'And, behold, they brought to him a man sick of the palsy, lying on a bed: and Jesus seeing their faith said unto the sick of the palsy; Son, be of good cheer; thy sins be forgiven thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 3, 'And, behold, certain of the scribes said within themselves, This man blasphemeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 4, 'And Jesus knowing their thoughts said, Wherefore think ye evil in your hearts?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 5, 'For whether is easier, to say, Thy sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Arise, and walk?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 6, 'But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins, (then saith he to the sick of the palsy,) Arise, take up thy bed, and go unto thine house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 7, 'And he arose, and departed to his house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 8, 'But when the multitudes saw it, they marvelled, and glorified God, which had given such power unto men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 9, 'And as Jesus passed forth from thence, he saw a man, named Matthew, sitting at the receipt of custom: and he saith unto him, Follow me. And he arose, and followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 10, 'And it came to pass, as Jesus sat at meat in the house, behold, many publicans and sinners came and sat down with him and his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 11, 'And when the Pharisees saw it, they said unto his disciples, Why eateth your Master with publicans and sinners?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 12, 'But when Jesus heard that, he said unto them, They that be whole need not a physician, but they that are sick.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 13, 'But go ye and learn what that meaneth, I will have mercy, and not sacrifice: for I am not come to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 14, 'Then came to him the disciples of John, saying, Why do we and the Pharisees fast oft, but thy disciples fast not?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 15, 'And Jesus said unto them, Can the children of the bridechamber mourn, as long as the bridegroom is with them? but the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken from them, and then shall they fast.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 16, 'No man putteth a piece of new cloth unto an old garment, for that which is put in to fill it up taketh from the garment, and the rent is made worse.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 17, 'Neither do men put new wine into old bottles: else the bottles break, and the wine runneth out, and the bottles perish: but they put new wine into new bottles, and both are preserved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 18, 'While he spake these things unto them, behold, there came a certain ruler, and worshipped him, saying, My daughter is even now dead: but come and lay thy hand upon her, and she shall live.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 19, 'And Jesus arose, and followed him, and so did his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 20, 'And, behold, a woman, which was diseased with an issue of blood twelve years, came behind him, and touched the hem of his garment:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 21, 'For she said within herself, If I may but touch his garment, I shall be whole.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 22, 'But Jesus turned him about, and when he saw her, he said, Daughter, be of good comfort; thy faith hath made thee whole. And the woman was made whole from that hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 23, 'And when Jesus came into the ruler''s house, and saw the minstrels and the people making a noise,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 24, 'He said unto them, Give place: for the maid is not dead, but sleepeth. And they laughed him to scorn.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 25, 'But when the people were put forth, he went in, and took her by the hand, and the maid arose.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 26, 'And the fame hereof went abroad into all that land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 27, 'And when Jesus departed thence, two blind men followed him, crying, and saying, Thou Son of David, have mercy on us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 28, 'And when he was come into the house, the blind men came to him: and Jesus saith unto them, Believe ye that I am able to do this? They said unto him, Yea, Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 29, 'Then touched he their eyes, saying, According to your faith be it unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 30, 'And their eyes were opened; and Jesus straitly charged them, saying, See that no man know it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 31, 'But they, when they were departed, spread abroad his fame in all that country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 32, 'As they went out, behold, they brought to him a dumb man possessed with a devil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 33, 'And when the devil was cast out, the dumb spake: and the multitudes marvelled, saying, It was never so seen in Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 34, 'But the Pharisees said, He casteth out devils through the prince of the devils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 35, 'And Jesus went about all the cities and villages, teaching in their synagogues, and preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every sickness and every disease among the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 36, 'But when he saw the multitudes, he was moved with compassion on them, because they fainted, and were scattered abroad, as sheep having no shepherd.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 37, 'Then saith he unto his disciples, The harvest truly is plenteous, but the labourers are few;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 9, 38, 'Pray ye therefore the Lord of the harvest, that he will send forth labourers into his harvest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 1, 'And when he had called unto him his twelve disciples, he gave them power against unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to heal all manner of sickness and all manner of disease.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 2, 'Now the names of the twelve apostles are these; The first, Simon, who is called Peter, and Andrew his brother; James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 3, 'Philip, and Bartholomew; Thomas, and Matthew the publican; James the son of Alphaeus, and Lebbaeus, whose surname was Thaddaeus;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 4, 'Simon the Canaanite, and Judas Iscariot, who also betrayed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 5, 'These twelve Jesus sent forth, and commanded them, saying, Go not into the way of the Gentiles, and into any city of the Samaritans enter ye not:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 6, 'But go rather to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 7, 'And as ye go, preach, saying, The kingdom of heaven is at hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 8, 'Heal the sick, cleanse the lepers, raise the dead, cast out devils: freely ye have received, freely give.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 9, 'Provide neither gold, nor silver, nor brass in your purses,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 10, 'Nor scrip for your journey, neither two coats, neither shoes, nor yet staves: for the workman is worthy of his meat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 11, 'And into whatsoever city or town ye shall enter, enquire who in it is worthy; and there abide till ye go thence.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 12, 'And when ye come into an house, salute it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 13, 'And if the house be worthy, let your peace come upon it: but if it be not worthy, let your peace return to you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 14, 'And whosoever shall not receive you, nor hear your words, when ye depart out of that house or city, shake off the dust of your feet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 15, 'Verily I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrha in the day of judgment, than for that city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 16, 'Behold, I send you forth as sheep in the midst of wolves: be ye therefore wise as serpents, and harmless as doves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 17, 'But beware of men: for they will deliver you up to the councils, and they will scourge you in their synagogues;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 18, 'And ye shall be brought before governors and kings for my sake, for a testimony against them and the Gentiles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 19, 'But when they deliver you up, take no thought how or what ye shall speak: for it shall be given you in that same hour what ye shall speak.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 20, 'For it is not ye that speak, but the Spirit of your Father which speaketh in you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 21, 'And the brother shall deliver up the brother to death, and the father the child: and the children shall rise up against their parents, and cause them to be put to death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 22, 'And ye shall be hated of all men for my name''s sake: but he that endureth to the end shall be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 23, 'But when they persecute you in this city, flee ye into another: for verily I say unto you, Ye shall not have gone over the cities of Israel, till the Son of man be come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 24, 'The disciple is not above his master, nor the servant above his lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 25, 'It is enough for the disciple that he be as his master, and the servant as his lord. If they have called the master of the house Beelzebub, how much more shall they call them of his household?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 26, 'Fear them not therefore: for there is nothing covered, that shall not be revealed; and hid, that shall not be known.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 27, 'What I tell you in darkness, that speak ye in light: and what ye hear in the ear, that preach ye upon the housetops.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 28, 'And fear not them which kill the body, but are not able to kill the soul: but rather fear him which is able to destroy both soul and body in hell.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 29, 'Are not two sparrows sold for a farthing? and one of them shall not fall on the ground without your Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 30, 'But the very hairs of your head are all numbered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 31, 'Fear ye not therefore, ye are of more value than many sparrows.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 32, 'Whosoever therefore shall confess me before men, him will I confess also before my Father which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 33, 'But whosoever shall deny me before men, him will I also deny before my Father which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 34, 'Think not that I am come to send peace on earth: I came not to send peace, but a sword.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 35, 'For I am come to set a man at variance against his father, and the daughter against her mother, and the daughter in law against her mother in law.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 36, 'And a man''s foes shall be they of his own household.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 37, 'He that loveth father or mother more than me is not worthy of me: and he that loveth son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 38, 'And he that taketh not his cross, and followeth after me, is not worthy of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 39, 'He that findeth his life shall lose it: and he that loseth his life for my sake shall find it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 40, 'He that receiveth you receiveth me, and he that receiveth me receiveth him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 41, 'He that receiveth a prophet in the name of a prophet shall receive a prophet''s reward; and he that receiveth a righteous man in the name of a righteous man shall receive a righteous man''s reward.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 10, 42, 'And whosoever shall give to drink unto one of these little ones a cup of cold water only in the name of a disciple, verily I say unto you, he shall in no wise lose his reward.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 1, 'And it came to pass, when Jesus had made an end of commanding his twelve disciples, he departed thence to teach and to preach in their cities.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 2, 'Now when John had heard in the prison the works of Christ, he sent two of his disciples,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 3, 'And said unto him, Art thou he that should come, or do we look for another?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 4, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, Go and shew John again those things which ye do hear and see:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 5, 'The blind receive their sight, and the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, and the deaf hear, the dead are raised up, and the poor have the gospel preached to them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 6, 'And blessed is he, whosoever shall not be offended in me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 7, 'And as they departed, Jesus began to say unto the multitudes concerning John, What went ye out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken with the wind?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 8, 'But what went ye out for to see? A man clothed in soft raiment? behold, they that wear soft clothing are in kings'' houses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 9, 'But what went ye out for to see? A prophet? yea, I say unto you, and more than a prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 10, 'For this is he, of whom it is written, Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 11, 'Verily I say unto you, Among them that are born of women there hath not risen a greater than John the Baptist: notwithstanding he that is least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 12, 'And from the days of John the Baptist until now the kingdom of heaven suffereth violence, and the violent take it by force.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 13, 'For all the prophets and the law prophesied until John.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 14, 'And if ye will receive it, this is Elias, which was for to come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 15, 'He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 16, 'But whereunto shall I liken this generation? It is like unto children sitting in the markets, and calling unto their fellows,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 17, 'And saying, We have piped unto you, and ye have not danced; we have mourned unto you, and ye have not lamented.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 18, 'For John came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, He hath a devil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 19, 'The Son of man came eating and drinking, and they say, Behold a man gluttonous, and a winebibber, a friend of publicans and sinners. But wisdom is justified of her children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 20, 'Then began he to upbraid the cities wherein most of his mighty works were done, because they repented not:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 21, 'Woe unto thee, Chorazin! woe unto thee, Bethsaida! for if the mighty works, which were done in you, had been done in Tyre and Sidon, they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 22, 'But I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the day of judgment, than for you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 23, 'And thou, Capernaum, which art exalted unto heaven, shalt be brought down to hell: for if the mighty works, which have been done in thee, had been done in Sodom, it would have remained until this day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 24, 'But I say unto you, That it shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom in the day of judgment, than for thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 25, 'At that time Jesus answered and said, I thank thee, O Father, Lord of heaven and earth, because thou hast hid these things from the wise and prudent, and hast revealed them unto babes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 26, 'Even so, Father: for so it seemed good in thy sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 27, 'All things are delivered unto me of my Father: and no man knoweth the Son, but the Father; neither knoweth any man the Father, save the Son, and he to whomsoever the Son will reveal him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 28, 'Come unto me, all ye that labour and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 29, 'Take my yoke upon you, and learn of me; for I am meek and lowly in heart: and ye shall find rest unto your souls.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 11, 30, 'For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 1, 'At that time Jesus went on the sabbath day through the corn; and his disciples were an hungred, and began to pluck the ears of corn, and to eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 2, 'But when the Pharisees saw it, they said unto him, Behold, thy disciples do that which is not lawful to do upon the sabbath day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 3, 'But he said unto them, Have ye not read what David did, when he was an hungred, and they that were with him;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 4, 'How he entered into the house of God, and did eat the shewbread, which was not lawful for him to eat, neither for them which were with him, but only for the priests?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 5, 'Or have ye not read in the law, how that on the sabbath days the priests in the temple profane the sabbath, and are blameless?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 6, 'But I say unto you, That in this place is one greater than the temple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 7, 'But if ye had known what this meaneth, I will have mercy, and not sacrifice, ye would not have condemned the guiltless.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 8, 'For the Son of man is Lord even of the sabbath day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 9, 'And when he was departed thence, he went into their synagogue:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 10, 'And, behold, there was a man which had his hand withered. And they asked him, saying, Is it lawful to heal on the sabbath days? that they might accuse him.')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 11, 'And he said unto them, What man shall there be among you, that shall have one sheep, and if it fall into a pit on the sabbath day, will he not lay hold on it, and lift it out?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 12, 'How much then is a man better than a sheep? Wherefore it is lawful to do well on the sabbath days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 13, 'Then saith he to the man, Stretch forth thine hand. And he stretched it forth; and it was restored whole, like as the other.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 14, 'Then the Pharisees went out, and held a council against him, how they might destroy him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 15, 'But when Jesus knew it, he withdrew himself from thence: and great multitudes followed him, and he healed them all;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 16, 'And charged them that they should not make him known:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 17, 'That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Esaias the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 18, 'Behold my servant, whom I have chosen; my beloved, in whom my soul is well pleased: I will put my spirit upon him, and he shall shew judgment to the Gentiles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 19, 'He shall not strive, nor cry; neither shall any man hear his voice in the streets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 20, 'A bruised reed shall he not break, and smoking flax shall he not quench, till he send forth judgment unto victory.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 21, 'And in his name shall the Gentiles trust.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 22, 'Then was brought unto him one possessed with a devil, blind, and dumb: and he healed him, insomuch that the blind and dumb both spake and saw.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 23, 'And all the people were amazed, and said, Is not this the son of David?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 24, 'But when the Pharisees heard it, they said, This fellow doth not cast out devils, but by Beelzebub the prince of the devils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 25, 'And Jesus knew their thoughts, and said unto them, Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation; and every city or house divided against itself shall not stand:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 26, 'And if Satan cast out Satan, he is divided against himself; how shall then his kingdom stand?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 27, 'And if I by Beelzebub cast out devils, by whom do your children cast them out? therefore they shall be your judges.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 28, 'But if I cast out devils by the Spirit of God, then the kingdom of God is come unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 29, 'Or else how can one enter into a strong man''s house, and spoil his goods, except he first bind the strong man? and then he will spoil his house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 30, 'He that is not with me is against me; and he that gathereth not with me scattereth abroad.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 31, 'Wherefore I say unto you, All manner of sin and blasphemy shall be forgiven unto men: but the blasphemy against the Holy Ghost shall not be forgiven unto men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 32, 'And whosoever speaketh a word against the Son of man, it shall be forgiven him: but whosoever speaketh against the Holy Ghost, it shall not be forgiven him, neither in this world, neither in the world to come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 33, 'Either make the tree good, and his fruit good; or else make the tree corrupt, and his fruit corrupt: for the tree is known by his fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 34, 'O generation of vipers, how can ye, being evil, speak good things? for out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaketh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 35, 'A good man out of the good treasure of the heart bringeth forth good things: and an evil man out of the evil treasure bringeth forth evil things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 36, 'But I say unto you, That every idle word that men shall speak, they shall give account thereof in the day of judgment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 37, 'For by thy words thou shalt be justified, and by thy words thou shalt be condemned.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 38, 'Then certain of the scribes and of the Pharisees answered, saying, Master, we would see a sign from thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 39, 'But he answered and said unto them, An evil and adulterous generation seeketh after a sign; and there shall no sign be given to it, but the sign of the prophet Jonas:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 40, 'For as Jonas was three days and three nights in the whale''s belly; so shall the Son of man be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 41, 'The men of Nineveh shall rise in judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: because they repented at the preaching of Jonas; and, behold, a greater than Jonas is here.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 42, 'The queen of the south shall rise up in the judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: for she came from the uttermost parts of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon; and, behold, a greater than Solomon is here.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 43, 'When the unclean spirit is gone out of a man, he walketh through dry places, seeking rest, and findeth none.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 44, 'Then he saith, I will return into my house from whence I came out; and when he is come, he findeth it empty, swept, and garnished.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 45, 'Then goeth he, and taketh with himself seven other spirits more wicked than himself, and they enter in and dwell there: and the last state of that man is worse than the first. Even so shall it be also unto this wicked generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 46, 'While he yet talked to the people, behold, his mother and his brethren stood without, desiring to speak with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 47, 'Then one said unto him, Behold, thy mother and thy brethren stand without, desiring to speak with thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 48, 'But he answered and said unto him that told him, Who is my mother? and who are my brethren?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 49, 'And he stretched forth his hand toward his disciples, and said, Behold my mother and my brethren!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 12, 50, 'For whosoever shall do the will of my Father which is in heaven, the same is my brother, and sister, and mother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 1, 'The same day went Jesus out of the house, and sat by the sea side.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 2, 'And great multitudes were gathered together unto him, so that he went into a ship, and sat; and the whole multitude stood on the shore.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 3, 'And he spake many things unto them in parables, saying, Behold, a sower went forth to sow;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 4, 'And when he sowed, some seeds fell by the way side, and the fowls came and devoured them up:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 5, 'Some fell upon stony places, where they had not much earth: and forthwith they sprung up, because they had no deepness of earth:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 6, 'And when the sun was up, they were scorched; and because they had no root, they withered away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 7, 'And some fell among thorns; and the thorns sprung up, and choked them:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 8, 'But other fell into good ground, and brought forth fruit, some an hundredfold, some sixtyfold, some thirtyfold.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 9, 'Who hath ears to hear, let him hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 10, 'And the disciples came, and said unto him, Why speakest thou unto them in parables?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 11, 'He answered and said unto them, Because it is given unto you to know the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven, but to them it is not given.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 12, 'For whosoever hath, to him shall be given, and he shall have more abundance: but whosoever hath not, from him shall be taken away even that he hath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 13, 'Therefore speak I to them in parables: because they seeing see not; and hearing they hear not, neither do they understand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 14, 'And in them is fulfilled the prophecy of Esaias, which saith, By hearing ye shall hear, and shall not understand; and seeing ye shall see, and shall not perceive:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 15, 'For this people''s heart is waxed gross, and their ears are dull of hearing, and their eyes they have closed; lest at any time they should see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and should understand with their heart, and should be converted, and I should heal them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 16, 'But blessed are your eyes, for they see: and your ears, for they hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 17, 'For verily I say unto you, That many prophets and righteous men have desired to see those things which ye see, and have not seen them; and to hear those things which ye hear, and have not heard them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 18, 'Hear ye therefore the parable of the sower.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 19, 'When any one heareth the word of the kingdom, and understandeth it not, then cometh the wicked one, and catcheth away that which was sown in his heart. This is he which received seed by the way side.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 20, 'But he that received the seed into stony places, the same is he that heareth the word, and anon with joy receiveth it;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 21, 'Yet hath he not root in himself, but dureth for a while: for when tribulation or persecution ariseth because of the word, by and by he is offended.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 22, 'He also that received seed among the thorns is he that heareth the word; and the care of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches, choke the word, and he becometh unfruitful.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 23, 'But he that received seed into the good ground is he that heareth the word, and understandeth it; which also beareth fruit, and bringeth forth, some an hundredfold, some sixty, some thirty.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 24, 'Another parable put he forth unto them, saying, The kingdom of heaven is likened unto a man which sowed good seed in his field:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 25, 'But while men slept, his enemy came and sowed tares among the wheat, and went his way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 26, 'But when the blade was sprung up, and brought forth fruit, then appeared the tares also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 27, 'So the servants of the householder came and said unto him, Sir, didst not thou sow good seed in thy field? from whence then hath it tares?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 28, 'He said unto them, An enemy hath done this. The servants said unto him, Wilt thou then that we go and gather them up?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 29, 'But he said, Nay; lest while ye gather up the tares, ye root up also the wheat with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 30, 'Let both grow together until the harvest: and in the time of harvest I will say to the reapers, Gather ye together first the tares, and bind them in bundles to burn them: but gather the wheat into my barn.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 31, 'Another parable put he forth unto them, saying, The kingdom of heaven is like to a grain of mustard seed, which a man took, and sowed in his field:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 32, 'Which indeed is the least of all seeds: but when it is grown, it is the greatest among herbs, and becometh a tree, so that the birds of the air come and lodge in the branches thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 33, 'Another parable spake he unto them; The kingdom of heaven is like unto leaven, which a woman took, and hid in three measures of meal, till the whole was leavened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 34, 'All these things spake Jesus unto the multitude in parables; and without a parable spake he not unto them:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 35, 'That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, saying, I will open my mouth in parables; I will utter things which have been kept secret from the foundation of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 36, 'Then Jesus sent the multitude away, and went into the house: and his disciples came unto him, saying, Declare unto us the parable of the tares of the field.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 37, 'He answered and said unto them, He that soweth the good seed is the Son of man;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 38, 'The field is the world; the good seed are the children of the kingdom; but the tares are the children of the wicked one;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 39, 'The enemy that sowed them is the devil; the harvest is the end of the world; and the reapers are the angels.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 40, 'As therefore the tares are gathered and burned in the fire; so shall it be in the end of this world.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 41, 'The Son of man shall send forth his angels, and they shall gather out of his kingdom all things that offend, and them which do iniquity;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 42, 'And shall cast them into a furnace of fire: there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 43, 'Then shall the righteous shine forth as the sun in the kingdom of their Father. Who hath ears to hear, let him hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 44, 'Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto treasure hid in a field; the which when a man hath found, he hideth, and for joy thereof goeth and selleth all that he hath, and buyeth that field.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 45, 'Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto a merchant man, seeking goodly pearls:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 46, 'Who, when he had found one pearl of great price, went and sold all that he had, and bought it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 47, 'Again, the kingdom of heaven is like unto a net, that was cast into the sea, and gathered of every kind:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 48, 'Which, when it was full, they drew to shore, and sat down, and gathered the good into vessels, but cast the bad away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 49, 'So shall it be at the end of the world: the angels shall come forth, and sever the wicked from among the just,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 50, 'And shall cast them into the furnace of fire: there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 51, 'Jesus saith unto them, Have ye understood all these things? They say unto him, Yea, Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 52, 'Then said he unto them, Therefore every scribe which is instructed unto the kingdom of heaven is like unto a man that is an householder, which bringeth forth out of his treasure things new and old.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 53, 'And it came to pass, that when Jesus had finished these parables, he departed thence.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 54, 'And when he was come into his own country, he taught them in their synagogue, insomuch that they were astonished, and said, Whence hath this man this wisdom, and these mighty works?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 55, 'Is not this the carpenter''s son? is not his mother called Mary? and his brethren, James, and Joses, and Simon, and Judas?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 56, 'And his sisters, are they not all with us? Whence then hath this man all these things?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 57, 'And they were offended in him. But Jesus said unto them, A prophet is not without honour, save in his own country, and in his own house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 13, 58, 'And he did not many mighty works there because of their unbelief.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 1, 'At that time Herod the tetrarch heard of the fame of Jesus,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 2, 'And said unto his servants, This is John the Baptist; he is risen from the dead; and therefore mighty works do shew forth themselves in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 3, 'For Herod had laid hold on John, and bound him, and put him in prison for Herodias'' sake, his brother Philip''s wife.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 4, 'For John said unto him, It is not lawful for thee to have her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 5, 'And when he would have put him to death, he feared the multitude, because they counted him as a prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 6, 'But when Herod''s birthday was kept, the daughter of Herodias danced before them, and pleased Herod.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 7, 'Whereupon he promised with an oath to give her whatsoever she would ask.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 8, 'And she, being before instructed of her mother, said, Give me here John Baptist''s head in a charger.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 9, 'And the king was sorry: nevertheless for the oath''s sake, and them which sat with him at meat, he commanded it to be given her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 10, 'And he sent, and beheaded John in the prison.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 11, 'And his head was brought in a charger, and given to the damsel: and she brought it to her mother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 12, 'And his disciples came, and took up the body, and buried it, and went and told Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 13, 'When Jesus heard of it, he departed thence by ship into a desert place apart: and when the people had heard thereof, they followed him on foot out of the cities.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 14, 'And Jesus went forth, and saw a great multitude, and was moved with compassion toward them, and he healed their sick.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 15, 'And when it was evening, his disciples came to him, saying, This is a desert place, and the time is now past; send the multitude away, that they may go into the villages, and buy themselves victuals.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 16, 'But Jesus said unto them, They need not depart; give ye them to eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 17, 'And they say unto him, We have here but five loaves, and two fishes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 18, 'He said, Bring them hither to me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 19, 'And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the grass, and took the five loaves, and the two fishes, and looking up to heaven, he blessed, and brake, and gave the loaves to his disciples, and the disciples to the multitude.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 20, 'And they did all eat, and were filled: and they took up of the fragments that remained twelve baskets full.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 21, 'And they that had eaten were about five thousand men, beside women and children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 22, 'And straightway Jesus constrained his disciples to get into a ship, and to go before him unto the other side, while he sent the multitudes away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 23, 'And when he had sent the multitudes away, he went up into a mountain apart to pray: and when the evening was come, he was there alone.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 24, 'But the ship was now in the midst of the sea, tossed with waves: for the wind was contrary.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 25, 'And in the fourth watch of the night Jesus went unto them, walking on the sea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 26, 'And when the disciples saw him walking on the sea, they were troubled, saying, It is a spirit; and they cried out for fear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 27, 'But straightway Jesus spake unto them, saying, Be of good cheer; it is I; be not afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 28, 'And Peter answered him and said, Lord, if it be thou, bid me come unto thee on the water.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 29, 'And he said, Come. And when Peter was come down out of the ship, he walked on the water, to go to Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 30, 'But when he saw the wind boisterous, he was afraid; and beginning to sink, he cried, saying, Lord, save me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 31, 'And immediately Jesus stretched forth his hand, and caught him, and said unto him, O thou of little faith, wherefore didst thou doubt?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 32, 'And when they were come into the ship, the wind ceased.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 33, 'Then they that were in the ship came and worshipped him, saying, Of a truth thou art the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 34, 'And when they were gone over, they came into the land of Gennesaret.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 35, 'And when the men of that place had knowledge of him, they sent out into all that country round about, and brought unto him all that were diseased;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 14, 36, 'And besought him that they might only touch the hem of his garment: and as many as touched were made perfectly whole.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 1, 'Then came to Jesus scribes and Pharisees, which were of Jerusalem, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 2, 'Why do thy disciples transgress the tradition of the elders? for they wash not their hands when they eat bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 3, 'But he answered and said unto them, Why do ye also transgress the commandment of God by your tradition?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 4, 'For God commanded, saying, Honour thy father and mother: and, He that curseth father or mother, let him die the death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 5, 'But ye say, Whosoever shall say to his father or his mother, It is a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 6, 'And honour not his father or his mother, he shall be free. Thus have ye made the commandment of God of none effect by your tradition.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 7, 'Ye hypocrites, well did Esaias prophesy of you, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 8, 'This people draweth nigh unto me with their mouth, and honoureth me with their lips; but their heart is far from me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 9, 'But in vain they do worship me, teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 10, 'And he called the multitude, and said unto them, Hear, and understand:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 11, 'Not that which goeth into the mouth defileth a man; but that which cometh out of the mouth, this defileth a man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 12, 'Then came his disciples, and said unto him, Knowest thou that the Pharisees were offended, after they heard this saying?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 13, 'But he answered and said, Every plant, which my heavenly Father hath not planted, shall be rooted up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 14, 'Let them alone: they be blind leaders of the blind. And if the blind lead the blind, both shall fall into the ditch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 15, 'Then answered Peter and said unto him, Declare unto us this parable.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 16, 'And Jesus said, Are ye also yet without understanding?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 17, 'Do not ye yet understand, that whatsoever entereth in at the mouth goeth into the belly, and is cast out into the draught?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 18, 'But those things which proceed out of the mouth come forth from the heart; and they defile the man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 19, 'For out of the heart proceed evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, fornications, thefts, false witness, blasphemies:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 20, 'These are the things which defile a man: but to eat with unwashen hands defileth not a man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 21, 'Then Jesus went thence, and departed into the coasts of Tyre and Sidon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 22, 'And, behold, a woman of Canaan came out of the same coasts, and cried unto him, saying, Have mercy on me, O Lord, thou Son of David; my daughter is grievously vexed with a devil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 23, 'But he answered her not a word. And his disciples came and besought him, saying, Send her away; for she crieth after us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 24, 'But he answered and said, I am not sent but unto the lost sheep of the house of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 25, 'Then came she and worshipped him, saying, Lord, help me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 26, 'But he answered and said, It is not meet to take the children''s bread, and to cast it to dogs.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 27, 'And she said, Truth, Lord: yet the dogs eat of the crumbs which fall from their masters'' table.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 28, 'Then Jesus answered and said unto her, O woman, great is thy faith: be it unto thee even as thou wilt. And her daughter was made whole from that very hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 29, 'And Jesus departed from thence, and came nigh unto the sea of Galilee; and went up into a mountain, and sat down there.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 30, 'And great multitudes came unto him, having with them those that were lame, blind, dumb, maimed, and many others, and cast them down at Jesus'' feet; and he healed them:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 31, 'Insomuch that the multitude wondered, when they saw the dumb to speak, the maimed to be whole, the lame to walk, and the blind to see: and they glorified the God of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 32, 'Then Jesus called his disciples unto him, and said, I have compassion on the multitude, because they continue with me now three days, and have nothing to eat: and I will not send them away fasting, lest they faint in the way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 33, 'And his disciples say unto him, Whence should we have so much bread in the wilderness, as to fill so great a multitude?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 34, 'And Jesus saith unto them, How many loaves have ye? And they said, Seven, and a few little fishes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 35, 'And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 36, 'And he took the seven loaves and the fishes, and gave thanks, and brake them, and gave to his disciples, and the disciples to the multitude.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 37, 'And they did all eat, and were filled: and they took up of the broken meat that was left seven baskets full.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 38, 'And they that did eat were four thousand men, beside women and children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 15, 39, 'And he sent away the multitude, and took ship, and came into the coasts of Magdala.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 1, 'The Pharisees also with the Sadducees came, and tempting desired him that he would shew them a sign from heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 2, 'He answered and said unto them, When it is evening, ye say, It will be fair weather: for the sky is red.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 3, 'And in the morning, It will be foul weather to day: for the sky is red and lowring. O ye hypocrites, ye can discern the face of the sky; but can ye not discern the signs of the times?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 4, 'A wicked and adulterous generation seeketh after a sign; and there shall no sign be given unto it, but the sign of the prophet Jonas. And he left them, and departed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 5, 'And when his disciples were come to the other side, they had forgotten to take bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 6, 'Then Jesus said unto them, Take heed and beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 7, 'And they reasoned among themselves, saying, It is because we have taken no bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 8, 'Which when Jesus perceived, he said unto them, O ye of little faith, why reason ye among yourselves, because ye have brought no bread?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 9, 'Do ye not yet understand, neither remember the five loaves of the five thousand, and how many baskets ye took up?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 10, 'Neither the seven loaves of the four thousand, and how many baskets ye took up?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 11, 'How is it that ye do not understand that I spake it not to you concerning bread, that ye should beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 12, 'Then understood they how that he bade them not beware of the leaven of bread, but of the doctrine of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 13, 'When Jesus came into the coasts of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, saying, Whom do men say that I the Son of man am?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 14, 'And they said, Some say that thou art John the Baptist: some, Elias; and others, Jeremias, or one of the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 15, 'He saith unto them, But whom say ye that I am?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 16, 'And Simon Peter answered and said, Thou art the Christ, the Son of the living God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 17, 'And Jesus answered and said unto him, Blessed art thou, Simon Barjona: for flesh and blood hath not revealed it unto thee, but my Father which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 18, 'And I say also unto thee, That thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church; and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 19, 'And I will give unto thee the keys of the kingdom of heaven: and whatsoever thou shalt bind on earth shall be bound in heaven: and whatsoever thou shalt loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 20, 'Then charged he his disciples that they should tell no man that he was Jesus the Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 21, 'From that time forth began Jesus to shew unto his disciples, how that he must go unto Jerusalem, and suffer many things of the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be killed, and be raised again the third day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 22, 'Then Peter took him, and began to rebuke him, saying, Be it far from thee, Lord: this shall not be unto thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 23, 'But he turned, and said unto Peter, Get thee behind me, Satan: thou art an offence unto me: for thou savourest not the things that be of God, but those that be of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 24, 'Then said Jesus unto his disciples, If any man will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 25, 'For whosoever will save his life shall lose it: and whosoever will lose his life for my sake shall find it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 26, 'For what is a man profited, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul? or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 27, 'For the Son of man shall come in the glory of his Father with his angels; and then he shall reward every man according to his works.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 16, 28, 'Verily I say unto you, There be some standing here, which shall not taste of death, till they see the Son of man coming in his kingdom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 1, 'And after six days Jesus taketh Peter, James, and John his brother, and bringeth them up into an high mountain apart,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 2, 'And was transfigured before them: and his face did shine as the sun, and his raiment was white as the light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 3, 'And, behold, there appeared unto them Moses and Elias talking with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 4, 'Then answered Peter, and said unto Jesus, Lord, it is good for us to be here: if thou wilt, let us make here three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 5, 'While he yet spake, behold, a bright cloud overshadowed them: and behold a voice out of the cloud, which said, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased; hear ye him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 6, 'And when the disciples heard it, they fell on their face, and were sore afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 7, 'And Jesus came and touched them, and said, Arise, and be not afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 8, 'And when they had lifted up their eyes, they saw no man, save Jesus only.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 9, 'And as they came down from the mountain, Jesus charged them, saying, Tell the vision to no man, until the Son of man be risen again from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 10, 'And his disciples asked him, saying, Why then say the scribes that Elias must first come?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 11, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, Elias truly shall first come, and restore all things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 12, 'But I say unto you, That Elias is come already, and they knew him not, but have done unto him whatsoever they listed. Likewise shall also the Son of man suffer of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 13, 'Then the disciples understood that he spake unto them of John the Baptist.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 14, 'And when they were come to the multitude, there came to him a certain man, kneeling down to him, and saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 15, 'Lord, have mercy on my son: for he is lunatick, and sore vexed: for ofttimes he falleth into the fire, and oft into the water.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 16, 'And I brought him to thy disciples, and they could not cure him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 17, 'Then Jesus answered and said, O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you? how long shall I suffer you? bring him hither to me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 18, 'And Jesus rebuked the devil; and he departed out of him: and the child was cured from that very hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 19, 'Then came the disciples to Jesus apart, and said, Why could not we cast him out?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 20, 'And Jesus said unto them, Because of your unbelief: for verily I say unto you, If ye have faith as a grain of mustard seed, ye shall say unto this mountain, Remove hence to yonder place; and it shall remove; and nothing shall be impossible unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 21, 'Howbeit this kind goeth not out but by prayer and fasting.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 22, 'And while they abode in Galilee, Jesus said unto them, The Son of man shall be betrayed into the hands of men:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 23, 'And they shall kill him, and the third day he shall be raised again. And they were exceeding sorry.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 24, 'And when they were come to Capernaum, they that received tribute money came to Peter, and said, Doth not your master pay tribute?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 25, 'He saith, Yes. And when he was come into the house, Jesus prevented him, saying, What thinkest thou, Simon? of whom do the kings of the earth take custom or tribute? of their own children, or of strangers?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 26, 'Peter saith unto him, Of strangers. Jesus saith unto him, Then are the children free.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 17, 27, 'Notwithstanding, lest we should offend them, go thou to the sea, and cast an hook, and take up the fish that first cometh up; and when thou hast opened his mouth, thou shalt find a piece of money: that take, and give unto them for me and thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 1, 'At the same time came the disciples unto Jesus, saying, Who is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 2, 'And Jesus called a little child unto him, and set him in the midst of them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 3, 'And said, Verily I say unto you, Except ye be converted, and become as little children, ye shall not enter into the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 4, 'Whosoever therefore shall humble himself as this little child, the same is greatest in the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 5, 'And whoso shall receive one such little child in my name receiveth me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 6, 'But whoso shall offend one of these little ones which believe in me, it were better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and that he were drowned in the depth of the sea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 7, 'Woe unto the world because of offences! for it must needs be that offences come; but woe to that man by whom the offence cometh!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 8, 'Wherefore if thy hand or thy foot offend thee, cut them off, and cast them from thee: it is better for thee to enter into life halt or maimed, rather than having two hands or two feet to be cast into everlasting fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 9, 'And if thine eye offend thee, pluck it out, and cast it from thee: it is better for thee to enter into life with one eye, rather than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 10, 'Take heed that ye despise not one of these little ones; for I say unto you, That in heaven their angels do always behold the face of my Father which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 11, 'For the Son of man is come to save that which was lost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 12, 'How think ye? if a man have an hundred sheep, and one of them be gone astray, doth he not leave the ninety and nine, and goeth into the mountains, and seeketh that which is gone astray?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 13, 'And if so be that he find it, verily I say unto you, he rejoiceth more of that sheep, than of the ninety and nine which went not astray.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 14, 'Even so it is not the will of your Father which is in heaven, that one of these little ones should perish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 15, 'Moreover if thy brother shall trespass against thee, go and tell him his fault between thee and him alone: if he shall hear thee, thou hast gained thy brother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 16, 'But if he will not hear thee, then take with thee one or two more, that in the mouth of two or three witnesses every word may be established.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 17, 'And if he shall neglect to hear them, tell it unto the church: but if he neglect to hear the church, let him be unto thee as an heathen man and a publican.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 18, 'Verily I say unto you, Whatsoever ye shall bind on earth shall be bound in heaven: and whatsoever ye shall loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 19, 'Again I say unto you, That if two of you shall agree on earth as touching any thing that they shall ask, it shall be done for them of my Father which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 20, 'For where two or three are gathered together in my name, there am I in the midst of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 21, 'Then came Peter to him, and said, Lord, how oft shall my brother sin against me, and I forgive him? till seven times?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 22, 'Jesus saith unto him, I say not unto thee, Until seven times: but, Until seventy times seven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 23, 'Therefore is the kingdom of heaven likened unto a certain king, which would take account of his servants.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 24, 'And when he had begun to reckon, one was brought unto him, which owed him ten thousand talents.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 25, 'But forasmuch as he had not to pay, his lord commanded him to be sold, and his wife, and children, and all that he had, and payment to be made.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 26, 'The servant therefore fell down, and worshipped him, saying, Lord, have patience with me, and I will pay thee all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 27, 'Then the lord of that servant was moved with compassion, and loosed him, and forgave him the debt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 28, 'But the same servant went out, and found one of his fellowservants, which owed him an hundred pence: and he laid hands on him, and took him by the throat, saying, Pay me that thou owest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 29, 'And his fellowservant fell down at his feet, and besought him, saying, Have patience with me, and I will pay thee all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 30, 'And he would not: but went and cast him into prison, till he should pay the debt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 31, 'So when his fellowservants saw what was done, they were very sorry, and came and told unto their lord all that was done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 32, 'Then his lord, after that he had called him, said unto him, O thou wicked servant, I forgave thee all that debt, because thou desiredst me:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 33, 'Shouldest not thou also have had compassion on thy fellowservant, even as I had pity on thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 34, 'And his lord was wroth, and delivered him to the tormentors, till he should pay all that was due unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 18, 35, 'So likewise shall my heavenly Father do also unto you, if ye from your hearts forgive not every one his brother their trespasses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 1, 'And it came to pass, that when Jesus had finished these sayings, he departed from Galilee, and came into the coasts of Judaea beyond Jordan;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 2, 'And great multitudes followed him; and he healed them there.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 3, 'The Pharisees also came unto him, tempting him, and saying unto him, Is it lawful for a man to put away his wife for every cause?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 4, 'And he answered and said unto them, Have ye not read, that he which made them at the beginning made them male and female,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 5, 'And said, For this cause shall a man leave father and mother, and shall cleave to his wife: and they twain shall be one flesh?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 6, 'Wherefore they are no more twain, but one flesh. What therefore God hath joined together, let not man put asunder.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 7, 'They say unto him, Why did Moses then command to give a writing of divorcement, and to put her away?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 8, 'He saith unto them, Moses because of the hardness of your hearts suffered you to put away your wives: but from the beginning it was not so.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 9, 'And I say unto you, Whosoever shall put away his wife, except it be for fornication, and shall marry another, committeth adultery: and whoso marrieth her which is put away doth commit adultery.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 10, 'His disciples say unto him, If the case of the man be so with his wife, it is not good to marry.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 11, 'But he said unto them, All men cannot receive this saying, save they to whom it is given.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 12, 'For there are some eunuchs, which were so born from their mother''s womb: and there are some eunuchs, which were made eunuchs of men: and there be eunuchs, which have made themselves eunuchs for the kingdom of heaven''s sake. He that is able to receive it, let him receive it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 13, 'Then were there brought unto him little children, that he should put his hands on them, and pray: and the disciples rebuked them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 14, 'But Jesus said, Suffer little children, and forbid them not, to come unto me: for of such is the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 15, 'And he laid his hands on them, and departed thence.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 16, 'And, behold, one came and said unto him, Good Master, what good thing shall I do, that I may have eternal life?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 17, 'And he said unto him, Why callest thou me good? there is none good but one, that is, God: but if thou wilt enter into life, keep the commandments.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 18, 'He saith unto him, Which? Jesus said, Thou shalt do no murder, Thou shalt not commit adultery, Thou shalt not steal, Thou shalt not bear false witness,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 19, 'Honour thy father and thy mother: and, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 20, 'The young man saith unto him, All these things have I kept from my youth up: what lack I yet?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 21, 'Jesus said unto him, If thou wilt be perfect, go and sell that thou hast, and give to the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven: and come and follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 22, 'But when the young man heard that saying, he went away sorrowful: for he had great possessions.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 23, 'Then said Jesus unto his disciples, Verily I say unto you, That a rich man shall hardly enter into the kingdom of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 24, 'And again I say unto you, It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 25, 'When his disciples heard it, they were exceedingly amazed, saying, Who then can be saved?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 26, 'But Jesus beheld them, and said unto them, With men this is impossible; but with God all things are possible.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 27, 'Then answered Peter and said unto him, Behold, we have forsaken all, and followed thee; what shall we have therefore?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 28, 'And Jesus said unto them, Verily I say unto you, That ye which have followed me, in the regeneration when the Son of man shall sit in the throne of his glory, ye also shall sit upon twelve thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 29, 'And every one that hath forsaken houses, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, for my name''s sake, shall receive an hundredfold, and shall inherit everlasting life.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 19, 30, 'But many that are first shall be last; and the last shall be first.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 1, 'For the kingdom of heaven is like unto a man that is an householder, which went out early in the morning to hire labourers into his vineyard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 2, 'And when he had agreed with the labourers for a penny a day, he sent them into his vineyard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 3, 'And he went out about the third hour, and saw others standing idle in the marketplace,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 4, 'And said unto them; Go ye also into the vineyard, and whatsoever is right I will give you. And they went their way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 5, 'Again he went out about the sixth and ninth hour, and did likewise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 6, 'And about the eleventh hour he went out, and found others standing idle, and saith unto them, Why stand ye here all the day idle?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 7, 'They say unto him, Because no man hath hired us. He saith unto them, Go ye also into the vineyard; and whatsoever is right, that shall ye receive.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 8, 'So when even was come, the lord of the vineyard saith unto his steward, Call the labourers, and give them their hire, beginning from the last unto the first.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 9, 'And when they came that were hired about the eleventh hour, they received every man a penny.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 10, 'But when the first came, they supposed that they should have received more; and they likewise received every man a penny.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 11, 'And when they had received it, they murmured against the goodman of the house,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 12, 'Saying, These last have wrought but one hour, and thou hast made them equal unto us, which have borne the burden and heat of the day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 13, 'But he answered one of them, and said, Friend, I do thee no wrong: didst not thou agree with me for a penny?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 14, 'Take that thine is, and go thy way: I will give unto this last, even as unto thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 15, 'Is it not lawful for me to do what I will with mine own? Is thine eye evil, because I am good?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 16, 'So the last shall be first, and the first last: for many be called, but few chosen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 17, 'And Jesus going up to Jerusalem took the twelve disciples apart in the way, and said unto them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 18, 'Behold, we go up to Jerusalem; and the Son of man shall be betrayed unto the chief priests and unto the scribes, and they shall condemn him to death,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 19, 'And shall deliver him to the Gentiles to mock, and to scourge, and to crucify him: and the third day he shall rise again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 20, 'Then came to him the mother of Zebedee''s children with her sons, worshipping him, and desiring a certain thing of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 21, 'And he said unto her, What wilt thou? She saith unto him, Grant that these my two sons may sit, the one on thy right hand, and the other on the left, in thy kingdom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 22, 'But Jesus answered and said, Ye know not what ye ask. Are ye able to drink of the cup that I shall drink of, and to be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with? They say unto him, We are able.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 23, 'And he saith unto them, Ye shall drink indeed of my cup, and be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with: but to sit on my right hand, and on my left, is not mine to give, but it shall be given to them for whom it is prepared of my Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 24, 'And when the ten heard it, they were moved with indignation against the two brethren.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 25, 'But Jesus called them unto him, and said, Ye know that the princes of the Gentiles exercise dominion over them, and they that are great exercise authority upon them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 26, 'But it shall not be so among you: but whosoever will be great among you, let him be your minister;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 27, 'And whosoever will be chief among you, let him be your servant:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 28, 'Even as the Son of man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister, and to give his life a ransom for many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 29, 'And as they departed from Jericho, a great multitude followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 30, 'And, behold, two blind men sitting by the way side, when they heard that Jesus passed by, cried out, saying, Have mercy on us, O Lord, thou Son of David.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 31, 'And the multitude rebuked them, because they should hold their peace: but they cried the more, saying, Have mercy on us, O Lord, thou Son of David.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 32, 'And Jesus stood still, and called them, and said, What will ye that I shall do unto you?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 33, 'They say unto him, Lord, that our eyes may be opened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 20, 34, 'So Jesus had compassion on them, and touched their eyes: and immediately their eyes received sight, and they followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 1, 'And when they drew nigh unto Jerusalem, and were come to Bethphage, unto the mount of Olives, then sent Jesus two disciples,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 2, 'Saying unto them, Go into the village over against you, and straightway ye shall find an ass tied, and a colt with her: loose them, and bring them unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 3, 'And if any man say ought unto you, ye shall say, The Lord hath need of them; and straightway he will send them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 4, 'All this was done, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 5, 'Tell ye the daughter of Sion, Behold, thy King cometh unto thee, meek, and sitting upon an ass, and a colt the foal of an ass.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 6, 'And the disciples went, and did as Jesus commanded them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 7, 'And brought the ass, and the colt, and put on them their clothes, and they set him thereon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 8, 'And a very great multitude spread their garments in the way; others cut down branches from the trees, and strawed them in the way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 9, 'And the multitudes that went before, and that followed, cried, saying, Hosanna to the Son of David: Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord; Hosanna in the highest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 10, 'And when he was come into Jerusalem, all the city was moved, saying, Who is this?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 11, 'And the multitude said, This is Jesus the prophet of Nazareth of Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 12, 'And Jesus went into the temple of God, and cast out all them that sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the moneychangers, and the seats of them that sold doves,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 13, 'And said unto them, It is written, My house shall be called the house of prayer; but ye have made it a den of thieves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 14, 'And the blind and the lame came to him in the temple; and he healed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 15, 'And when the chief priests and scribes saw the wonderful things that he did, and the children crying in the temple, and saying, Hosanna to the Son of David; they were sore displeased,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 16, 'And said unto him, Hearest thou what these say? And Jesus saith unto them, Yea; have ye never read, Out of the mouth of babes and sucklings thou hast perfected praise?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 17, 'And he left them, and went out of the city into Bethany; and he lodged there.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 18, 'Now in the morning as he returned into the city, he hungered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 19, 'And when he saw a fig tree in the way, he came to it, and found nothing thereon, but leaves only, and said unto it, Let no fruit grow on thee henceforward for ever. And presently the fig tree withered away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 20, 'And when the disciples saw it, they marvelled, saying, How soon is the fig tree withered away!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 21, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, Verily I say unto you, If ye have faith, and doubt not, ye shall not only do this which is done to the fig tree, but also if ye shall say unto this mountain, Be thou removed, and be thou cast into the sea; it shall be done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 22, 'And all things, whatsoever ye shall ask in prayer, believing, ye shall receive.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 23, 'And when he was come into the temple, the chief priests and the elders of the people came unto him as he was teaching, and said, By what authority doest thou these things? and who gave thee this authority?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 24, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, I also will ask you one thing, which if ye tell me, I in like wise will tell you by what authority I do these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 25, 'The baptism of John, whence was it? from heaven, or of men? And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say unto us, Why did ye not then believe him?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 26, 'But if we shall say, Of men; we fear the people; for all hold John as a prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 27, 'And they answered Jesus, and said, We cannot tell. And he said unto them, Neither tell I you by what authority I do these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 28, 'But what think ye? A certain man had two sons; and he came to the first, and said, Son, go work to day in my vineyard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 29, 'He answered and said, I will not: but afterward he repented, and went.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 30, 'And he came to the second, and said likewise. And he answered and said, I go, sir: and went not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 31, 'Whether of them twain did the will of his father? They say unto him, The first. Jesus saith unto them, Verily I say unto you, That the publicans and the harlots go into the kingdom of God before you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 32, 'For John came unto you in the way of righteousness, and ye believed him not: but the publicans and the harlots believed him: and ye, when ye had seen it, repented not afterward, that ye might believe him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 33, 'Hear another parable: There was a certain householder, which planted a vineyard, and hedged it round about, and digged a winepress in it, and built a tower, and let it out to husbandmen, and went into a far country:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 34, 'And when the time of the fruit drew near, he sent his servants to the husbandmen, that they might receive the fruits of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 35, 'And the husbandmen took his servants, and beat one, and killed another, and stoned another.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 36, 'Again, he sent other servants more than the first: and they did unto them likewise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 37, 'But last of all he sent unto them his son, saying, They will reverence my son.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 38, 'But when the husbandmen saw the son, they said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and let us seize on his inheritance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 39, 'And they caught him, and cast him out of the vineyard, and slew him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 40, 'When the lord therefore of the vineyard cometh, what will he do unto those husbandmen?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 41, 'They say unto him, He will miserably destroy those wicked men, and will let out his vineyard unto other husbandmen, which shall render him the fruits in their seasons.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 42, 'Jesus saith unto them, Did ye never read in the scriptures, The stone which the builders rejected, the same is become the head of the corner: this is the Lord''s doing, and it is marvellous in our eyes?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 43, 'Therefore say I unto you, The kingdom of God shall be taken from you, and given to a nation bringing forth the fruits thereof.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 44, 'And whosoever shall fall on this stone shall be broken: but on whomsoever it shall fall, it will grind him to powder.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 45, 'And when the chief priests and Pharisees had heard his parables, they perceived that he spake of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 21, 46, 'But when they sought to lay hands on him, they feared the multitude, because they took him for a prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 1, 'And Jesus answered and spake unto them again by parables, and said,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 2, 'The kingdom of heaven is like unto a certain king, which made a marriage for his son,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 3, 'And sent forth his servants to call them that were bidden to the wedding: and they would not come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 4, 'Again, he sent forth other servants, saying, Tell them which are bidden, Behold, I have prepared my dinner: my oxen and my fatlings are killed, and all things are ready: come unto the marriage.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 5, 'But they made light of it, and went their ways, one to his farm, another to his merchandise:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 6, 'And the remnant took his servants, and entreated them spitefully, and slew them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 7, 'But when the king heard thereof, he was wroth: and he sent forth his armies, and destroyed those murderers, and burned up their city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 8, 'Then saith he to his servants, The wedding is ready, but they which were bidden were not worthy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 9, 'Go ye therefore into the highways, and as many as ye shall find, bid to the marriage.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 10, 'So those servants went out into the highways, and gathered together all as many as they found, both bad and good: and the wedding was furnished with guests.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 11, 'And when the king came in to see the guests, he saw there a man which had not on a wedding garment:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 12, 'And he saith unto him, Friend, how camest thou in hither not having a wedding garment? And he was speechless.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 13, 'Then said the king to the servants, Bind him hand and foot, and take him away, and cast him into outer darkness; there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 14, 'For many are called, but few are chosen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 15, 'Then went the Pharisees, and took counsel how they might entangle him in his talk.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 16, 'And they sent out unto him their disciples with the Herodians, saying, Master, we know that thou art true, and teachest the way of God in truth, neither carest thou for any man: for thou regardest not the person of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 17, 'Tell us therefore, What thinkest thou? Is it lawful to give tribute unto Caesar, or not?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 18, 'But Jesus perceived their wickedness, and said, Why tempt ye me, ye hypocrites?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 19, 'Shew me the tribute money. And they brought unto him a penny.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 20, 'And he saith unto them, Whose is this image and superscription?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 21, 'They say unto him, Caesar''s. Then saith he unto them, Render therefore unto Caesar the things which are Caesar''s; and unto God the things that are God''s.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 22, 'When they had heard these words, they marvelled, and left him, and went their way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 23, 'The same day came to him the Sadducees, which say that there is no resurrection, and asked him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 24, 'Saying, Master, Moses said, If a man die, having no children, his brother shall marry his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 25, 'Now there were with us seven brethren: and the first, when he had married a wife, deceased, and, having no issue, left his wife unto his brother:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 26, 'Likewise the second also, and the third, unto the seventh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 27, 'And last of all the woman died also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 28, 'Therefore in the resurrection whose wife shall she be of the seven? for they all had her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 29, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, Ye do err, not knowing the scriptures, nor the power of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 30, 'For in the resurrection they neither marry, nor are given in marriage, but are as the angels of God in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 31, 'But as touching the resurrection of the dead, have ye not read that which was spoken unto you by God, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 32, 'I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob? God is not the God of the dead, but of the living.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 33, 'And when the multitude heard this, they were astonished at his doctrine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 34, 'But when the Pharisees had heard that he had put the Sadducees to silence, they were gathered together.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 35, 'Then one of them, which was a lawyer, asked him a question, tempting him, and saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 36, 'Master, which is the great commandment in the law?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 37, 'Jesus said unto him, Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 38, 'This is the first and great commandment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 39, 'And the second is like unto it, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 40, 'On these two commandments hang all the law and the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 41, 'While the Pharisees were gathered together, Jesus asked them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 42, 'Saying, What think ye of Christ? whose son is he? They say unto him, The Son of David.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 43, 'He saith unto them, How then doth David in spirit call him Lord, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 44, 'The LORD said unto my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 45, 'If David then call him Lord, how is he his son?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 22, 46, 'And no man was able to answer him a word, neither durst any man from that day forth ask him any more questions.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 1, 'Then spake Jesus to the multitude, and to his disciples,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 2, 'Saying, The scribes and the Pharisees sit in Moses'' seat:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 3, 'All therefore whatsoever they bid you observe, that observe and do; but do not ye after their works: for they say, and do not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 4, 'For they bind heavy burdens and grievous to be borne, and lay them on men''s shoulders; but they themselves will not move them with one of their fingers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 5, 'But all their works they do for to be seen of men: they make broad their phylacteries, and enlarge the borders of their garments,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 6, 'And love the uppermost rooms at feasts, and the chief seats in the synagogues,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 7, 'And greetings in the markets, and to be called of men, Rabbi, Rabbi.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 8, 'But be not ye called Rabbi: for one is your Master, even Christ; and all ye are brethren.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 9, 'And call no man your father upon the earth: for one is your Father, which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 10, 'Neither be ye called masters: for one is your Master, even Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 11, 'But he that is greatest among you shall be your servant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 12, 'And whosoever shall exalt himself shall be abased; and he that shall humble himself shall be exalted.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 13, 'But woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye shut up the kingdom of heaven against men: for ye neither go in yourselves, neither suffer ye them that are entering to go in.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 14, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye devour widows'' houses, and for a pretence make long prayer: therefore ye shall receive the greater damnation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 15, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye compass sea and land to make one proselyte, and when he is made, ye make him twofold more the child of hell than yourselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 16, 'Woe unto you, ye blind guides, which say, Whosoever shall swear by the temple, it is nothing; but whosoever shall swear by the gold of the temple, he is a debtor!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 17, 'Ye fools and blind: for whether is greater, the gold, or the temple that sanctifieth the gold?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 18, 'And, Whosoever shall swear by the altar, it is nothing; but whosoever sweareth by the gift that is upon it, he is guilty.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 19, 'Ye fools and blind: for whether is greater, the gift, or the altar that sanctifieth the gift?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 20, 'Whoso therefore shall swear by the altar, sweareth by it, and by all things thereon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 21, 'And whoso shall swear by the temple, sweareth by it, and by him that dwelleth therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 22, 'And he that shall swear by heaven, sweareth by the throne of God, and by him that sitteth thereon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 23, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye pay tithe of mint and anise and cummin, and have omitted the weightier matters of the law, judgment, mercy, and faith: these ought ye to have done, and not to leave the other undone.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 24, 'Ye blind guides, which strain at a gnat, and swallow a camel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 25, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye make clean the outside of the cup and of the platter, but within they are full of extortion and excess.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 26, 'Thou blind Pharisee, cleanse first that which is within the cup and platter, that the outside of them may be clean also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 27, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye are like unto whited sepulchres, which indeed appear beautiful outward, but are within full of dead men''s bones, and of all uncleanness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 28, 'Even so ye also outwardly appear righteous unto men, but within ye are full of hypocrisy and iniquity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 29, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! because ye build the tombs of the prophets, and garnish the sepulchres of the righteous,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 30, 'And say, If we had been in the days of our fathers, we would not have been partakers with them in the blood of the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 31, 'Wherefore ye be witnesses unto yourselves, that ye are the children of them which killed the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 32, 'Fill ye up then the measure of your fathers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 33, 'Ye serpents, ye generation of vipers, how can ye escape the damnation of hell?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 34, 'Wherefore, behold, I send unto you prophets, and wise men, and scribes: and some of them ye shall kill and crucify; and some of them shall ye scourge in your synagogues, and persecute them from city to city:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 35, 'That upon you may come all the righteous blood shed upon the earth, from the blood of righteous Abel unto the blood of Zacharias son of Barachias, whom ye slew between the temple and the altar.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 36, 'Verily I say unto you, All these things shall come upon this generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 37, 'O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, thou that killest the prophets, and stonest them which are sent unto thee, how often would I have gathered thy children together, even as a hen gathereth her chickens under her wings, and ye would not!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 38, 'Behold, your house is left unto you desolate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 23, 39, 'For I say unto you, Ye shall not see me henceforth, till ye shall say, Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 1, 'And Jesus went out, and departed from the temple: and his disciples came to him for to shew him the buildings of the temple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 2, 'And Jesus said unto them, See ye not all these things? verily I say unto you, There shall not be left here one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 3, 'And as he sat upon the mount of Olives, the disciples came unto him privately, saying, Tell us, when shall these things be? and what shall be the sign of thy coming, and of the end of the world?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 4, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, Take heed that no man deceive you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 5, 'For many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and shall deceive many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 6, 'And ye shall hear of wars and rumours of wars: see that ye be not troubled: for all these things must come to pass, but the end is not yet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 7, 'For nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be famines, and pestilences, and earthquakes, in divers places.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 8, 'All these are the beginning of sorrows.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 9, 'Then shall they deliver you up to be afflicted, and shall kill you: and ye shall be hated of all nations for my name''s sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 10, 'And then shall many be offended, and shall betray one another, and shall hate one another.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 11, 'And many false prophets shall rise, and shall deceive many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 12, 'And because iniquity shall abound, the love of many shall wax cold.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 13, 'But he that shall endure unto the end, the same shall be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 14, 'And this gospel of the kingdom shall be preached in all the world for a witness unto all nations; and then shall the end come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 15, 'When ye therefore shall see the abomination of desolation, spoken of by Daniel the prophet, stand in the holy place, (whoso readeth, let him understand:)'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 16, 'Then let them which be in Judaea flee into the mountains:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 17, 'Let him which is on the housetop not come down to take any thing out of his house:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 18, 'Neither let him which is in the field return back to take his clothes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 19, 'And woe unto them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 20, 'But pray ye that your flight be not in the winter, neither on the sabbath day:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 21, 'For then shall be great tribulation, such as was not since the beginning of the world to this time, no, nor ever shall be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 22, 'And except those days should be shortened, there should no flesh be saved: but for the elect''s sake those days shall be shortened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 23, 'Then if any man shall say unto you, Lo, here is Christ, or there; believe it not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 24, 'For there shall arise false Christs, and false prophets, and shall shew great signs and wonders; insomuch that, if it were possible, they shall deceive the very elect.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 25, 'Behold, I have told you before.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 26, 'Wherefore if they shall say unto you, Behold, he is in the desert; go not forth: behold, he is in the secret chambers; believe it not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 27, 'For as the lightning cometh out of the east, and shineth even unto the west; so shall also the coming of the Son of man be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 28, 'For wheresoever the carcase is, there will the eagles be gathered together.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 29, 'Immediately after the tribulation of those days shall the sun be darkened, and the moon shall not give her light, and the stars shall fall from heaven, and the powers of the heavens shall be shaken:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 30, 'And then shall appear the sign of the Son of man in heaven: and then shall all the tribes of the earth mourn, and they shall see the Son of man coming in the clouds of heaven with power and great glory.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 31, 'And he shall send his angels with a great sound of a trumpet, and they shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from one end of heaven to the other.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 32, 'Now learn a parable of the fig tree; When his branch is yet tender, and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is nigh:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 33, 'So likewise ye, when ye shall see all these things, know that it is near, even at the doors.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 34, 'Verily I say unto you, This generation shall not pass, till all these things be fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 35, 'Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 36, 'But of that day and hour knoweth no man, no, not the angels of heaven, but my Father only.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 37, 'But as the days of Noe were, so shall also the coming of the Son of man be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 38, 'For as in the days that were before the flood they were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage, until the day that Noe entered into the ark,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 39, 'And knew not until the flood came, and took them all away; so shall also the coming of the Son of man be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 40, 'Then shall two be in the field; the one shall be taken, and the other left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 41, 'Two women shall be grinding at the mill; the one shall be taken, and the other left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 42, 'Watch therefore: for ye know not what hour your Lord doth come.')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 43, 'But know this, that if the goodman of the house had known in what watch the thief would come, he would have watched, and would not have suffered his house to be broken up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 44, 'Therefore be ye also ready: for in such an hour as ye think not the Son of man cometh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 45, 'Who then is a faithful and wise servant, whom his lord hath made ruler over his household, to give them meat in due season?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 46, 'Blessed is that servant, whom his lord when he cometh shall find so doing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 47, 'Verily I say unto you, That he shall make him ruler over all his goods.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 48, 'But and if that evil servant shall say in his heart, My lord delayeth his coming;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 49, 'And shall begin to smite his fellowservants, and to eat and drink with the drunken;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 50, 'The lord of that servant shall come in a day when he looketh not for him, and in an hour that he is not aware of,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 24, 51, 'And shall cut him asunder, and appoint him his portion with the hypocrites: there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 1, 'Then shall the kingdom of heaven be likened unto ten virgins, which took their lamps, and went forth to meet the bridegroom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 2, 'And five of them were wise, and five were foolish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 3, 'They that were foolish took their lamps, and took no oil with them:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 4, 'But the wise took oil in their vessels with their lamps.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 5, 'While the bridegroom tarried, they all slumbered and slept.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 6, 'And at midnight there was a cry made, Behold, the bridegroom cometh; go ye out to meet him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 7, 'Then all those virgins arose, and trimmed their lamps.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 8, 'And the foolish said unto the wise, Give us of your oil; for our lamps are gone out.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 9, 'But the wise answered, saying, Not so; lest there be not enough for us and you: but go ye rather to them that sell, and buy for yourselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 10, 'And while they went to buy, the bridegroom came; and they that were ready went in with him to the marriage: and the door was shut.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 11, 'Afterward came also the other virgins, saying, Lord, Lord, open to us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 12, 'But he answered and said, Verily I say unto you, I know you not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 13, 'Watch therefore, for ye know neither the day nor the hour wherein the Son of man cometh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 14, 'For the kingdom of heaven is as a man travelling into a far country, who called his own servants, and delivered unto them his goods.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 15, 'And unto one he gave five talents, to another two, and to another one; to every man according to his several ability; and straightway took his journey.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 16, 'Then he that had received the five talents went and traded with the same, and made them other five talents.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 17, 'And likewise he that had received two, he also gained other two.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 18, 'But he that had received one went and digged in the earth, and hid his lord''s money.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 19, 'After a long time the lord of those servants cometh, and reckoneth with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 20, 'And so he that had received five talents came and brought other five talents, saying, Lord, thou deliveredst unto me five talents: behold, I have gained beside them five talents more.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 21, 'His lord said unto him, Well done, thou good and faithful servant: thou hast been faithful over a few things, I will make thee ruler over many things: enter thou into the joy of thy lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 22, 'He also that had received two talents came and said, Lord, thou deliveredst unto me two talents: behold, I have gained two other talents beside them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 23, 'His lord said unto him, Well done, good and faithful servant; thou hast been faithful over a few things, I will make thee ruler over many things: enter thou into the joy of thy lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 24, 'Then he which had received the one talent came and said, Lord, I knew thee that thou art an hard man, reaping where thou hast not sown, and gathering where thou hast not strawed:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 25, 'And I was afraid, and went and hid thy talent in the earth: lo, there thou hast that is thine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 26, 'His lord answered and said unto him, Thou wicked and slothful servant, thou knewest that I reap where I sowed not, and gather where I have not strawed:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 27, 'Thou oughtest therefore to have put my money to the exchangers, and then at my coming I should have received mine own with usury.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 28, 'Take therefore the talent from him, and give it unto him which hath ten talents.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 29, 'For unto every one that hath shall be given, and he shall have abundance: but from him that hath not shall be taken away even that which he hath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 30, 'And cast ye the unprofitable servant into outer darkness: there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 31, 'When the Son of man shall come in his glory, and all the holy angels with him, then shall he sit upon the throne of his glory:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 32, 'And before him shall be gathered all nations: and he shall separate them one from another, as a shepherd divideth his sheep from the goats:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 33, 'And he shall set the sheep on his right hand, but the goats on the left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 34, 'Then shall the King say unto them on his right hand, Come, ye blessed of my Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 35, 'For I was an hungred, and ye gave me meat: I was thirsty, and ye gave me drink: I was a stranger, and ye took me in:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 36, 'Naked, and ye clothed me: I was sick, and ye visited me: I was in prison, and ye came unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 37, 'Then shall the righteous answer him, saying, Lord, when saw we thee an hungred, and fed thee? or thirsty, and gave thee drink?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 38, 'When saw we thee a stranger, and took thee in? or naked, and clothed thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 39, 'Or when saw we thee sick, or in prison, and came unto thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 40, 'And the King shall answer and say unto them, Verily I say unto you, Inasmuch as ye have done it unto one of the least of these my brethren, ye have done it unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 41, 'Then shall he say also unto them on the left hand, Depart from me, ye cursed, into everlasting fire, prepared for the devil and his angels:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 42, 'For I was an hungred, and ye gave me no meat: I was thirsty, and ye gave me no drink:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 43, 'I was a stranger, and ye took me not in: naked, and ye clothed me not: sick, and in prison, and ye visited me not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 44, 'Then shall they also answer him, saying, Lord, when saw we thee an hungred, or athirst, or a stranger, or naked, or sick, or in prison, and did not minister unto thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 45, 'Then shall he answer them, saying, Verily I say unto you, Inasmuch as ye did it not to one of the least of these, ye did it not to me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 25, 46, 'And these shall go away into everlasting punishment: but the righteous into life eternal.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 1, 'And it came to pass, when Jesus had finished all these sayings, he said unto his disciples,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 2, 'Ye know that after two days is the feast of the passover, and the Son of man is betrayed to be crucified.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 3, 'Then assembled together the chief priests, and the scribes, and the elders of the people, unto the palace of the high priest, who was called Caiaphas,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 4, 'And consulted that they might take Jesus by subtilty, and kill him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 5, 'But they said, Not on the feast day, lest there be an uproar among the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 6, 'Now when Jesus was in Bethany, in the house of Simon the leper,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 7, 'There came unto him a woman having an alabaster box of very precious ointment, and poured it on his head, as he sat at meat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 8, 'But when his disciples saw it, they had indignation, saying, To what purpose is this waste?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 9, 'For this ointment might have been sold for much, and given to the poor.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 10, 'When Jesus understood it, he said unto them, Why trouble ye the woman? for she hath wrought a good work upon me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 11, 'For ye have the poor always with you; but me ye have not always.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 12, 'For in that she hath poured this ointment on my body, she did it for my burial.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 13, 'Verily I say unto you, Wheresoever this gospel shall be preached in the whole world, there shall also this, that this woman hath done, be told for a memorial of her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 14, 'Then one of the twelve, called Judas Iscariot, went unto the chief priests,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 15, 'And said unto them, What will ye give me, and I will deliver him unto you? And they covenanted with him for thirty pieces of silver.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 16, 'And from that time he sought opportunity to betray him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 17, 'Now the first day of the feast of unleavened bread the disciples came to Jesus, saying unto him, Where wilt thou that we prepare for thee to eat the passover?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 18, 'And he said, Go into the city to such a man, and say unto him, The Master saith, My time is at hand; I will keep the passover at thy house with my disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 19, 'And the disciples did as Jesus had appointed them; and they made ready the passover.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 20, 'Now when the even was come, he sat down with the twelve.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 21, 'And as they did eat, he said, Verily I say unto you, that one of you shall betray me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 22, 'And they were exceeding sorrowful, and began every one of them to say unto him, Lord, is it I?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 23, 'And he answered and said, He that dippeth his hand with me in the dish, the same shall betray me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 24, 'The Son of man goeth as it is written of him: but woe unto that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! it had been good for that man if he had not been born.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 25, 'Then Judas, which betrayed him, answered and said, Master, is it I? He said unto him, Thou hast said.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 26, 'And as they were eating, Jesus took bread, and blessed it, and brake it, and gave it to the disciples, and said, Take, eat; this is my body.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 27, 'And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and gave it to them, saying, Drink ye all of it;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 28, 'For this is my blood of the new testament, which is shed for many for the remission of sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 29, 'But I say unto you, I will not drink henceforth of this fruit of the vine, until that day when I drink it new with you in my Father''s kingdom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 30, 'And when they had sung an hymn, they went out into the mount of Olives.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 31, 'Then saith Jesus unto them, All ye shall be offended because of me this night: for it is written, I will smite the shepherd, and the sheep of the flock shall be scattered abroad.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 32, 'But after I am risen again, I will go before you into Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 33, 'Peter answered and said unto him, Though all men shall be offended because of thee, yet will I never be offended.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 34, 'Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto thee, That this night, before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 35, 'Peter said unto him, Though I should die with thee, yet will I not deny thee. Likewise also said all the disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 36, 'Then cometh Jesus with them unto a place called Gethsemane, and saith unto the disciples, Sit ye here, while I go and pray yonder.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 37, 'And he took with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, and began to be sorrowful and very heavy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 38, 'Then saith he unto them, My soul is exceeding sorrowful, even unto death: tarry ye here, and watch with me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 39, 'And he went a little further, and fell on his face, and prayed, saying, O my Father, if it be possible, let this cup pass from me: nevertheless not as I will, but as thou wilt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 40, 'And he cometh unto the disciples, and findeth them asleep, and saith unto Peter, What, could ye not watch with me one hour?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 41, 'Watch and pray, that ye enter not into temptation: the spirit indeed is willing, but the flesh is weak.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 42, 'He went away again the second time, and prayed, saying, O my Father, if this cup may not pass away from me, except I drink it, thy will be done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 43, 'And he came and found them asleep again: for their eyes were heavy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 44, 'And he left them, and went away again, and prayed the third time, saying the same words.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 45, 'Then cometh he to his disciples, and saith unto them, Sleep on now, and take your rest: behold, the hour is at hand, and the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 46, 'Rise, let us be going: behold, he is at hand that doth betray me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 47, 'And while he yet spake, lo, Judas, one of the twelve, came, and with him a great multitude with swords and staves, from the chief priests and elders of the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 48, 'Now he that betrayed him gave them a sign, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he: hold him fast.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 49, 'And forthwith he came to Jesus, and said, Hail, master; and kissed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 50, 'And Jesus said unto him, Friend, wherefore art thou come? Then came they, and laid hands on Jesus, and took him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 51, 'And, behold, one of them which were with Jesus stretched out his hand, and drew his sword, and struck a servant of the high priest''s, and smote off his ear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 52, 'Then said Jesus unto him, Put up again thy sword into his place: for all they that take the sword shall perish with the sword.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 53, 'Thinkest thou that I cannot now pray to my Father, and he shall presently give me more than twelve legions of angels?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 54, 'But how then shall the scriptures be fulfilled, that thus it must be?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 55, 'In that same hour said Jesus to the multitudes, Are ye come out as against a thief with swords and staves for to take me? I sat daily with you teaching in the temple, and ye laid no hold on me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 56, 'But all this was done, that the scriptures of the prophets might be fulfilled. Then all the disciples forsook him, and fled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 57, 'And they that had laid hold on Jesus led him away to Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and the elders were assembled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 58, 'But Peter followed him afar off unto the high priest''s palace, and went in, and sat with the servants, to see the end.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 59, 'Now the chief priests, and elders, and all the council, sought false witness against Jesus, to put him to death;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 60, 'But found none: yea, though many false witnesses came, yet found they none. At the last came two false witnesses,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 61, 'And said, This fellow said, I am able to destroy the temple of God, and to build it in three days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 62, 'And the high priest arose, and said unto him, Answerest thou nothing? what is it which these witness against thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 63, 'But Jesus held his peace. And the high priest answered and said unto him, I adjure thee by the living God, that thou tell us whether thou be the Christ, the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 64, 'Jesus saith unto him, Thou hast said: nevertheless I say unto you, Hereafter shall ye see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 65, 'Then the high priest rent his clothes, saying, He hath spoken blasphemy; what further need have we of witnesses? behold, now ye have heard his blasphemy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 66, 'What think ye? They answered and said, He is guilty of death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 67, 'Then did they spit in his face, and buffeted him; and others smote him with the palms of their hands,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 68, 'Saying, Prophesy unto us, thou Christ, Who is he that smote thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 69, 'Now Peter sat without in the palace: and a damsel came unto him, saying, Thou also wast with Jesus of Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 70, 'But he denied before them all, saying, I know not what thou sayest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 71, 'And when he was gone out into the porch, another maid saw him, and said unto them that were there, This fellow was also with Jesus of Nazareth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 72, 'And again he denied with an oath, I do not know the man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 73, 'And after a while came unto him they that stood by, and said to Peter, Surely thou also art one of them; for thy speech bewrayeth thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 74, 'Then began he to curse and to swear, saying, I know not the man. And immediately the cock crew.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 26, 75, 'And Peter remembered the word of Jesus, which said unto him, Before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice. And he went out, and wept bitterly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 1, 'When the morning was come, all the chief priests and elders of the people took counsel against Jesus to put him to death:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 2, 'And when they had bound him, they led him away, and delivered him to Pontius Pilate the governor.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 3, 'Then Judas, which had betrayed him, when he saw that he was condemned, repented himself, and brought again the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 4, 'Saying, I have sinned in that I have betrayed the innocent blood. And they said, What is that to us? see thou to that.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 5, 'And he cast down the pieces of silver in the temple, and departed, and went and hanged himself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 6, 'And the chief priests took the silver pieces, and said, It is not lawful for to put them into the treasury, because it is the price of blood.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 7, 'And they took counsel, and bought with them the potter''s field, to bury strangers in.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 8, 'Wherefore that field was called, The field of blood, unto this day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 9, 'Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremy the prophet, saying, And they took the thirty pieces of silver, the price of him that was valued, whom they of the children of Israel did value;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 10, 'And gave them for the potter''s field, as the Lord appointed me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 11, 'And Jesus stood before the governor: and the governor asked him, saying, Art thou the King of the Jews? And Jesus said unto him, Thou sayest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 12, 'And when he was accused of the chief priests and elders, he answered nothing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 13, 'Then said Pilate unto him, Hearest thou not how many things they witness against thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 14, 'And he answered him to never a word; insomuch that the governor marvelled greatly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 15, 'Now at that feast the governor was wont to release unto the people a prisoner, whom they would.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 16, 'And they had then a notable prisoner, called Barabbas.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 17, 'Therefore when they were gathered together, Pilate said unto them, Whom will ye that I release unto you? Barabbas, or Jesus which is called Christ?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 18, 'For he knew that for envy they had delivered him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 19, 'When he was set down on the judgment seat, his wife sent unto him, saying, Have thou nothing to do with that just man: for I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 20, 'But the chief priests and elders persuaded the multitude that they should ask Barabbas, and destroy Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 21, 'The governor answered and said unto them, Whether of the twain will ye that I release unto you? They said, Barabbas.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 22, 'Pilate saith unto them, What shall I do then with Jesus which is called Christ? They all say unto him, Let him be crucified.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 23, 'And the governor said, Why, what evil hath he done? But they cried out the more, saying, Let him be crucified.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 24, 'When Pilate saw that he could prevail nothing, but that rather a tumult was made, he took water, and washed his hands before the multitude, saying, I am innocent of the blood of this just person: see ye to it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 25, 'Then answered all the people, and said, His blood be on us, and on our children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 26, 'Then released he Barabbas unto them: and when he had scourged Jesus, he delivered him to be crucified.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 27, 'Then the soldiers of the governor took Jesus into the common hall, and gathered unto him the whole band of soldiers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 28, 'And they stripped him, and put on him a scarlet robe.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 29, 'And when they had platted a crown of thorns, they put it upon his head, and a reed in his right hand: and they bowed the knee before him, and mocked him, saying, Hail, King of the Jews!'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 30, 'And they spit upon him, and took the reed, and smote him on the head.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 31, 'And after that they had mocked him, they took the robe off from him, and put his own raiment on him, and led him away to crucify him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 32, 'And as they came out, they found a man of Cyrene, Simon by name: him they compelled to bear his cross.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 33, 'And when they were come unto a place called Golgotha, that is to say, a place of a skull,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 34, 'They gave him vinegar to drink mingled with gall: and when he had tasted thereof, he would not drink.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 35, 'And they crucified him, and parted his garments, casting lots: that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the prophet, They parted my garments among them, and upon my vesture did they cast lots.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 36, 'And sitting down they watched him there;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 37, 'And set up over his head his accusation written, THIS IS JESUS THE KING OF THE JEWS.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 38, 'Then were there two thieves crucified with him, one on the right hand, and another on the left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 39, 'And they that passed by reviled him, wagging their heads,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 40, 'And saying, Thou that destroyest the temple, and buildest it in three days, save thyself. If thou be the Son of God, come down from the cross.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 41, 'Likewise also the chief priests mocking him, with the scribes and elders, said,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 42, 'He saved others; himself he cannot save. If he be the King of Israel, let him now come down from the cross, and we will believe him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 43, 'He trusted in God; let him deliver him now, if he will have him: for he said, I am the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 44, 'The thieves also, which were crucified with him, cast the same in his teeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 45, 'Now from the sixth hour there was darkness over all the land unto the ninth hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 46, 'And about the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, saying, Eli, Eli, lama sabachthani? that is to say, My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 47, 'Some of them that stood there, when they heard that, said, This man calleth for Elias.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 48, 'And straightway one of them ran, and took a spunge, and filled it with vinegar, and put it on a reed, and gave him to drink.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 49, 'The rest said, Let be, let us see whether Elias will come to save him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 50, 'Jesus, when he had cried again with a loud voice, yielded up the ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 51, 'And, behold, the veil of the temple was rent in twain from the top to the bottom; and the earth did quake, and the rocks rent;'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 52, 'And the graves were opened; and many bodies of the saints which slept arose,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 53, 'And came out of the graves after his resurrection, and went into the holy city, and appeared unto many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 54, 'Now when the centurion, and they that were with him, watching Jesus, saw the earthquake, and those things that were done, they feared greatly, saying, Truly this was the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 55, 'And many women were there beholding afar off, which followed Jesus from Galilee, ministering unto him:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 56, 'Among which was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James and Joses, and the mother of Zebedee''s children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 57, 'When the even was come, there came a rich man of Arimathaea, named Joseph, who also himself was Jesus'' disciple:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 58, 'He went to Pilate, and begged the body of Jesus. Then Pilate commanded the body to be delivered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 59, 'And when Joseph had taken the body, he wrapped it in a clean linen cloth,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 60, 'And laid it in his own new tomb, which he had hewn out in the rock: and he rolled a great stone to the door of the sepulchre, and departed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 61, 'And there was Mary Magdalene, and the other Mary, sitting over against the sepulchre.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 62, 'Now the next day, that followed the day of the preparation, the chief priests and Pharisees came together unto Pilate,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 63, 'Saying, Sir, we remember that that deceiver said, while he was yet alive, After three days I will rise again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 64, 'Command therefore that the sepulchre be made sure until the third day, lest his disciples come by night, and steal him away, and say unto the people, He is risen from the dead: so the last error shall be worse than the first.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 65, 'Pilate said unto them, Ye have a watch: go your way, make it as sure as ye can.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 27, 66, 'So they went, and made the sepulchre sure, sealing the stone, and setting a watch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 1, 'In the end of the sabbath, as it began to dawn toward the first day of the week, came Mary Magdalene and the other Mary to see the sepulchre.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 2, 'And, behold, there was a great earthquake: for the angel of the Lord descended from heaven, and came and rolled back the stone from the door, and sat upon it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 3, 'His countenance was like lightning, and his raiment white as snow:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 4, 'And for fear of him the keepers did shake, and became as dead men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 5, 'And the angel answered and said unto the women, Fear not ye: for I know that ye seek Jesus, which was crucified.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 6, 'He is not here: for he is risen, as he said. Come, see the place where the Lord lay.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 7, 'And go quickly, and tell his disciples that he is risen from the dead; and, behold, he goeth before you into Galilee; there shall ye see him: lo, I have told you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 8, 'And they departed quickly from the sepulchre with fear and great joy; and did run to bring his disciples word.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 9, 'And as they went to tell his disciples, behold, Jesus met them, saying, All hail. And they came and held him by the feet, and worshipped him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 10, 'Then said Jesus unto them, Be not afraid: go tell my brethren that they go into Galilee, and there shall they see me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 11, 'Now when they were going, behold, some of the watch came into the city, and shewed unto the chief priests all the things that were done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 12, 'And when they were assembled with the elders, and had taken counsel, they gave large money unto the soldiers,'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 13, 'Saying, Say ye, His disciples came by night, and stole him away while we slept.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 14, 'And if this come to the governor''s ears, we will persuade him, and secure you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 15, 'So they took the money, and did as they were taught: and this saying is commonly reported among the Jews until this day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 16, 'Then the eleven disciples went away into Galilee, into a mountain where Jesus had appointed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 17, 'And when they saw him, they worshipped him: but some doubted.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 18, 'And Jesus came and spake unto them, saying, All power is given unto me in heaven and in earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 19, 'Go ye therefore, and teach all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Ghost:'),
  ('KJV', 'Matthew', 40, 28, 20, 'Teaching them to observe all things whatsoever I have commanded you: and, lo, I am with you alway, even unto the end of the world. Amen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 1, 'The beginning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 2, 'As it is written in the prophets, Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 3, 'The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 4, 'John did baptize in the wilderness, and preach the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 5, 'And there went out unto him all the land of Judaea, and they of Jerusalem, and were all baptized of him in the river of Jordan, confessing their sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 6, 'And John was clothed with camel''s hair, and with a girdle of a skin about his loins; and he did eat locusts and wild honey;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 7, 'And preached, saying, There cometh one mightier than I after me, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to stoop down and unloose.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 8, 'I indeed have baptized you with water: but he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 9, 'And it came to pass in those days, that Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee, and was baptized of John in Jordan.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 10, 'And straightway coming up out of the water, he saw the heavens opened, and the Spirit like a dove descending upon him:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 11, 'And there came a voice from heaven, saying, Thou art my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 12, 'And immediately the Spirit driveth him into the wilderness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 13, 'And he was there in the wilderness forty days, tempted of Satan; and was with the wild beasts; and the angels ministered unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 14, 'Now after that John was put in prison, Jesus came into Galilee, preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 15, 'And saying, The time is fulfilled, and the kingdom of God is at hand: repent ye, and believe the gospel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 16, 'Now as he walked by the sea of Galilee, he saw Simon and Andrew his brother casting a net into the sea: for they were fishers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 17, 'And Jesus said unto them, Come ye after me, and I will make you to become fishers of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 18, 'And straightway they forsook their nets, and followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 19, 'And when he had gone a little further thence, he saw James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother, who also were in the ship mending their nets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 20, 'And straightway he called them: and they left their father Zebedee in the ship with the hired servants, and went after him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 21, 'And they went into Capernaum; and straightway on the sabbath day he entered into the synagogue, and taught.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 22, 'And they were astonished at his doctrine: for he taught them as one that had authority, and not as the scribes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 23, 'And there was in their synagogue a man with an unclean spirit; and he cried out,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 24, 'Saying, Let us alone; what have we to do with thee, thou Jesus of Nazareth? art thou come to destroy us? I know thee who thou art, the Holy One of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 25, 'And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 26, 'And when the unclean spirit had torn him, and cried with a loud voice, he came out of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 27, 'And they were all amazed, insomuch that they questioned among themselves, saying, What thing is this? what new doctrine is this? for with authority commandeth he even the unclean spirits, and they do obey him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 28, 'And immediately his fame spread abroad throughout all the region round about Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 29, 'And forthwith, when they were come out of the synagogue, they entered into the house of Simon and Andrew, with James and John.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 30, 'But Simon''s wife''s mother lay sick of a fever, and anon they tell him of her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 31, 'And he came and took her by the hand, and lifted her up; and immediately the fever left her, and she ministered unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 32, 'And at even, when the sun did set, they brought unto him all that were diseased, and them that were possessed with devils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 33, 'And all the city was gathered together at the door.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 34, 'And he healed many that were sick of divers diseases, and cast out many devils; and suffered not the devils to speak, because they knew him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 35, 'And in the morning, rising up a great while before day, he went out, and departed into a solitary place, and there prayed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 36, 'And Simon and they that were with him followed after him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 37, 'And when they had found him, they said unto him, All men seek for thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 38, 'And he said unto them, Let us go into the next towns, that I may preach there also: for therefore came I forth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 39, 'And he preached in their synagogues throughout all Galilee, and cast out devils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 40, 'And there came a leper to him, beseeching him, and kneeling down to him, and saying unto him, If thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 41, 'And Jesus, moved with compassion, put forth his hand, and touched him, and saith unto him, I will; be thou clean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 42, 'And as soon as he had spoken, immediately the leprosy departed from him, and he was cleansed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 43, 'And he straitly charged him, and forthwith sent him away;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 44, 'And saith unto him, See thou say nothing to any man: but go thy way, shew thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing those things which Moses commanded, for a testimony unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 1, 45, 'But he went out, and began to publish it much, and to blaze abroad the matter, insomuch that Jesus could no more openly enter into the city, but was without in desert places: and they came to him from every quarter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 1, 'And again he entered into Capernaum after some days; and it was noised that he was in the house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 2, 'And straightway many were gathered together, insomuch that there was no room to receive them, no, not so much as about the door: and he preached the word unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 3, 'And they come unto him, bringing one sick of the palsy, which was borne of four.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 4, 'And when they could not come nigh unto him for the press, they uncovered the roof where he was: and when they had broken it up, they let down the bed wherein the sick of the palsy lay.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 5, 'When Jesus saw their faith, he said unto the sick of the palsy, Son, thy sins be forgiven thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 6, 'But there were certain of the scribes sitting there, and reasoning in their hearts,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 7, 'Why doth this man thus speak blasphemies? who can forgive sins but God only?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 8, 'And immediately when Jesus perceived in his spirit that they so reasoned within themselves, he said unto them, Why reason ye these things in your hearts?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 9, 'Whether is it easier to say to the sick of the palsy, Thy sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Arise, and take up thy bed, and walk?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 10, 'But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins, (he saith to the sick of the palsy,)'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 11, 'I say unto thee, Arise, and take up thy bed, and go thy way into thine house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 12, 'And immediately he arose, took up the bed, and went forth before them all; insomuch that they were all amazed, and glorified God, saying, We never saw it on this fashion.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 13, 'And he went forth again by the sea side; and all the multitude resorted unto him, and he taught them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 14, 'And as he passed by, he saw Levi the son of Alphaeus sitting at the receipt of custom, and said unto him, Follow me. And he arose and followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 15, 'And it came to pass, that, as Jesus sat at meat in his house, many publicans and sinners sat also together with Jesus and his disciples: for there were many, and they followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 16, 'And when the scribes and Pharisees saw him eat with publicans and sinners, they said unto his disciples, How is it that he eateth and drinketh with publicans and sinners?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 17, 'When Jesus heard it, he saith unto them, They that are whole have no need of the physician, but they that are sick: I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 18, 'And the disciples of John and of the Pharisees used to fast: and they come and say unto him, Why do the disciples of John and of the Pharisees fast, but thy disciples fast not?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 19, 'And Jesus said unto them, Can the children of the bridechamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them? as long as they have the bridegroom with them, they cannot fast.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 20, 'But the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken away from them, and then shall they fast in those days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 21, 'No man also seweth a piece of new cloth on an old garment: else the new piece that filled it up taketh away from the old, and the rent is made worse.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 22, 'And no man putteth new wine into old bottles: else the new wine doth burst the bottles, and the wine is spilled, and the bottles will be marred: but new wine must be put into new bottles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 23, 'And it came to pass, that he went through the corn fields on the sabbath day; and his disciples began, as they went, to pluck the ears of corn.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 24, 'And the Pharisees said unto him, Behold, why do they on the sabbath day that which is not lawful?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 25, 'And he said unto them, Have ye never read what David did, when he had need, and was an hungred, he, and they that were with him?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 26, 'How he went into the house of God in the days of Abiathar the high priest, and did eat the shewbread, which is not lawful to eat but for the priests, and gave also to them which were with him?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 27, 'And he said unto them, The sabbath was made for man, and not man for the sabbath:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 2, 28, 'Therefore the Son of man is Lord also of the sabbath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 1, 'And he entered again into the synagogue; and there was a man there which had a withered hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 2, 'And they watched him, whether he would heal him on the sabbath day; that they might accuse him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 3, 'And he saith unto the man which had the withered hand, Stand forth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 4, 'And he saith unto them, Is it lawful to do good on the sabbath days, or to do evil? to save life, or to kill? But they held their peace.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 5, 'And when he had looked round about on them with anger, being grieved for the hardness of their hearts, he saith unto the man, Stretch forth thine hand. And he stretched it out: and his hand was restored whole as the other.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 6, 'And the Pharisees went forth, and straightway took counsel with the Herodians against him, how they might destroy him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 7, 'But Jesus withdrew himself with his disciples to the sea: and a great multitude from Galilee followed him, and from Judaea,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 8, 'And from Jerusalem, and from Idumaea, and from beyond Jordan; and they about Tyre and Sidon, a great multitude, when they had heard what great things he did, came unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 9, 'And he spake to his disciples, that a small ship should wait on him because of the multitude, lest they should throng him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 10, 'For he had healed many; insomuch that they pressed upon him for to touch him, as many as had plagues.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 11, 'And unclean spirits, when they saw him, fell down before him, and cried, saying, Thou art the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 12, 'And he straitly charged them that they should not make him known.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 13, 'And he goeth up into a mountain, and calleth unto him whom he would: and they came unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 14, 'And he ordained twelve, that they should be with him, and that he might send them forth to preach,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 15, 'And to have power to heal sicknesses, and to cast out devils:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 16, 'And Simon he surnamed Peter;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 17, 'And James the son of Zebedee, and John the brother of James; and he surnamed them Boanerges, which is, The sons of thunder:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 18, 'And Andrew, and Philip, and Bartholomew, and Matthew, and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus, and Simon the Canaanite,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 19, 'And Judas Iscariot, which also betrayed him: and they went into an house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 20, 'And the multitude cometh together again, so that they could not so much as eat bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 21, 'And when his friends heard of it, they went out to lay hold on him: for they said, He is beside himself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 22, 'And the scribes which came down from Jerusalem said, He hath Beelzebub, and by the prince of the devils casteth he out devils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 23, 'And he called them unto him, and said unto them in parables, How can Satan cast out Satan?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 24, 'And if a kingdom be divided against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 25, 'And if a house be divided against itself, that house cannot stand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 26, 'And if Satan rise up against himself, and be divided, he cannot stand, but hath an end.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 27, 'No man can enter into a strong man''s house, and spoil his goods, except he will first bind the strong man; and then he will spoil his house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 28, 'Verily I say unto you, All sins shall be forgiven unto the sons of men, and blasphemies wherewith soever they shall blaspheme:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 29, 'But he that shall blaspheme against the Holy Ghost hath never forgiveness, but is in danger of eternal damnation:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 30, 'Because they said, He hath an unclean spirit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 31, 'There came then his brethren and his mother, and, standing without, sent unto him, calling him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 32, 'And the multitude sat about him, and they said unto him, Behold, thy mother and thy brethren without seek for thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 33, 'And he answered them, saying, Who is my mother, or my brethren?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 34, 'And he looked round about on them which sat about him, and said, Behold my mother and my brethren!'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 3, 35, 'For whosoever shall do the will of God, the same is my brother, and my sister, and mother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 1, 'And he began again to teach by the sea side: and there was gathered unto him a great multitude, so that he entered into a ship, and sat in the sea; and the whole multitude was by the sea on the land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 2, 'And he taught them many things by parables, and said unto them in his doctrine,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 3, 'Hearken; Behold, there went out a sower to sow:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 4, 'And it came to pass, as he sowed, some fell by the way side, and the fowls of the air came and devoured it up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 5, 'And some fell on stony ground, where it had not much earth; and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth of earth:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 6, 'But when the sun was up, it was scorched; and because it had no root, it withered away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 7, 'And some fell among thorns, and the thorns grew up, and choked it, and it yielded no fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 8, 'And other fell on good ground, and did yield fruit that sprang up and increased; and brought forth, some thirty, and some sixty, and some an hundred.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 9, 'And he said unto them, He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 10, 'And when he was alone, they that were about him with the twelve asked of him the parable.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 11, 'And he said unto them, Unto you it is given to know the mystery of the kingdom of God: but unto them that are without, all these things are done in parables:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 12, 'That seeing they may see, and not perceive; and hearing they may hear, and not understand; lest at any time they should be converted, and their sins should be forgiven them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 13, 'And he said unto them, Know ye not this parable? and how then will ye know all parables?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 14, 'The sower soweth the word.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 15, 'And these are they by the way side, where the word is sown; but when they have heard, Satan cometh immediately, and taketh away the word that was sown in their hearts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 16, 'And these are they likewise which are sown on stony ground; who, when they have heard the word, immediately receive it with gladness;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 17, 'And have no root in themselves, and so endure but for a time: afterward, when affliction or persecution ariseth for the word''s sake, immediately they are offended.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 18, 'And these are they which are sown among thorns; such as hear the word,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 19, 'And the cares of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches, and the lusts of other things entering in, choke the word, and it becometh unfruitful.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 20, 'And these are they which are sown on good ground; such as hear the word, and receive it, and bring forth fruit, some thirtyfold, some sixty, and some an hundred.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 21, 'And he said unto them, Is a candle brought to be put under a bushel, or under a bed? and not to be set on a candlestick?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 22, 'For there is nothing hid, which shall not be manifested; neither was any thing kept secret, but that it should come abroad.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 23, 'If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 24, 'And he said unto them, Take heed what ye hear: with what measure ye mete, it shall be measured to you: and unto you that hear shall more be given.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 25, 'For he that hath, to him shall be given: and he that hath not, from him shall be taken even that which he hath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 26, 'And he said, So is the kingdom of God, as if a man should cast seed into the ground;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 27, 'And should sleep, and rise night and day, and the seed should spring and grow up, he knoweth not how.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 28, 'For the earth bringeth forth fruit of herself; first the blade, then the ear, after that the full corn in the ear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 29, 'But when the fruit is brought forth, immediately he putteth in the sickle, because the harvest is come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 30, 'And he said, Whereunto shall we liken the kingdom of God? or with what comparison shall we compare it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 31, 'It is like a grain of mustard seed, which, when it is sown in the earth, is less than all the seeds that be in the earth:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 32, 'But when it is sown, it groweth up, and becometh greater than all herbs, and shooteth out great branches; so that the fowls of the air may lodge under the shadow of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 33, 'And with many such parables spake he the word unto them, as they were able to hear it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 34, 'But without a parable spake he not unto them: and when they were alone, he expounded all things to his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 35, 'And the same day, when the even was come, he saith unto them, Let us pass over unto the other side.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 36, 'And when they had sent away the multitude, they took him even as he was in the ship. And there were also with him other little ships.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 37, 'And there arose a great storm of wind, and the waves beat into the ship, so that it was now full.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 38, 'And he was in the hinder part of the ship, asleep on a pillow: and they awake him, and say unto him, Master, carest thou not that we perish?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 39, 'And he arose, and rebuked the wind, and said unto the sea, Peace, be still. And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 40, 'And he said unto them, Why are ye so fearful? how is it that ye have no faith?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 4, 41, 'And they feared exceedingly, and said one to another, What manner of man is this, that even the wind and the sea obey him?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 1, 'And they came over unto the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gadarenes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 2, 'And when he was come out of the ship, immediately there met him out of the tombs a man with an unclean spirit,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 3, 'Who had his dwelling among the tombs; and no man could bind him, no, not with chains:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 4, 'Because that he had been often bound with fetters and chains, and the chains had been plucked asunder by him, and the fetters broken in pieces: neither could any man tame him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 5, 'And always, night and day, he was in the mountains, and in the tombs, crying, and cutting himself with stones.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 6, 'But when he saw Jesus afar off, he ran and worshipped him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 7, 'And cried with a loud voice, and said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, thou Son of the most high God? I adjure thee by God, that thou torment me not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 8, 'For he said unto him, Come out of the man, thou unclean spirit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 9, 'And he asked him, What is thy name? And he answered, saying, My name is Legion: for we are many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 10, 'And he besought him much that he would not send them away out of the country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 11, 'Now there was there nigh unto the mountains a great herd of swine feeding.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 12, 'And all the devils besought him, saying, Send us into the swine, that we may enter into them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 13, 'And forthwith Jesus gave them leave. And the unclean spirits went out, and entered into the swine: and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the sea, (they were about two thousand;) and were choked in the sea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 14, 'And they that fed the swine fled, and told it in the city, and in the country. And they went out to see what it was that was done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 15, 'And they come to Jesus, and see him that was possessed with the devil, and had the legion, sitting, and clothed, and in his right mind: and they were afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 16, 'And they that saw it told them how it befell to him that was possessed with the devil, and also concerning the swine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 17, 'And they began to pray him to depart out of their coasts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 18, 'And when he was come into the ship, he that had been possessed with the devil prayed him that he might be with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 19, 'Howbeit Jesus suffered him not, but saith unto him, Go home to thy friends, and tell them how great things the Lord hath done for thee, and hath had compassion on thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 20, 'And he departed, and began to publish in Decapolis how great things Jesus had done for him: and all men did marvel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 21, 'And when Jesus was passed over again by ship unto the other side, much people gathered unto him: and he was nigh unto the sea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 22, 'And, behold, there cometh one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jairus by name; and when he saw him, he fell at his feet,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 23, 'And besought him greatly, saying, My little daughter lieth at the point of death: I pray thee, come and lay thy hands on her, that she may be healed; and she shall live.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 24, 'And Jesus went with him; and much people followed him, and thronged him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 25, 'And a certain woman, which had an issue of blood twelve years,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 26, 'And had suffered many things of many physicians, and had spent all that she had, and was nothing bettered, but rather grew worse,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 27, 'When she had heard of Jesus, came in the press behind, and touched his garment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 28, 'For she said, If I may touch but his clothes, I shall be whole.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 29, 'And straightway the fountain of her blood was dried up; and she felt in her body that she was healed of that plague.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 30, 'And Jesus, immediately knowing in himself that virtue had gone out of him, turned him about in the press, and said, Who touched my clothes?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 31, 'And his disciples said unto him, Thou seest the multitude thronging thee, and sayest thou, Who touched me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 32, 'And he looked round about to see her that had done this thing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 33, 'But the woman fearing and trembling, knowing what was done in her, came and fell down before him, and told him all the truth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 34, 'And he said unto her, Daughter, thy faith hath made thee whole; go in peace, and be whole of thy plague.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 35, 'While he yet spake, there came from the ruler of the synagogue''s house certain which said, Thy daughter is dead: why troublest thou the Master any further?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 36, 'As soon as Jesus heard the word that was spoken, he saith unto the ruler of the synagogue, Be not afraid, only believe.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 37, 'And he suffered no man to follow him, save Peter, and James, and John the brother of James.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 38, 'And he cometh to the house of the ruler of the synagogue, and seeth the tumult, and them that wept and wailed greatly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 39, 'And when he was come in, he saith unto them, Why make ye this ado, and weep? the damsel is not dead, but sleepeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 40, 'And they laughed him to scorn. But when he had put them all out, he taketh the father and the mother of the damsel, and them that were with him, and entereth in where the damsel was lying.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 41, 'And he took the damsel by the hand, and said unto her, Talitha cumi; which is, being interpreted, Damsel, I say unto thee, arise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 42, 'And straightway the damsel arose, and walked; for she was of the age of twelve years. And they were astonished with a great astonishment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 5, 43, 'And he charged them straitly that no man should know it; and commanded that something should be given her to eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 1, 'And he went out from thence, and came into his own country; and his disciples follow him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 2, 'And when the sabbath day was come, he began to teach in the synagogue: and many hearing him were astonished, saying, From whence hath this man these things? and what wisdom is this which is given unto him, that even such mighty works are wrought by his hands?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 3, 'Is not this the carpenter, the son of Mary, the brother of James, and Joses, and of Juda, and Simon? and are not his sisters here with us? And they were offended at him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 4, 'But Jesus said unto them, A prophet is not without honour, but in his own country, and among his own kin, and in his own house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 5, 'And he could there do no mighty work, save that he laid his hands upon a few sick folk, and healed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 6, 'And he marvelled because of their unbelief. And he went round about the villages, teaching.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 7, 'And he called unto him the twelve, and began to send them forth by two and two; and gave them power over unclean spirits;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 8, 'And commanded them that they should take nothing for their journey, save a staff only; no scrip, no bread, no money in their purse:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 9, 'But be shod with sandals; and not put on two coats.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 10, 'And he said unto them, In what place soever ye enter into an house, there abide till ye depart from that place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 11, 'And whosoever shall not receive you, nor hear you, when ye depart thence, shake off the dust under your feet for a testimony against them. Verily I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for Sodom and Gomorrha in the day of judgment, than for that city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 12, 'And they went out, and preached that men should repent.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 13, 'And they cast out many devils, and anointed with oil many that were sick, and healed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 14, 'And king Herod heard of him; (for his name was spread abroad:) and he said, That John the Baptist was risen from the dead, and therefore mighty works do shew forth themselves in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 15, 'Others said, That it is Elias. And others said, That it is a prophet, or as one of the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 16, 'But when Herod heard thereof, he said, It is John, whom I beheaded: he is risen from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 17, 'For Herod himself had sent forth and laid hold upon John, and bound him in prison for Herodias'' sake, his brother Philip''s wife: for he had married her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 18, 'For John had said unto Herod, It is not lawful for thee to have thy brother''s wife.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 19, 'Therefore Herodias had a quarrel against him, and would have killed him; but she could not:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 20, 'For Herod feared John, knowing that he was a just man and an holy, and observed him; and when he heard him, he did many things, and heard him gladly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 21, 'And when a convenient day was come, that Herod on his birthday made a supper to his lords, high captains, and chief estates of Galilee;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 22, 'And when the daughter of the said Herodias came in, and danced, and pleased Herod and them that sat with him, the king said unto the damsel, Ask of me whatsoever thou wilt, and I will give it thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 23, 'And he sware unto her, Whatsoever thou shalt ask of me, I will give it thee, unto the half of my kingdom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 24, 'And she went forth, and said unto her mother, What shall I ask? And she said, The head of John the Baptist.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 25, 'And she came in straightway with haste unto the king, and asked, saying, I will that thou give me by and by in a charger the head of John the Baptist.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 26, 'And the king was exceeding sorry; yet for his oath''s sake, and for their sakes which sat with him, he would not reject her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 27, 'And immediately the king sent an executioner, and commanded his head to be brought: and he went and beheaded him in the prison,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 28, 'And brought his head in a charger, and gave it to the damsel: and the damsel gave it to her mother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 29, 'And when his disciples heard of it, they came and took up his corpse, and laid it in a tomb.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 30, 'And the apostles gathered themselves together unto Jesus, and told him all things, both what they had done, and what they had taught.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 31, 'And he said unto them, Come ye yourselves apart into a desert place, and rest a while: for there were many coming and going, and they had no leisure so much as to eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 32, 'And they departed into a desert place by ship privately.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 33, 'And the people saw them departing, and many knew him, and ran afoot thither out of all cities, and outwent them, and came together unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 34, 'And Jesus, when he came out, saw much people, and was moved with compassion toward them, because they were as sheep not having a shepherd: and he began to teach them many things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 35, 'And when the day was now far spent, his disciples came unto him, and said, This is a desert place, and now the time is far passed:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 36, 'Send them away, that they may go into the country round about, and into the villages, and buy themselves bread: for they have nothing to eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 37, 'He answered and said unto them, Give ye them to eat. And they say unto him, Shall we go and buy two hundred pennyworth of bread, and give them to eat?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 38, 'He saith unto them, How many loaves have ye? go and see. And when they knew, they say, Five, and two fishes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 39, 'And he commanded them to make all sit down by companies upon the green grass.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 40, 'And they sat down in ranks, by hundreds, and by fifties.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 41, 'And when he had taken the five loaves and the two fishes, he looked up to heaven, and blessed, and brake the loaves, and gave them to his disciples to set before them; and the two fishes divided he among them all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 42, 'And they did all eat, and were filled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 43, 'And they took up twelve baskets full of the fragments, and of the fishes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 44, 'And they that did eat of the loaves were about five thousand men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 45, 'And straightway he constrained his disciples to get into the ship, and to go to the other side before unto Bethsaida, while he sent away the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 46, 'And when he had sent them away, he departed into a mountain to pray.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 47, 'And when even was come, the ship was in the midst of the sea, and he alone on the land.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 48, 'And he saw them toiling in rowing; for the wind was contrary unto them: and about the fourth watch of the night he cometh unto them, walking upon the sea, and would have passed by them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 49, 'But when they saw him walking upon the sea, they supposed it had been a spirit, and cried out:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 50, 'For they all saw him, and were troubled. And immediately he talked with them, and saith unto them, Be of good cheer: it is I; be not afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 51, 'And he went up unto them into the ship; and the wind ceased: and they were sore amazed in themselves beyond measure, and wondered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 52, 'For they considered not the miracle of the loaves: for their heart was hardened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 53, 'And when they had passed over, they came into the land of Gennesaret, and drew to the shore.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 54, 'And when they were come out of the ship, straightway they knew him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 55, 'And ran through that whole region round about, and began to carry about in beds those that were sick, where they heard he was.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 6, 56, 'And whithersoever he entered, into villages, or cities, or country, they laid the sick in the streets, and besought him that they might touch if it were but the border of his garment: and as many as touched him were made whole.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 1, 'Then came together unto him the Pharisees, and certain of the scribes, which came from Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 2, 'And when they saw some of his disciples eat bread with defiled, that is to say, with unwashen, hands, they found fault.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 3, 'For the Pharisees, and all the Jews, except they wash their hands oft, eat not, holding the tradition of the elders.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 4, 'And when they come from the market, except they wash, they eat not. And many other things there be, which they have received to hold, as the washing of cups, and pots, brasen vessels, and of tables.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 5, 'Then the Pharisees and scribes asked him, Why walk not thy disciples according to the tradition of the elders, but eat bread with unwashen hands?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 6, 'He answered and said unto them, Well hath Esaias prophesied of you hypocrites, as it is written, This people honoureth me with their lips, but their heart is far from me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 7, 'Howbeit in vain do they worship me, teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 8, 'For laying aside the commandment of God, ye hold the tradition of men, as the washing of pots and cups: and many other such like things ye do.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 9, 'And he said unto them, Full well ye reject the commandment of God, that ye may keep your own tradition.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 10, 'For Moses said, Honour thy father and thy mother; and, Whoso curseth father or mother, let him die the death:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 11, 'But ye say, If a man shall say to his father or mother, It is Corban, that is to say, a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me; he shall be free.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 12, 'And ye suffer him no more to do ought for his father or his mother;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 13, 'Making the word of God of none effect through your tradition, which ye have delivered: and many such like things do ye.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 14, 'And when he had called all the people unto him, he said unto them, Hearken unto me every one of you, and understand:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 15, 'There is nothing from without a man, that entering into him can defile him: but the things which come out of him, those are they that defile the man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 16, 'If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 17, 'And when he was entered into the house from the people, his disciples asked him concerning the parable.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 18, 'And he saith unto them, Are ye so without understanding also? Do ye not perceive, that whatsoever thing from without entereth into the man, it cannot defile him;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 19, 'Because it entereth not into his heart, but into the belly, and goeth out into the draught, purging all meats?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 20, 'And he said, That which cometh out of the man, that defileth the man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 21, 'For from within, out of the heart of men, proceed evil thoughts, adulteries, fornications, murders,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 22, 'Thefts, covetousness, wickedness, deceit, lasciviousness, an evil eye, blasphemy, pride, foolishness:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 23, 'All these evil things come from within, and defile the man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 24, 'And from thence he arose, and went into the borders of Tyre and Sidon, and entered into an house, and would have no man know it: but he could not be hid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 25, 'For a certain woman, whose young daughter had an unclean spirit, heard of him, and came and fell at his feet:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 26, 'The woman was a Greek, a Syrophenician by nation; and she besought him that he would cast forth the devil out of her daughter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 27, 'But Jesus said unto her, Let the children first be filled: for it is not meet to take the children''s bread, and to cast it unto the dogs.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 28, 'And she answered and said unto him, Yes, Lord: yet the dogs under the table eat of the children''s crumbs.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 29, 'And he said unto her, For this saying go thy way; the devil is gone out of thy daughter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 30, 'And when she was come to her house, she found the devil gone out, and her daughter laid upon the bed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 31, 'And again, departing from the coasts of Tyre and Sidon, he came unto the sea of Galilee, through the midst of the coasts of Decapolis.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 32, 'And they bring unto him one that was deaf, and had an impediment in his speech; and they beseech him to put his hand upon him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 33, 'And he took him aside from the multitude, and put his fingers into his ears, and he spit, and touched his tongue;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 34, 'And looking up to heaven, he sighed, and saith unto him, Ephphatha, that is, Be opened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 35, 'And straightway his ears were opened, and the string of his tongue was loosed, and he spake plain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 36, 'And he charged them that they should tell no man: but the more he charged them, so much the more a great deal they published it;')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 7, 37, 'And were beyond measure astonished, saying, He hath done all things well: he maketh both the deaf to hear, and the dumb to speak.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 1, 'In those days the multitude being very great, and having nothing to eat, Jesus called his disciples unto him, and saith unto them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 2, 'I have compassion on the multitude, because they have now been with me three days, and have nothing to eat:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 3, 'And if I send them away fasting to their own houses, they will faint by the way: for divers of them came from far.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 4, 'And his disciples answered him, From whence can a man satisfy these men with bread here in the wilderness?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 5, 'And he asked them, How many loaves have ye? And they said, Seven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 6, 'And he commanded the people to sit down on the ground: and he took the seven loaves, and gave thanks, and brake, and gave to his disciples to set before them; and they did set them before the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 7, 'And they had a few small fishes: and he blessed, and commanded to set them also before them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 8, 'So they did eat, and were filled: and they took up of the broken meat that was left seven baskets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 9, 'And they that had eaten were about four thousand: and he sent them away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 10, 'And straightway he entered into a ship with his disciples, and came into the parts of Dalmanutha.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 11, 'And the Pharisees came forth, and began to question with him, seeking of him a sign from heaven, tempting him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 12, 'And he sighed deeply in his spirit, and saith, Why doth this generation seek after a sign? verily I say unto you, There shall no sign be given unto this generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 13, 'And he left them, and entering into the ship again departed to the other side.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 14, 'Now the disciples had forgotten to take bread, neither had they in the ship with them more than one loaf.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 15, 'And he charged them, saying, Take heed, beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, and of the leaven of Herod.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 16, 'And they reasoned among themselves, saying, It is because we have no bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 17, 'And when Jesus knew it, he saith unto them, Why reason ye, because ye have no bread? perceive ye not yet, neither understand? have ye your heart yet hardened?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 18, 'Having eyes, see ye not? and having ears, hear ye not? and do ye not remember?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 19, 'When I brake the five loaves among five thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? They say unto him, Twelve.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 20, 'And when the seven among four thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? And they said, Seven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 21, 'And he said unto them, How is it that ye do not understand?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 22, 'And he cometh to Bethsaida; and they bring a blind man unto him, and besought him to touch him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 23, 'And he took the blind man by the hand, and led him out of the town; and when he had spit on his eyes, and put his hands upon him, he asked him if he saw ought.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 24, 'And he looked up, and said, I see men as trees, walking.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 25, 'After that he put his hands again upon his eyes, and made him look up: and he was restored, and saw every man clearly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 26, 'And he sent him away to his house, saying, Neither go into the town, nor tell it to any in the town.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 27, 'And Jesus went out, and his disciples, into the towns of Caesarea Philippi: and by the way he asked his disciples, saying unto them, Whom do men say that I am?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 28, 'And they answered, John the Baptist: but some say, Elias; and others, One of the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 29, 'And he saith unto them, But whom say ye that I am? And Peter answereth and saith unto him, Thou art the Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 30, 'And he charged them that they should tell no man of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 31, 'And he began to teach them, that the Son of man must suffer many things, and be rejected of the elders, and of the chief priests, and scribes, and be killed, and after three days rise again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 32, 'And he spake that saying openly. And Peter took him, and began to rebuke him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 33, 'But when he had turned about and looked on his disciples, he rebuked Peter, saying, Get thee behind me, Satan: for thou savourest not the things that be of God, but the things that be of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 34, 'And when he had called the people unto him with his disciples also, he said unto them, Whosoever will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 35, 'For whosoever will save his life shall lose it; but whosoever shall lose his life for my sake and the gospel''s, the same shall save it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 36, 'For what shall it profit a man, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 37, 'Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 8, 38, 'Whosoever therefore shall be ashamed of me and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation; of him also shall the Son of man be ashamed, when he cometh in the glory of his Father with the holy angels.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 1, 'And he said unto them, Verily I say unto you, That there be some of them that stand here, which shall not taste of death, till they have seen the kingdom of God come with power.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 2, 'And after six days Jesus taketh with him Peter, and James, and John, and leadeth them up into an high mountain apart by themselves: and he was transfigured before them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 3, 'And his raiment became shining, exceeding white as snow; so as no fuller on earth can white them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 4, 'And there appeared unto them Elias with Moses: and they were talking with Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 5, 'And Peter answered and said to Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here: and let us make three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 6, 'For he wist not what to say; for they were sore afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 7, 'And there was a cloud that overshadowed them: and a voice came out of the cloud, saying, This is my beloved Son: hear him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 8, 'And suddenly, when they had looked round about, they saw no man any more, save Jesus only with themselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 9, 'And as they came down from the mountain, he charged them that they should tell no man what things they had seen, till the Son of man were risen from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 10, 'And they kept that saying with themselves, questioning one with another what the rising from the dead should mean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 11, 'And they asked him, saying, Why say the scribes that Elias must first come?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 12, 'And he answered and told them, Elias verily cometh first, and restoreth all things; and how it is written of the Son of man, that he must suffer many things, and be set at nought.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 13, 'But I say unto you, That Elias is indeed come, and they have done unto him whatsoever they listed, as it is written of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 14, 'And when he came to his disciples, he saw a great multitude about them, and the scribes questioning with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 15, 'And straightway all the people, when they beheld him, were greatly amazed, and running to him saluted him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 16, 'And he asked the scribes, What question ye with them?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 17, 'And one of the multitude answered and said, Master, I have brought unto thee my son, which hath a dumb spirit;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 18, 'And wheresoever he taketh him, he teareth him: and he foameth, and gnasheth with his teeth, and pineth away: and I spake to thy disciples that they should cast him out; and they could not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 19, 'He answereth him, and saith, O faithless generation, how long shall I be with you? how long shall I suffer you? bring him unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 20, 'And they brought him unto him: and when he saw him, straightway the spirit tare him; and he fell on the ground, and wallowed foaming.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 21, 'And he asked his father, How long is it ago since this came unto him? And he said, Of a child.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 22, 'And ofttimes it hath cast him into the fire, and into the waters, to destroy him: but if thou canst do any thing, have compassion on us, and help us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 23, 'Jesus said unto him, If thou canst believe, all things are possible to him that believeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 24, 'And straightway the father of the child cried out, and said with tears, Lord, I believe; help thou mine unbelief.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 25, 'When Jesus saw that the people came running together, he rebuked the foul spirit, saying unto him, Thou dumb and deaf spirit, I charge thee, come out of him, and enter no more into him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 26, 'And the spirit cried, and rent him sore, and came out of him: and he was as one dead; insomuch that many said, He is dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 27, 'But Jesus took him by the hand, and lifted him up; and he arose.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 28, 'And when he was come into the house, his disciples asked him privately, Why could not we cast him out?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 29, 'And he said unto them, This kind can come forth by nothing, but by prayer and fasting.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 30, 'And they departed thence, and passed through Galilee; and he would not that any man should know it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 31, 'For he taught his disciples, and said unto them, The Son of man is delivered into the hands of men, and they shall kill him; and after that he is killed, he shall rise the third day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 32, 'But they understood not that saying, and were afraid to ask him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 33, 'And he came to Capernaum: and being in the house he asked them, What was it that ye disputed among yourselves by the way?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 34, 'But they held their peace: for by the way they had disputed among themselves, who should be the greatest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 35, 'And he sat down, and called the twelve, and saith unto them, If any man desire to be first, the same shall be last of all, and servant of all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 36, 'And he took a child, and set him in the midst of them: and when he had taken him in his arms, he said unto them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 37, 'Whosoever shall receive one of such children in my name, receiveth me: and whosoever shall receive me, receiveth not me, but him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 38, 'And John answered him, saying, Master, we saw one casting out devils in thy name, and he followeth not us: and we forbad him, because he followeth not us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 39, 'But Jesus said, Forbid him not: for there is no man which shall do a miracle in my name, that can lightly speak evil of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 40, 'For he that is not against us is on our part.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 41, 'For whosoever shall give you a cup of water to drink in my name, because ye belong to Christ, verily I say unto you, he shall not lose his reward.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 42, 'And whosoever shall offend one of these little ones that believe in me, it is better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he were cast into the sea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 43, 'And if thy hand offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter into life maimed, than having two hands to go into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 44, 'Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 45, 'And if thy foot offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter halt into life, than having two feet to be cast into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 46, 'Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 47, 'And if thine eye offend thee, pluck it out: it is better for thee to enter into the kingdom of God with one eye, than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 48, 'Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 49, 'For every one shall be salted with fire, and every sacrifice shall be salted with salt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 9, 50, 'Salt is good: but if the salt have lost his saltness, wherewith will ye season it? Have salt in yourselves, and have peace one with another.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 1, 'And he arose from thence, and cometh into the coasts of Judaea by the farther side of Jordan: and the people resort unto him again; and, as he was wont, he taught them again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 2, 'And the Pharisees came to him, and asked him, Is it lawful for a man to put away his wife? tempting him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 3, 'And he answered and said unto them, What did Moses command you?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 4, 'And they said, Moses suffered to write a bill of divorcement, and to put her away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 5, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, For the hardness of your heart he wrote you this precept.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 6, 'But from the beginning of the creation God made them male and female.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 7, 'For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and cleave to his wife;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 8, 'And they twain shall be one flesh: so then they are no more twain, but one flesh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 9, 'What therefore God hath joined together, let not man put asunder.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 10, 'And in the house his disciples asked him again of the same matter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 11, 'And he saith unto them, Whosoever shall put away his wife, and marry another, committeth adultery against her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 12, 'And if a woman shall put away her husband, and be married to another, she committeth adultery.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 13, 'And they brought young children to him, that he should touch them: and his disciples rebuked those that brought them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 14, 'But when Jesus saw it, he was much displeased, and said unto them, Suffer the little children to come unto me, and forbid them not: for of such is the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 15, 'Verily I say unto you, Whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God as a little child, he shall not enter therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 16, 'And he took them up in his arms, put his hands upon them, and blessed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 17, 'And when he was gone forth into the way, there came one running, and kneeled to him, and asked him, Good Master, what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 18, 'And Jesus said unto him, Why callest thou me good? there is none good but one, that is, God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 19, 'Thou knowest the commandments, Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Defraud not, Honour thy father and mother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 20, 'And he answered and said unto him, Master, all these have I observed from my youth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 21, 'Then Jesus beholding him loved him, and said unto him, One thing thou lackest: go thy way, sell whatsoever thou hast, and give to the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven: and come, take up the cross, and follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 22, 'And he was sad at that saying, and went away grieved: for he had great possessions.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 23, 'And Jesus looked round about, and saith unto his disciples, How hardly shall they that have riches enter into the kingdom of God!'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 24, 'And the disciples were astonished at his words. But Jesus answereth again, and saith unto them, Children, how hard is it for them that trust in riches to enter into the kingdom of God!'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 25, 'It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 26, 'And they were astonished out of measure, saying among themselves, Who then can be saved?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 27, 'And Jesus looking upon them saith, With men it is impossible, but not with God: for with God all things are possible.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 28, 'Then Peter began to say unto him, Lo, we have left all, and have followed thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 29, 'And Jesus answered and said, Verily I say unto you, There is no man that hath left house, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, for my sake, and the gospel''s,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 30, 'But he shall receive an hundredfold now in this time, houses, and brethren, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and lands, with persecutions; and in the world to come eternal life.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 31, 'But many that are first shall be last; and the last first.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 32, 'And they were in the way going up to Jerusalem; and Jesus went before them: and they were amazed; and as they followed, they were afraid. And he took again the twelve, and began to tell them what things should happen unto him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 33, 'Saying, Behold, we go up to Jerusalem; and the Son of man shall be delivered unto the chief priests, and unto the scribes; and they shall condemn him to death, and shall deliver him to the Gentiles:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 34, 'And they shall mock him, and shall scourge him, and shall spit upon him, and shall kill him: and the third day he shall rise again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 35, 'And James and John, the sons of Zebedee, come unto him, saying, Master, we would that thou shouldest do for us whatsoever we shall desire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 36, 'And he said unto them, What would ye that I should do for you?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 37, 'They said unto him, Grant unto us that we may sit, one on thy right hand, and the other on thy left hand, in thy glory.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 38, 'But Jesus said unto them, Ye know not what ye ask: can ye drink of the cup that I drink of? and be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 39, 'And they said unto him, We can. And Jesus said unto them, Ye shall indeed drink of the cup that I drink of; and with the baptism that I am baptized withal shall ye be baptized:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 40, 'But to sit on my right hand and on my left hand is not mine to give; but it shall be given to them for whom it is prepared.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 41, 'And when the ten heard it, they began to be much displeased with James and John.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 42, 'But Jesus called them to him, and saith unto them, Ye know that they which are accounted to rule over the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and their great ones exercise authority upon them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 43, 'But so shall it not be among you: but whosoever will be great among you, shall be your minister:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 44, 'And whosoever of you will be the chiefest, shall be servant of all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 45, 'For even the Son of man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister, and to give his life a ransom for many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 46, 'And they came to Jericho: and as he went out of Jericho with his disciples and a great number of people, blind Bartimaeus, the son of Timaeus, sat by the highway side begging.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 47, 'And when he heard that it was Jesus of Nazareth, he began to cry out, and say, Jesus, thou Son of David, have mercy on me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 48, 'And many charged him that he should hold his peace: but he cried the more a great deal, Thou Son of David, have mercy on me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 49, 'And Jesus stood still, and commanded him to be called. And they call the blind man, saying unto him, Be of good comfort, rise; he calleth thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 50, 'And he, casting away his garment, rose, and came to Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 51, 'And Jesus answered and said unto him, What wilt thou that I should do unto thee? The blind man said unto him, Lord, that I might receive my sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 10, 52, 'And Jesus said unto him, Go thy way; thy faith hath made thee whole. And immediately he received his sight, and followed Jesus in the way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 1, 'And when they came nigh to Jerusalem, unto Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount of Olives, he sendeth forth two of his disciples,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 2, 'And saith unto them, Go your way into the village over against you: and as soon as ye be entered into it, ye shall find a colt tied, whereon never man sat; loose him, and bring him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 3, 'And if any man say unto you, Why do ye this? say ye that the Lord hath need of him; and straightway he will send him hither.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 4, 'And they went their way, and found the colt tied by the door without in a place where two ways met; and they loose him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 5, 'And certain of them that stood there said unto them, What do ye, loosing the colt?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 6, 'And they said unto them even as Jesus had commanded: and they let them go.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 7, 'And they brought the colt to Jesus, and cast their garments on him; and he sat upon him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 8, 'And many spread their garments in the way: and others cut down branches off the trees, and strawed them in the way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 9, 'And they that went before, and they that followed, cried, saying, Hosanna; Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 10, 'Blessed be the kingdom of our father David, that cometh in the name of the Lord: Hosanna in the highest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 11, 'And Jesus entered into Jerusalem, and into the temple: and when he had looked round about upon all things, and now the eventide was come, he went out unto Bethany with the twelve.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 12, 'And on the morrow, when they were come from Bethany, he was hungry:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 13, 'And seeing a fig tree afar off having leaves, he came, if haply he might find any thing thereon: and when he came to it, he found nothing but leaves; for the time of figs was not yet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 14, 'And Jesus answered and said unto it, No man eat fruit of thee hereafter for ever. And his disciples heard it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 15, 'And they come to Jerusalem: and Jesus went into the temple, and began to cast out them that sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the moneychangers, and the seats of them that sold doves;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 16, 'And would not suffer that any man should carry any vessel through the temple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 17, 'And he taught, saying unto them, Is it not written, My house shall be called of all nations the house of prayer? but ye have made it a den of thieves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 18, 'And the scribes and chief priests heard it, and sought how they might destroy him: for they feared him, because all the people was astonished at his doctrine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 19, 'And when even was come, he went out of the city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 20, 'And in the morning, as they passed by, they saw the fig tree dried up from the roots.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 21, 'And Peter calling to remembrance saith unto him, Master, behold, the fig tree which thou cursedst is withered away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 22, 'And Jesus answering saith unto them, Have faith in God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 23, 'For verily I say unto you, That whosoever shall say unto this mountain, Be thou removed, and be thou cast into the sea; and shall not doubt in his heart, but shall believe that those things which he saith shall come to pass; he shall have whatsoever he saith.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 24, 'Therefore I say unto you, What things soever ye desire, when ye pray, believe that ye receive them, and ye shall have them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 25, 'And when ye stand praying, forgive, if ye have ought against any: that your Father also which is in heaven may forgive you your trespasses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 26, 'But if ye do not forgive, neither will your Father which is in heaven forgive your trespasses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 27, 'And they come again to Jerusalem: and as he was walking in the temple, there come to him the chief priests, and the scribes, and the elders,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 28, 'And say unto him, By what authority doest thou these things? and who gave thee this authority to do these things?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 29, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, I will also ask of you one question, and answer me, and I will tell you by what authority I do these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 30, 'The baptism of John, was it from heaven, or of men? answer me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 31, 'And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say, Why then did ye not believe him?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 32, 'But if we shall say, Of men; they feared the people: for all men counted John, that he was a prophet indeed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 11, 33, 'And they answered and said unto Jesus, We cannot tell. And Jesus answering saith unto them, Neither do I tell you by what authority I do these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 1, 'And he began to speak unto them by parables. A certain man planted a vineyard, and set an hedge about it, and digged a place for the winefat, and built a tower, and let it out to husbandmen, and went into a far country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 2, 'And at the season he sent to the husbandmen a servant, that he might receive from the husbandmen of the fruit of the vineyard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 3, 'And they caught him, and beat him, and sent him away empty.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 4, 'And again he sent unto them another servant; and at him they cast stones, and wounded him in the head, and sent him away shamefully handled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 5, 'And again he sent another; and him they killed, and many others; beating some, and killing some.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 6, 'Having yet therefore one son, his wellbeloved, he sent him also last unto them, saying, They will reverence my son.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 7, 'But those husbandmen said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and the inheritance shall be ours.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 8, 'And they took him, and killed him, and cast him out of the vineyard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 9, 'What shall therefore the lord of the vineyard do? he will come and destroy the husbandmen, and will give the vineyard unto others.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 10, 'And have ye not read this scripture; The stone which the builders rejected is become the head of the corner:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 11, 'This was the Lord''s doing, and it is marvellous in our eyes?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 12, 'And they sought to lay hold on him, but feared the people: for they knew that he had spoken the parable against them: and they left him, and went their way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 13, 'And they send unto him certain of the Pharisees and of the Herodians, to catch him in his words.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 14, 'And when they were come, they say unto him, Master, we know that thou art true, and carest for no man: for thou regardest not the person of men, but teachest the way of God in truth: Is it lawful to give tribute to Caesar, or not?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 15, 'Shall we give, or shall we not give? But he, knowing their hypocrisy, said unto them, Why tempt ye me? bring me a penny, that I may see it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 16, 'And they brought it. And he saith unto them, Whose is this image and superscription? And they said unto him, Caesar''s.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 17, 'And Jesus answering said unto them, Render to Caesar the things that are Caesar''s, and to God the things that are God''s. And they marvelled at him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 18, 'Then come unto him the Sadducees, which say there is no resurrection; and they asked him, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 19, 'Master, Moses wrote unto us, If a man''s brother die, and leave his wife behind him, and leave no children, that his brother should take his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 20, 'Now there were seven brethren: and the first took a wife, and dying left no seed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 21, 'And the second took her, and died, neither left he any seed: and the third likewise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 22, 'And the seven had her, and left no seed: last of all the woman died also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 23, 'In the resurrection therefore, when they shall rise, whose wife shall she be of them? for the seven had her to wife.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 24, 'And Jesus answering said unto them, Do ye not therefore err, because ye know not the scriptures, neither the power of God?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 25, 'For when they shall rise from the dead, they neither marry, nor are given in marriage; but are as the angels which are in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 26, 'And as touching the dead, that they rise: have ye not read in the book of Moses, how in the bush God spake unto him, saying, I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 27, 'He is not the God of the dead, but the God of the living: ye therefore do greatly err.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 28, 'And one of the scribes came, and having heard them reasoning together, and perceiving that he had answered them well, asked him, Which is the first commandment of all?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 29, 'And Jesus answered him, The first of all the commandments is, Hear, O Israel; The Lord our God is one Lord:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 30, 'And thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind, and with all thy strength: this is the first commandment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 31, 'And the second is like, namely this, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself. There is none other commandment greater than these.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 32, 'And the scribe said unto him, Well, Master, thou hast said the truth: for there is one God; and there is none other but he:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 33, 'And to love him with all the heart, and with all the understanding, and with all the soul, and with all the strength, and to love his neighbour as himself, is more than all whole burnt offerings and sacrifices.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 34, 'And when Jesus saw that he answered discreetly, he said unto him, Thou art not far from the kingdom of God. And no man after that durst ask him any question.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 35, 'And Jesus answered and said, while he taught in the temple, How say the scribes that Christ is the Son of David?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 36, 'For David himself said by the Holy Ghost, The LORD said to my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 37, 'David therefore himself calleth him Lord; and whence is he then his son? And the common people heard him gladly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 38, 'And he said unto them in his doctrine, Beware of the scribes, which love to go in long clothing, and love salutations in the marketplaces,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 39, 'And the chief seats in the synagogues, and the uppermost rooms at feasts:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 40, 'Which devour widows'' houses, and for a pretence make long prayers: these shall receive greater damnation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 41, 'And Jesus sat over against the treasury, and beheld how the people cast money into the treasury: and many that were rich cast in much.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 42, 'And there came a certain poor widow, and she threw in two mites, which make a farthing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 43, 'And he called unto him his disciples, and saith unto them, Verily I say unto you, That this poor widow hath cast more in, than all they which have cast into the treasury:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 12, 44, 'For all they did cast in of their abundance; but she of her want did cast in all that she had, even all her living.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 1, 'And as he went out of the temple, one of his disciples saith unto him, Master, see what manner of stones and what buildings are here!'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 2, 'And Jesus answering said unto him, Seest thou these great buildings? there shall not be left one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 3, 'And as he sat upon the mount of Olives over against the temple, Peter and James and John and Andrew asked him privately,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 4, 'Tell us, when shall these things be? and what shall be the sign when all these things shall be fulfilled?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 5, 'And Jesus answering them began to say, Take heed lest any man deceive you:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 6, 'For many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and shall deceive many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 7, 'And when ye shall hear of wars and rumours of wars, be ye not troubled: for such things must needs be; but the end shall not be yet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 8, 'For nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be earthquakes in divers places, and there shall be famines and troubles: these are the beginnings of sorrows.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 9, 'But take heed to yourselves: for they shall deliver you up to councils; and in the synagogues ye shall be beaten: and ye shall be brought before rulers and kings for my sake, for a testimony against them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 10, 'And the gospel must first be published among all nations.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 11, 'But when they shall lead you, and deliver you up, take no thought beforehand what ye shall speak, neither do ye premeditate: but whatsoever shall be given you in that hour, that speak ye: for it is not ye that speak, but the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 12, 'Now the brother shall betray the brother to death, and the father the son; and children shall rise up against their parents, and shall cause them to be put to death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 13, 'And ye shall be hated of all men for my name''s sake: but he that shall endure unto the end, the same shall be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 14, 'But when ye shall see the abomination of desolation, spoken of by Daniel the prophet, standing where it ought not, (let him that readeth understand,) then let them that be in Judaea flee to the mountains:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 15, 'And let him that is on the housetop not go down into the house, neither enter therein, to take any thing out of his house:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 16, 'And let him that is in the field not turn back again for to take up his garment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 17, 'But woe to them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days!'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 18, 'And pray ye that your flight be not in the winter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 19, 'For in those days shall be affliction, such as was not from the beginning of the creation which God created unto this time, neither shall be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 20, 'And except that the Lord had shortened those days, no flesh should be saved: but for the elect''s sake, whom he hath chosen, he hath shortened the days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 21, 'And then if any man shall say to you, Lo, here is Christ; or, lo, he is there; believe him not:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 22, 'For false Christs and false prophets shall rise, and shall shew signs and wonders, to seduce, if it were possible, even the elect.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 23, 'But take ye heed: behold, I have foretold you all things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 24, 'But in those days, after that tribulation, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give her light,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 25, 'And the stars of heaven shall fall, and the powers that are in heaven shall be shaken.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 26, 'And then shall they see the Son of man coming in the clouds with great power and glory.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 27, 'And then shall he send his angels, and shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from the uttermost part of the earth to the uttermost part of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 28, 'Now learn a parable of the fig tree; When her branch is yet tender, and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is near:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 29, 'So ye in like manner, when ye shall see these things come to pass, know that it is nigh, even at the doors.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 30, 'Verily I say unto you, that this generation shall not pass, till all these things be done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 31, 'Heaven and earth shall pass away: but my words shall not pass away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 32, 'But of that day and that hour knoweth no man, no, not the angels which are in heaven, neither the Son, but the Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 33, 'Take ye heed, watch and pray: for ye know not when the time is.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 34, 'For the Son of man is as a man taking a far journey, who left his house, and gave authority to his servants, and to every man his work, and commanded the porter to watch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 35, 'Watch ye therefore: for ye know not when the master of the house cometh, at even, or at midnight, or at the cockcrowing, or in the morning:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 36, 'Lest coming suddenly he find you sleeping.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 13, 37, 'And what I say unto you I say unto all, Watch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 1, 'After two days was the feast of the passover, and of unleavened bread: and the chief priests and the scribes sought how they might take him by craft, and put him to death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 2, 'But they said, Not on the feast day, lest there be an uproar of the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 3, 'And being in Bethany in the house of Simon the leper, as he sat at meat, there came a woman having an alabaster box of ointment of spikenard very precious; and she brake the box, and poured it on his head.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 4, 'And there were some that had indignation within themselves, and said, Why was this waste of the ointment made?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 5, 'For it might have been sold for more than three hundred pence, and have been given to the poor. And they murmured against her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 6, 'And Jesus said, Let her alone; why trouble ye her? she hath wrought a good work on me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 7, 'For ye have the poor with you always, and whensoever ye will ye may do them good: but me ye have not always.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 8, 'She hath done what she could: she is come aforehand to anoint my body to the burying.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 9, 'Verily I say unto you, Wheresoever this gospel shall be preached throughout the whole world, this also that she hath done shall be spoken of for a memorial of her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 10, 'And Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve, went unto the chief priests, to betray him unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 11, 'And when they heard it, they were glad, and promised to give him money. And he sought how he might conveniently betray him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 12, 'And the first day of unleavened bread, when they killed the passover, his disciples said unto him, Where wilt thou that we go and prepare that thou mayest eat the passover?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 13, 'And he sendeth forth two of his disciples, and saith unto them, Go ye into the city, and there shall meet you a man bearing a pitcher of water: follow him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 14, 'And wheresoever he shall go in, say ye to the goodman of the house, The Master saith, Where is the guestchamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 15, 'And he will shew you a large upper room furnished and prepared: there make ready for us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 16, 'And his disciples went forth, and came into the city, and found as he had said unto them: and they made ready the passover.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 17, 'And in the evening he cometh with the twelve.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 18, 'And as they sat and did eat, Jesus said, Verily I say unto you, One of you which eateth with me shall betray me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 19, 'And they began to be sorrowful, and to say unto him one by one, Is it I? and another said, Is it I?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 20, 'And he answered and said unto them, It is one of the twelve, that dippeth with me in the dish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 21, 'The Son of man indeed goeth, as it is written of him: but woe to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! good were it for that man if he had never been born.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 22, 'And as they did eat, Jesus took bread, and blessed, and brake it, and gave to them, and said, Take, eat: this is my body.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 23, 'And he took the cup, and when he had given thanks, he gave it to them: and they all drank of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 24, 'And he said unto them, This is my blood of the new testament, which is shed for many.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 25, 'Verily I say unto you, I will drink no more of the fruit of the vine, until that day that I drink it new in the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 26, 'And when they had sung an hymn, they went out into the mount of Olives.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 27, 'And Jesus saith unto them, All ye shall be offended because of me this night: for it is written, I will smite the shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 28, 'But after that I am risen, I will go before you into Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 29, 'But Peter said unto him, Although all shall be offended, yet will not I.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 30, 'And Jesus saith unto him, Verily I say unto thee, That this day, even in this night, before the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 31, 'But he spake the more vehemently, If I should die with thee, I will not deny thee in any wise. Likewise also said they all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 32, 'And they came to a place which was named Gethsemane: and he saith to his disciples, Sit ye here, while I shall pray.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 33, 'And he taketh with him Peter and James and John, and began to be sore amazed, and to be very heavy;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 34, 'And saith unto them, My soul is exceeding sorrowful unto death: tarry ye here, and watch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 35, 'And he went forward a little, and fell on the ground, and prayed that, if it were possible, the hour might pass from him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 36, 'And he said, Abba, Father, all things are possible unto thee; take away this cup from me: nevertheless not what I will, but what thou wilt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 37, 'And he cometh, and findeth them sleeping, and saith unto Peter, Simon, sleepest thou? couldest not thou watch one hour?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 38, 'Watch ye and pray, lest ye enter into temptation. The spirit truly is ready, but the flesh is weak.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 39, 'And again he went away, and prayed, and spake the same words.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 40, 'And when he returned, he found them asleep again, (for their eyes were heavy,) neither wist they what to answer him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 41, 'And he cometh the third time, and saith unto them, Sleep on now, and take your rest: it is enough, the hour is come; behold, the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 42, 'Rise up, let us go; lo, he that betrayeth me is at hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 43, 'And immediately, while he yet spake, cometh Judas, one of the twelve, and with him a great multitude with swords and staves, from the chief priests and the scribes and the elders.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 44, 'And he that betrayed him had given them a token, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he; take him, and lead him away safely.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 45, 'And as soon as he was come, he goeth straightway to him, and saith, Master, master; and kissed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 46, 'And they laid their hands on him, and took him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 47, 'And one of them that stood by drew a sword, and smote a servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 48, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, Are ye come out, as against a thief, with swords and with staves to take me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 49, 'I was daily with you in the temple teaching, and ye took me not: but the scriptures must be fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 50, 'And they all forsook him, and fled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 51, 'And there followed him a certain young man, having a linen cloth cast about his naked body; and the young men laid hold on him:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 52, 'And he left the linen cloth, and fled from them naked.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 53, 'And they led Jesus away to the high priest: and with him were assembled all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 54, 'And Peter followed him afar off, even into the palace of the high priest: and he sat with the servants, and warmed himself at the fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 55, 'And the chief priests and all the council sought for witness against Jesus to put him to death; and found none.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 56, 'For many bare false witness against him, but their witness agreed not together.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 57, 'And there arose certain, and bare false witness against him, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 58, 'We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 59, 'But neither so did their witness agree together.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 60, 'And the high priest stood up in the midst, and asked Jesus, saying, Answerest thou nothing? what is it which these witness against thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 61, 'But he held his peace, and answered nothing. Again the high priest asked him, and said unto him, Art thou the Christ, the Son of the Blessed?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 62, 'And Jesus said, I am: and ye shall see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 63, 'Then the high priest rent his clothes, and saith, What need we any further witnesses?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 64, 'Ye have heard the blasphemy: what think ye? And they all condemned him to be guilty of death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 65, 'And some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to buffet him, and to say unto him, Prophesy: and the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 66, 'And as Peter was beneath in the palace, there cometh one of the maids of the high priest:'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 67, 'And when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked upon him, and said, And thou also wast with Jesus of Nazareth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 68, 'But he denied, saying, I know not, neither understand I what thou sayest. And he went out into the porch; and the cock crew.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 69, 'And a maid saw him again, and began to say to them that stood by, This is one of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 70, 'And he denied it again. And a little after, they that stood by said again to Peter, Surely thou art one of them: for thou art a Galilaean, and thy speech agreeth thereto.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 71, 'But he began to curse and to swear, saying, I know not this man of whom ye speak.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 14, 72, 'And the second time the cock crew. And Peter called to mind the word that Jesus said unto him, Before the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice. And when he thought thereon, he wept.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 1, 'And straightway in the morning the chief priests held a consultation with the elders and scribes and the whole council, and bound Jesus, and carried him away, and delivered him to Pilate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 2, 'And Pilate asked him, Art thou the King of the Jews? And he answering said unto him, Thou sayest it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 3, 'And the chief priests accused him of many things: but he answered nothing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 4, 'And Pilate asked him again, saying, Answerest thou nothing? behold how many things they witness against thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 5, 'But Jesus yet answered nothing; so that Pilate marvelled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 6, 'Now at that feast he released unto them one prisoner, whomsoever they desired.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 7, 'And there was one named Barabbas, which lay bound with them that had made insurrection with him, who had committed murder in the insurrection.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 8, 'And the multitude crying aloud began to desire him to do as he had ever done unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 9, 'But Pilate answered them, saying, Will ye that I release unto you the King of the Jews?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 10, 'For he knew that the chief priests had delivered him for envy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 11, 'But the chief priests moved the people, that he should rather release Barabbas unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 12, 'And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will ye then that I shall do unto him whom ye call the King of the Jews?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 13, 'And they cried out again, Crucify him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 14, 'Then Pilate said unto them, Why, what evil hath he done? And they cried out the more exceedingly, Crucify him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 15, 'And so Pilate, willing to content the people, released Barabbas unto them, and delivered Jesus, when he had scourged him, to be crucified.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 16, 'And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium; and they call together the whole band.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 17, 'And they clothed him with purple, and platted a crown of thorns, and put it about his head,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 18, 'And began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jews!'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 19, 'And they smote him on the head with a reed, and did spit upon him, and bowing their knees worshipped him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 20, 'And when they had mocked him, they took off the purple from him, and put his own clothes on him, and led him out to crucify him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 21, 'And they compel one Simon a Cyrenian, who passed by, coming out of the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 22, 'And they bring him unto the place Golgotha, which is, being interpreted, The place of a skull.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 23, 'And they gave him to drink wine mingled with myrrh: but he received it not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 24, 'And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots upon them, what every man should take.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 25, 'And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 26, 'And the superscription of his accusation was written over, THE KING OF THE JEWS.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 27, 'And with him they crucify two thieves; the one on his right hand, and the other on his left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 28, 'And the scripture was fulfilled, which saith, And he was numbered with the transgressors.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 29, 'And they that passed by railed on him, wagging their heads, and saying, Ah, thou that destroyest the temple, and buildest it in three days,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 30, 'Save thyself, and come down from the cross.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 31, 'Likewise also the chief priests mocking said among themselves with the scribes, He saved others; himself he cannot save.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 32, 'Let Christ the King of Israel descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe. And they that were crucified with him reviled him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 33, 'And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 34, 'And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, saying, Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani? which is, being interpreted, My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 35, 'And some of them that stood by, when they heard it, said, Behold, he calleth Elias.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 36, 'And one ran and filled a spunge full of vinegar, and put it on a reed, and gave him to drink, saying, Let alone; let us see whether Elias will come to take him down.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 37, 'And Jesus cried with a loud voice, and gave up the ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 38, 'And the veil of the temple was rent in twain from the top to the bottom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 39, 'And when the centurion, which stood over against him, saw that he so cried out, and gave up the ghost, he said, Truly this man was the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 40, 'There were also women looking on afar off: among whom was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the less and of Joses, and Salome;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 41, '(Who also, when he was in Galilee, followed him, and ministered unto him;) and many other women which came up with him unto Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 42, 'And now when the even was come, because it was the preparation, that is, the day before the sabbath,'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 43, 'Joseph of Arimathaea, an honourable counsellor, which also waited for the kingdom of God, came, and went in boldly unto Pilate, and craved the body of Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 44, 'And Pilate marvelled if he were already dead: and calling unto him the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 45, 'And when he knew it of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 46, 'And he bought fine linen, and took him down, and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a sepulchre which was hewn out of a rock, and rolled a stone unto the door of the sepulchre.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 15, 47, 'And Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses beheld where he was laid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 1, 'And when the sabbath was past, Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James, and Salome, had bought sweet spices, that they might come and anoint him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 2, 'And very early in the morning the first day of the week, they came unto the sepulchre at the rising of the sun.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 3, 'And they said among themselves, Who shall roll us away the stone from the door of the sepulchre?'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 4, 'And when they looked, they saw that the stone was rolled away: for it was very great.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 5, 'And entering into the sepulchre, they saw a young man sitting on the right side, clothed in a long white garment; and they were affrighted.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 6, 'And he saith unto them, Be not affrighted: Ye seek Jesus of Nazareth, which was crucified: he is risen; he is not here: behold the place where they laid him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 7, 'But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter that he goeth before you into Galilee: there shall ye see him, as he said unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 8, 'And they went out quickly, and fled from the sepulchre; for they trembled and were amazed: neither said they any thing to any man; for they were afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 9, 'Now when Jesus was risen early the first day of the week, he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven devils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 10, 'And she went and told them that had been with him, as they mourned and wept.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 11, 'And they, when they had heard that he was alive, and had been seen of her, believed not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 12, 'After that he appeared in another form unto two of them, as they walked, and went into the country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 13, 'And they went and told it unto the residue: neither believed they them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 14, 'Afterward he appeared unto the eleven as they sat at meat, and upbraided them with their unbelief and hardness of heart, because they believed not them which had seen him after he was risen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 15, 'And he said unto them, Go ye into all the world, and preach the gospel to every creature.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 16, 'He that believeth and is baptized shall be saved; but he that believeth not shall be damned.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 17, 'And these signs shall follow them that believe; In my name shall they cast out devils; they shall speak with new tongues;'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 18, 'They shall take up serpents; and if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them; they shall lay hands on the sick, and they shall recover.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 19, 'So then after the Lord had spoken unto them, he was received up into heaven, and sat on the right hand of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Mark', 41, 16, 20, 'And they went forth, and preached every where, the Lord working with them, and confirming the word with signs following. Amen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 1, 'Forasmuch as many have taken in hand to set forth in order a declaration of those things which are most surely believed among us,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 2, 'Even as they delivered them unto us, which from the beginning were eyewitnesses, and ministers of the word;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 3, 'It seemed good to me also, having had perfect understanding of all things from the very first, to write unto thee in order, most excellent Theophilus,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 4, 'That thou mightest know the certainty of those things, wherein thou hast been instructed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 5, 'There was in the days of Herod, the king of Judaea, a certain priest named Zacharias, of the course of Abia: and his wife was of the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elisabeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 6, 'And they were both righteous before God, walking in all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord blameless.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 7, 'And they had no child, because that Elisabeth was barren, and they both were now well stricken in years.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 8, 'And it came to pass, that while he executed the priest''s office before God in the order of his course,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 9, 'According to the custom of the priest''s office, his lot was to burn incense when he went into the temple of the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 10, 'And the whole multitude of the people were praying without at the time of incense.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 11, 'And there appeared unto him an angel of the Lord standing on the right side of the altar of incense.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 12, 'And when Zacharias saw him, he was troubled, and fear fell upon him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 13, 'But the angel said unto him, Fear not, Zacharias: for thy prayer is heard; and thy wife Elisabeth shall bear thee a son, and thou shalt call his name John.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 14, 'And thou shalt have joy and gladness; and many shall rejoice at his birth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 15, 'For he shall be great in the sight of the Lord, and shall drink neither wine nor strong drink; and he shall be filled with the Holy Ghost, even from his mother''s womb.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 16, 'And many of the children of Israel shall he turn to the Lord their God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 17, 'And he shall go before him in the spirit and power of Elias, to turn the hearts of the fathers to the children, and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just; to make ready a people prepared for the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 18, 'And Zacharias said unto the angel, Whereby shall I know this? for I am an old man, and my wife well stricken in years.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 19, 'And the angel answering said unto him, I am Gabriel, that stand in the presence of God; and am sent to speak unto thee, and to shew thee these glad tidings.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 20, 'And, behold, thou shalt be dumb, and not able to speak, until the day that these things shall be performed, because thou believest not my words, which shall be fulfilled in their season.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 21, 'And the people waited for Zacharias, and marvelled that he tarried so long in the temple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 22, 'And when he came out, he could not speak unto them: and they perceived that he had seen a vision in the temple: for he beckoned unto them, and remained speechless.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 23, 'And it came to pass, that, as soon as the days of his ministration were accomplished, he departed to his own house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 24, 'And after those days his wife Elisabeth conceived, and hid herself five months, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 25, 'Thus hath the Lord dealt with me in the days wherein he looked on me, to take away my reproach among men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 26, 'And in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God unto a city of Galilee, named Nazareth,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 27, 'To a virgin espoused to a man whose name was Joseph, of the house of David; and the virgin''s name was Mary.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 28, 'And the angel came in unto her, and said, Hail, thou that art highly favoured, the Lord is with thee: blessed art thou among women.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 29, 'And when she saw him, she was troubled at his saying, and cast in her mind what manner of salutation this should be.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 30, 'And the angel said unto her, Fear not, Mary: for thou hast found favour with God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 31, 'And, behold, thou shalt conceive in thy womb, and bring forth a son, and shalt call his name JESUS.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 32, 'He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Highest: and the Lord God shall give unto him the throne of his father David:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 33, 'And he shall reign over the house of Jacob for ever; and of his kingdom there shall be no end.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 34, 'Then said Mary unto the angel, How shall this be, seeing I know not a man?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 35, 'And the angel answered and said unto her, The Holy Ghost shall come upon thee, and the power of the Highest shall overshadow thee: therefore also that holy thing which shall be born of thee shall be called the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 36, 'And, behold, thy cousin Elisabeth, she hath also conceived a son in her old age: and this is the sixth month with her, who was called barren.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 37, 'For with God nothing shall be impossible.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 38, 'And Mary said, Behold the handmaid of the Lord; be it unto me according to thy word. And the angel departed from her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 39, 'And Mary arose in those days, and went into the hill country with haste, into a city of Juda;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 40, 'And entered into the house of Zacharias, and saluted Elisabeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 41, 'And it came to pass, that, when Elisabeth heard the salutation of Mary, the babe leaped in her womb; and Elisabeth was filled with the Holy Ghost:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 42, 'And she spake out with a loud voice, and said, Blessed art thou among women, and blessed is the fruit of thy womb.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 43, 'And whence is this to me, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 44, 'For, lo, as soon as the voice of thy salutation sounded in mine ears, the babe leaped in my womb for joy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 45, 'And blessed is she that believed: for there shall be a performance of those things which were told her from the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 46, 'And Mary said, My soul doth magnify the Lord,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 47, 'And my spirit hath rejoiced in God my Saviour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 48, 'For he hath regarded the low estate of his handmaiden: for, behold, from henceforth all generations shall call me blessed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 49, 'For he that is mighty hath done to me great things; and holy is his name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 50, 'And his mercy is on them that fear him from generation to generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 51, 'He hath shewed strength with his arm; he hath scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 52, 'He hath put down the mighty from their seats, and exalted them of low degree.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 53, 'He hath filled the hungry with good things; and the rich he hath sent empty away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 54, 'He hath holpen his servant Israel, in remembrance of his mercy;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 55, 'As he spake to our fathers, to Abraham, and to his seed for ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 56, 'And Mary abode with her about three months, and returned to her own house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 57, 'Now Elisabeth''s full time came that she should be delivered; and she brought forth a son.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 58, 'And her neighbours and her cousins heard how the Lord had shewed great mercy upon her; and they rejoiced with her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 59, 'And it came to pass, that on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child; and they called him Zacharias, after the name of his father.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 60, 'And his mother answered and said, Not so; but he shall be called John.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 61, 'And they said unto her, There is none of thy kindred that is called by this name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 62, 'And they made signs to his father, how he would have him called.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 63, 'And he asked for a writing table, and wrote, saying, His name is John. And they marvelled all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 64, 'And his mouth was opened immediately, and his tongue loosed, and he spake, and praised God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 65, 'And fear came on all that dwelt round about them: and all these sayings were noised abroad throughout all the hill country of Judaea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 66, 'And all they that heard them laid them up in their hearts, saying, What manner of child shall this be! And the hand of the Lord was with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 67, 'And his father Zacharias was filled with the Holy Ghost, and prophesied, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 68, 'Blessed be the Lord God of Israel; for he hath visited and redeemed his people,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 69, 'And hath raised up an horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 70, 'As he spake by the mouth of his holy prophets, which have been since the world began:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 71, 'That we should be saved from our enemies, and from the hand of all that hate us;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 72, 'To perform the mercy promised to our fathers, and to remember his holy covenant;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 73, 'The oath which he sware to our father Abraham,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 74, 'That he would grant unto us, that we being delivered out of the hand of our enemies might serve him without fear,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 75, 'In holiness and righteousness before him, all the days of our life.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 76, 'And thou, child, shalt be called the prophet of the Highest: for thou shalt go before the face of the Lord to prepare his ways;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 77, 'To give knowledge of salvation unto his people by the remission of their sins,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 78, 'Through the tender mercy of our God; whereby the dayspring from on high hath visited us,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 79, 'To give light to them that sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, to guide our feet into the way of peace.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 1, 80, 'And the child grew, and waxed strong in spirit, and was in the deserts till the day of his shewing unto Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 1, 'And it came to pass in those days, that there went out a decree from Caesar Augustus, that all the world should be taxed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 2, '(And this taxing was first made when Cyrenius was governor of Syria.)'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 3, 'And all went to be taxed, every one into his own city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 4, 'And Joseph also went up from Galilee, out of the city of Nazareth, into Judaea, unto the city of David, which is called Bethlehem; (because he was of the house and lineage of David:)'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 5, 'To be taxed with Mary his espoused wife, being great with child.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 6, 'And so it was, that, while they were there, the days were accomplished that she should be delivered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 7, 'And she brought forth her firstborn son, and wrapped him in swaddling clothes, and laid him in a manger; because there was no room for them in the inn.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 8, 'And there were in the same country shepherds abiding in the field, keeping watch over their flock by night.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 9, 'And, lo, the angel of the Lord came upon them, and the glory of the Lord shone round about them: and they were sore afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 10, 'And the angel said unto them, Fear not: for, behold, I bring you good tidings of great joy, which shall be to all people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 11, 'For unto you is born this day in the city of David a Saviour, which is Christ the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 12, 'And this shall be a sign unto you; Ye shall find the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes, lying in a manger.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 13, 'And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host praising God, and saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 14, 'Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace, good will toward men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 15, 'And it came to pass, as the angels were gone away from them into heaven, the shepherds said one to another, Let us now go even unto Bethlehem, and see this thing which is come to pass, which the Lord hath made known unto us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 16, 'And they came with haste, and found Mary, and Joseph, and the babe lying in a manger.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 17, 'And when they had seen it, they made known abroad the saying which was told them concerning this child.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 18, 'And all they that heard it wondered at those things which were told them by the shepherds.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 19, 'But Mary kept all these things, and pondered them in her heart.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 20, 'And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things that they had heard and seen, as it was told unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 21, 'And when eight days were accomplished for the circumcising of the child, his name was called JESUS, which was so named of the angel before he was conceived in the womb.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 22, 'And when the days of her purification according to the law of Moses were accomplished, they brought him to Jerusalem, to present him to the Lord;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 23, '(As it is written in the law of the Lord, Every male that openeth the womb shall be called holy to the Lord;)'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 24, 'And to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, A pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 25, 'And, behold, there was a man in Jerusalem, whose name was Simeon; and the same man was just and devout, waiting for the consolation of Israel: and the Holy Ghost was upon him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 26, 'And it was revealed unto him by the Holy Ghost, that he should not see death, before he had seen the Lord''s Christ.')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 27, 'And he came by the Spirit into the temple: and when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him after the custom of the law,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 28, 'Then took he him up in his arms, and blessed God, and said,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 29, 'Lord, now lettest thou thy servant depart in peace, according to thy word:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 30, 'For mine eyes have seen thy salvation,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 31, 'Which thou hast prepared before the face of all people;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 32, 'A light to lighten the Gentiles, and the glory of thy people Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 33, 'And Joseph and his mother marvelled at those things which were spoken of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 34, 'And Simeon blessed them, and said unto Mary his mother, Behold, this child is set for the fall and rising again of many in Israel; and for a sign which shall be spoken against;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 35, '(Yea, a sword shall pierce through thy own soul also,) that the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 36, 'And there was one Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Aser: she was of a great age, and had lived with an husband seven years from her virginity;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 37, 'And she was a widow of about fourscore and four years, which departed not from the temple, but served God with fastings and prayers night and day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 38, 'And she coming in that instant gave thanks likewise unto the Lord, and spake of him to all them that looked for redemption in Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 39, 'And when they had performed all things according to the law of the Lord, they returned into Galilee, to their own city Nazareth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 40, 'And the child grew, and waxed strong in spirit, filled with wisdom: and the grace of God was upon him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 41, 'Now his parents went to Jerusalem every year at the feast of the passover.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 42, 'And when he was twelve years old, they went up to Jerusalem after the custom of the feast.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 43, 'And when they had fulfilled the days, as they returned, the child Jesus tarried behind in Jerusalem; and Joseph and his mother knew not of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 44, 'But they, supposing him to have been in the company, went a day''s journey; and they sought him among their kinsfolk and acquaintance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 45, 'And when they found him not, they turned back again to Jerusalem, seeking him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 46, 'And it came to pass, that after three days they found him in the temple, sitting in the midst of the doctors, both hearing them, and asking them questions.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 47, 'And all that heard him were astonished at his understanding and answers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 48, 'And when they saw him, they were amazed: and his mother said unto him, Son, why hast thou thus dealt with us? behold, thy father and I have sought thee sorrowing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 49, 'And he said unto them, How is it that ye sought me? wist ye not that I must be about my Father''s business?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 50, 'And they understood not the saying which he spake unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 51, 'And he went down with them, and came to Nazareth, and was subject unto them: but his mother kept all these sayings in her heart.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 2, 52, 'And Jesus increased in wisdom and stature, and in favour with God and man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 1, 'Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, Pontius Pilate being governor of Judaea, and Herod being tetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip tetrarch of Ituraea and of the region of Trachonitis, and Lysanias the tetrarch of Abilene,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 2, 'Annas and Caiaphas being the high priests, the word of God came unto John the son of Zacharias in the wilderness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 3, 'And he came into all the country about Jordan, preaching the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 4, 'As it is written in the book of the words of Esaias the prophet, saying, The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 5, 'Every valley shall be filled, and every mountain and hill shall be brought low; and the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough ways shall be made smooth;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 6, 'And all flesh shall see the salvation of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 7, 'Then said he to the multitude that came forth to be baptized of him, O generation of vipers, who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 8, 'Bring forth therefore fruits worthy of repentance, and begin not to say within yourselves, We have Abraham to our father: for I say unto you, That God is able of these stones to raise up children unto Abraham.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 9, 'And now also the axe is laid unto the root of the trees: every tree therefore which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 10, 'And the people asked him, saying, What shall we do then?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 11, 'He answereth and saith unto them, He that hath two coats, let him impart to him that hath none; and he that hath meat, let him do likewise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 12, 'Then came also publicans to be baptized, and said unto him, Master, what shall we do?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 13, 'And he said unto them, Exact no more than that which is appointed you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 14, 'And the soldiers likewise demanded of him, saying, And what shall we do? And he said unto them, Do violence to no man, neither accuse any falsely; and be content with your wages.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 15, 'And as the people were in expectation, and all men mused in their hearts of John, whether he were the Christ, or not;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 16, 'John answered, saying unto them all, I indeed baptize you with water; but one mightier than I cometh, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to unloose: he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost and with fire:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 17, 'Whose fan is in his hand, and he will throughly purge his floor, and will gather the wheat into his garner; but the chaff he will burn with fire unquenchable.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 18, 'And many other things in his exhortation preached he unto the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 19, 'But Herod the tetrarch, being reproved by him for Herodias his brother Philip''s wife, and for all the evils which Herod had done,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 20, 'Added yet this above all, that he shut up John in prison.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 21, 'Now when all the people were baptized, it came to pass, that Jesus also being baptized, and praying, the heaven was opened,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 22, 'And the Holy Ghost descended in a bodily shape like a dove upon him, and a voice came from heaven, which said, Thou art my beloved Son; in thee I am well pleased.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 23, 'And Jesus himself began to be about thirty years of age, being (as was supposed) the son of Joseph, which was the son of Heli,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 24, 'Which was the son of Matthat, which was the son of Levi, which was the son of Melchi, which was the son of Janna, which was the son of Joseph,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 25, 'Which was the son of Mattathias, which was the son of Amos, which was the son of Naum, which was the son of Esli, which was the son of Nagge,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 26, 'Which was the son of Maath, which was the son of Mattathias, which was the son of Semei, which was the son of Joseph, which was the son of Juda,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 27, 'Which was the son of Joanna, which was the son of Rhesa, which was the son of Zorobabel, which was the son of Salathiel, which was the son of Neri,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 28, 'Which was the son of Melchi, which was the son of Addi, which was the son of Cosam, which was the son of Elmodam, which was the son of Er,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 29, 'Which was the son of Jose, which was the son of Eliezer, which was the son of Jorim, which was the son of Matthat, which was the son of Levi,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 30, 'Which was the son of Simeon, which was the son of Juda, which was the son of Joseph, which was the son of Jonan, which was the son of Eliakim,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 31, 'Which was the son of Melea, which was the son of Menan, which was the son of Mattatha, which was the son of Nathan, which was the son of David,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 32, 'Which was the son of Jesse, which was the son of Obed, which was the son of Booz, which was the son of Salmon, which was the son of Naasson,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 33, 'Which was the son of Aminadab, which was the son of Aram, which was the son of Esrom, which was the son of Phares, which was the son of Juda,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 34, 'Which was the son of Jacob, which was the son of Isaac, which was the son of Abraham, which was the son of Thara, which was the son of Nachor,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 35, 'Which was the son of Saruch, which was the son of Ragau, which was the son of Phalec, which was the son of Heber, which was the son of Sala,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 36, 'Which was the son of Cainan, which was the son of Arphaxad, which was the son of Sem, which was the son of Noe, which was the son of Lamech,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 37, 'Which was the son of Mathusala, which was the son of Enoch, which was the son of Jared, which was the son of Maleleel, which was the son of Cainan,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 3, 38, 'Which was the son of Enos, which was the son of Seth, which was the son of Adam, which was the son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 1, 'And Jesus being full of the Holy Ghost returned from Jordan, and was led by the Spirit into the wilderness,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 2, 'Being forty days tempted of the devil. And in those days he did eat nothing: and when they were ended, he afterward hungered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 3, 'And the devil said unto him, If thou be the Son of God, command this stone that it be made bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 4, 'And Jesus answered him, saying, It is written, That man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 5, 'And the devil, taking him up into an high mountain, shewed unto him all the kingdoms of the world in a moment of time.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 6, 'And the devil said unto him, All this power will I give thee, and the glory of them: for that is delivered unto me; and to whomsoever I will I give it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 7, 'If thou therefore wilt worship me, all shall be thine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 8, 'And Jesus answered and said unto him, Get thee behind me, Satan: for it is written, Thou shalt worship the Lord thy God, and him only shalt thou serve.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 9, 'And he brought him to Jerusalem, and set him on a pinnacle of the temple, and said unto him, If thou be the Son of God, cast thyself down from hence:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 10, 'For it is written, He shall give his angels charge over thee, to keep thee:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 11, 'And in their hands they shall bear thee up, lest at any time thou dash thy foot against a stone.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 12, 'And Jesus answering said unto him, It is said, Thou shalt not tempt the Lord thy God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 13, 'And when the devil had ended all the temptation, he departed from him for a season.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 14, 'And Jesus returned in the power of the Spirit into Galilee: and there went out a fame of him through all the region round about.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 15, 'And he taught in their synagogues, being glorified of all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 16, 'And he came to Nazareth, where he had been brought up: and, as his custom was, he went into the synagogue on the sabbath day, and stood up for to read.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 17, 'And there was delivered unto him the book of the prophet Esaias. And when he had opened the book, he found the place where it was written,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 18, 'The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, because he hath anointed me to preach the gospel to the poor; he hath sent me to heal the brokenhearted, to preach deliverance to the captives, and recovering of sight to the blind, to set at liberty them that are bruised,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 19, 'To preach the acceptable year of the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 20, 'And he closed the book, and he gave it again to the minister, and sat down. And the eyes of all them that were in the synagogue were fastened on him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 21, 'And he began to say unto them, This day is this scripture fulfilled in your ears.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 22, 'And all bare him witness, and wondered at the gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth. And they said, Is not this Joseph''s son?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 23, 'And he said unto them, Ye will surely say unto me this proverb, Physician, heal thyself: whatsoever we have heard done in Capernaum, do also here in thy country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 24, 'And he said, Verily I say unto you, No prophet is accepted in his own country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 25, 'But I tell you of a truth, many widows were in Israel in the days of Elias, when the heaven was shut up three years and six months, when great famine was throughout all the land;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 26, 'But unto none of them was Elias sent, save unto Sarepta, a city of Sidon, unto a woman that was a widow.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 27, 'And many lepers were in Israel in the time of Eliseus the prophet; and none of them was cleansed, saving Naaman the Syrian.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 28, 'And all they in the synagogue, when they heard these things, were filled with wrath,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 29, 'And rose up, and thrust him out of the city, and led him unto the brow of the hill whereon their city was built, that they might cast him down headlong.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 30, 'But he passing through the midst of them went his way,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 31, 'And came down to Capernaum, a city of Galilee, and taught them on the sabbath days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 32, 'And they were astonished at his doctrine: for his word was with power.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 33, 'And in the synagogue there was a man, which had a spirit of an unclean devil, and cried out with a loud voice,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 34, 'Saying, Let us alone; what have we to do with thee, thou Jesus of Nazareth? art thou come to destroy us? I know thee who thou art; the Holy One of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 35, 'And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him. And when the devil had thrown him in the midst, he came out of him, and hurt him not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 36, 'And they were all amazed, and spake among themselves, saying, What a word is this! for with authority and power he commandeth the unclean spirits, and they come out.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 37, 'And the fame of him went out into every place of the country round about.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 38, 'And he arose out of the synagogue, and entered into Simon''s house. And Simon''s wife''s mother was taken with a great fever; and they besought him for her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 39, 'And he stood over her, and rebuked the fever; and it left her: and immediately she arose and ministered unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 40, 'Now when the sun was setting, all they that had any sick with divers diseases brought them unto him; and he laid his hands on every one of them, and healed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 41, 'And devils also came out of many, crying out, and saying, Thou art Christ the Son of God. And he rebuking them suffered them not to speak: for they knew that he was Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 42, 'And when it was day, he departed and went into a desert place: and the people sought him, and came unto him, and stayed him, that he should not depart from them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 43, 'And he said unto them, I must preach the kingdom of God to other cities also: for therefore am I sent.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 4, 44, 'And he preached in the synagogues of Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 1, 'And it came to pass, that, as the people pressed upon him to hear the word of God, he stood by the lake of Gennesaret,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 2, 'And saw two ships standing by the lake: but the fishermen were gone out of them, and were washing their nets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 3, 'And he entered into one of the ships, which was Simon''s, and prayed him that he would thrust out a little from the land. And he sat down, and taught the people out of the ship.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 4, 'Now when he had left speaking, he said unto Simon, Launch out into the deep, and let down your nets for a draught.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 5, 'And Simon answering said unto him, Master, we have toiled all the night, and have taken nothing: nevertheless at thy word I will let down the net.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 6, 'And when they had this done, they inclosed a great multitude of fishes: and their net brake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 7, 'And they beckoned unto their partners, which were in the other ship, that they should come and help them. And they came, and filled both the ships, so that they began to sink.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 8, 'When Simon Peter saw it, he fell down at Jesus'' knees, saying, Depart from me; for I am a sinful man, O Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 9, 'For he was astonished, and all that were with him, at the draught of the fishes which they had taken:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 10, 'And so was also James, and John, the sons of Zebedee, which were partners with Simon. And Jesus said unto Simon, Fear not; from henceforth thou shalt catch men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 11, 'And when they had brought their ships to land, they forsook all, and followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 12, 'And it came to pass, when he was in a certain city, behold a man full of leprosy: who seeing Jesus fell on his face, and besought him, saying, Lord, if thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 13, 'And he put forth his hand, and touched him, saying, I will: be thou clean. And immediately the leprosy departed from him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 14, 'And he charged him to tell no man: but go, and shew thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing, according as Moses commanded, for a testimony unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 15, 'But so much the more went there a fame abroad of him: and great multitudes came together to hear, and to be healed by him of their infirmities.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 16, 'And he withdrew himself into the wilderness, and prayed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 17, 'And it came to pass on a certain day, as he was teaching, that there were Pharisees and doctors of the law sitting by, which were come out of every town of Galilee, and Judaea, and Jerusalem: and the power of the Lord was present to heal them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 18, 'And, behold, men brought in a bed a man which was taken with a palsy: and they sought means to bring him in, and to lay him before him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 19, 'And when they could not find by what way they might bring him in because of the multitude, they went upon the housetop, and let him down through the tiling with his couch into the midst before Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 20, 'And when he saw their faith, he said unto him, Man, thy sins are forgiven thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 21, 'And the scribes and the Pharisees began to reason, saying, Who is this which speaketh blasphemies? Who can forgive sins, but God alone?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 22, 'But when Jesus perceived their thoughts, he answering said unto them, What reason ye in your hearts?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 23, 'Whether is easier, to say, Thy sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Rise up and walk?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 24, 'But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power upon earth to forgive sins, (he said unto the sick of the palsy,) I say unto thee, Arise, and take up thy couch, and go into thine house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 25, 'And immediately he rose up before them, and took up that whereon he lay, and departed to his own house, glorifying God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 26, 'And they were all amazed, and they glorified God, and were filled with fear, saying, We have seen strange things to day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 27, 'And after these things he went forth, and saw a publican, named Levi, sitting at the receipt of custom: and he said unto him, Follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 28, 'And he left all, rose up, and followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 29, 'And Levi made him a great feast in his own house: and there was a great company of publicans and of others that sat down with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 30, 'But their scribes and Pharisees murmured against his disciples, saying, Why do ye eat and drink with publicans and sinners?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 31, 'And Jesus answering said unto them, They that are whole need not a physician; but they that are sick.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 32, 'I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 33, 'And they said unto him, Why do the disciples of John fast often, and make prayers, and likewise the disciples of the Pharisees; but thine eat and drink?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 34, 'And he said unto them, Can ye make the children of the bridechamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 35, 'But the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken away from them, and then shall they fast in those days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 36, 'And he spake also a parable unto them; No man putteth a piece of a new garment upon an old; if otherwise, then both the new maketh a rent, and the piece that was taken out of the new agreeth not with the old.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 37, 'And no man putteth new wine into old bottles; else the new wine will burst the bottles, and be spilled, and the bottles shall perish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 38, 'But new wine must be put into new bottles; and both are preserved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 5, 39, 'No man also having drunk old wine straightway desireth new: for he saith, The old is better.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 1, 'And it came to pass on the second sabbath after the first, that he went through the corn fields; and his disciples plucked the ears of corn, and did eat, rubbing them in their hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 2, 'And certain of the Pharisees said unto them, Why do ye that which is not lawful to do on the sabbath days?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 3, 'And Jesus answering them said, Have ye not read so much as this, what David did, when himself was an hungred, and they which were with him;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 4, 'How he went into the house of God, and did take and eat the shewbread, and gave also to them that were with him; which it is not lawful to eat but for the priests alone?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 5, 'And he said unto them, That the Son of man is Lord also of the sabbath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 6, 'And it came to pass also on another sabbath, that he entered into the synagogue and taught: and there was a man whose right hand was withered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 7, 'And the scribes and Pharisees watched him, whether he would heal on the sabbath day; that they might find an accusation against him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 8, 'But he knew their thoughts, and said to the man which had the withered hand, Rise up, and stand forth in the midst. And he arose and stood forth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 9, 'Then said Jesus unto them, I will ask you one thing; Is it lawful on the sabbath days to do good, or to do evil? to save life, or to destroy it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 10, 'And looking round about upon them all, he said unto the man, Stretch forth thy hand. And he did so: and his hand was restored whole as the other.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 11, 'And they were filled with madness; and communed one with another what they might do to Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 12, 'And it came to pass in those days, that he went out into a mountain to pray, and continued all night in prayer to God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 13, 'And when it was day, he called unto him his disciples: and of them he chose twelve, whom also he named apostles;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 14, 'Simon, (whom he also named Peter,) and Andrew his brother, James and John, Philip and Bartholomew,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 15, 'Matthew and Thomas, James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon called Zelotes,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 16, 'And Judas the brother of James, and Judas Iscariot, which also was the traitor.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 17, 'And he came down with them, and stood in the plain, and the company of his disciples, and a great multitude of people out of all Judaea and Jerusalem, and from the sea coast of Tyre and Sidon, which came to hear him, and to be healed of their diseases;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 18, 'And they that were vexed with unclean spirits: and they were healed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 19, 'And the whole multitude sought to touch him: for there went virtue out of him, and healed them all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 20, 'And he lifted up his eyes on his disciples, and said, Blessed be ye poor: for yours is the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 21, 'Blessed are ye that hunger now: for ye shall be filled. Blessed are ye that weep now: for ye shall laugh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 22, 'Blessed are ye, when men shall hate you, and when they shall separate you from their company, and shall reproach you, and cast out your name as evil, for the Son of man''s sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 23, 'Rejoice ye in that day, and leap for joy: for, behold, your reward is great in heaven: for in the like manner did their fathers unto the prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 24, 'But woe unto you that are rich! for ye have received your consolation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 25, 'Woe unto you that are full! for ye shall hunger. Woe unto you that laugh now! for ye shall mourn and weep.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 26, 'Woe unto you, when all men shall speak well of you! for so did their fathers to the false prophets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 27, 'But I say unto you which hear, Love your enemies, do good to them which hate you,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 28, 'Bless them that curse you, and pray for them which despitefully use you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 29, 'And unto him that smiteth thee on the one cheek offer also the other; and him that taketh away thy cloke forbid not to take thy coat also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 30, 'Give to every man that asketh of thee; and of him that taketh away thy goods ask them not again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 31, 'And as ye would that men should do to you, do ye also to them likewise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 32, 'For if ye love them which love you, what thank have ye? for sinners also love those that love them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 33, 'And if ye do good to them which do good to you, what thank have ye? for sinners also do even the same.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 34, 'And if ye lend to them of whom ye hope to receive, what thank have ye? for sinners also lend to sinners, to receive as much again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 35, 'But love ye your enemies, and do good, and lend, hoping for nothing again; and your reward shall be great, and ye shall be the children of the Highest: for he is kind unto the unthankful and to the evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 36, 'Be ye therefore merciful, as your Father also is merciful.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 37, 'Judge not, and ye shall not be judged: condemn not, and ye shall not be condemned: forgive, and ye shall be forgiven:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 38, 'Give, and it shall be given unto you; good measure, pressed down, and shaken together, and running over, shall men give into your bosom. For with the same measure that ye mete withal it shall be measured to you again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 39, 'And he spake a parable unto them, Can the blind lead the blind? shall they not both fall into the ditch?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 40, 'The disciple is not above his master: but every one that is perfect shall be as his master.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 41, 'And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother''s eye, but perceivest not the beam that is in thine own eye?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 42, 'Either how canst thou say to thy brother, Brother, let me pull out the mote that is in thine eye, when thou thyself beholdest not the beam that is in thine own eye? Thou hypocrite, cast out first the beam out of thine own eye, and then shalt thou see clearly to pull out the mote that is in thy brother''s eye.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 43, 'For a good tree bringeth not forth corrupt fruit; neither doth a corrupt tree bring forth good fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 44, 'For every tree is known by his own fruit. For of thorns men do not gather figs, nor of a bramble bush gather they grapes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 45, 'A good man out of the good treasure of his heart bringeth forth that which is good; and an evil man out of the evil treasure of his heart bringeth forth that which is evil: for of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaketh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 46, 'And why call ye me, Lord, Lord, and do not the things which I say?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 47, 'Whosoever cometh to me, and heareth my sayings, and doeth them, I will shew you to whom he is like:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 48, 'He is like a man which built an house, and digged deep, and laid the foundation on a rock: and when the flood arose, the stream beat vehemently upon that house, and could not shake it: for it was founded upon a rock.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 6, 49, 'But he that heareth, and doeth not, is like a man that without a foundation built an house upon the earth; against which the stream did beat vehemently, and immediately it fell; and the ruin of that house was great.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 1, 'Now when he had ended all his sayings in the audience of the people, he entered into Capernaum.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 2, 'And a certain centurion''s servant, who was dear unto him, was sick, and ready to die.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 3, 'And when he heard of Jesus, he sent unto him the elders of the Jews, beseeching him that he would come and heal his servant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 4, 'And when they came to Jesus, they besought him instantly, saying, That he was worthy for whom he should do this:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 5, 'For he loveth our nation, and he hath built us a synagogue.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 6, 'Then Jesus went with them. And when he was now not far from the house, the centurion sent friends to him, saying unto him, Lord, trouble not thyself: for I am not worthy that thou shouldest enter under my roof:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 7, 'Wherefore neither thought I myself worthy to come unto thee: but say in a word, and my servant shall be healed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 8, 'For I also am a man set under authority, having under me soldiers, and I say unto one, Go, and he goeth; and to another, Come, and he cometh; and to my servant, Do this, and he doeth it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 9, 'When Jesus heard these things, he marvelled at him, and turned him about, and said unto the people that followed him, I say unto you, I have not found so great faith, no, not in Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 10, 'And they that were sent, returning to the house, found the servant whole that had been sick.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 11, 'And it came to pass the day after, that he went into a city called Nain; and many of his disciples went with him, and much people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 12, 'Now when he came nigh to the gate of the city, behold, there was a dead man carried out, the only son of his mother, and she was a widow: and much people of the city was with her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 13, 'And when the Lord saw her, he had compassion on her, and said unto her, Weep not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 14, 'And he came and touched the bier: and they that bare him stood still. And he said, Young man, I say unto thee, Arise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 15, 'And he that was dead sat up, and began to speak. And he delivered him to his mother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 16, 'And there came a fear on all: and they glorified God, saying, That a great prophet is risen up among us; and, That God hath visited his people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 17, 'And this rumour of him went forth throughout all Judaea, and throughout all the region round about.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 18, 'And the disciples of John shewed him of all these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 19, 'And John calling unto him two of his disciples sent them to Jesus, saying, Art thou he that should come? or look we for another?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 20, 'When the men were come unto him, they said, John Baptist hath sent us unto thee, saying, Art thou he that should come? or look we for another?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 21, 'And in that same hour he cured many of their infirmities and plagues, and of evil spirits; and unto many that were blind he gave sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 22, 'Then Jesus answering said unto them, Go your way, and tell John what things ye have seen and heard; how that the blind see, the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised, to the poor the gospel is preached.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 23, 'And blessed is he, whosoever shall not be offended in me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 24, 'And when the messengers of John were departed, he began to speak unto the people concerning John, What went ye out into the wilderness for to see? A reed shaken with the wind?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 25, 'But what went ye out for to see? A man clothed in soft raiment? Behold, they which are gorgeously apparelled, and live delicately, are in kings'' courts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 26, 'But what went ye out for to see? A prophet? Yea, I say unto you, and much more than a prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 27, 'This is he, of whom it is written, Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 28, 'For I say unto you, Among those that are born of women there is not a greater prophet than John the Baptist: but he that is least in the kingdom of God is greater than he.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 29, 'And all the people that heard him, and the publicans, justified God, being baptized with the baptism of John.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 30, 'But the Pharisees and lawyers rejected the counsel of God against themselves, being not baptized of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 31, 'And the Lord said, Whereunto then shall I liken the men of this generation? and to what are they like?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 32, 'They are like unto children sitting in the marketplace, and calling one to another, and saying, We have piped unto you, and ye have not danced; we have mourned to you, and ye have not wept.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 33, 'For John the Baptist came neither eating bread nor drinking wine; and ye say, He hath a devil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 34, 'The Son of man is come eating and drinking; and ye say, Behold a gluttonous man, and a winebibber, a friend of publicans and sinners!'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 35, 'But wisdom is justified of all her children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 36, 'And one of the Pharisees desired him that he would eat with him. And he went into the Pharisee''s house, and sat down to meat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 37, 'And, behold, a woman in the city, which was a sinner, when she knew that Jesus sat at meat in the Pharisee''s house, brought an alabaster box of ointment,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 38, 'And stood at his feet behind him weeping, and began to wash his feet with tears, and did wipe them with the hairs of her head, and kissed his feet, and anointed them with the ointment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 39, 'Now when the Pharisee which had bidden him saw it, he spake within himself, saying, This man, if he were a prophet, would have known who and what manner of woman this is that toucheth him: for she is a sinner.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 40, 'And Jesus answering said unto him, Simon, I have somewhat to say unto thee. And he saith, Master, say on.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 41, 'There was a certain creditor which had two debtors: the one owed five hundred pence, and the other fifty.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 42, 'And when they had nothing to pay, he frankly forgave them both. Tell me therefore, which of them will love him most?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 43, 'Simon answered and said, I suppose that he, to whom he forgave most. And he said unto him, Thou hast rightly judged.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 44, 'And he turned to the woman, and said unto Simon, Seest thou this woman? I entered into thine house, thou gavest me no water for my feet: but she hath washed my feet with tears, and wiped them with the hairs of her head.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 45, 'Thou gavest me no kiss: but this woman since the time I came in hath not ceased to kiss my feet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 46, 'My head with oil thou didst not anoint: but this woman hath anointed my feet with ointment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 47, 'Wherefore I say unto thee, Her sins, which are many, are forgiven; for she loved much: but to whom little is forgiven, the same loveth little.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 48, 'And he said unto her, Thy sins are forgiven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 49, 'And they that sat at meat with him began to say within themselves, Who is this that forgiveth sins also?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 7, 50, 'And he said to the woman, Thy faith hath saved thee; go in peace.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 1, 'And it came to pass afterward, that he went throughout every city and village, preaching and shewing the glad tidings of the kingdom of God: and the twelve were with him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 2, 'And certain women, which had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities, Mary called Magdalene, out of whom went seven devils,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 3, 'And Joanna the wife of Chuza Herod''s steward, and Susanna, and many others, which ministered unto him of their substance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 4, 'And when much people were gathered together, and were come to him out of every city, he spake by a parable:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 5, 'A sower went out to sow his seed: and as he sowed, some fell by the way side; and it was trodden down, and the fowls of the air devoured it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 6, 'And some fell upon a rock; and as soon as it was sprung up, it withered away, because it lacked moisture.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 7, 'And some fell among thorns; and the thorns sprang up with it, and choked it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 8, 'And other fell on good ground, and sprang up, and bare fruit an hundredfold. And when he had said these things, he cried, He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 9, 'And his disciples asked him, saying, What might this parable be?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 10, 'And he said, Unto you it is given to know the mysteries of the kingdom of God: but to others in parables; that seeing they might not see, and hearing they might not understand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 11, 'Now the parable is this: The seed is the word of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 12, 'Those by the way side are they that hear; then cometh the devil, and taketh away the word out of their hearts, lest they should believe and be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 13, 'They on the rock are they, which, when they hear, receive the word with joy; and these have no root, which for a while believe, and in time of temptation fall away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 14, 'And that which fell among thorns are they, which, when they have heard, go forth, and are choked with cares and riches and pleasures of this life, and bring no fruit to perfection.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 15, 'But that on the good ground are they, which in an honest and good heart, having heard the word, keep it, and bring forth fruit with patience.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 16, 'No man, when he hath lighted a candle, covereth it with a vessel, or putteth it under a bed; but setteth it on a candlestick, that they which enter in may see the light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 17, 'For nothing is secret, that shall not be made manifest; neither any thing hid, that shall not be known and come abroad.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 18, 'Take heed therefore how ye hear: for whosoever hath, to him shall be given; and whosoever hath not, from him shall be taken even that which he seemeth to have.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 19, 'Then came to him his mother and his brethren, and could not come at him for the press.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 20, 'And it was told him by certain which said, Thy mother and thy brethren stand without, desiring to see thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 21, 'And he answered and said unto them, My mother and my brethren are these which hear the word of God, and do it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 22, 'Now it came to pass on a certain day, that he went into a ship with his disciples: and he said unto them, Let us go over unto the other side of the lake. And they launched forth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 23, 'But as they sailed he fell asleep: and there came down a storm of wind on the lake; and they were filled with water, and were in jeopardy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 24, 'And they came to him, and awoke him, saying, Master, master, we perish. Then he arose, and rebuked the wind and the raging of the water: and they ceased, and there was a calm.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 25, 'And he said unto them, Where is your faith? And they being afraid wondered, saying one to another, What manner of man is this! for he commandeth even the winds and water, and they obey him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 26, 'And they arrived at the country of the Gadarenes, which is over against Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 27, 'And when he went forth to land, there met him out of the city a certain man, which had devils long time, and ware no clothes, neither abode in any house, but in the tombs.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 28, 'When he saw Jesus, he cried out, and fell down before him, and with a loud voice said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, thou Son of God most high? I beseech thee, torment me not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 29, '(For he had commanded the unclean spirit to come out of the man. For oftentimes it had caught him: and he was kept bound with chains and in fetters; and he brake the bands, and was driven of the devil into the wilderness.)'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 30, 'And Jesus asked him, saying, What is thy name? And he said, Legion: because many devils were entered into him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 31, 'And they besought him that he would not command them to go out into the deep.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 32, 'And there was there an herd of many swine feeding on the mountain: and they besought him that he would suffer them to enter into them. And he suffered them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 33, 'Then went the devils out of the man, and entered into the swine: and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the lake, and were choked.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 34, 'When they that fed them saw what was done, they fled, and went and told it in the city and in the country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 35, 'Then they went out to see what was done; and came to Jesus, and found the man, out of whom the devils were departed, sitting at the feet of Jesus, clothed, and in his right mind: and they were afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 36, 'They also which saw it told them by what means he that was possessed of the devils was healed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 37, 'Then the whole multitude of the country of the Gadarenes round about besought him to depart from them; for they were taken with great fear: and he went up into the ship, and returned back again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 38, 'Now the man out of whom the devils were departed besought him that he might be with him: but Jesus sent him away, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 39, 'Return to thine own house, and shew how great things God hath done unto thee. And he went his way, and published throughout the whole city how great things Jesus had done unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 40, 'And it came to pass, that, when Jesus was returned, the people gladly received him: for they were all waiting for him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 41, 'And, behold, there came a man named Jairus, and he was a ruler of the synagogue: and he fell down at Jesus'' feet, and besought him that he would come into his house:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 42, 'For he had one only daughter, about twelve years of age, and she lay a dying. But as he went the people thronged him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 43, 'And a woman having an issue of blood twelve years, which had spent all her living upon physicians, neither could be healed of any,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 44, 'Came behind him, and touched the border of his garment: and immediately her issue of blood stanched.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 45, 'And Jesus said, Who touched me? When all denied, Peter and they that were with him said, Master, the multitude throng thee and press thee, and sayest thou, Who touched me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 46, 'And Jesus said, Somebody hath touched me: for I perceive that virtue is gone out of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 47, 'And when the woman saw that she was not hid, she came trembling, and falling down before him, she declared unto him before all the people for what cause she had touched him, and how she was healed immediately.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 48, 'And he said unto her, Daughter, be of good comfort: thy faith hath made thee whole; go in peace.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 49, 'While he yet spake, there cometh one from the ruler of the synagogue''s house, saying to him, Thy daughter is dead; trouble not the Master.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 50, 'But when Jesus heard it, he answered him, saying, Fear not: believe only, and she shall be made whole.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 51, 'And when he came into the house, he suffered no man to go in, save Peter, and James, and John, and the father and the mother of the maiden.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 52, 'And all wept, and bewailed her: but he said, Weep not; she is not dead, but sleepeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 53, 'And they laughed him to scorn, knowing that she was dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 54, 'And he put them all out, and took her by the hand, and called, saying, Maid, arise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 55, 'And her spirit came again, and she arose straightway: and he commanded to give her meat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 8, 56, 'And her parents were astonished: but he charged them that they should tell no man what was done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 1, 'Then he called his twelve disciples together, and gave them power and authority over all devils, and to cure diseases.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 2, 'And he sent them to preach the kingdom of God, and to heal the sick.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 3, 'And he said unto them, Take nothing for your journey, neither staves, nor scrip, neither bread, neither money; neither have two coats apiece.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 4, 'And whatsoever house ye enter into, there abide, and thence depart.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 5, 'And whosoever will not receive you, when ye go out of that city, shake off the very dust from your feet for a testimony against them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 6, 'And they departed, and went through the towns, preaching the gospel, and healing every where.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 7, 'Now Herod the tetrarch heard of all that was done by him: and he was perplexed, because that it was said of some, that John was risen from the dead;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 8, 'And of some, that Elias had appeared; and of others, that one of the old prophets was risen again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 9, 'And Herod said, John have I beheaded: but who is this, of whom I hear such things? And he desired to see him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 10, 'And the apostles, when they were returned, told him all that they had done. And he took them, and went aside privately into a desert place belonging to the city called Bethsaida.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 11, 'And the people, when they knew it, followed him: and he received them, and spake unto them of the kingdom of God, and healed them that had need of healing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 12, 'And when the day began to wear away, then came the twelve, and said unto him, Send the multitude away, that they may go into the towns and country round about, and lodge, and get victuals: for we are here in a desert place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 13, 'But he said unto them, Give ye them to eat. And they said, We have no more but five loaves and two fishes; except we should go and buy meat for all this people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 14, 'For they were about five thousand men. And he said to his disciples, Make them sit down by fifties in a company.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 15, 'And they did so, and made them all sit down.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 16, 'Then he took the five loaves and the two fishes, and looking up to heaven, he blessed them, and brake, and gave to the disciples to set before the multitude.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 17, 'And they did eat, and were all filled: and there was taken up of fragments that remained to them twelve baskets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 18, 'And it came to pass, as he was alone praying, his disciples were with him: and he asked them, saying, Whom say the people that I am?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 19, 'They answering said, John the Baptist; but some say, Elias; and others say, that one of the old prophets is risen again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 20, 'He said unto them, But whom say ye that I am? Peter answering said, The Christ of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 21, 'And he straitly charged them, and commanded them to tell no man that thing;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 22, 'Saying, The Son of man must suffer many things, and be rejected of the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be slain, and be raised the third day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 23, 'And he said to them all, If any man will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross daily, and follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 24, 'For whosoever will save his life shall lose it: but whosoever will lose his life for my sake, the same shall save it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 25, 'For what is a man advantaged, if he gain the whole world, and lose himself, or be cast away?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 26, 'For whosoever shall be ashamed of me and of my words, of him shall the Son of man be ashamed, when he shall come in his own glory, and in his Father''s, and of the holy angels.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 27, 'But I tell you of a truth, there be some standing here, which shall not taste of death, till they see the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 28, 'And it came to pass about an eight days after these sayings, he took Peter and John and James, and went up into a mountain to pray.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 29, 'And as he prayed, the fashion of his countenance was altered, and his raiment was white and glistering.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 30, 'And, behold, there talked with him two men, which were Moses and Elias:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 31, 'Who appeared in glory, and spake of his decease which he should accomplish at Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 32, 'But Peter and they that were with him were heavy with sleep: and when they were awake, they saw his glory, and the two men that stood with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 33, 'And it came to pass, as they departed from him, Peter said unto Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here: and let us make three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias: not knowing what he said.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 34, 'While he thus spake, there came a cloud, and overshadowed them: and they feared as they entered into the cloud.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 35, 'And there came a voice out of the cloud, saying, This is my beloved Son: hear him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 36, 'And when the voice was past, Jesus was found alone. And they kept it close, and told no man in those days any of those things which they had seen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 37, 'And it came to pass, that on the next day, when they were come down from the hill, much people met him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 38, 'And, behold, a man of the company cried out, saying, Master, I beseech thee, look upon my son: for he is mine only child.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 39, 'And, lo, a spirit taketh him, and he suddenly crieth out; and it teareth him that he foameth again, and bruising him hardly departeth from him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 40, 'And I besought thy disciples to cast him out; and they could not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 41, 'And Jesus answering said, O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you, and suffer you? Bring thy son hither.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 42, 'And as he was yet a coming, the devil threw him down, and tare him. And Jesus rebuked the unclean spirit, and healed the child, and delivered him again to his father.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 43, 'And they were all amazed at the mighty power of God. But while they wondered every one at all things which Jesus did, he said unto his disciples,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 44, 'Let these sayings sink down into your ears: for the Son of man shall be delivered into the hands of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 45, 'But they understood not this saying, and it was hid from them, that they perceived it not: and they feared to ask him of that saying.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 46, 'Then there arose a reasoning among them, which of them should be greatest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 47, 'And Jesus, perceiving the thought of their heart, took a child, and set him by him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 48, 'And said unto them, Whosoever shall receive this child in my name receiveth me: and whosoever shall receive me receiveth him that sent me: for he that is least among you all, the same shall be great.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 49, 'And John answered and said, Master, we saw one casting out devils in thy name; and we forbad him, because he followeth not with us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 50, 'And Jesus said unto him, Forbid him not: for he that is not against us is for us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 51, 'And it came to pass, when the time was come that he should be received up, he stedfastly set his face to go to Jerusalem,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 52, 'And sent messengers before his face: and they went, and entered into a village of the Samaritans, to make ready for him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 53, 'And they did not receive him, because his face was as though he would go to Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 54, 'And when his disciples James and John saw this, they said, Lord, wilt thou that we command fire to come down from heaven, and consume them, even as Elias did?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 55, 'But he turned, and rebuked them, and said, Ye know not what manner of spirit ye are of.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 56, 'For the Son of man is not come to destroy men''s lives, but to save them. And they went to another village.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 57, 'And it came to pass, that, as they went in the way, a certain man said unto him, Lord, I will follow thee whithersoever thou goest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 58, 'And Jesus said unto him, Foxes have holes, and birds of the air have nests; but the Son of man hath not where to lay his head.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 59, 'And he said unto another, Follow me. But he said, Lord, suffer me first to go and bury my father.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 60, 'Jesus said unto him, Let the dead bury their dead: but go thou and preach the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 61, 'And another also said, Lord, I will follow thee; but let me first go bid them farewell, which are at home at my house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 9, 62, 'And Jesus said unto him, No man, having put his hand to the plough, and looking back, is fit for the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 1, 'After these things the Lord appointed other seventy also, and sent them two and two before his face into every city and place, whither he himself would come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 2, 'Therefore said he unto them, The harvest truly is great, but the labourers are few: pray ye therefore the Lord of the harvest, that he would send forth labourers into his harvest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 3, 'Go your ways: behold, I send you forth as lambs among wolves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 4, 'Carry neither purse, nor scrip, nor shoes: and salute no man by the way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 5, 'And into whatsoever house ye enter, first say, Peace be to this house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 6, 'And if the son of peace be there, your peace shall rest upon it: if not, it shall turn to you again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 7, 'And in the same house remain, eating and drinking such things as they give: for the labourer is worthy of his hire. Go not from house to house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 8, 'And into whatsoever city ye enter, and they receive you, eat such things as are set before you:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 9, 'And heal the sick that are therein, and say unto them, The kingdom of God is come nigh unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 10, 'But into whatsoever city ye enter, and they receive you not, go your ways out into the streets of the same, and say,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 11, 'Even the very dust of your city, which cleaveth on us, we do wipe off against you: notwithstanding be ye sure of this, that the kingdom of God is come nigh unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 12, 'But I say unto you, that it shall be more tolerable in that day for Sodom, than for that city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 13, 'Woe unto thee, Chorazin! woe unto thee, Bethsaida! for if the mighty works had been done in Tyre and Sidon, which have been done in you, they had a great while ago repented, sitting in sackcloth and ashes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 14, 'But it shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the judgment, than for you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 15, 'And thou, Capernaum, which art exalted to heaven, shalt be thrust down to hell.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 16, 'He that heareth you heareth me; and he that despiseth you despiseth me; and he that despiseth me despiseth him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 17, 'And the seventy returned again with joy, saying, Lord, even the devils are subject unto us through thy name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 18, 'And he said unto them, I beheld Satan as lightning fall from heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 19, 'Behold, I give unto you power to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy: and nothing shall by any means hurt you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 20, 'Notwithstanding in this rejoice not, that the spirits are subject unto you; but rather rejoice, because your names are written in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 21, 'In that hour Jesus rejoiced in spirit, and said, I thank thee, O Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that thou hast hid these things from the wise and prudent, and hast revealed them unto babes: even so, Father; for so it seemed good in thy sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 22, 'All things are delivered to me of my Father: and no man knoweth who the Son is, but the Father; and who the Father is, but the Son, and he to whom the Son will reveal him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 23, 'And he turned him unto his disciples, and said privately, Blessed are the eyes which see the things that ye see:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 24, 'For I tell you, that many prophets and kings have desired to see those things which ye see, and have not seen them; and to hear those things which ye hear, and have not heard them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 25, 'And, behold, a certain lawyer stood up, and tempted him, saying, Master, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 26, 'He said unto him, What is written in the law? how readest thou?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 27, 'And he answering said, Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy strength, and with all thy mind; and thy neighbour as thyself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 28, 'And he said unto him, Thou hast answered right: this do, and thou shalt live.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 29, 'But he, willing to justify himself, said unto Jesus, And who is my neighbour?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 30, 'And Jesus answering said, A certain man went down from Jerusalem to Jericho, and fell among thieves, which stripped him of his raiment, and wounded him, and departed, leaving him half dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 31, 'And by chance there came down a certain priest that way: and when he saw him, he passed by on the other side.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 32, 'And likewise a Levite, when he was at the place, came and looked on him, and passed by on the other side.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 33, 'But a certain Samaritan, as he journeyed, came where he was: and when he saw him, he had compassion on him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 34, 'And went to him, and bound up his wounds, pouring in oil and wine, and set him on his own beast, and brought him to an inn, and took care of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 35, 'And on the morrow when he departed, he took out two pence, and gave them to the host, and said unto him, Take care of him; and whatsoever thou spendest more, when I come again, I will repay thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 36, 'Which now of these three, thinkest thou, was neighbour unto him that fell among the thieves?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 37, 'And he said, He that shewed mercy on him. Then said Jesus unto him, Go, and do thou likewise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 38, 'Now it came to pass, as they went, that he entered into a certain village: and a certain woman named Martha received him into her house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 39, 'And she had a sister called Mary, which also sat at Jesus'' feet, and heard his word.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 40, 'But Martha was cumbered about much serving, and came to him, and said, Lord, dost thou not care that my sister hath left me to serve alone? bid her therefore that she help me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 41, 'And Jesus answered and said unto her, Martha, Martha, thou art careful and troubled about many things:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 10, 42, 'But one thing is needful: and Mary hath chosen that good part, which shall not be taken away from her.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 1, 'And it came to pass, that, as he was praying in a certain place, when he ceased, one of his disciples said unto him, Lord, teach us to pray, as John also taught his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 2, 'And he said unto them, When ye pray, say, Our Father which art in heaven, Hallowed be thy name. Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done, as in heaven, so in earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 3, 'Give us day by day our daily bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 4, 'And forgive us our sins; for we also forgive every one that is indebted to us. And lead us not into temptation; but deliver us from evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 5, 'And he said unto them, Which of you shall have a friend, and shall go unto him at midnight, and say unto him, Friend, lend me three loaves;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 6, 'For a friend of mine in his journey is come to me, and I have nothing to set before him?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 7, 'And he from within shall answer and say, Trouble me not: the door is now shut, and my children are with me in bed; I cannot rise and give thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 8, 'I say unto you, Though he will not rise and give him, because he is his friend, yet because of his importunity he will rise and give him as many as he needeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 9, 'And I say unto you, Ask, and it shall be given you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 10, 'For every one that asketh receiveth; and he that seeketh findeth; and to him that knocketh it shall be opened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 11, 'If a son shall ask bread of any of you that is a father, will he give him a stone? or if he ask a fish, will he for a fish give him a serpent?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 12, 'Or if he shall ask an egg, will he offer him a scorpion?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 13, 'If ye then, being evil, know how to give good gifts unto your children: how much more shall your heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to them that ask him?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 14, 'And he was casting out a devil, and it was dumb. And it came to pass, when the devil was gone out, the dumb spake; and the people wondered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 15, 'But some of them said, He casteth out devils through Beelzebub the chief of the devils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 16, 'And others, tempting him, sought of him a sign from heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 17, 'But he, knowing their thoughts, said unto them, Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation; and a house divided against a house falleth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 18, 'If Satan also be divided against himself, how shall his kingdom stand? because ye say that I cast out devils through Beelzebub.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 19, 'And if I by Beelzebub cast out devils, by whom do your sons cast them out? therefore shall they be your judges.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 20, 'But if I with the finger of God cast out devils, no doubt the kingdom of God is come upon you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 21, 'When a strong man armed keepeth his palace, his goods are in peace:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 22, 'But when a stronger than he shall come upon him, and overcome him, he taketh from him all his armour wherein he trusted, and divideth his spoils.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 23, 'He that is not with me is against me: and he that gathereth not with me scattereth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 24, 'When the unclean spirit is gone out of a man, he walketh through dry places, seeking rest; and finding none, he saith, I will return unto my house whence I came out.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 25, 'And when he cometh, he findeth it swept and garnished.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 26, 'Then goeth he, and taketh to him seven other spirits more wicked than himself; and they enter in, and dwell there: and the last state of that man is worse than the first.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 27, 'And it came to pass, as he spake these things, a certain woman of the company lifted up her voice, and said unto him, Blessed is the womb that bare thee, and the paps which thou hast sucked.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 28, 'But he said, Yea rather, blessed are they that hear the word of God, and keep it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 29, 'And when the people were gathered thick together, he began to say, This is an evil generation: they seek a sign; and there shall no sign be given it, but the sign of Jonas the prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 30, 'For as Jonas was a sign unto the Ninevites, so shall also the Son of man be to this generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 31, 'The queen of the south shall rise up in the judgment with the men of this generation, and condemn them: for she came from the utmost parts of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon; and, behold, a greater than Solomon is here.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 32, 'The men of Nineve shall rise up in the judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: for they repented at the preaching of Jonas; and, behold, a greater than Jonas is here.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 33, 'No man, when he hath lighted a candle, putteth it in a secret place, neither under a bushel, but on a candlestick, that they which come in may see the light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 34, 'The light of the body is the eye: therefore when thine eye is single, thy whole body also is full of light; but when thine eye is evil, thy body also is full of darkness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 35, 'Take heed therefore that the light which is in thee be not darkness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 36, 'If thy whole body therefore be full of light, having no part dark, the whole shall be full of light, as when the bright shining of a candle doth give thee light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 37, 'And as he spake, a certain Pharisee besought him to dine with him: and he went in, and sat down to meat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 38, 'And when the Pharisee saw it, he marvelled that he had not first washed before dinner.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 39, 'And the Lord said unto him, Now do ye Pharisees make clean the outside of the cup and the platter; but your inward part is full of ravening and wickedness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 40, 'Ye fools, did not he that made that which is without make that which is within also?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 41, 'But rather give alms of such things as ye have; and, behold, all things are clean unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 42, 'But woe unto you, Pharisees! for ye tithe mint and rue and all manner of herbs, and pass over judgment and the love of God: these ought ye to have done, and not to leave the other undone.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 43, 'Woe unto you, Pharisees! for ye love the uppermost seats in the synagogues, and greetings in the markets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 44, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye are as graves which appear not, and the men that walk over them are not aware of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 45, 'Then answered one of the lawyers, and said unto him, Master, thus saying thou reproachest us also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 46, 'And he said, Woe unto you also, ye lawyers! for ye lade men with burdens grievous to be borne, and ye yourselves touch not the burdens with one of your fingers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 47, 'Woe unto you! for ye build the sepulchres of the prophets, and your fathers killed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 48, 'Truly ye bear witness that ye allow the deeds of your fathers: for they indeed killed them, and ye build their sepulchres.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 49, 'Therefore also said the wisdom of God, I will send them prophets and apostles, and some of them they shall slay and persecute:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 50, 'That the blood of all the prophets, which was shed from the foundation of the world, may be required of this generation;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 51, 'From the blood of Abel unto the blood of Zacharias, which perished between the altar and the temple: verily I say unto you, It shall be required of this generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 52, 'Woe unto you, lawyers! for ye have taken away the key of knowledge: ye entered not in yourselves, and them that were entering in ye hindered.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 53, 'And as he said these things unto them, the scribes and the Pharisees began to urge him vehemently, and to provoke him to speak of many things:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 11, 54, 'Laying wait for him, and seeking to catch something out of his mouth, that they might accuse him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 1, 'In the mean time, when there were gathered together an innumerable multitude of people, insomuch that they trode one upon another, he began to say unto his disciples first of all, Beware ye of the leaven of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 2, 'For there is nothing covered, that shall not be revealed; neither hid, that shall not be known.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 3, 'Therefore whatsoever ye have spoken in darkness shall be heard in the light; and that which ye have spoken in the ear in closets shall be proclaimed upon the housetops.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 4, 'And I say unto you my friends, Be not afraid of them that kill the body, and after that have no more that they can do.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 5, 'But I will forewarn you whom ye shall fear: Fear him, which after he hath killed hath power to cast into hell; yea, I say unto you, Fear him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 6, 'Are not five sparrows sold for two farthings, and not one of them is forgotten before God?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 7, 'But even the very hairs of your head are all numbered. Fear not therefore: ye are of more value than many sparrows.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 8, 'Also I say unto you, Whosoever shall confess me before men, him shall the Son of man also confess before the angels of God:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 9, 'But he that denieth me before men shall be denied before the angels of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 10, 'And whosoever shall speak a word against the Son of man, it shall be forgiven him: but unto him that blasphemeth against the Holy Ghost it shall not be forgiven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 11, 'And when they bring you unto the synagogues, and unto magistrates, and powers, take ye no thought how or what thing ye shall answer, or what ye shall say:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 12, 'For the Holy Ghost shall teach you in the same hour what ye ought to say.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 13, 'And one of the company said unto him, Master, speak to my brother, that he divide the inheritance with me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 14, 'And he said unto him, Man, who made me a judge or a divider over you?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 15, 'And he said unto them, Take heed, and beware of covetousness: for a man''s life consisteth not in the abundance of the things which he possesseth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 16, 'And he spake a parable unto them, saying, The ground of a certain rich man brought forth plentifully:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 17, 'And he thought within himself, saying, What shall I do, because I have no room where to bestow my fruits?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 18, 'And he said, This will I do: I will pull down my barns, and build greater; and there will I bestow all my fruits and my goods.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 19, 'And I will say to my soul, Soul, thou hast much goods laid up for many years; take thine ease, eat, drink, and be merry.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 20, 'But God said unto him, Thou fool, this night thy soul shall be required of thee: then whose shall those things be, which thou hast provided?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 21, 'So is he that layeth up treasure for himself, and is not rich toward God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 22, 'And he said unto his disciples, Therefore I say unto you, Take no thought for your life, what ye shall eat; neither for the body, what ye shall put on.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 23, 'The life is more than meat, and the body is more than raiment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 24, 'Consider the ravens: for they neither sow nor reap; which neither have storehouse nor barn; and God feedeth them: how much more are ye better than the fowls?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 25, 'And which of you with taking thought can add to his stature one cubit?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 26, 'If ye then be not able to do that thing which is least, why take ye thought for the rest?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 27, 'Consider the lilies how they grow: they toil not, they spin not; and yet I say unto you, that Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 28, 'If then God so clothe the grass, which is to day in the field, and to morrow is cast into the oven; how much more will he clothe you, O ye of little faith?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 29, 'And seek not ye what ye shall eat, or what ye shall drink, neither be ye of doubtful mind.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 30, 'For all these things do the nations of the world seek after: and your Father knoweth that ye have need of these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 31, 'But rather seek ye the kingdom of God; and all these things shall be added unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 32, 'Fear not, little flock; for it is your Father''s good pleasure to give you the kingdom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 33, 'Sell that ye have, and give alms; provide yourselves bags which wax not old, a treasure in the heavens that faileth not, where no thief approacheth, neither moth corrupteth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 34, 'For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 35, 'Let your loins be girded about, and your lights burning;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 36, 'And ye yourselves like unto men that wait for their lord, when he will return from the wedding; that when he cometh and knocketh, they may open unto him immediately.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 37, 'Blessed are those servants, whom the lord when he cometh shall find watching: verily I say unto you, that he shall gird himself, and make them to sit down to meat, and will come forth and serve them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 38, 'And if he shall come in the second watch, or come in the third watch, and find them so, blessed are those servants.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 39, 'And this know, that if the goodman of the house had known what hour the thief would come, he would have watched, and not have suffered his house to be broken through.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 40, 'Be ye therefore ready also: for the Son of man cometh at an hour when ye think not.')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 41, 'Then Peter said unto him, Lord, speakest thou this parable unto us, or even to all?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 42, 'And the Lord said, Who then is that faithful and wise steward, whom his lord shall make ruler over his household, to give them their portion of meat in due season?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 43, 'Blessed is that servant, whom his lord when he cometh shall find so doing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 44, 'Of a truth I say unto you, that he will make him ruler over all that he hath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 45, 'But and if that servant say in his heart, My lord delayeth his coming; and shall begin to beat the menservants and maidens, and to eat and drink, and to be drunken;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 46, 'The lord of that servant will come in a day when he looketh not for him, and at an hour when he is not aware, and will cut him in sunder, and will appoint him his portion with the unbelievers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 47, 'And that servant, which knew his lord''s will, and prepared not himself, neither did according to his will, shall be beaten with many stripes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 48, 'But he that knew not, and did commit things worthy of stripes, shall be beaten with few stripes. For unto whomsoever much is given, of him shall be much required: and to whom men have committed much, of him they will ask the more.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 49, 'I am come to send fire on the earth; and what will I, if it be already kindled?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 50, 'But I have a baptism to be baptized with; and how am I straitened till it be accomplished!'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 51, 'Suppose ye that I am come to give peace on earth? I tell you, Nay; but rather division:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 52, 'For from henceforth there shall be five in one house divided, three against two, and two against three.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 53, 'The father shall be divided against the son, and the son against the father; the mother against the daughter, and the daughter against the mother; the mother in law against her daughter in law, and the daughter in law against her mother in law.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 54, 'And he said also to the people, When ye see a cloud rise out of the west, straightway ye say, There cometh a shower; and so it is.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 55, 'And when ye see the south wind blow, ye say, There will be heat; and it cometh to pass.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 56, 'Ye hypocrites, ye can discern the face of the sky and of the earth; but how is it that ye do not discern this time?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 57, 'Yea, and why even of yourselves judge ye not what is right?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 58, 'When thou goest with thine adversary to the magistrate, as thou art in the way, give diligence that thou mayest be delivered from him; lest he hale thee to the judge, and the judge deliver thee to the officer, and the officer cast thee into prison.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 12, 59, 'I tell thee, thou shalt not depart thence, till thou hast paid the very last mite.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 1, 'There were present at that season some that told him of the Galilaeans, whose blood Pilate had mingled with their sacrifices.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 2, 'And Jesus answering said unto them, Suppose ye that these Galilaeans were sinners above all the Galilaeans, because they suffered such things?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 3, 'I tell you, Nay: but, except ye repent, ye shall all likewise perish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 4, 'Or those eighteen, upon whom the tower in Siloam fell, and slew them, think ye that they were sinners above all men that dwelt in Jerusalem?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 5, 'I tell you, Nay: but, except ye repent, ye shall all likewise perish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 6, 'He spake also this parable; A certain man had a fig tree planted in his vineyard; and he came and sought fruit thereon, and found none.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 7, 'Then said he unto the dresser of his vineyard, Behold, these three years I come seeking fruit on this fig tree, and find none: cut it down; why cumbereth it the ground?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 8, 'And he answering said unto him, Lord, let it alone this year also, till I shall dig about it, and dung it:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 9, 'And if it bear fruit, well: and if not, then after that thou shalt cut it down.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 10, 'And he was teaching in one of the synagogues on the sabbath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 11, 'And, behold, there was a woman which had a spirit of infirmity eighteen years, and was bowed together, and could in no wise lift up herself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 12, 'And when Jesus saw her, he called her to him, and said unto her, Woman, thou art loosed from thine infirmity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 13, 'And he laid his hands on her: and immediately she was made straight, and glorified God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 14, 'And the ruler of the synagogue answered with indignation, because that Jesus had healed on the sabbath day, and said unto the people, There are six days in which men ought to work: in them therefore come and be healed, and not on the sabbath day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 15, 'The Lord then answered him, and said, Thou hypocrite, doth not each one of you on the sabbath loose his ox or his ass from the stall, and lead him away to watering?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 16, 'And ought not this woman, being a daughter of Abraham, whom Satan hath bound, lo, these eighteen years, be loosed from this bond on the sabbath day?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 17, 'And when he had said these things, all his adversaries were ashamed: and all the people rejoiced for all the glorious things that were done by him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 18, 'Then said he, Unto what is the kingdom of God like? and whereunto shall I resemble it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 19, 'It is like a grain of mustard seed, which a man took, and cast into his garden; and it grew, and waxed a great tree; and the fowls of the air lodged in the branches of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 20, 'And again he said, Whereunto shall I liken the kingdom of God?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 21, 'It is like leaven, which a woman took and hid in three measures of meal, till the whole was leavened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 22, 'And he went through the cities and villages, teaching, and journeying toward Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 23, 'Then said one unto him, Lord, are there few that be saved? And he said unto them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 24, 'Strive to enter in at the strait gate: for many, I say unto you, will seek to enter in, and shall not be able.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 25, 'When once the master of the house is risen up, and hath shut to the door, and ye begin to stand without, and to knock at the door, saying, Lord, Lord, open unto us; and he shall answer and say unto you, I know you not whence ye are:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 26, 'Then shall ye begin to say, We have eaten and drunk in thy presence, and thou hast taught in our streets.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 27, 'But he shall say, I tell you, I know you not whence ye are; depart from me, all ye workers of iniquity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 28, 'There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when ye shall see Abraham, and Isaac, and Jacob, and all the prophets, in the kingdom of God, and you yourselves thrust out.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 29, 'And they shall come from the east, and from the west, and from the north, and from the south, and shall sit down in the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 30, 'And, behold, there are last which shall be first, and there are first which shall be last.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 31, 'The same day there came certain of the Pharisees, saying unto him, Get thee out, and depart hence: for Herod will kill thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 32, 'And he said unto them, Go ye, and tell that fox, Behold, I cast out devils, and I do cures to day and to morrow, and the third day I shall be perfected.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 33, 'Nevertheless I must walk to day, and to morrow, and the day following: for it cannot be that a prophet perish out of Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 34, 'O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, which killest the prophets, and stonest them that are sent unto thee; how often would I have gathered thy children together, as a hen doth gather her brood under her wings, and ye would not!'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 13, 35, 'Behold, your house is left unto you desolate: and verily I say unto you, Ye shall not see me, until the time come when ye shall say, Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 1, 'And it came to pass, as he went into the house of one of the chief Pharisees to eat bread on the sabbath day, that they watched him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 2, 'And, behold, there was a certain man before him which had the dropsy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 3, 'And Jesus answering spake unto the lawyers and Pharisees, saying, Is it lawful to heal on the sabbath day?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 4, 'And they held their peace. And he took him, and healed him, and let him go;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 5, 'And answered them, saying, Which of you shall have an ass or an ox fallen into a pit, and will not straightway pull him out on the sabbath day?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 6, 'And they could not answer him again to these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 7, 'And he put forth a parable to those which were bidden, when he marked how they chose out the chief rooms; saying unto them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 8, 'When thou art bidden of any man to a wedding, sit not down in the highest room; lest a more honourable man than thou be bidden of him;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 9, 'And he that bade thee and him come and say to thee, Give this man place; and thou begin with shame to take the lowest room.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 10, 'But when thou art bidden, go and sit down in the lowest room; that when he that bade thee cometh, he may say unto thee, Friend, go up higher: then shalt thou have worship in the presence of them that sit at meat with thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 11, 'For whosoever exalteth himself shall be abased; and he that humbleth himself shall be exalted.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 12, 'Then said he also to him that bade him, When thou makest a dinner or a supper, call not thy friends, nor thy brethren, neither thy kinsmen, nor thy rich neighbours; lest they also bid thee again, and a recompence be made thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 13, 'But when thou makest a feast, call the poor, the maimed, the lame, the blind:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 14, 'And thou shalt be blessed; for they cannot recompense thee: for thou shalt be recompensed at the resurrection of the just.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 15, 'And when one of them that sat at meat with him heard these things, he said unto him, Blessed is he that shall eat bread in the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 16, 'Then said he unto him, A certain man made a great supper, and bade many:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 17, 'And sent his servant at supper time to say to them that were bidden, Come; for all things are now ready.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 18, 'And they all with one consent began to make excuse. The first said unto him, I have bought a piece of ground, and I must needs go and see it: I pray thee have me excused.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 19, 'And another said, I have bought five yoke of oxen, and I go to prove them: I pray thee have me excused.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 20, 'And another said, I have married a wife, and therefore I cannot come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 21, 'So that servant came, and shewed his lord these things. Then the master of the house being angry said to his servant, Go out quickly into the streets and lanes of the city, and bring in hither the poor, and the maimed, and the halt, and the blind.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 22, 'And the servant said, Lord, it is done as thou hast commanded, and yet there is room.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 23, 'And the lord said unto the servant, Go out into the highways and hedges, and compel them to come in, that my house may be filled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 24, 'For I say unto you, That none of those men which were bidden shall taste of my supper.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 25, 'And there went great multitudes with him: and he turned, and said unto them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 26, 'If any man come to me, and hate not his father, and mother, and wife, and children, and brethren, and sisters, yea, and his own life also, he cannot be my disciple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 27, 'And whosoever doth not bear his cross, and come after me, cannot be my disciple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 28, 'For which of you, intending to build a tower, sitteth not down first, and counteth the cost, whether he have sufficient to finish it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 29, 'Lest haply, after he hath laid the foundation, and is not able to finish it, all that behold it begin to mock him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 30, 'Saying, This man began to build, and was not able to finish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 31, 'Or what king, going to make war against another king, sitteth not down first, and consulteth whether he be able with ten thousand to meet him that cometh against him with twenty thousand?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 32, 'Or else, while the other is yet a great way off, he sendeth an ambassage, and desireth conditions of peace.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 33, 'So likewise, whosoever he be of you that forsaketh not all that he hath, he cannot be my disciple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 34, 'Salt is good: but if the salt have lost his savour, wherewith shall it be seasoned?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 14, 35, 'It is neither fit for the land, nor yet for the dunghill; but men cast it out. He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 1, 'Then drew near unto him all the publicans and sinners for to hear him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 2, 'And the Pharisees and scribes murmured, saying, This man receiveth sinners, and eateth with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 3, 'And he spake this parable unto them, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 4, 'What man of you, having an hundred sheep, if he lose one of them, doth not leave the ninety and nine in the wilderness, and go after that which is lost, until he find it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 5, 'And when he hath found it, he layeth it on his shoulders, rejoicing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 6, 'And when he cometh home, he calleth together his friends and neighbours, saying unto them, Rejoice with me; for I have found my sheep which was lost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 7, 'I say unto you, that likewise joy shall be in heaven over one sinner that repenteth, more than over ninety and nine just persons, which need no repentance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 8, 'Either what woman having ten pieces of silver, if she lose one piece, doth not light a candle, and sweep the house, and seek diligently till she find it?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 9, 'And when she hath found it, she calleth her friends and her neighbours together, saying, Rejoice with me; for I have found the piece which I had lost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 10, 'Likewise, I say unto you, there is joy in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner that repenteth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 11, 'And he said, A certain man had two sons:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 12, 'And the younger of them said to his father, Father, give me the portion of goods that falleth to me. And he divided unto them his living.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 13, 'And not many days after the younger son gathered all together, and took his journey into a far country, and there wasted his substance with riotous living.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 14, 'And when he had spent all, there arose a mighty famine in that land; and he began to be in want.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 15, 'And he went and joined himself to a citizen of that country; and he sent him into his fields to feed swine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 16, 'And he would fain have filled his belly with the husks that the swine did eat: and no man gave unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 17, 'And when he came to himself, he said, How many hired servants of my father''s have bread enough and to spare, and I perish with hunger!'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 18, 'I will arise and go to my father, and will say unto him, Father, I have sinned against heaven, and before thee,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 19, 'And am no more worthy to be called thy son: make me as one of thy hired servants.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 20, 'And he arose, and came to his father. But when he was yet a great way off, his father saw him, and had compassion, and ran, and fell on his neck, and kissed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 21, 'And the son said unto him, Father, I have sinned against heaven, and in thy sight, and am no more worthy to be called thy son.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 22, 'But the father said to his servants, Bring forth the best robe, and put it on him; and put a ring on his hand, and shoes on his feet:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 23, 'And bring hither the fatted calf, and kill it; and let us eat, and be merry:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 24, 'For this my son was dead, and is alive again; he was lost, and is found. And they began to be merry.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 25, 'Now his elder son was in the field: and as he came and drew nigh to the house, he heard musick and dancing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 26, 'And he called one of the servants, and asked what these things meant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 27, 'And he said unto him, Thy brother is come; and thy father hath killed the fatted calf, because he hath received him safe and sound.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 28, 'And he was angry, and would not go in: therefore came his father out, and intreated him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 29, 'And he answering said to his father, Lo, these many years do I serve thee, neither transgressed I at any time thy commandment: and yet thou never gavest me a kid, that I might make merry with my friends:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 30, 'But as soon as this thy son was come, which hath devoured thy living with harlots, thou hast killed for him the fatted calf.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 31, 'And he said unto him, Son, thou art ever with me, and all that I have is thine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 15, 32, 'It was meet that we should make merry, and be glad: for this thy brother was dead, and is alive again; and was lost, and is found.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 1, 'And he said also unto his disciples, There was a certain rich man, which had a steward; and the same was accused unto him that he had wasted his goods.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 2, 'And he called him, and said unto him, How is it that I hear this of thee? give an account of thy stewardship; for thou mayest be no longer steward.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 3, 'Then the steward said within himself, What shall I do? for my lord taketh away from me the stewardship: I cannot dig; to beg I am ashamed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 4, 'I am resolved what to do, that, when I am put out of the stewardship, they may receive me into their houses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 5, 'So he called every one of his lord''s debtors unto him, and said unto the first, How much owest thou unto my lord?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 6, 'And he said, An hundred measures of oil. And he said unto him, Take thy bill, and sit down quickly, and write fifty.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 7, 'Then said he to another, And how much owest thou? And he said, An hundred measures of wheat. And he said unto him, Take thy bill, and write fourscore.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 8, 'And the lord commended the unjust steward, because he had done wisely: for the children of this world are in their generation wiser than the children of light.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 9, 'And I say unto you, Make to yourselves friends of the mammon of unrighteousness; that, when ye fail, they may receive you into everlasting habitations.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 10, 'He that is faithful in that which is least is faithful also in much: and he that is unjust in the least is unjust also in much.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 11, 'If therefore ye have not been faithful in the unrighteous mammon, who will commit to your trust the true riches?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 12, 'And if ye have not been faithful in that which is another man''s, who shall give you that which is your own?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 13, 'No servant can serve two masters: for either he will hate the one, and love the other; or else he will hold to the one, and despise the other. Ye cannot serve God and mammon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 14, 'And the Pharisees also, who were covetous, heard all these things: and they derided him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 15, 'And he said unto them, Ye are they which justify yourselves before men; but God knoweth your hearts: for that which is highly esteemed among men is abomination in the sight of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 16, 'The law and the prophets were until John: since that time the kingdom of God is preached, and every man presseth into it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 17, 'And it is easier for heaven and earth to pass, than one tittle of the law to fail.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 18, 'Whosoever putteth away his wife, and marrieth another, committeth adultery: and whosoever marrieth her that is put away from her husband committeth adultery.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 19, 'There was a certain rich man, which was clothed in purple and fine linen, and fared sumptuously every day:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 20, 'And there was a certain beggar named Lazarus, which was laid at his gate, full of sores,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 21, 'And desiring to be fed with the crumbs which fell from the rich man''s table: moreover the dogs came and licked his sores.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 22, 'And it came to pass, that the beggar died, and was carried by the angels into Abraham''s bosom: the rich man also died, and was buried;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 23, 'And in hell he lift up his eyes, being in torments, and seeth Abraham afar off, and Lazarus in his bosom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 24, 'And he cried and said, Father Abraham, have mercy on me, and send Lazarus, that he may dip the tip of his finger in water, and cool my tongue; for I am tormented in this flame.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 25, 'But Abraham said, Son, remember that thou in thy lifetime receivedst thy good things, and likewise Lazarus evil things: but now he is comforted, and thou art tormented.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 26, 'And beside all this, between us and you there is a great gulf fixed: so that they which would pass from hence to you cannot; neither can they pass to us, that would come from thence.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 27, 'Then he said, I pray thee therefore, father, that thou wouldest send him to my father''s house:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 28, 'For I have five brethren; that he may testify unto them, lest they also come into this place of torment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 29, 'Abraham saith unto him, They have Moses and the prophets; let them hear them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 30, 'And he said, Nay, father Abraham: but if one went unto them from the dead, they will repent.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 16, 31, 'And he said unto him, If they hear not Moses and the prophets, neither will they be persuaded, though one rose from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 1, 'Then said he unto the disciples, It is impossible but that offences will come: but woe unto him, through whom they come!'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 2, 'It were better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he cast into the sea, than that he should offend one of these little ones.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 3, 'Take heed to yourselves: If thy brother trespass against thee, rebuke him; and if he repent, forgive him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 4, 'And if he trespass against thee seven times in a day, and seven times in a day turn again to thee, saying, I repent; thou shalt forgive him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 5, 'And the apostles said unto the Lord, Increase our faith.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 6, 'And the Lord said, If ye had faith as a grain of mustard seed, ye might say unto this sycamine tree, Be thou plucked up by the root, and be thou planted in the sea; and it should obey you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 7, 'But which of you, having a servant plowing or feeding cattle, will say unto him by and by, when he is come from the field, Go and sit down to meat?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 8, 'And will not rather say unto him, Make ready wherewith I may sup, and gird thyself, and serve me, till I have eaten and drunken; and afterward thou shalt eat and drink?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 9, 'Doth he thank that servant because he did the things that were commanded him? I trow not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 10, 'So likewise ye, when ye shall have done all those things which are commanded you, say, We are unprofitable servants: we have done that which was our duty to do.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 11, 'And it came to pass, as he went to Jerusalem, that he passed through the midst of Samaria and Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 12, 'And as he entered into a certain village, there met him ten men that were lepers, which stood afar off:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 13, 'And they lifted up their voices, and said, Jesus, Master, have mercy on us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 14, 'And when he saw them, he said unto them, Go shew yourselves unto the priests. And it came to pass, that, as they went, they were cleansed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 15, 'And one of them, when he saw that he was healed, turned back, and with a loud voice glorified God,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 16, 'And fell down on his face at his feet, giving him thanks: and he was a Samaritan.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 17, 'And Jesus answering said, Were there not ten cleansed? but where are the nine?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 18, 'There are not found that returned to give glory to God, save this stranger.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 19, 'And he said unto him, Arise, go thy way: thy faith hath made thee whole.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 20, 'And when he was demanded of the Pharisees, when the kingdom of God should come, he answered them and said, The kingdom of God cometh not with observation:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 21, 'Neither shall they say, Lo here! or, lo there! for, behold, the kingdom of God is within you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 22, 'And he said unto the disciples, The days will come, when ye shall desire to see one of the days of the Son of man, and ye shall not see it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 23, 'And they shall say to you, See here; or, see there: go not after them, nor follow them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 24, 'For as the lightning, that lighteneth out of the one part under heaven, shineth unto the other part under heaven; so shall also the Son of man be in his day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 25, 'But first must he suffer many things, and be rejected of this generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 26, 'And as it was in the days of Noe, so shall it be also in the days of the Son of man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 27, 'They did eat, they drank, they married wives, they were given in marriage, until the day that Noe entered into the ark, and the flood came, and destroyed them all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 28, 'Likewise also as it was in the days of Lot; they did eat, they drank, they bought, they sold, they planted, they builded;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 29, 'But the same day that Lot went out of Sodom it rained fire and brimstone from heaven, and destroyed them all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 30, 'Even thus shall it be in the day when the Son of man is revealed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 31, 'In that day, he which shall be upon the housetop, and his stuff in the house, let him not come down to take it away: and he that is in the field, let him likewise not return back.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 32, 'Remember Lot''s wife.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 33, 'Whosoever shall seek to save his life shall lose it; and whosoever shall lose his life shall preserve it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 34, 'I tell you, in that night there shall be two men in one bed; the one shall be taken, and the other shall be left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 35, 'Two women shall be grinding together; the one shall be taken, and the other left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 36, 'Two men shall be in the field; the one shall be taken, and the other left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 17, 37, 'And they answered and said unto him, Where, Lord? And he said unto them, Wheresoever the body is, thither will the eagles be gathered together.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 1, 'And he spake a parable unto them to this end, that men ought always to pray, and not to faint;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 2, 'Saying, There was in a city a judge, which feared not God, neither regarded man:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 3, 'And there was a widow in that city; and she came unto him, saying, Avenge me of mine adversary.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 4, 'And he would not for a while: but afterward he said within himself, Though I fear not God, nor regard man;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 5, 'Yet because this widow troubleth me, I will avenge her, lest by her continual coming she weary me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 6, 'And the Lord said, Hear what the unjust judge saith.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 7, 'And shall not God avenge his own elect, which cry day and night unto him, though he bear long with them?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 8, 'I tell you that he will avenge them speedily. Nevertheless when the Son of man cometh, shall he find faith on the earth?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 9, 'And he spake this parable unto certain which trusted in themselves that they were righteous, and despised others:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 10, 'Two men went up into the temple to pray; the one a Pharisee, and the other a publican.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 11, 'The Pharisee stood and prayed thus with himself, God, I thank thee, that I am not as other men are, extortioners, unjust, adulterers, or even as this publican.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 12, 'I fast twice in the week, I give tithes of all that I possess.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 13, 'And the publican, standing afar off, would not lift up so much as his eyes unto heaven, but smote upon his breast, saying, God be merciful to me a sinner.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 14, 'I tell you, this man went down to his house justified rather than the other: for every one that exalteth himself shall be abased; and he that humbleth himself shall be exalted.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 15, 'And they brought unto him also infants, that he would touch them: but when his disciples saw it, they rebuked them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 16, 'But Jesus called them unto him, and said, Suffer little children to come unto me, and forbid them not: for of such is the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 17, 'Verily I say unto you, Whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God as a little child shall in no wise enter therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 18, 'And a certain ruler asked him, saying, Good Master, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 19, 'And Jesus said unto him, Why callest thou me good? none is good, save one, that is, God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 20, 'Thou knowest the commandments, Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Honour thy father and thy mother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 21, 'And he said, All these have I kept from my youth up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 22, 'Now when Jesus heard these things, he said unto him, Yet lackest thou one thing: sell all that thou hast, and distribute unto the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven: and come, follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 23, 'And when he heard this, he was very sorrowful: for he was very rich.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 24, 'And when Jesus saw that he was very sorrowful, he said, How hardly shall they that have riches enter into the kingdom of God!'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 25, 'For it is easier for a camel to go through a needle''s eye, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 26, 'And they that heard it said, Who then can be saved?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 27, 'And he said, The things which are impossible with men are possible with God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 28, 'Then Peter said, Lo, we have left all, and followed thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 29, 'And he said unto them, Verily I say unto you, There is no man that hath left house, or parents, or brethren, or wife, or children, for the kingdom of God''s sake,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 30, 'Who shall not receive manifold more in this present time, and in the world to come life everlasting.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 31, 'Then he took unto him the twelve, and said unto them, Behold, we go up to Jerusalem, and all things that are written by the prophets concerning the Son of man shall be accomplished.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 32, 'For he shall be delivered unto the Gentiles, and shall be mocked, and spitefully entreated, and spitted on:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 33, 'And they shall scourge him, and put him to death: and the third day he shall rise again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 34, 'And they understood none of these things: and this saying was hid from them, neither knew they the things which were spoken.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 35, 'And it came to pass, that as he was come nigh unto Jericho, a certain blind man sat by the way side begging:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 36, 'And hearing the multitude pass by, he asked what it meant.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 37, 'And they told him, that Jesus of Nazareth passeth by.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 38, 'And he cried, saying, Jesus, thou Son of David, have mercy on me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 39, 'And they which went before rebuked him, that he should hold his peace: but he cried so much the more, Thou Son of David, have mercy on me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 40, 'And Jesus stood, and commanded him to be brought unto him: and when he was come near, he asked him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 41, 'Saying, What wilt thou that I shall do unto thee? And he said, Lord, that I may receive my sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 42, 'And Jesus said unto him, Receive thy sight: thy faith hath saved thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 18, 43, 'And immediately he received his sight, and followed him, glorifying God: and all the people, when they saw it, gave praise unto God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 1, 'And Jesus entered and passed through Jericho.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 2, 'And, behold, there was a man named Zacchaeus, which was the chief among the publicans, and he was rich.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 3, 'And he sought to see Jesus who he was; and could not for the press, because he was little of stature.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 4, 'And he ran before, and climbed up into a sycomore tree to see him: for he was to pass that way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 5, 'And when Jesus came to the place, he looked up, and saw him, and said unto him, Zacchaeus, make haste, and come down; for to day I must abide at thy house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 6, 'And he made haste, and came down, and received him joyfully.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 7, 'And when they saw it, they all murmured, saying, That he was gone to be guest with a man that is a sinner.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 8, 'And Zacchaeus stood, and said unto the Lord; Behold, Lord, the half of my goods I give to the poor; and if I have taken any thing from any man by false accusation, I restore him fourfold.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 9, 'And Jesus said unto him, This day is salvation come to this house, forsomuch as he also is a son of Abraham.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 10, 'For the Son of man is come to seek and to save that which was lost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 11, 'And as they heard these things, he added and spake a parable, because he was nigh to Jerusalem, and because they thought that the kingdom of God should immediately appear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 12, 'He said therefore, A certain nobleman went into a far country to receive for himself a kingdom, and to return.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 13, 'And he called his ten servants, and delivered them ten pounds, and said unto them, Occupy till I come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 14, 'But his citizens hated him, and sent a message after him, saying, We will not have this man to reign over us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 15, 'And it came to pass, that when he was returned, having received the kingdom, then he commanded these servants to be called unto him, to whom he had given the money, that he might know how much every man had gained by trading.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 16, 'Then came the first, saying, Lord, thy pound hath gained ten pounds.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 17, 'And he said unto him, Well, thou good servant: because thou hast been faithful in a very little, have thou authority over ten cities.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 18, 'And the second came, saying, Lord, thy pound hath gained five pounds.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 19, 'And he said likewise to him, Be thou also over five cities.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 20, 'And another came, saying, Lord, behold, here is thy pound, which I have kept laid up in a napkin:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 21, 'For I feared thee, because thou art an austere man: thou takest up that thou layedst not down, and reapest that thou didst not sow.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 22, 'And he saith unto him, Out of thine own mouth will I judge thee, thou wicked servant. Thou knewest that I was an austere man, taking up that I laid not down, and reaping that I did not sow:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 23, 'Wherefore then gavest not thou my money into the bank, that at my coming I might have required mine own with usury?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 24, 'And he said unto them that stood by, Take from him the pound, and give it to him that hath ten pounds.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 25, '(And they said unto him, Lord, he hath ten pounds.)'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 26, 'For I say unto you, That unto every one which hath shall be given; and from him that hath not, even that he hath shall be taken away from him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 27, 'But those mine enemies, which would not that I should reign over them, bring hither, and slay them before me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 28, 'And when he had thus spoken, he went before, ascending up to Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 29, 'And it came to pass, when he was come nigh to Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount called the mount of Olives, he sent two of his disciples,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 30, 'Saying, Go ye into the village over against you; in the which at your entering ye shall find a colt tied, whereon yet never man sat: loose him, and bring him hither.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 31, 'And if any man ask you, Why do ye loose him? thus shall ye say unto him, Because the Lord hath need of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 32, 'And they that were sent went their way, and found even as he had said unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 33, 'And as they were loosing the colt, the owners thereof said unto them, Why loose ye the colt?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 34, 'And they said, The Lord hath need of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 35, 'And they brought him to Jesus: and they cast their garments upon the colt, and they set Jesus thereon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 36, 'And as he went, they spread their clothes in the way.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 37, 'And when he was come nigh, even now at the descent of the mount of Olives, the whole multitude of the disciples began to rejoice and praise God with a loud voice for all the mighty works that they had seen;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 38, 'Saying, Blessed be the King that cometh in the name of the Lord: peace in heaven, and glory in the highest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 39, 'And some of the Pharisees from among the multitude said unto him, Master, rebuke thy disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 40, 'And he answered and said unto them, I tell you that, if these should hold their peace, the stones would immediately cry out.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 41, 'And when he was come near, he beheld the city, and wept over it,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 42, 'Saying, If thou hadst known, even thou, at least in this thy day, the things which belong unto thy peace! but now they are hid from thine eyes.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 43, 'For the days shall come upon thee, that thine enemies shall cast a trench about thee, and compass thee round, and keep thee in on every side,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 44, 'And shall lay thee even with the ground, and thy children within thee; and they shall not leave in thee one stone upon another; because thou knewest not the time of thy visitation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 45, 'And he went into the temple, and began to cast out them that sold therein, and them that bought;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 46, 'Saying unto them, It is written, My house is the house of prayer: but ye have made it a den of thieves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 47, 'And he taught daily in the temple. But the chief priests and the scribes and the chief of the people sought to destroy him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 19, 48, 'And could not find what they might do: for all the people were very attentive to hear him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 1, 'And it came to pass, that on one of those days, as he taught the people in the temple, and preached the gospel, the chief priests and the scribes came upon him with the elders,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 2, 'And spake unto him, saying, Tell us, by what authority doest thou these things? or who is he that gave thee this authority?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 3, 'And he answered and said unto them, I will also ask you one thing; and answer me:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 4, 'The baptism of John, was it from heaven, or of men?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 5, 'And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say, Why then believed ye him not?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 6, 'But and if we say, Of men; all the people will stone us: for they be persuaded that John was a prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 7, 'And they answered, that they could not tell whence it was.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 8, 'And Jesus said unto them, Neither tell I you by what authority I do these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 9, 'Then began he to speak to the people this parable; A certain man planted a vineyard, and let it forth to husbandmen, and went into a far country for a long time.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 10, 'And at the season he sent a servant to the husbandmen, that they should give him of the fruit of the vineyard: but the husbandmen beat him, and sent him away empty.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 11, 'And again he sent another servant: and they beat him also, and entreated him shamefully, and sent him away empty.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 12, 'And again he sent a third: and they wounded him also, and cast him out.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 13, 'Then said the lord of the vineyard, What shall I do? I will send my beloved son: it may be they will reverence him when they see him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 14, 'But when the husbandmen saw him, they reasoned among themselves, saying, This is the heir: come, let us kill him, that the inheritance may be ours.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 15, 'So they cast him out of the vineyard, and killed him. What therefore shall the lord of the vineyard do unto them?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 16, 'He shall come and destroy these husbandmen, and shall give the vineyard to others. And when they heard it, they said, God forbid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 17, 'And he beheld them, and said, What is this then that is written, The stone which the builders rejected, the same is become the head of the corner?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 18, 'Whosoever shall fall upon that stone shall be broken; but on whomsoever it shall fall, it will grind him to powder.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 19, 'And the chief priests and the scribes the same hour sought to lay hands on him; and they feared the people: for they perceived that he had spoken this parable against them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 20, 'And they watched him, and sent forth spies, which should feign themselves just men, that they might take hold of his words, that so they might deliver him unto the power and authority of the governor.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 21, 'And they asked him, saying, Master, we know that thou sayest and teachest rightly, neither acceptest thou the person of any, but teachest the way of God truly:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 22, 'Is it lawful for us to give tribute unto Caesar, or no?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 23, 'But he perceived their craftiness, and said unto them, Why tempt ye me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 24, 'Shew me a penny. Whose image and superscription hath it? They answered and said, Caesar''s.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 25, 'And he said unto them, Render therefore unto Caesar the things which be Caesar''s, and unto God the things which be God''s.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 26, 'And they could not take hold of his words before the people: and they marvelled at his answer, and held their peace.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 27, 'Then came to him certain of the Sadducees, which deny that there is any resurrection; and they asked him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 28, 'Saying, Master, Moses wrote unto us, If any man''s brother die, having a wife, and he die without children, that his brother should take his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 29, 'There were therefore seven brethren: and the first took a wife, and died without children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 30, 'And the second took her to wife, and he died childless.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 31, 'And the third took her; and in like manner the seven also: and they left no children, and died.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 32, 'Last of all the woman died also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 33, 'Therefore in the resurrection whose wife of them is she? for seven had her to wife.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 34, 'And Jesus answering said unto them, The children of this world marry, and are given in marriage:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 35, 'But they which shall be accounted worthy to obtain that world, and the resurrection from the dead, neither marry, nor are given in marriage:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 36, 'Neither can they die any more: for they are equal unto the angels; and are the children of God, being the children of the resurrection.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 37, 'Now that the dead are raised, even Moses shewed at the bush, when he calleth the Lord the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 38, 'For he is not a God of the dead, but of the living: for all live unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 39, 'Then certain of the scribes answering said, Master, thou hast well said.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 40, 'And after that they durst not ask him any question at all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 41, 'And he said unto them, How say they that Christ is David''s son?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 42, 'And David himself saith in the book of Psalms, The LORD said unto my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 43, 'Till I make thine enemies thy footstool.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 44, 'David therefore calleth him Lord, how is he then his son?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 45, 'Then in the audience of all the people he said unto his disciples,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 46, 'Beware of the scribes, which desire to walk in long robes, and love greetings in the markets, and the highest seats in the synagogues, and the chief rooms at feasts;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 20, 47, 'Which devour widows'' houses, and for a shew make long prayers: the same shall receive greater damnation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 1, 'And he looked up, and saw the rich men casting their gifts into the treasury.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 2, 'And he saw also a certain poor widow casting in thither two mites.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 3, 'And he said, Of a truth I say unto you, that this poor widow hath cast in more than they all:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 4, 'For all these have of their abundance cast in unto the offerings of God: but she of her penury hath cast in all the living that she had.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 5, 'And as some spake of the temple, how it was adorned with goodly stones and gifts, he said,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 6, 'As for these things which ye behold, the days will come, in the which there shall not be left one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 7, 'And they asked him, saying, Master, but when shall these things be? and what sign will there be when these things shall come to pass?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 8, 'And he said, Take heed that ye be not deceived: for many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and the time draweth near: go ye not therefore after them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 9, 'But when ye shall hear of wars and commotions, be not terrified: for these things must first come to pass; but the end is not by and by.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 10, 'Then said he unto them, Nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 11, 'And great earthquakes shall be in divers places, and famines, and pestilences; and fearful sights and great signs shall there be from heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 12, 'But before all these, they shall lay their hands on you, and persecute you, delivering you up to the synagogues, and into prisons, being brought before kings and rulers for my name''s sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 13, 'And it shall turn to you for a testimony.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 14, 'Settle it therefore in your hearts, not to meditate before what ye shall answer:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 15, 'For I will give you a mouth and wisdom, which all your adversaries shall not be able to gainsay nor resist.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 16, 'And ye shall be betrayed both by parents, and brethren, and kinsfolks, and friends; and some of you shall they cause to be put to death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 17, 'And ye shall be hated of all men for my name''s sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 18, 'But there shall not an hair of your head perish.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 19, 'In your patience possess ye your souls.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 20, 'And when ye shall see Jerusalem compassed with armies, then know that the desolation thereof is nigh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 21, 'Then let them which are in Judaea flee to the mountains; and let them which are in the midst of it depart out; and let not them that are in the countries enter thereinto.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 22, 'For these be the days of vengeance, that all things which are written may be fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 23, 'But woe unto them that are with child, and to them that give suck, in those days! for there shall be great distress in the land, and wrath upon this people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 24, 'And they shall fall by the edge of the sword, and shall be led away captive into all nations: and Jerusalem shall be trodden down of the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles be fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 25, 'And there shall be signs in the sun, and in the moon, and in the stars; and upon the earth distress of nations, with perplexity; the sea and the waves roaring;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 26, 'Men''s hearts failing them for fear, and for looking after those things which are coming on the earth: for the powers of heaven shall be shaken.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 27, 'And then shall they see the Son of man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 28, 'And when these things begin to come to pass, then look up, and lift up your heads; for your redemption draweth nigh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 29, 'And he spake to them a parable; Behold the fig tree, and all the trees;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 30, 'When they now shoot forth, ye see and know of your own selves that summer is now nigh at hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 31, 'So likewise ye, when ye see these things come to pass, know ye that the kingdom of God is nigh at hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 32, 'Verily I say unto you, This generation shall not pass away, till all be fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 33, 'Heaven and earth shall pass away: but my words shall not pass away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 34, 'And take heed to yourselves, lest at any time your hearts be overcharged with surfeiting, and drunkenness, and cares of this life, and so that day come upon you unawares.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 35, 'For as a snare shall it come on all them that dwell on the face of the whole earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 36, 'Watch ye therefore, and pray always, that ye may be accounted worthy to escape all these things that shall come to pass, and to stand before the Son of man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 37, 'And in the day time he was teaching in the temple; and at night he went out, and abode in the mount that is called the mount of Olives.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 21, 38, 'And all the people came early in the morning to him in the temple, for to hear him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 1, 'Now the feast of unleavened bread drew nigh, which is called the Passover.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 2, 'And the chief priests and scribes sought how they might kill him; for they feared the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 3, 'Then entered Satan into Judas surnamed Iscariot, being of the number of the twelve.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 4, 'And he went his way, and communed with the chief priests and captains, how he might betray him unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 5, 'And they were glad, and covenanted to give him money.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 6, 'And he promised, and sought opportunity to betray him unto them in the absence of the multitude.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 7, 'Then came the day of unleavened bread, when the passover must be killed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 8, 'And he sent Peter and John, saying, Go and prepare us the passover, that we may eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 9, 'And they said unto him, Where wilt thou that we prepare?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 10, 'And he said unto them, Behold, when ye are entered into the city, there shall a man meet you, bearing a pitcher of water; follow him into the house where he entereth in.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 11, 'And ye shall say unto the goodman of the house, The Master saith unto thee, Where is the guestchamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 12, 'And he shall shew you a large upper room furnished: there make ready.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 13, 'And they went, and found as he had said unto them: and they made ready the passover.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 14, 'And when the hour was come, he sat down, and the twelve apostles with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 15, 'And he said unto them, With desire I have desired to eat this passover with you before I suffer:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 16, 'For I say unto you, I will not any more eat thereof, until it be fulfilled in the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 17, 'And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and said, Take this, and divide it among yourselves:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 18, 'For I say unto you, I will not drink of the fruit of the vine, until the kingdom of God shall come.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 19, 'And he took bread, and gave thanks, and brake it, and gave unto them, saying, This is my body which is given for you: this do in remembrance of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 20, 'Likewise also the cup after supper, saying, This cup is the new testament in my blood, which is shed for you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 21, 'But, behold, the hand of him that betrayeth me is with me on the table.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 22, 'And truly the Son of man goeth, as it was determined: but woe unto that man by whom he is betrayed!'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 23, 'And they began to enquire among themselves, which of them it was that should do this thing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 24, 'And there was also a strife among them, which of them should be accounted the greatest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 25, 'And he said unto them, The kings of the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and they that exercise authority upon them are called benefactors.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 26, 'But ye shall not be so: but he that is greatest among you, let him be as the younger; and he that is chief, as he that doth serve.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 27, 'For whether is greater, he that sitteth at meat, or he that serveth? is not he that sitteth at meat? but I am among you as he that serveth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 28, 'Ye are they which have continued with me in my temptations.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 29, 'And I appoint unto you a kingdom, as my Father hath appointed unto me;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 30, 'That ye may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 31, 'And the Lord said, Simon, Simon, behold, Satan hath desired to have you, that he may sift you as wheat:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 32, 'But I have prayed for thee, that thy faith fail not: and when thou art converted, strengthen thy brethren.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 33, 'And he said unto him, Lord, I am ready to go with thee, both into prison, and to death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 34, 'And he said, I tell thee, Peter, the cock shall not crow this day, before that thou shalt thrice deny that thou knowest me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 35, 'And he said unto them, When I sent you without purse, and scrip, and shoes, lacked ye any thing? And they said, Nothing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 36, 'Then said he unto them, But now, he that hath a purse, let him take it, and likewise his scrip: and he that hath no sword, let him sell his garment, and buy one.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 37, 'For I say unto you, that this that is written must yet be accomplished in me, And he was reckoned among the transgressors: for the things concerning me have an end.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 38, 'And they said, Lord, behold, here are two swords. And he said unto them, It is enough.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 39, 'And he came out, and went, as he was wont, to the mount of Olives; and his disciples also followed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 40, 'And when he was at the place, he said unto them, Pray that ye enter not into temptation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 41, 'And he was withdrawn from them about a stone''s cast, and kneeled down, and prayed,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 42, 'Saying, Father, if thou be willing, remove this cup from me: nevertheless not my will, but thine, be done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 43, 'And there appeared an angel unto him from heaven, strengthening him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 44, 'And being in an agony he prayed more earnestly: and his sweat was as it were great drops of blood falling down to the ground.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 45, 'And when he rose up from prayer, and was come to his disciples, he found them sleeping for sorrow,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 46, 'And said unto them, Why sleep ye? rise and pray, lest ye enter into temptation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 47, 'And while he yet spake, behold a multitude, and he that was called Judas, one of the twelve, went before them, and drew near unto Jesus to kiss him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 48, 'But Jesus said unto him, Judas, betrayest thou the Son of man with a kiss?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 49, 'When they which were about him saw what would follow, they said unto him, Lord, shall we smite with the sword?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 50, 'And one of them smote the servant of the high priest, and cut off his right ear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 51, 'And Jesus answered and said, Suffer ye thus far. And he touched his ear, and healed him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 52, 'Then Jesus said unto the chief priests, and captains of the temple, and the elders, which were come to him, Be ye come out, as against a thief, with swords and staves?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 53, 'When I was daily with you in the temple, ye stretched forth no hands against me: but this is your hour, and the power of darkness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 54, 'Then took they him, and led him, and brought him into the high priest''s house. And Peter followed afar off.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 55, 'And when they had kindled a fire in the midst of the hall, and were set down together, Peter sat down among them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 56, 'But a certain maid beheld him as he sat by the fire, and earnestly looked upon him, and said, This man was also with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 57, 'And he denied him, saying, Woman, I know him not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 58, 'And after a little while another saw him, and said, Thou art also of them. And Peter said, Man, I am not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 59, 'And about the space of one hour after another confidently affirmed, saying, Of a truth this fellow also was with him: for he is a Galilaean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 60, 'And Peter said, Man, I know not what thou sayest. And immediately, while he yet spake, the cock crew.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 61, 'And the Lord turned, and looked upon Peter. And Peter remembered the word of the Lord, how he had said unto him, Before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 62, 'And Peter went out, and wept bitterly.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 63, 'And the men that held Jesus mocked him, and smote him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 64, 'And when they had blindfolded him, they struck him on the face, and asked him, saying, Prophesy, who is it that smote thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 65, 'And many other things blasphemously spake they against him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 66, 'And as soon as it was day, the elders of the people and the chief priests and the scribes came together, and led him into their council, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 67, 'Art thou the Christ? tell us. And he said unto them, If I tell you, ye will not believe:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 68, 'And if I also ask you, ye will not answer me, nor let me go.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 69, 'Hereafter shall the Son of man sit on the right hand of the power of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 70, 'Then said they all, Art thou then the Son of God? And he said unto them, Ye say that I am.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 22, 71, 'And they said, What need we any further witness? for we ourselves have heard of his own mouth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 1, 'And the whole multitude of them arose, and led him unto Pilate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 2, 'And they began to accuse him, saying, We found this fellow perverting the nation, and forbidding to give tribute to Caesar, saying that he himself is Christ a King.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 3, 'And Pilate asked him, saying, Art thou the King of the Jews? And he answered him and said, Thou sayest it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 4, 'Then said Pilate to the chief priests and to the people, I find no fault in this man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 5, 'And they were the more fierce, saying, He stirreth up the people, teaching throughout all Jewry, beginning from Galilee to this place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 6, 'When Pilate heard of Galilee, he asked whether the man were a Galilaean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 7, 'And as soon as he knew that he belonged unto Herod''s jurisdiction, he sent him to Herod, who himself also was at Jerusalem at that time.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 8, 'And when Herod saw Jesus, he was exceeding glad: for he was desirous to see him of a long season, because he had heard many things of him; and he hoped to have seen some miracle done by him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 9, 'Then he questioned with him in many words; but he answered him nothing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 10, 'And the chief priests and scribes stood and vehemently accused him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 11, 'And Herod with his men of war set him at nought, and mocked him, and arrayed him in a gorgeous robe, and sent him again to Pilate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 12, 'And the same day Pilate and Herod were made friends together: for before they were at enmity between themselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 13, 'And Pilate, when he had called together the chief priests and the rulers and the people,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 14, 'Said unto them, Ye have brought this man unto me, as one that perverteth the people: and, behold, I, having examined him before you, have found no fault in this man touching those things whereof ye accuse him:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 15, 'No, nor yet Herod: for I sent you to him; and, lo, nothing worthy of death is done unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 16, 'I will therefore chastise him, and release him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 17, '(For of necessity he must release one unto them at the feast.)'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 18, 'And they cried out all at once, saying, Away with this man, and release unto us Barabbas:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 19, '(Who for a certain sedition made in the city, and for murder, was cast into prison.)'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 20, 'Pilate therefore, willing to release Jesus, spake again to them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 21, 'But they cried, saying, Crucify him, crucify him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 22, 'And he said unto them the third time, Why, what evil hath he done? I have found no cause of death in him: I will therefore chastise him, and let him go.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 23, 'And they were instant with loud voices, requiring that he might be crucified. And the voices of them and of the chief priests prevailed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 24, 'And Pilate gave sentence that it should be as they required.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 25, 'And he released unto them him that for sedition and murder was cast into prison, whom they had desired; but he delivered Jesus to their will.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 26, 'And as they led him away, they laid hold upon one Simon, a Cyrenian, coming out of the country, and on him they laid the cross, that he might bear it after Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 27, 'And there followed him a great company of people, and of women, which also bewailed and lamented him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 28, 'But Jesus turning unto them said, Daughters of Jerusalem, weep not for me, but weep for yourselves, and for your children.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 29, 'For, behold, the days are coming, in the which they shall say, Blessed are the barren, and the wombs that never bare, and the paps which never gave suck.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 30, 'Then shall they begin to say to the mountains, Fall on us; and to the hills, Cover us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 31, 'For if they do these things in a green tree, what shall be done in the dry?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 32, 'And there were also two other, malefactors, led with him to be put to death.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 33, 'And when they were come to the place, which is called Calvary, there they crucified him, and the malefactors, one on the right hand, and the other on the left.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 34, 'Then said Jesus, Father, forgive them; for they know not what they do. And they parted his raiment, and cast lots.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 35, 'And the people stood beholding. And the rulers also with them derided him, saying, He saved others; let him save himself, if he be Christ, the chosen of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 36, 'And the soldiers also mocked him, coming to him, and offering him vinegar,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 37, 'And saying, If thou be the king of the Jews, save thyself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 38, 'And a superscription also was written over him in letters of Greek, and Latin, and Hebrew, THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 39, 'And one of the malefactors which were hanged railed on him, saying, If thou be Christ, save thyself and us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 40, 'But the other answering rebuked him, saying, Dost not thou fear God, seeing thou art in the same condemnation?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 41, 'And we indeed justly; for we receive the due reward of our deeds: but this man hath done nothing amiss.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 42, 'And he said unto Jesus, Lord, remember me when thou comest into thy kingdom.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 43, 'And Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto thee, To day shalt thou be with me in paradise.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 44, 'And it was about the sixth hour, and there was a darkness over all the earth until the ninth hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 45, 'And the sun was darkened, and the veil of the temple was rent in the midst.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 46, 'And when Jesus had cried with a loud voice, he said, Father, into thy hands I commend my spirit: and having said thus, he gave up the ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 47, 'Now when the centurion saw what was done, he glorified God, saying, Certainly this was a righteous man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 48, 'And all the people that came together to that sight, beholding the things which were done, smote their breasts, and returned.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 49, 'And all his acquaintance, and the women that followed him from Galilee, stood afar off, beholding these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 50, 'And, behold, there was a man named Joseph, a counsellor; and he was a good man, and a just:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 51, '(The same had not consented to the counsel and deed of them;) he was of Arimathaea, a city of the Jews: who also himself waited for the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 52, 'This man went unto Pilate, and begged the body of Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 53, 'And he took it down, and wrapped it in linen, and laid it in a sepulchre that was hewn in stone, wherein never man before was laid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 54, 'And that day was the preparation, and the sabbath drew on.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 55, 'And the women also, which came with him from Galilee, followed after, and beheld the sepulchre, and how his body was laid.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 23, 56, 'And they returned, and prepared spices and ointments; and rested the sabbath day according to the commandment.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 1, 'Now upon the first day of the week, very early in the morning, they came unto the sepulchre, bringing the spices which they had prepared, and certain others with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 2, 'And they found the stone rolled away from the sepulchre.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 3, 'And they entered in, and found not the body of the Lord Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 4, 'And it came to pass, as they were much perplexed thereabout, behold, two men stood by them in shining garments:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 5, 'And as they were afraid, and bowed down their faces to the earth, they said unto them, Why seek ye the living among the dead?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 6, 'He is not here, but is risen: remember how he spake unto you when he was yet in Galilee,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 7, 'Saying, The Son of man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified, and the third day rise again.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 8, 'And they remembered his words,')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 9, 'And returned from the sepulchre, and told all these things unto the eleven, and to all the rest.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 10, 'It was Mary Magdalene, and Joanna, and Mary the mother of James, and other women that were with them, which told these things unto the apostles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 11, 'And their words seemed to them as idle tales, and they believed them not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 12, 'Then arose Peter, and ran unto the sepulchre; and stooping down, he beheld the linen clothes laid by themselves, and departed, wondering in himself at that which was come to pass.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 13, 'And, behold, two of them went that same day to a village called Emmaus, which was from Jerusalem about threescore furlongs.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 14, 'And they talked together of all these things which had happened.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 15, 'And it came to pass, that, while they communed together and reasoned, Jesus himself drew near, and went with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 16, 'But their eyes were holden that they should not know him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 17, 'And he said unto them, What manner of communications are these that ye have one to another, as ye walk, and are sad?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 18, 'And the one of them, whose name was Cleopas, answering said unto him, Art thou only a stranger in Jerusalem, and hast not known the things which are come to pass there in these days?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 19, 'And he said unto them, What things? And they said unto him, Concerning Jesus of Nazareth, which was a prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 20, 'And how the chief priests and our rulers delivered him to be condemned to death, and have crucified him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 21, 'But we trusted that it had been he which should have redeemed Israel: and beside all this, to day is the third day since these things were done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 22, 'Yea, and certain women also of our company made us astonished, which were early at the sepulchre;'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 23, 'And when they found not his body, they came, saying, that they had also seen a vision of angels, which said that he was alive.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 24, 'And certain of them which were with us went to the sepulchre, and found it even so as the women had said: but him they saw not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 25, 'Then he said unto them, O fools, and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 26, 'Ought not Christ to have suffered these things, and to enter into his glory?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 27, 'And beginning at Moses and all the prophets, he expounded unto them in all the scriptures the things concerning himself.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 28, 'And they drew nigh unto the village, whither they went: and he made as though he would have gone further.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 29, 'But they constrained him, saying, Abide with us: for it is toward evening, and the day is far spent. And he went in to tarry with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 30, 'And it came to pass, as he sat at meat with them, he took bread, and blessed it, and brake, and gave to them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 31, 'And their eyes were opened, and they knew him; and he vanished out of their sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 32, 'And they said one to another, Did not our heart burn within us, while he talked with us by the way, and while he opened to us the scriptures?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 33, 'And they rose up the same hour, and returned to Jerusalem, and found the eleven gathered together, and them that were with them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 34, 'Saying, The Lord is risen indeed, and hath appeared to Simon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 35, 'And they told what things were done in the way, and how he was known of them in breaking of bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 36, 'And as they thus spake, Jesus himself stood in the midst of them, and saith unto them, Peace be unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 37, 'But they were terrified and affrighted, and supposed that they had seen a spirit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 38, 'And he said unto them, Why are ye troubled? and why do thoughts arise in your hearts?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 39, 'Behold my hands and my feet, that it is I myself: handle me, and see; for a spirit hath not flesh and bones, as ye see me have.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 40, 'And when he had thus spoken, he shewed them his hands and his feet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 41, 'And while they yet believed not for joy, and wondered, he said unto them, Have ye here any meat?'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 42, 'And they gave him a piece of a broiled fish, and of an honeycomb.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 43, 'And he took it, and did eat before them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 44, 'And he said unto them, These are the words which I spake unto you, while I was yet with you, that all things must be fulfilled, which were written in the law of Moses, and in the prophets, and in the psalms, concerning me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 45, 'Then opened he their understanding, that they might understand the scriptures,'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 46, 'And said unto them, Thus it is written, and thus it behoved Christ to suffer, and to rise from the dead the third day:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 47, 'And that repentance and remission of sins should be preached in his name among all nations, beginning at Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 48, 'And ye are witnesses of these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 49, 'And, behold, I send the promise of my Father upon you: but tarry ye in the city of Jerusalem, until ye be endued with power from on high.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 50, 'And he led them out as far as to Bethany, and he lifted up his hands, and blessed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 51, 'And it came to pass, while he blessed them, he was parted from them, and carried up into heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 52, 'And they worshipped him, and returned to Jerusalem with great joy:'),
  ('KJV', 'Luke', 42, 24, 53, 'And were continually in the temple, praising and blessing God. Amen.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 1, 'In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 2, 'The same was in the beginning with God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 3, 'All things were made by him; and without him was not any thing made that was made.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 4, 'In him was life; and the life was the light of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 5, 'And the light shineth in darkness; and the darkness comprehended it not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 6, 'There was a man sent from God, whose name was John.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 7, 'The same came for a witness, to bear witness of the Light, that all men through him might believe.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 8, 'He was not that Light, but was sent to bear witness of that Light.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 9, 'That was the true Light, which lighteth every man that cometh into the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 10, 'He was in the world, and the world was made by him, and the world knew him not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 11, 'He came unto his own, and his own received him not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 12, 'But as many as received him, to them gave he power to become the sons of God, even to them that believe on his name:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 13, 'Which were born, not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 14, 'And the Word was made flesh, and dwelt among us, (and we beheld his glory, the glory as of the only begotten of the Father,) full of grace and truth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 15, 'John bare witness of him, and cried, saying, This was he of whom I spake, He that cometh after me is preferred before me: for he was before me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 16, 'And of his fulness have all we received, and grace for grace.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 17, 'For the law was given by Moses, but grace and truth came by Jesus Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 18, 'No man hath seen God at any time; the only begotten Son, which is in the bosom of the Father, he hath declared him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 19, 'And this is the record of John, when the Jews sent priests and Levites from Jerusalem to ask him, Who art thou?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 20, 'And he confessed, and denied not; but confessed, I am not the Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 21, 'And they asked him, What then? Art thou Elias? And he saith, I am not. Art thou that prophet? And he answered, No.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 22, 'Then said they unto him, Who art thou? that we may give an answer to them that sent us. What sayest thou of thyself?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 23, 'He said, I am the voice of one crying in the wilderness, Make straight the way of the Lord, as said the prophet Esaias.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 24, 'And they which were sent were of the Pharisees.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 25, 'And they asked him, and said unto him, Why baptizest thou then, if thou be not that Christ, nor Elias, neither that prophet?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 26, 'John answered them, saying, I baptize with water: but there standeth one among you, whom ye know not;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 27, 'He it is, who coming after me is preferred before me, whose shoe''s latchet I am not worthy to unloose.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 28, 'These things were done in Bethabara beyond Jordan, where John was baptizing.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 29, 'The next day John seeth Jesus coming unto him, and saith, Behold the Lamb of God, which taketh away the sin of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 30, 'This is he of whom I said, After me cometh a man which is preferred before me: for he was before me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 31, 'And I knew him not: but that he should be made manifest to Israel, therefore am I come baptizing with water.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 32, 'And John bare record, saying, I saw the Spirit descending from heaven like a dove, and it abode upon him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 33, 'And I knew him not: but he that sent me to baptize with water, the same said unto me, Upon whom thou shalt see the Spirit descending, and remaining on him, the same is he which baptizeth with the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 34, 'And I saw, and bare record that this is the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 35, 'Again the next day after John stood, and two of his disciples;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 36, 'And looking upon Jesus as he walked, he saith, Behold the Lamb of God!'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 37, 'And the two disciples heard him speak, and they followed Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 38, 'Then Jesus turned, and saw them following, and saith unto them, What seek ye? They said unto him, Rabbi, (which is to say, being interpreted, Master,) where dwellest thou?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 39, 'He saith unto them, Come and see. They came and saw where he dwelt, and abode with him that day: for it was about the tenth hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 40, 'One of the two which heard John speak, and followed him, was Andrew, Simon Peter''s brother.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 41, 'He first findeth his own brother Simon, and saith unto him, We have found the Messias, which is, being interpreted, the Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 42, 'And he brought him to Jesus. And when Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 43, 'The day following Jesus would go forth into Galilee, and findeth Philip, and saith unto him, Follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 44, 'Now Philip was of Bethsaida, the city of Andrew and Peter.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 45, 'Philip findeth Nathanael, and saith unto him, We have found him, of whom Moses in the law, and the prophets, did write, Jesus of Nazareth, the son of Joseph.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 46, 'And Nathanael said unto him, Can there any good thing come out of Nazareth? Philip saith unto him, Come and see.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 47, 'Jesus saw Nathanael coming to him, and saith of him, Behold an Israelite indeed, in whom is no guile!'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 48, 'Nathanael saith unto him, Whence knowest thou me? Jesus answered and said unto him, Before that Philip called thee, when thou wast under the fig tree, I saw thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 49, 'Nathanael answered and saith unto him, Rabbi, thou art the Son of God; thou art the King of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 50, 'Jesus answered and said unto him, Because I said unto thee, I saw thee under the fig tree, believest thou? thou shalt see greater things than these.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 1, 51, 'And he saith unto him, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Hereafter ye shall see heaven open, and the angels of God ascending and descending upon the Son of man.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 1, 'And the third day there was a marriage in Cana of Galilee; and the mother of Jesus was there:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 2, 'And both Jesus was called, and his disciples, to the marriage.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 3, 'And when they wanted wine, the mother of Jesus saith unto him, They have no wine.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 4, 'Jesus saith unto her, Woman, what have I to do with thee? mine hour is not yet come.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 5, 'His mother saith unto the servants, Whatsoever he saith unto you, do it.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 6, 'And there were set there six waterpots of stone, after the manner of the purifying of the Jews, containing two or three firkins apiece.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 7, 'Jesus saith unto them, Fill the waterpots with water. And they filled them up to the brim.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 8, 'And he saith unto them, Draw out now, and bear unto the governor of the feast. And they bare it.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 9, 'When the ruler of the feast had tasted the water that was made wine, and knew not whence it was: (but the servants which drew the water knew;) the governor of the feast called the bridegroom,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 10, 'And saith unto him, Every man at the beginning doth set forth good wine; and when men have well drunk, then that which is worse: but thou hast kept the good wine until now.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 11, 'This beginning of miracles did Jesus in Cana of Galilee, and manifested forth his glory; and his disciples believed on him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 12, 'After this he went down to Capernaum, he, and his mother, and his brethren, and his disciples: and they continued there not many days.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 13, 'And the Jews'' passover was at hand, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 14, 'And found in the temple those that sold oxen and sheep and doves, and the changers of money sitting:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 15, 'And when he had made a scourge of small cords, he drove them all out of the temple, and the sheep, and the oxen; and poured out the changers'' money, and overthrew the tables;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 16, 'And said unto them that sold doves, Take these things hence; make not my Father''s house an house of merchandise.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 17, 'And his disciples remembered that it was written, The zeal of thine house hath eaten me up.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 18, 'Then answered the Jews and said unto him, What sign shewest thou unto us, seeing that thou doest these things?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 19, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 20, 'Then said the Jews, Forty and six years was this temple in building, and wilt thou rear it up in three days?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 21, 'But he spake of the temple of his body.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 22, 'When therefore he was risen from the dead, his disciples remembered that he had said this unto them; and they believed the scripture, and the word which Jesus had said.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 23, 'Now when he was in Jerusalem at the passover, in the feast day, many believed in his name, when they saw the miracles which he did.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 24, 'But Jesus did not commit himself unto them, because he knew all men,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 2, 25, 'And needed not that any should testify of man: for he knew what was in man.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 1, 'There was a man of the Pharisees, named Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 2, 'The same came to Jesus by night, and said unto him, Rabbi, we know that thou art a teacher come from God: for no man can do these miracles that thou doest, except God be with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 3, 'Jesus answered and said unto him, Verily, verily, I say unto thee, Except a man be born again, he cannot see the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 4, 'Nicodemus saith unto him, How can a man be born when he is old? can he enter the second time into his mother''s womb, and be born?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 5, 'Jesus answered, Verily, verily, I say unto thee, Except a man be born of water and of the Spirit, he cannot enter into the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 6, 'That which is born of the flesh is flesh; and that which is born of the Spirit is spirit.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 7, 'Marvel not that I said unto thee, Ye must be born again.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 8, 'The wind bloweth where it listeth, and thou hearest the sound thereof, but canst not tell whence it cometh, and whither it goeth: so is every one that is born of the Spirit.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 9, 'Nicodemus answered and said unto him, How can these things be?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 10, 'Jesus answered and said unto him, Art thou a master of Israel, and knowest not these things?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 11, 'Verily, verily, I say unto thee, We speak that we do know, and testify that we have seen; and ye receive not our witness.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 12, 'If I have told you earthly things, and ye believe not, how shall ye believe, if I tell you of heavenly things?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 13, 'And no man hath ascended up to heaven, but he that came down from heaven, even the Son of man which is in heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 14, 'And as Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness, even so must the Son of man be lifted up:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 15, 'That whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have eternal life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 16, 'For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 17, 'For God sent not his Son into the world to condemn the world; but that the world through him might be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 18, 'He that believeth on him is not condemned: but he that believeth not is condemned already, because he hath not believed in the name of the only begotten Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 19, 'And this is the condemnation, that light is come into the world, and men loved darkness rather than light, because their deeds were evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 20, 'For every one that doeth evil hateth the light, neither cometh to the light, lest his deeds should be reproved.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 21, 'But he that doeth truth cometh to the light, that his deeds may be made manifest, that they are wrought in God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 22, 'After these things came Jesus and his disciples into the land of Judaea; and there he tarried with them, and baptized.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 23, 'And John also was baptizing in Aenon near to Salim, because there was much water there: and they came, and were baptized.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 24, 'For John was not yet cast into prison.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 25, 'Then there arose a question between some of John''s disciples and the Jews about purifying.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 26, 'And they came unto John, and said unto him, Rabbi, he that was with thee beyond Jordan, to whom thou barest witness, behold, the same baptizeth, and all men come to him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 27, 'John answered and said, A man can receive nothing, except it be given him from heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 28, 'Ye yourselves bear me witness, that I said, I am not the Christ, but that I am sent before him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 29, 'He that hath the bride is the bridegroom: but the friend of the bridegroom, which standeth and heareth him, rejoiceth greatly because of the bridegroom''s voice: this my joy therefore is fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 30, 'He must increase, but I must decrease.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 31, 'He that cometh from above is above all: he that is of the earth is earthly, and speaketh of the earth: he that cometh from heaven is above all.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 32, 'And what he hath seen and heard, that he testifieth; and no man receiveth his testimony.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 33, 'He that hath received his testimony hath set to his seal that God is true.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 34, 'For he whom God hath sent speaketh the words of God: for God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 35, 'The Father loveth the Son, and hath given all things into his hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 3, 36, 'He that believeth on the Son hath everlasting life: and he that believeth not the Son shall not see life; but the wrath of God abideth on him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 1, 'When therefore the Lord knew how the Pharisees had heard that Jesus made and baptized more disciples than John,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 2, '(Though Jesus himself baptized not, but his disciples,)'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 3, 'He left Judaea, and departed again into Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 4, 'And he must needs go through Samaria.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 5, 'Then cometh he to a city of Samaria, which is called Sychar, near to the parcel of ground that Jacob gave to his son Joseph.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 6, 'Now Jacob''s well was there. Jesus therefore, being wearied with his journey, sat thus on the well: and it was about the sixth hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 7, 'There cometh a woman of Samaria to draw water: Jesus saith unto her, Give me to drink.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 8, '(For his disciples were gone away unto the city to buy meat.)'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 9, 'Then saith the woman of Samaria unto him, How is it that thou, being a Jew, askest drink of me, which am a woman of Samaria? for the Jews have no dealings with the Samaritans.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 10, 'Jesus answered and said unto her, If thou knewest the gift of God, and who it is that saith to thee, Give me to drink; thou wouldest have asked of him, and he would have given thee living water.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 11, 'The woman saith unto him, Sir, thou hast nothing to draw with, and the well is deep: from whence then hast thou that living water?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 12, 'Art thou greater than our father Jacob, which gave us the well, and drank thereof himself, and his children, and his cattle?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 13, 'Jesus answered and said unto her, Whosoever drinketh of this water shall thirst again:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 14, 'But whosoever drinketh of the water that I shall give him shall never thirst; but the water that I shall give him shall be in him a well of water springing up into everlasting life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 15, 'The woman saith unto him, Sir, give me this water, that I thirst not, neither come hither to draw.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 16, 'Jesus saith unto her, Go, call thy husband, and come hither.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 17, 'The woman answered and said, I have no husband. Jesus said unto her, Thou hast well said, I have no husband:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 18, 'For thou hast had five husbands; and he whom thou now hast is not thy husband: in that saidst thou truly.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 19, 'The woman saith unto him, Sir, I perceive that thou art a prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 20, 'Our fathers worshipped in this mountain; and ye say, that in Jerusalem is the place where men ought to worship.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 21, 'Jesus saith unto her, Woman, believe me, the hour cometh, when ye shall neither in this mountain, nor yet at Jerusalem, worship the Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 22, 'Ye worship ye know not what: we know what we worship: for salvation is of the Jews.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 23, 'But the hour cometh, and now is, when the true worshippers shall worship the Father in spirit and in truth: for the Father seeketh such to worship him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 24, 'God is a Spirit: and they that worship him must worship him in spirit and in truth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 25, 'The woman saith unto him, I know that Messias cometh, which is called Christ: when he is come, he will tell us all things.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 26, 'Jesus saith unto her, I that speak unto thee am he.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 27, 'And upon this came his disciples, and marvelled that he talked with the woman: yet no man said, What seekest thou? or, Why talkest thou with her?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 28, 'The woman then left her waterpot, and went her way into the city, and saith to the men,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 29, 'Come, see a man, which told me all things that ever I did: is not this the Christ?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 30, 'Then they went out of the city, and came unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 31, 'In the mean while his disciples prayed him, saying, Master, eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 32, 'But he said unto them, I have meat to eat that ye know not of.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 33, 'Therefore said the disciples one to another, Hath any man brought him ought to eat?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 34, 'Jesus saith unto them, My meat is to do the will of him that sent me, and to finish his work.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 35, 'Say not ye, There are yet four months, and then cometh harvest? behold, I say unto you, Lift up your eyes, and look on the fields; for they are white already to harvest.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 36, 'And he that reapeth receiveth wages, and gathereth fruit unto life eternal: that both he that soweth and he that reapeth may rejoice together.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 37, 'And herein is that saying true, One soweth, and another reapeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 38, 'I sent you to reap that whereon ye bestowed no labour: other men laboured, and ye are entered into their labours.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 39, 'And many of the Samaritans of that city believed on him for the saying of the woman, which testified, He told me all that ever I did.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 40, 'So when the Samaritans were come unto him, they besought him that he would tarry with them: and he abode there two days.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 41, 'And many more believed because of his own word;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 42, 'And said unto the woman, Now we believe, not because of thy saying: for we have heard him ourselves, and know that this is indeed the Christ, the Saviour of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 43, 'Now after two days he departed thence, and went into Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 44, 'For Jesus himself testified, that a prophet hath no honour in his own country.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 45, 'Then when he was come into Galilee, the Galilaeans received him, having seen all the things that he did at Jerusalem at the feast: for they also went unto the feast.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 46, 'So Jesus came again into Cana of Galilee, where he made the water wine. And there was a certain nobleman, whose son was sick at Capernaum.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 47, 'When he heard that Jesus was come out of Judaea into Galilee, he went unto him, and besought him that he would come down, and heal his son: for he was at the point of death.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 48, 'Then said Jesus unto him, Except ye see signs and wonders, ye will not believe.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 49, 'The nobleman saith unto him, Sir, come down ere my child die.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 50, 'Jesus saith unto him, Go thy way; thy son liveth. And the man believed the word that Jesus had spoken unto him, and he went his way.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 51, 'And as he was now going down, his servants met him, and told him, saying, Thy son liveth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 52, 'Then enquired he of them the hour when he began to amend. And they said unto him, Yesterday at the seventh hour the fever left him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 53, 'So the father knew that it was at the same hour, in the which Jesus said unto him, Thy son liveth: and himself believed, and his whole house.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 4, 54, 'This is again the second miracle that Jesus did, when he was come out of Judaea into Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 1, 'After this there was a feast of the Jews; and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 2, 'Now there is at Jerusalem by the sheep market a pool, which is called in the Hebrew tongue Bethesda, having five porches.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 3, 'In these lay a great multitude of impotent folk, of blind, halt, withered, waiting for the moving of the water.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 4, 'For an angel went down at a certain season into the pool, and troubled the water: whosoever then first after the troubling of the water stepped in was made whole of whatsoever disease he had.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 5, 'And a certain man was there, which had an infirmity thirty and eight years.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 6, 'When Jesus saw him lie, and knew that he had been now a long time in that case, he saith unto him, Wilt thou be made whole?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 7, 'The impotent man answered him, Sir, I have no man, when the water is troubled, to put me into the pool: but while I am coming, another steppeth down before me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 8, 'Jesus saith unto him, Rise, take up thy bed, and walk.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 9, 'And immediately the man was made whole, and took up his bed, and walked: and on the same day was the sabbath.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 10, 'The Jews therefore said unto him that was cured, It is the sabbath day: it is not lawful for thee to carry thy bed.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 11, 'He answered them, He that made me whole, the same said unto me, Take up thy bed, and walk.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 12, 'Then asked they him, What man is that which said unto thee, Take up thy bed, and walk?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 13, 'And he that was healed wist not who it was: for Jesus had conveyed himself away, a multitude being in that place.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 14, 'Afterward Jesus findeth him in the temple, and said unto him, Behold, thou art made whole: sin no more, lest a worse thing come unto thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 15, 'The man departed, and told the Jews that it was Jesus, which had made him whole.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 16, 'And therefore did the Jews persecute Jesus, and sought to slay him, because he had done these things on the sabbath day.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 17, 'But Jesus answered them, My Father worketh hitherto, and I work.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 18, 'Therefore the Jews sought the more to kill him, because he not only had broken the sabbath, but said also that God was his Father, making himself equal with God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 19, 'Then answered Jesus and said unto them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, The Son can do nothing of himself, but what he seeth the Father do: for what things soever he doeth, these also doeth the Son likewise.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 20, 'For the Father loveth the Son, and sheweth him all things that himself doeth: and he will shew him greater works than these, that ye may marvel.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 21, 'For as the Father raiseth up the dead, and quickeneth them; even so the Son quickeneth whom he will.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 22, 'For the Father judgeth no man, but hath committed all judgment unto the Son:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 23, 'That all men should honour the Son, even as they honour the Father. He that honoureth not the Son honoureth not the Father which hath sent him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 24, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that heareth my word, and believeth on him that sent me, hath everlasting life, and shall not come into condemnation; but is passed from death unto life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 25, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, The hour is coming, and now is, when the dead shall hear the voice of the Son of God: and they that hear shall live.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 26, 'For as the Father hath life in himself; so hath he given to the Son to have life in himself;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 27, 'And hath given him authority to execute judgment also, because he is the Son of man.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 28, 'Marvel not at this: for the hour is coming, in the which all that are in the graves shall hear his voice,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 29, 'And shall come forth; they that have done good, unto the resurrection of life; and they that have done evil, unto the resurrection of damnation.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 30, 'I can of mine own self do nothing: as I hear, I judge: and my judgment is just; because I seek not mine own will, but the will of the Father which hath sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 31, 'If I bear witness of myself, my witness is not true.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 32, 'There is another that beareth witness of me; and I know that the witness which he witnesseth of me is true.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 33, 'Ye sent unto John, and he bare witness unto the truth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 34, 'But I receive not testimony from man: but these things I say, that ye might be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 35, 'He was a burning and a shining light: and ye were willing for a season to rejoice in his light.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 36, 'But I have greater witness than that of John: for the works which the Father hath given me to finish, the same works that I do, bear witness of me, that the Father hath sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 37, 'And the Father himself, which hath sent me, hath borne witness of me. Ye have neither heard his voice at any time, nor seen his shape.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 38, 'And ye have not his word abiding in you: for whom he hath sent, him ye believe not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 39, 'Search the scriptures; for in them ye think ye have eternal life: and they are they which testify of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 40, 'And ye will not come to me, that ye might have life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 41, 'I receive not honour from men.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 42, 'But I know you, that ye have not the love of God in you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 43, 'I am come in my Father''s name, and ye receive me not: if another shall come in his own name, him ye will receive.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 44, 'How can ye believe, which receive honour one of another, and seek not the honour that cometh from God only?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 45, 'Do not think that I will accuse you to the Father: there is one that accuseth you, even Moses, in whom ye trust.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 46, 'For had ye believed Moses, ye would have believed me: for he wrote of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 5, 47, 'But if ye believe not his writings, how shall ye believe my words?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 1, 'After these things Jesus went over the sea of Galilee, which is the sea of Tiberias.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 2, 'And a great multitude followed him, because they saw his miracles which he did on them that were diseased.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 3, 'And Jesus went up into a mountain, and there he sat with his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 4, 'And the passover, a feast of the Jews, was nigh.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 5, 'When Jesus then lifted up his eyes, and saw a great company come unto him, he saith unto Philip, Whence shall we buy bread, that these may eat?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 6, 'And this he said to prove him: for he himself knew what he would do.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 7, 'Philip answered him, Two hundred pennyworth of bread is not sufficient for them, that every one of them may take a little.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 8, 'One of his disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter''s brother, saith unto him,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 9, 'There is a lad here, which hath five barley loaves, and two small fishes: but what are they among so many?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 10, 'And Jesus said, Make the men sit down. Now there was much grass in the place. So the men sat down, in number about five thousand.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 11, 'And Jesus took the loaves; and when he had given thanks, he distributed to the disciples, and the disciples to them that were set down; and likewise of the fishes as much as they would.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 12, 'When they were filled, he said unto his disciples, Gather up the fragments that remain, that nothing be lost.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 13, 'Therefore they gathered them together, and filled twelve baskets with the fragments of the five barley loaves, which remained over and above unto them that had eaten.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 14, 'Then those men, when they had seen the miracle that Jesus did, said, This is of a truth that prophet that should come into the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 15, 'When Jesus therefore perceived that they would come and take him by force, to make him a king, he departed again into a mountain himself alone.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 16, 'And when even was now come, his disciples went down unto the sea,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 17, 'And entered into a ship, and went over the sea toward Capernaum. And it was now dark, and Jesus was not come to them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 18, 'And the sea arose by reason of a great wind that blew.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 19, 'So when they had rowed about five and twenty or thirty furlongs, they see Jesus walking on the sea, and drawing nigh unto the ship: and they were afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 20, 'But he saith unto them, It is I; be not afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 21, 'Then they willingly received him into the ship: and immediately the ship was at the land whither they went.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 22, 'The day following, when the people which stood on the other side of the sea saw that there was none other boat there, save that one whereinto his disciples were entered, and that Jesus went not with his disciples into the boat, but that his disciples were gone away alone;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 23, '(Howbeit there came other boats from Tiberias nigh unto the place where they did eat bread, after that the Lord had given thanks:)'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 24, 'When the people therefore saw that Jesus was not there, neither his disciples, they also took shipping, and came to Capernaum, seeking for Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 25, 'And when they had found him on the other side of the sea, they said unto him, Rabbi, when camest thou hither?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 26, 'Jesus answered them and said, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Ye seek me, not because ye saw the miracles, but because ye did eat of the loaves, and were filled.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 27, 'Labour not for the meat which perisheth, but for that meat which endureth unto everlasting life, which the Son of man shall give unto you: for him hath God the Father sealed.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 28, 'Then said they unto him, What shall we do, that we might work the works of God?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 29, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, This is the work of God, that ye believe on him whom he hath sent.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 30, 'They said therefore unto him, What sign shewest thou then, that we may see, and believe thee? what dost thou work?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 31, 'Our fathers did eat manna in the desert; as it is written, He gave them bread from heaven to eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 32, 'Then Jesus said unto them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Moses gave you not that bread from heaven; but my Father giveth you the true bread from heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 33, 'For the bread of God is he which cometh down from heaven, and giveth life unto the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 34, 'Then said they unto him, Lord, evermore give us this bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 35, 'And Jesus said unto them, I am the bread of life: he that cometh to me shall never hunger; and he that believeth on me shall never thirst.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 36, 'But I said unto you, That ye also have seen me, and believe not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 37, 'All that the Father giveth me shall come to me; and him that cometh to me I will in no wise cast out.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 38, 'For I came down from heaven, not to do mine own will, but the will of him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 39, 'And this is the Father''s will which hath sent me, that of all which he hath given me I should lose nothing, but should raise it up again at the last day.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 40, 'And this is the will of him that sent me, that every one which seeth the Son, and believeth on him, may have everlasting life: and I will raise him up at the last day.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 41, 'The Jews then murmured at him, because he said, I am the bread which came down from heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 42, 'And they said, Is not this Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? how is it then that he saith, I came down from heaven?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 43, 'Jesus therefore answered and said unto them, Murmur not among yourselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 44, 'No man can come to me, except the Father which hath sent me draw him: and I will raise him up at the last day.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 45, 'It is written in the prophets, And they shall be all taught of God. Every man therefore that hath heard, and hath learned of the Father, cometh unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 46, 'Not that any man hath seen the Father, save he which is of God, he hath seen the Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 47, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that believeth on me hath everlasting life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 48, 'I am that bread of life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 49, 'Your fathers did eat manna in the wilderness, and are dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 50, 'This is the bread which cometh down from heaven, that a man may eat thereof, and not die.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 51, 'I am the living bread which came down from heaven: if any man eat of this bread, he shall live for ever: and the bread that I will give is my flesh, which I will give for the life of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 52, 'The Jews therefore strove among themselves, saying, How can this man give us his flesh to eat?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 53, 'Then Jesus said unto them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Except ye eat the flesh of the Son of man, and drink his blood, ye have no life in you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 54, 'Whoso eateth my flesh, and drinketh my blood, hath eternal life; and I will raise him up at the last day.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 55, 'For my flesh is meat indeed, and my blood is drink indeed.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 56, 'He that eateth my flesh, and drinketh my blood, dwelleth in me, and I in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 57, 'As the living Father hath sent me, and I live by the Father: so he that eateth me, even he shall live by me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 58, 'This is that bread which came down from heaven: not as your fathers did eat manna, and are dead: he that eateth of this bread shall live for ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 59, 'These things said he in the synagogue, as he taught in Capernaum.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 60, 'Many therefore of his disciples, when they had heard this, said, This is an hard saying; who can hear it?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 61, 'When Jesus knew in himself that his disciples murmured at it, he said unto them, Doth this offend you?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 62, 'What and if ye shall see the Son of man ascend up where he was before?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 63, 'It is the spirit that quickeneth; the flesh profiteth nothing: the words that I speak unto you, they are spirit, and they are life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 64, 'But there are some of you that believe not. For Jesus knew from the beginning who they were that believed not, and who should betray him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 65, 'And he said, Therefore said I unto you, that no man can come unto me, except it were given unto him of my Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 66, 'From that time many of his disciples went back, and walked no more with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 67, 'Then said Jesus unto the twelve, Will ye also go away?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 68, 'Then Simon Peter answered him, Lord, to whom shall we go? thou hast the words of eternal life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 69, 'And we believe and are sure that thou art that Christ, the Son of the living God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 70, 'Jesus answered them, Have not I chosen you twelve, and one of you is a devil?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 6, 71, 'He spake of Judas Iscariot the son of Simon: for he it was that should betray him, being one of the twelve.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 1, 'After these things Jesus walked in Galilee: for he would not walk in Jewry, because the Jews sought to kill him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 2, 'Now the Jews'' feast of tabernacles was at hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 3, 'His brethren therefore said unto him, Depart hence, and go into Judaea, that thy disciples also may see the works that thou doest.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 4, 'For there is no man that doeth any thing in secret, and he himself seeketh to be known openly. If thou do these things, shew thyself to the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 5, 'For neither did his brethren believe in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 6, 'Then Jesus said unto them, My time is not yet come: but your time is alway ready.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 7, 'The world cannot hate you; but me it hateth, because I testify of it, that the works thereof are evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 8, 'Go ye up unto this feast: I go not up yet unto this feast; for my time is not yet full come.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 9, 'When he had said these words unto them, he abode still in Galilee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 10, 'But when his brethren were gone up, then went he also up unto the feast, not openly, but as it were in secret.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 11, 'Then the Jews sought him at the feast, and said, Where is he?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 12, 'And there was much murmuring among the people concerning him: for some said, He is a good man: others said, Nay; but he deceiveth the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 13, 'Howbeit no man spake openly of him for fear of the Jews.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 14, 'Now about the midst of the feast Jesus went up into the temple, and taught.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 15, 'And the Jews marvelled, saying, How knoweth this man letters, having never learned?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 16, 'Jesus answered them, and said, My doctrine is not mine, but his that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 17, 'If any man will do his will, he shall know of the doctrine, whether it be of God, or whether I speak of myself.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 18, 'He that speaketh of himself seeketh his own glory: but he that seeketh his glory that sent him, the same is true, and no unrighteousness is in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 19, 'Did not Moses give you the law, and yet none of you keepeth the law? Why go ye about to kill me?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 20, 'The people answered and said, Thou hast a devil: who goeth about to kill thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 21, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, I have done one work, and ye all marvel.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 22, 'Moses therefore gave unto you circumcision; (not because it is of Moses, but of the fathers;) and ye on the sabbath day circumcise a man.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 23, 'If a man on the sabbath day receive circumcision, that the law of Moses should not be broken; are ye angry at me, because I have made a man every whit whole on the sabbath day?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 24, 'Judge not according to the appearance, but judge righteous judgment.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 25, 'Then said some of them of Jerusalem, Is not this he, whom they seek to kill?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 26, 'But, lo, he speaketh boldly, and they say nothing unto him. Do the rulers know indeed that this is the very Christ?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 27, 'Howbeit we know this man whence he is: but when Christ cometh, no man knoweth whence he is.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 28, 'Then cried Jesus in the temple as he taught, saying, Ye both know me, and ye know whence I am: and I am not come of myself, but he that sent me is true, whom ye know not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 29, 'But I know him: for I am from him, and he hath sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 30, 'Then they sought to take him: but no man laid hands on him, because his hour was not yet come.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 31, 'And many of the people believed on him, and said, When Christ cometh, will he do more miracles than these which this man hath done?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 32, 'The Pharisees heard that the people murmured such things concerning him; and the Pharisees and the chief priests sent officers to take him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 33, 'Then said Jesus unto them, Yet a little while am I with you, and then I go unto him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 34, 'Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, thither ye cannot come.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 35, 'Then said the Jews among themselves, Whither will he go, that we shall not find him? will he go unto the dispersed among the Gentiles, and teach the Gentiles?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 36, 'What manner of saying is this that he said, Ye shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, thither ye cannot come?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 37, 'In the last day, that great day of the feast, Jesus stood and cried, saying, If any man thirst, let him come unto me, and drink.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 38, 'He that believeth on me, as the scripture hath said, out of his belly shall flow rivers of living water.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 39, '(But this spake he of the Spirit, which they that believe on him should receive: for the Holy Ghost was not yet given; because that Jesus was not yet glorified.)'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 40, 'Many of the people therefore, when they heard this saying, said, Of a truth this is the Prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 41, 'Others said, This is the Christ. But some said, Shall Christ come out of Galilee?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 42, 'Hath not the scripture said, That Christ cometh of the seed of David, and out of the town of Bethlehem, where David was?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 43, 'So there was a division among the people because of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 44, 'And some of them would have taken him; but no man laid hands on him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 45, 'Then came the officers to the chief priests and Pharisees; and they said unto them, Why have ye not brought him?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 46, 'The officers answered, Never man spake like this man.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 47, 'Then answered them the Pharisees, Are ye also deceived?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 48, 'Have any of the rulers or of the Pharisees believed on him?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 49, 'But this people who knoweth not the law are cursed.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 50, 'Nicodemus saith unto them, (he that came to Jesus by night, being one of them,)'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 51, 'Doth our law judge any man, before it hear him, and know what he doeth?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 52, 'They answered and said unto him, Art thou also of Galilee? Search, and look: for out of Galilee ariseth no prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 7, 53, 'And every man went unto his own house.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 1, 'Jesus went unto the mount of Olives.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 2, 'And early in the morning he came again into the temple, and all the people came unto him; and he sat down, and taught them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 3, 'And the scribes and Pharisees brought unto him a woman taken in adultery; and when they had set her in the midst,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 4, 'They say unto him, Master, this woman was taken in adultery, in the very act.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 5, 'Now Moses in the law commanded us, that such should be stoned: but what sayest thou?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 6, 'This they said, tempting him, that they might have to accuse him. But Jesus stooped down, and with his finger wrote on the ground, as though he heard them not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 7, 'So when they continued asking him, he lifted up himself, and said unto them, He that is without sin among you, let him first cast a stone at her.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 8, 'And again he stooped down, and wrote on the ground.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 9, 'And they which heard it, being convicted by their own conscience, went out one by one, beginning at the eldest, even unto the last: and Jesus was left alone, and the woman standing in the midst.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 10, 'When Jesus had lifted up himself, and saw none but the woman, he said unto her, Woman, where are those thine accusers? hath no man condemned thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 11, 'She said, No man, Lord. And Jesus said unto her, Neither do I condemn thee: go, and sin no more.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 12, 'Then spake Jesus again unto them, saying, I am the light of the world: he that followeth me shall not walk in darkness, but shall have the light of life.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 13, 'The Pharisees therefore said unto him, Thou bearest record of thyself; thy record is not true.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 14, 'Jesus answered and said unto them, Though I bear record of myself, yet my record is true: for I know whence I came, and whither I go; but ye cannot tell whence I come, and whither I go.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 15, 'Ye judge after the flesh; I judge no man.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 16, 'And yet if I judge, my judgment is true: for I am not alone, but I and the Father that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 17, 'It is also written in your law, that the testimony of two men is true.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 18, 'I am one that bear witness of myself, and the Father that sent me beareth witness of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 19, 'Then said they unto him, Where is thy Father? Jesus answered, Ye neither know me, nor my Father: if ye had known me, ye should have known my Father also.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 20, 'These words spake Jesus in the treasury, as he taught in the temple: and no man laid hands on him; for his hour was not yet come.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 21, 'Then said Jesus again unto them, I go my way, and ye shall seek me, and shall die in your sins: whither I go, ye cannot come.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 22, 'Then said the Jews, Will he kill himself? because he saith, Whither I go, ye cannot come.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 23, 'And he said unto them, Ye are from beneath; I am from above: ye are of this world; I am not of this world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 24, 'I said therefore unto you, that ye shall die in your sins: for if ye believe not that I am he, ye shall die in your sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 25, 'Then said they unto him, Who art thou? And Jesus saith unto them, Even the same that I said unto you from the beginning.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 26, 'I have many things to say and to judge of you: but he that sent me is true; and I speak to the world those things which I have heard of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 27, 'They understood not that he spake to them of the Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 28, 'Then said Jesus unto them, When ye have lifted up the Son of man, then shall ye know that I am he, and that I do nothing of myself; but as my Father hath taught me, I speak these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 29, 'And he that sent me is with me: the Father hath not left me alone; for I do always those things that please him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 30, 'As he spake these words, many believed on him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 31, 'Then said Jesus to those Jews which believed on him, If ye continue in my word, then are ye my disciples indeed;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 32, 'And ye shall know the truth, and the truth shall make you free.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 33, 'They answered him, We be Abraham''s seed, and were never in bondage to any man: how sayest thou, Ye shall be made free?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 34, 'Jesus answered them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Whosoever committeth sin is the servant of sin.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 35, 'And the servant abideth not in the house for ever: but the Son abideth ever.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 36, 'If the Son therefore shall make you free, ye shall be free indeed.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 37, 'I know that ye are Abraham''s seed; but ye seek to kill me, because my word hath no place in you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 38, 'I speak that which I have seen with my Father: and ye do that which ye have seen with your father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 39, 'They answered and said unto him, Abraham is our father. Jesus saith unto them, If ye were Abraham''s children, ye would do the works of Abraham.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 40, 'But now ye seek to kill me, a man that hath told you the truth, which I have heard of God: this did not Abraham.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 41, 'Ye do the deeds of your father. Then said they to him, We be not born of fornication; we have one Father, even God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 42, 'Jesus said unto them, If God were your Father, ye would love me: for I proceeded forth and came from God; neither came I of myself, but he sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 43, 'Why do ye not understand my speech? even because ye cannot hear my word.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 44, 'Ye are of your father the devil, and the lusts of your father ye will do. He was a murderer from the beginning, and abode not in the truth, because there is no truth in him. When he speaketh a lie, he speaketh of his own: for he is a liar, and the father of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 45, 'And because I tell you the truth, ye believe me not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 46, 'Which of you convinceth me of sin? And if I say the truth, why do ye not believe me?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 47, 'He that is of God heareth God''s words: ye therefore hear them not, because ye are not of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 48, 'Then answered the Jews, and said unto him, Say we not well that thou art a Samaritan, and hast a devil?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 49, 'Jesus answered, I have not a devil; but I honour my Father, and ye do dishonour me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 50, 'And I seek not mine own glory: there is one that seeketh and judgeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 51, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, If a man keep my saying, he shall never see death.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 52, 'Then said the Jews unto him, Now we know that thou hast a devil. Abraham is dead, and the prophets; and thou sayest, If a man keep my saying, he shall never taste of death.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 53, 'Art thou greater than our father Abraham, which is dead? and the prophets are dead: whom makest thou thyself?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 54, 'Jesus answered, If I honour myself, my honour is nothing: it is my Father that honoureth me; of whom ye say, that he is your God:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 55, 'Yet ye have not known him; but I know him: and if I should say, I know him not, I shall be a liar like unto you: but I know him, and keep his saying.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 56, 'Your father Abraham rejoiced to see my day: and he saw it, and was glad.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 57, 'Then said the Jews unto him, Thou art not yet fifty years old, and hast thou seen Abraham?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 58, 'Jesus said unto them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Before Abraham was, I am.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 8, 59, 'Then took they up stones to cast at him: but Jesus hid himself, and went out of the temple, going through the midst of them, and so passed by.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 1, 'And as Jesus passed by, he saw a man which was blind from his birth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 2, 'And his disciples asked him, saying, Master, who did sin, this man, or his parents, that he was born blind?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 3, 'Jesus answered, Neither hath this man sinned, nor his parents: but that the works of God should be made manifest in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 4, 'I must work the works of him that sent me, while it is day: the night cometh, when no man can work.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 5, 'As long as I am in the world, I am the light of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 6, 'When he had thus spoken, he spat on the ground, and made clay of the spittle, and he anointed the eyes of the blind man with the clay,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 7, 'And said unto him, Go, wash in the pool of Siloam, (which is by interpretation, Sent.) He went his way therefore, and washed, and came seeing.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 8, 'The neighbours therefore, and they which before had seen him that he was blind, said, Is not this he that sat and begged?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 9, 'Some said, This is he: others said, He is like him: but he said, I am he.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 10, 'Therefore said they unto him, How were thine eyes opened?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 11, 'He answered and said, A man that is called Jesus made clay, and anointed mine eyes, and said unto me, Go to the pool of Siloam, and wash: and I went and washed, and I received sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 12, 'Then said they unto him, Where is he? He said, I know not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 13, 'They brought to the Pharisees him that aforetime was blind.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 14, 'And it was the sabbath day when Jesus made the clay, and opened his eyes.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 15, 'Then again the Pharisees also asked him how he had received his sight. He said unto them, He put clay upon mine eyes, and I washed, and do see.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 16, 'Therefore said some of the Pharisees, This man is not of God, because he keepeth not the sabbath day. Others said, How can a man that is a sinner do such miracles? And there was a division among them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 17, 'They say unto the blind man again, What sayest thou of him, that he hath opened thine eyes? He said, He is a prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 18, 'But the Jews did not believe concerning him, that he had been blind, and received his sight, until they called the parents of him that had received his sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 19, 'And they asked them, saying, Is this your son, who ye say was born blind? how then doth he now see?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 20, 'His parents answered them and said, We know that this is our son, and that he was born blind:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 21, 'But by what means he now seeth, we know not; or who hath opened his eyes, we know not: he is of age; ask him: he shall speak for himself.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 22, 'These words spake his parents, because they feared the Jews: for the Jews had agreed already, that if any man did confess that he was Christ, he should be put out of the synagogue.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 23, 'Therefore said his parents, He is of age; ask him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 24, 'Then again called they the man that was blind, and said unto him, Give God the praise: we know that this man is a sinner.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 25, 'He answered and said, Whether he be a sinner or no, I know not: one thing I know, that, whereas I was blind, now I see.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 26, 'Then said they to him again, What did he to thee? how opened he thine eyes?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 27, 'He answered them, I have told you already, and ye did not hear: wherefore would ye hear it again? will ye also be his disciples?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 28, 'Then they reviled him, and said, Thou art his disciple; but we are Moses'' disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 29, 'We know that God spake unto Moses: as for this fellow, we know not from whence he is.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 30, 'The man answered and said unto them, Why herein is a marvellous thing, that ye know not from whence he is, and yet he hath opened mine eyes.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 31, 'Now we know that God heareth not sinners: but if any man be a worshipper of God, and doeth his will, him he heareth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 32, 'Since the world began was it not heard that any man opened the eyes of one that was born blind.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 33, 'If this man were not of God, he could do nothing.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 34, 'They answered and said unto him, Thou wast altogether born in sins, and dost thou teach us? And they cast him out.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 35, 'Jesus heard that they had cast him out; and when he had found him, he said unto him, Dost thou believe on the Son of God?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 36, 'He answered and said, Who is he, Lord, that I might believe on him?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 37, 'And Jesus said unto him, Thou hast both seen him, and it is he that talketh with thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 38, 'And he said, Lord, I believe. And he worshipped him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 39, 'And Jesus said, For judgment I am come into this world, that they which see not might see; and that they which see might be made blind.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 40, 'And some of the Pharisees which were with him heard these words, and said unto him, Are we blind also?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 9, 41, 'Jesus said unto them, If ye were blind, ye should have no sin: but now ye say, We see; therefore your sin remaineth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 1, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that entereth not by the door into the sheepfold, but climbeth up some other way, the same is a thief and a robber.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 2, 'But he that entereth in by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 3, 'To him the porter openeth; and the sheep hear his voice: and he calleth his own sheep by name, and leadeth them out.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 4, 'And when he putteth forth his own sheep, he goeth before them, and the sheep follow him: for they know his voice.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 5, 'And a stranger will they not follow, but will flee from him: for they know not the voice of strangers.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 6, 'This parable spake Jesus unto them: but they understood not what things they were which he spake unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 7, 'Then said Jesus unto them again, Verily, verily, I say unto you, I am the door of the sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 8, 'All that ever came before me are thieves and robbers: but the sheep did not hear them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 9, 'I am the door: by me if any man enter in, he shall be saved, and shall go in and out, and find pasture.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 10, 'The thief cometh not, but for to steal, and to kill, and to destroy: I am come that they might have life, and that they might have it more abundantly.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 11, 'I am the good shepherd: the good shepherd giveth his life for the sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 12, 'But he that is an hireling, and not the shepherd, whose own the sheep are not, seeth the wolf coming, and leaveth the sheep, and fleeth: and the wolf catcheth them, and scattereth the sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 13, 'The hireling fleeth, because he is an hireling, and careth not for the sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 14, 'I am the good shepherd, and know my sheep, and am known of mine.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 15, 'As the Father knoweth me, even so know I the Father: and I lay down my life for the sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 16, 'And other sheep I have, which are not of this fold: them also I must bring, and they shall hear my voice; and there shall be one fold, and one shepherd.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 17, 'Therefore doth my Father love me, because I lay down my life, that I might take it again.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 18, 'No man taketh it from me, but I lay it down of myself. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it again. This commandment have I received of my Father.')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 19, 'There was a division therefore again among the Jews for these sayings.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 20, 'And many of them said, He hath a devil, and is mad; why hear ye him?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 21, 'Others said, These are not the words of him that hath a devil. Can a devil open the eyes of the blind?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 22, 'And it was at Jerusalem the feast of the dedication, and it was winter.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 23, 'And Jesus walked in the temple in Solomon''s porch.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 24, 'Then came the Jews round about him, and said unto him, How long dost thou make us to doubt? If thou be the Christ, tell us plainly.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 25, 'Jesus answered them, I told you, and ye believed not: the works that I do in my Father''s name, they bear witness of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 26, 'But ye believe not, because ye are not of my sheep, as I said unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 27, 'My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 28, 'And I give unto them eternal life; and they shall never perish, neither shall any man pluck them out of my hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 29, 'My Father, which gave them me, is greater than all; and no man is able to pluck them out of my Father''s hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 30, 'I and my Father are one.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 31, 'Then the Jews took up stones again to stone him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 32, 'Jesus answered them, Many good works have I shewed you from my Father; for which of those works do ye stone me?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 33, 'The Jews answered him, saying, For a good work we stone thee not; but for blasphemy; and because that thou, being a man, makest thyself God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 34, 'Jesus answered them, Is it not written in your law, I said, Ye are gods?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 35, 'If he called them gods, unto whom the word of God came, and the scripture cannot be broken;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 36, 'Say ye of him, whom the Father hath sanctified, and sent into the world, Thou blasphemest; because I said, I am the Son of God?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 37, 'If I do not the works of my Father, believe me not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 38, 'But if I do, though ye believe not me, believe the works: that ye may know, and believe, that the Father is in me, and I in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 39, 'Therefore they sought again to take him: but he escaped out of their hand,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 40, 'And went away again beyond Jordan into the place where John at first baptized; and there he abode.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 41, 'And many resorted unto him, and said, John did no miracle: but all things that John spake of this man were true.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 10, 42, 'And many believed on him there.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 1, 'Now a certain man was sick, named Lazarus, of Bethany, the town of Mary and her sister Martha.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 2, '(It was that Mary which anointed the Lord with ointment, and wiped his feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick.)'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 3, 'Therefore his sisters sent unto him, saying, Lord, behold, he whom thou lovest is sick.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 4, 'When Jesus heard that, he said, This sickness is not unto death, but for the glory of God, that the Son of God might be glorified thereby.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 5, 'Now Jesus loved Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 6, 'When he had heard therefore that he was sick, he abode two days still in the same place where he was.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 7, 'Then after that saith he to his disciples, Let us go into Judaea again.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 8, 'His disciples say unto him, Master, the Jews of late sought to stone thee; and goest thou thither again?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 9, 'Jesus answered, Are there not twelve hours in the day? If any man walk in the day, he stumbleth not, because he seeth the light of this world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 10, 'But if a man walk in the night, he stumbleth, because there is no light in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 11, 'These things said he: and after that he saith unto them, Our friend Lazarus sleepeth; but I go, that I may awake him out of sleep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 12, 'Then said his disciples, Lord, if he sleep, he shall do well.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 13, 'Howbeit Jesus spake of his death: but they thought that he had spoken of taking of rest in sleep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 14, 'Then said Jesus unto them plainly, Lazarus is dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 15, 'And I am glad for your sakes that I was not there, to the intent ye may believe; nevertheless let us go unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 16, 'Then said Thomas, which is called Didymus, unto his fellowdisciples, Let us also go, that we may die with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 17, 'Then when Jesus came, he found that he had lain in the grave four days already.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 18, 'Now Bethany was nigh unto Jerusalem, about fifteen furlongs off:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 19, 'And many of the Jews came to Martha and Mary, to comfort them concerning their brother.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 20, 'Then Martha, as soon as she heard that Jesus was coming, went and met him: but Mary sat still in the house.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 21, 'Then said Martha unto Jesus, Lord, if thou hadst been here, my brother had not died.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 22, 'But I know, that even now, whatsoever thou wilt ask of God, God will give it thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 23, 'Jesus saith unto her, Thy brother shall rise again.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 24, 'Martha saith unto him, I know that he shall rise again in the resurrection at the last day.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 25, 'Jesus said unto her, I am the resurrection, and the life: he that believeth in me, though he were dead, yet shall he live:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 26, 'And whosoever liveth and believeth in me shall never die. Believest thou this?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 27, 'She saith unto him, Yea, Lord: I believe that thou art the Christ, the Son of God, which should come into the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 28, 'And when she had so said, she went her way, and called Mary her sister secretly, saying, The Master is come, and calleth for thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 29, 'As soon as she heard that, she arose quickly, and came unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 30, 'Now Jesus was not yet come into the town, but was in that place where Martha met him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 31, 'The Jews then which were with her in the house, and comforted her, when they saw Mary, that she rose up hastily and went out, followed her, saying, She goeth unto the grave to weep there.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 32, 'Then when Mary was come where Jesus was, and saw him, she fell down at his feet, saying unto him, Lord, if thou hadst been here, my brother had not died.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 33, 'When Jesus therefore saw her weeping, and the Jews also weeping which came with her, he groaned in the spirit, and was troubled,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 34, 'And said, Where have ye laid him? They said unto him, Lord, come and see.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 35, 'Jesus wept.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 36, 'Then said the Jews, Behold how he loved him!'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 37, 'And some of them said, Could not this man, which opened the eyes of the blind, have caused that even this man should not have died?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 38, 'Jesus therefore again groaning in himself cometh to the grave. It was a cave, and a stone lay upon it.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 39, 'Jesus said, Take ye away the stone. Martha, the sister of him that was dead, saith unto him, Lord, by this time he stinketh: for he hath been dead four days.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 40, 'Jesus saith unto her, Said I not unto thee, that, if thou wouldest believe, thou shouldest see the glory of God?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 41, 'Then they took away the stone from the place where the dead was laid. And Jesus lifted up his eyes, and said, Father, I thank thee that thou hast heard me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 42, 'And I knew that thou hearest me always: but because of the people which stand by I said it, that they may believe that thou hast sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 43, 'And when he thus had spoken, he cried with a loud voice, Lazarus, come forth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 44, 'And he that was dead came forth, bound hand and foot with graveclothes: and his face was bound about with a napkin. Jesus saith unto them, Loose him, and let him go.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 45, 'Then many of the Jews which came to Mary, and had seen the things which Jesus did, believed on him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 46, 'But some of them went their ways to the Pharisees, and told them what things Jesus had done.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 47, 'Then gathered the chief priests and the Pharisees a council, and said, What do we? for this man doeth many miracles.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 48, 'If we let him thus alone, all men will believe on him: and the Romans shall come and take away both our place and nation.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 49, 'And one of them, named Caiaphas, being the high priest that same year, said unto them, Ye know nothing at all,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 50, 'Nor consider that it is expedient for us, that one man should die for the people, and that the whole nation perish not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 51, 'And this spake he not of himself: but being high priest that year, he prophesied that Jesus should die for that nation;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 52, 'And not for that nation only, but that also he should gather together in one the children of God that were scattered abroad.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 53, 'Then from that day forth they took counsel together for to put him to death.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 54, 'Jesus therefore walked no more openly among the Jews; but went thence unto a country near to the wilderness, into a city called Ephraim, and there continued with his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 55, 'And the Jews'' passover was nigh at hand: and many went out of the country up to Jerusalem before the passover, to purify themselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 56, 'Then sought they for Jesus, and spake among themselves, as they stood in the temple, What think ye, that he will not come to the feast?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 11, 57, 'Now both the chief priests and the Pharisees had given a commandment, that, if any man knew where he were, he should shew it, that they might take him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 1, 'Then Jesus six days before the passover came to Bethany, where Lazarus was which had been dead, whom he raised from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 2, 'There they made him a supper; and Martha served: but Lazarus was one of them that sat at the table with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 3, 'Then took Mary a pound of ointment of spikenard, very costly, and anointed the feet of Jesus, and wiped his feet with her hair: and the house was filled with the odour of the ointment.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 4, 'Then saith one of his disciples, Judas Iscariot, Simon''s son, which should betray him,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 5, 'Why was not this ointment sold for three hundred pence, and given to the poor?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 6, 'This he said, not that he cared for the poor; but because he was a thief, and had the bag, and bare what was put therein.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 7, 'Then said Jesus, Let her alone: against the day of my burying hath she kept this.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 8, 'For the poor always ye have with you; but me ye have not always.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 9, 'Much people of the Jews therefore knew that he was there: and they came not for Jesus'' sake only, but that they might see Lazarus also, whom he had raised from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 10, 'But the chief priests consulted that they might put Lazarus also to death;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 11, 'Because that by reason of him many of the Jews went away, and believed on Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 12, 'On the next day much people that were come to the feast, when they heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 13, 'Took branches of palm trees, and went forth to meet him, and cried, Hosanna: Blessed is the King of Israel that cometh in the name of the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 14, 'And Jesus, when he had found a young ass, sat thereon; as it is written,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 15, 'Fear not, daughter of Sion: behold, thy King cometh, sitting on an ass''s colt.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 16, 'These things understood not his disciples at the first: but when Jesus was glorified, then remembered they that these things were written of him, and that they had done these things unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 17, 'The people therefore that was with him when he called Lazarus out of his grave, and raised him from the dead, bare record.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 18, 'For this cause the people also met him, for that they heard that he had done this miracle.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 19, 'The Pharisees therefore said among themselves, Perceive ye how ye prevail nothing? behold, the world is gone after him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 20, 'And there were certain Greeks among them that came up to worship at the feast:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 21, 'The same came therefore to Philip, which was of Bethsaida of Galilee, and desired him, saying, Sir, we would see Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 22, 'Philip cometh and telleth Andrew: and again Andrew and Philip tell Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 23, 'And Jesus answered them, saying, The hour is come, that the Son of man should be glorified.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 24, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, Except a corn of wheat fall into the ground and die, it abideth alone: but if it die, it bringeth forth much fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 25, 'He that loveth his life shall lose it; and he that hateth his life in this world shall keep it unto life eternal.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 26, 'If any man serve me, let him follow me; and where I am, there shall also my servant be: if any man serve me, him will my Father honour.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 27, 'Now is my soul troubled; and what shall I say? Father, save me from this hour: but for this cause came I unto this hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 28, 'Father, glorify thy name. Then came there a voice from heaven, saying, I have both glorified it, and will glorify it again.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 29, 'The people therefore, that stood by, and heard it, said that it thundered: others said, An angel spake to him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 30, 'Jesus answered and said, This voice came not because of me, but for your sakes.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 31, 'Now is the judgment of this world: now shall the prince of this world be cast out.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 32, 'And I, if I be lifted up from the earth, will draw all men unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 33, 'This he said, signifying what death he should die.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 34, 'The people answered him, We have heard out of the law that Christ abideth for ever: and how sayest thou, The Son of man must be lifted up? who is this Son of man?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 35, 'Then Jesus said unto them, Yet a little while is the light with you. Walk while ye have the light, lest darkness come upon you: for he that walketh in darkness knoweth not whither he goeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 36, 'While ye have light, believe in the light, that ye may be the children of light. These things spake Jesus, and departed, and did hide himself from them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 37, 'But though he had done so many miracles before them, yet they believed not on him:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 38, 'That the saying of Esaias the prophet might be fulfilled, which he spake, Lord, who hath believed our report? and to whom hath the arm of the Lord been revealed?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 39, 'Therefore they could not believe, because that Esaias said again,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 40, 'He hath blinded their eyes, and hardened their heart; that they should not see with their eyes, nor understand with their heart, and be converted, and I should heal them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 41, 'These things said Esaias, when he saw his glory, and spake of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 42, 'Nevertheless among the chief rulers also many believed on him; but because of the Pharisees they did not confess him, lest they should be put out of the synagogue:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 43, 'For they loved the praise of men more than the praise of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 44, 'Jesus cried and said, He that believeth on me, believeth not on me, but on him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 45, 'And he that seeth me seeth him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 46, 'I am come a light into the world, that whosoever believeth on me should not abide in darkness.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 47, 'And if any man hear my words, and believe not, I judge him not: for I came not to judge the world, but to save the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 48, 'He that rejecteth me, and receiveth not my words, hath one that judgeth him: the word that I have spoken, the same shall judge him in the last day.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 49, 'For I have not spoken of myself; but the Father which sent me, he gave me a commandment, what I should say, and what I should speak.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 12, 50, 'And I know that his commandment is life everlasting: whatsoever I speak therefore, even as the Father said unto me, so I speak.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 1, 'Now before the feast of the passover, when Jesus knew that his hour was come that he should depart out of this world unto the Father, having loved his own which were in the world, he loved them unto the end.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 2, 'And supper being ended, the devil having now put into the heart of Judas Iscariot, Simon''s son, to betray him;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 3, 'Jesus knowing that the Father had given all things into his hands, and that he was come from God, and went to God;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 4, 'He riseth from supper, and laid aside his garments; and took a towel, and girded himself.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 5, 'After that he poureth water into a bason, and began to wash the disciples'' feet, and to wipe them with the towel wherewith he was girded.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 6, 'Then cometh he to Simon Peter: and Peter saith unto him, Lord, dost thou wash my feet?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 7, 'Jesus answered and said unto him, What I do thou knowest not now; but thou shalt know hereafter.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 8, 'Peter saith unto him, Thou shalt never wash my feet. Jesus answered him, If I wash thee not, thou hast no part with me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 9, 'Simon Peter saith unto him, Lord, not my feet only, but also my hands and my head.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 10, 'Jesus saith to him, He that is washed needeth not save to wash his feet, but is clean every whit: and ye are clean, but not all.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 11, 'For he knew who should betray him; therefore said he, Ye are not all clean.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 12, 'So after he had washed their feet, and had taken his garments, and was set down again, he said unto them, Know ye what I have done to you?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 13, 'Ye call me Master and Lord: and ye say well; for so I am.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 14, 'If I then, your Lord and Master, have washed your feet; ye also ought to wash one another''s feet.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 15, 'For I have given you an example, that ye should do as I have done to you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 16, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, The servant is not greater than his lord; neither he that is sent greater than he that sent him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 17, 'If ye know these things, happy are ye if ye do them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 18, 'I speak not of you all: I know whom I have chosen: but that the scripture may be fulfilled, He that eateth bread with me hath lifted up his heel against me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 19, 'Now I tell you before it come, that, when it is come to pass, ye may believe that I am he.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 20, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that receiveth whomsoever I send receiveth me; and he that receiveth me receiveth him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 21, 'When Jesus had thus said, he was troubled in spirit, and testified, and said, Verily, verily, I say unto you, that one of you shall betray me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 22, 'Then the disciples looked one on another, doubting of whom he spake.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 23, 'Now there was leaning on Jesus'' bosom one of his disciples, whom Jesus loved.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 24, 'Simon Peter therefore beckoned to him, that he should ask who it should be of whom he spake.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 25, 'He then lying on Jesus'' breast saith unto him, Lord, who is it?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 26, 'Jesus answered, He it is, to whom I shall give a sop, when I have dipped it. And when he had dipped the sop, he gave it to Judas Iscariot, the son of Simon.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 27, 'And after the sop Satan entered into him. Then said Jesus unto him, That thou doest, do quickly.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 28, 'Now no man at the table knew for what intent he spake this unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 29, 'For some of them thought, because Judas had the bag, that Jesus had said unto him, Buy those things that we have need of against the feast; or, that he should give something to the poor.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 30, 'He then having received the sop went immediately out: and it was night.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 31, 'Therefore, when he was gone out, Jesus said, Now is the Son of man glorified, and God is glorified in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 32, 'If God be glorified in him, God shall also glorify him in himself, and shall straightway glorify him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 33, 'Little children, yet a little while I am with you. Ye shall seek me: and as I said unto the Jews, Whither I go, ye cannot come; so now I say to you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 34, 'A new commandment I give unto you, That ye love one another; as I have loved you, that ye also love one another.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 35, 'By this shall all men know that ye are my disciples, if ye have love one to another.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 36, 'Simon Peter said unto him, Lord, whither goest thou? Jesus answered him, Whither I go, thou canst not follow me now; but thou shalt follow me afterwards.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 37, 'Peter said unto him, Lord, why cannot I follow thee now? I will lay down my life for thy sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 13, 38, 'Jesus answered him, Wilt thou lay down thy life for my sake? Verily, verily, I say unto thee, The cock shall not crow, till thou hast denied me thrice.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 1, 'Let not your heart be troubled: ye believe in God, believe also in me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 2, 'In my Father''s house are many mansions: if it were not so, I would have told you. I go to prepare a place for you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 3, 'And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and receive you unto myself; that where I am, there ye may be also.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 4, 'And whither I go ye know, and the way ye know.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 5, 'Thomas saith unto him, Lord, we know not whither thou goest; and how can we know the way?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 6, 'Jesus saith unto him, I am the way, the truth, and the life: no man cometh unto the Father, but by me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 7, 'If ye had known me, ye should have known my Father also: and from henceforth ye know him, and have seen him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 8, 'Philip saith unto him, Lord, shew us the Father, and it sufficeth us.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 9, 'Jesus saith unto him, Have I been so long time with you, and yet hast thou not known me, Philip? he that hath seen me hath seen the Father; and how sayest thou then, Shew us the Father?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 10, 'Believest thou not that I am in the Father, and the Father in me? the words that I speak unto you I speak not of myself: but the Father that dwelleth in me, he doeth the works.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 11, 'Believe me that I am in the Father, and the Father in me: or else believe me for the very works'' sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 12, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that believeth on me, the works that I do shall he do also; and greater works than these shall he do; because I go unto my Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 13, 'And whatsoever ye shall ask in my name, that will I do, that the Father may be glorified in the Son.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 14, 'If ye shall ask any thing in my name, I will do it.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 15, 'If ye love me, keep my commandments.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 16, 'And I will pray the Father, and he shall give you another Comforter, that he may abide with you for ever;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 17, 'Even the Spirit of truth; whom the world cannot receive, because it seeth him not, neither knoweth him: but ye know him; for he dwelleth with you, and shall be in you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 18, 'I will not leave you comfortless: I will come to you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 19, 'Yet a little while, and the world seeth me no more; but ye see me: because I live, ye shall live also.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 20, 'At that day ye shall know that I am in my Father, and ye in me, and I in you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 21, 'He that hath my commandments, and keepeth them, he it is that loveth me: and he that loveth me shall be loved of my Father, and I will love him, and will manifest myself to him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 22, 'Judas saith unto him, not Iscariot, Lord, how is it that thou wilt manifest thyself unto us, and not unto the world?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 23, 'Jesus answered and said unto him, If a man love me, he will keep my words: and my Father will love him, and we will come unto him, and make our abode with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 24, 'He that loveth me not keepeth not my sayings: and the word which ye hear is not mine, but the Father''s which sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 25, 'These things have I spoken unto you, being yet present with you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 26, 'But the Comforter, which is the Holy Ghost, whom the Father will send in my name, he shall teach you all things, and bring all things to your remembrance, whatsoever I have said unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 27, 'Peace I leave with you, my peace I give unto you: not as the world giveth, give I unto you. Let not your heart be troubled, neither let it be afraid.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 28, 'Ye have heard how I said unto you, I go away, and come again unto you. If ye loved me, ye would rejoice, because I said, I go unto the Father: for my Father is greater than I.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 29, 'And now I have told you before it come to pass, that, when it is come to pass, ye might believe.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 30, 'Hereafter I will not talk much with you: for the prince of this world cometh, and hath nothing in me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 14, 31, 'But that the world may know that I love the Father; and as the Father gave me commandment, even so I do. Arise, let us go hence.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 1, 'I am the true vine, and my Father is the husbandman.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 2, 'Every branch in me that beareth not fruit he taketh away: and every branch that beareth fruit, he purgeth it, that it may bring forth more fruit.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 3, 'Now ye are clean through the word which I have spoken unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 4, 'Abide in me, and I in you. As the branch cannot bear fruit of itself, except it abide in the vine; no more can ye, except ye abide in me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 5, 'I am the vine, ye are the branches: He that abideth in me, and I in him, the same bringeth forth much fruit: for without me ye can do nothing.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 6, 'If a man abide not in me, he is cast forth as a branch, and is withered; and men gather them, and cast them into the fire, and they are burned.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 7, 'If ye abide in me, and my words abide in you, ye shall ask what ye will, and it shall be done unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 8, 'Herein is my Father glorified, that ye bear much fruit; so shall ye be my disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 9, 'As the Father hath loved me, so have I loved you: continue ye in my love.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 10, 'If ye keep my commandments, ye shall abide in my love; even as I have kept my Father''s commandments, and abide in his love.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 11, 'These things have I spoken unto you, that my joy might remain in you, and that your joy might be full.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 12, 'This is my commandment, That ye love one another, as I have loved you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 13, 'Greater love hath no man than this, that a man lay down his life for his friends.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 14, 'Ye are my friends, if ye do whatsoever I command you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 15, 'Henceforth I call you not servants; for the servant knoweth not what his lord doeth: but I have called you friends; for all things that I have heard of my Father I have made known unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 16, 'Ye have not chosen me, but I have chosen you, and ordained you, that ye should go and bring forth fruit, and that your fruit should remain: that whatsoever ye shall ask of the Father in my name, he may give it you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 17, 'These things I command you, that ye love one another.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 18, 'If the world hate you, ye know that it hated me before it hated you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 19, 'If ye were of the world, the world would love his own: but because ye are not of the world, but I have chosen you out of the world, therefore the world hateth you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 20, 'Remember the word that I said unto you, The servant is not greater than his lord. If they have persecuted me, they will also persecute you; if they have kept my saying, they will keep yours also.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 21, 'But all these things will they do unto you for my name''s sake, because they know not him that sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 22, 'If I had not come and spoken unto them, they had not had sin: but now they have no cloke for their sin.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 23, 'He that hateth me hateth my Father also.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 24, 'If I had not done among them the works which none other man did, they had not had sin: but now have they both seen and hated both me and my Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 25, 'But this cometh to pass, that the word might be fulfilled that is written in their law, They hated me without a cause.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 26, 'But when the Comforter is come, whom I will send unto you from the Father, even the Spirit of truth, which proceedeth from the Father, he shall testify of me:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 15, 27, 'And ye also shall bear witness, because ye have been with me from the beginning.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 1, 'These things have I spoken unto you, that ye should not be offended.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 2, 'They shall put you out of the synagogues: yea, the time cometh, that whosoever killeth you will think that he doeth God service.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 3, 'And these things will they do unto you, because they have not known the Father, nor me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 4, 'But these things have I told you, that when the time shall come, ye may remember that I told you of them. And these things I said not unto you at the beginning, because I was with you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 5, 'But now I go my way to him that sent me; and none of you asketh me, Whither goest thou?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 6, 'But because I have said these things unto you, sorrow hath filled your heart.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 7, 'Nevertheless I tell you the truth; It is expedient for you that I go away: for if I go not away, the Comforter will not come unto you; but if I depart, I will send him unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 8, 'And when he is come, he will reprove the world of sin, and of righteousness, and of judgment:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 9, 'Of sin, because they believe not on me;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 10, 'Of righteousness, because I go to my Father, and ye see me no more;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 11, 'Of judgment, because the prince of this world is judged.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 12, 'I have yet many things to say unto you, but ye cannot bear them now.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 13, 'Howbeit when he, the Spirit of truth, is come, he will guide you into all truth: for he shall not speak of himself; but whatsoever he shall hear, that shall he speak: and he will shew you things to come.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 14, 'He shall glorify me: for he shall receive of mine, and shall shew it unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 15, 'All things that the Father hath are mine: therefore said I, that he shall take of mine, and shall shew it unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 16, 'A little while, and ye shall not see me: and again, a little while, and ye shall see me, because I go to the Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 17, 'Then said some of his disciples among themselves, What is this that he saith unto us, A little while, and ye shall not see me: and again, a little while, and ye shall see me: and, Because I go to the Father?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 18, 'They said therefore, What is this that he saith, A little while? we cannot tell what he saith.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 19, 'Now Jesus knew that they were desirous to ask him, and said unto them, Do ye enquire among yourselves of that I said, A little while, and ye shall not see me: and again, a little while, and ye shall see me?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 20, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, That ye shall weep and lament, but the world shall rejoice: and ye shall be sorrowful, but your sorrow shall be turned into joy.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 21, 'A woman when she is in travail hath sorrow, because her hour is come: but as soon as she is delivered of the child, she remembereth no more the anguish, for joy that a man is born into the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 22, 'And ye now therefore have sorrow: but I will see you again, and your heart shall rejoice, and your joy no man taketh from you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 23, 'And in that day ye shall ask me nothing. Verily, verily, I say unto you, Whatsoever ye shall ask the Father in my name, he will give it you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 24, 'Hitherto have ye asked nothing in my name: ask, and ye shall receive, that your joy may be full.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 25, 'These things have I spoken unto you in proverbs: but the time cometh, when I shall no more speak unto you in proverbs, but I shall shew you plainly of the Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 26, 'At that day ye shall ask in my name: and I say not unto you, that I will pray the Father for you:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 27, 'For the Father himself loveth you, because ye have loved me, and have believed that I came out from God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 28, 'I came forth from the Father, and am come into the world: again, I leave the world, and go to the Father.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 29, 'His disciples said unto him, Lo, now speakest thou plainly, and speakest no proverb.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 30, 'Now are we sure that thou knowest all things, and needest not that any man should ask thee: by this we believe that thou camest forth from God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 31, 'Jesus answered them, Do ye now believe?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 32, 'Behold, the hour cometh, yea, is now come, that ye shall be scattered, every man to his own, and shall leave me alone: and yet I am not alone, because the Father is with me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 16, 33, 'These things I have spoken unto you, that in me ye might have peace. In the world ye shall have tribulation: but be of good cheer; I have overcome the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 1, 'These words spake Jesus, and lifted up his eyes to heaven, and said, Father, the hour is come; glorify thy Son, that thy Son also may glorify thee:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 2, 'As thou hast given him power over all flesh, that he should give eternal life to as many as thou hast given him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 3, 'And this is life eternal, that they might know thee the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom thou hast sent.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 4, 'I have glorified thee on the earth: I have finished the work which thou gavest me to do.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 5, 'And now, O Father, glorify thou me with thine own self with the glory which I had with thee before the world was.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 6, 'I have manifested thy name unto the men which thou gavest me out of the world: thine they were, and thou gavest them me; and they have kept thy word.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 7, 'Now they have known that all things whatsoever thou hast given me are of thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 8, 'For I have given unto them the words which thou gavest me; and they have received them, and have known surely that I came out from thee, and they have believed that thou didst send me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 9, 'I pray for them: I pray not for the world, but for them which thou hast given me; for they are thine.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 10, 'And all mine are thine, and thine are mine; and I am glorified in them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 11, 'And now I am no more in the world, but these are in the world, and I come to thee. Holy Father, keep through thine own name those whom thou hast given me, that they may be one, as we are.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 12, 'While I was with them in the world, I kept them in thy name: those that thou gavest me I have kept, and none of them is lost, but the son of perdition; that the scripture might be fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 13, 'And now come I to thee; and these things I speak in the world, that they might have my joy fulfilled in themselves.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 14, 'I have given them thy word; and the world hath hated them, because they are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 15, 'I pray not that thou shouldest take them out of the world, but that thou shouldest keep them from the evil.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 16, 'They are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 17, 'Sanctify them through thy truth: thy word is truth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 18, 'As thou hast sent me into the world, even so have I also sent them into the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 19, 'And for their sakes I sanctify myself, that they also might be sanctified through the truth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 20, 'Neither pray I for these alone, but for them also which shall believe on me through their word;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 21, 'That they all may be one; as thou, Father, art in me, and I in thee, that they also may be one in us: that the world may believe that thou hast sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 22, 'And the glory which thou gavest me I have given them; that they may be one, even as we are one:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 23, 'I in them, and thou in me, that they may be made perfect in one; and that the world may know that thou hast sent me, and hast loved them, as thou hast loved me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 24, 'Father, I will that they also, whom thou hast given me, be with me where I am; that they may behold my glory, which thou hast given me: for thou lovedst me before the foundation of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 25, 'O righteous Father, the world hath not known thee: but I have known thee, and these have known that thou hast sent me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 17, 26, 'And I have declared unto them thy name, and will declare it: that the love wherewith thou hast loved me may be in them, and I in them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 1, 'When Jesus had spoken these words, he went forth with his disciples over the brook Cedron, where was a garden, into the which he entered, and his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 2, 'And Judas also, which betrayed him, knew the place: for Jesus ofttimes resorted thither with his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 3, 'Judas then, having received a band of men and officers from the chief priests and Pharisees, cometh thither with lanterns and torches and weapons.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 4, 'Jesus therefore, knowing all things that should come upon him, went forth, and said unto them, Whom seek ye?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 5, 'They answered him, Jesus of Nazareth. Jesus saith unto them, I am he. And Judas also, which betrayed him, stood with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 6, 'As soon then as he had said unto them, I am he, they went backward, and fell to the ground.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 7, 'Then asked he them again, Whom seek ye? And they said, Jesus of Nazareth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 8, 'Jesus answered, I have told you that I am he: if therefore ye seek me, let these go their way:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 9, 'That the saying might be fulfilled, which he spake, Of them which thou gavest me have I lost none.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 10, 'Then Simon Peter having a sword drew it, and smote the high priest''s servant, and cut off his right ear. The servant''s name was Malchus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 11, 'Then said Jesus unto Peter, Put up thy sword into the sheath: the cup which my Father hath given me, shall I not drink it?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 12, 'Then the band and the captain and officers of the Jews took Jesus, and bound him,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 13, 'And led him away to Annas first; for he was father in law to Caiaphas, which was the high priest that same year.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 14, 'Now Caiaphas was he, which gave counsel to the Jews, that it was expedient that one man should die for the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 15, 'And Simon Peter followed Jesus, and so did another disciple: that disciple was known unto the high priest, and went in with Jesus into the palace of the high priest.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 16, 'But Peter stood at the door without. Then went out that other disciple, which was known unto the high priest, and spake unto her that kept the door, and brought in Peter.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 17, 'Then saith the damsel that kept the door unto Peter, Art not thou also one of this man''s disciples? He saith, I am not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 18, 'And the servants and officers stood there, who had made a fire of coals; for it was cold: and they warmed themselves: and Peter stood with them, and warmed himself.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 19, 'The high priest then asked Jesus of his disciples, and of his doctrine.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 20, 'Jesus answered him, I spake openly to the world; I ever taught in the synagogue, and in the temple, whither the Jews always resort; and in secret have I said nothing.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 21, 'Why askest thou me? ask them which heard me, what I have said unto them: behold, they know what I said.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 22, 'And when he had thus spoken, one of the officers which stood by struck Jesus with the palm of his hand, saying, Answerest thou the high priest so?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 23, 'Jesus answered him, If I have spoken evil, bear witness of the evil: but if well, why smitest thou me?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 24, 'Now Annas had sent him bound unto Caiaphas the high priest.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 25, 'And Simon Peter stood and warmed himself. They said therefore unto him, Art not thou also one of his disciples? He denied it, and said, I am not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 26, 'One of the servants of the high priest, being his kinsman whose ear Peter cut off, saith, Did not I see thee in the garden with him?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 27, 'Peter then denied again: and immediately the cock crew.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 28, 'Then led they Jesus from Caiaphas unto the hall of judgment: and it was early; and they themselves went not into the judgment hall, lest they should be defiled; but that they might eat the passover.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 29, 'Pilate then went out unto them, and said, What accusation bring ye against this man?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 30, 'They answered and said unto him, If he were not a malefactor, we would not have delivered him up unto thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 31, 'Then said Pilate unto them, Take ye him, and judge him according to your law. The Jews therefore said unto him, It is not lawful for us to put any man to death:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 32, 'That the saying of Jesus might be fulfilled, which he spake, signifying what death he should die.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 33, 'Then Pilate entered into the judgment hall again, and called Jesus, and said unto him, Art thou the King of the Jews?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 34, 'Jesus answered him, Sayest thou this thing of thyself, or did others tell it thee of me?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 35, 'Pilate answered, Am I a Jew? Thine own nation and the chief priests have delivered thee unto me: what hast thou done?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 36, 'Jesus answered, My kingdom is not of this world: if my kingdom were of this world, then would my servants fight, that I should not be delivered to the Jews: but now is my kingdom not from hence.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 37, 'Pilate therefore said unto him, Art thou a king then? Jesus answered, Thou sayest that I am a king. To this end was I born, and for this cause came I into the world, that I should bear witness unto the truth. Every one that is of the truth heareth my voice.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 38, 'Pilate saith unto him, What is truth? And when he had said this, he went out again unto the Jews, and saith unto them, I find in him no fault at all.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 39, 'But ye have a custom, that I should release unto you one at the passover: will ye therefore that I release unto you the King of the Jews?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 18, 40, 'Then cried they all again, saying, Not this man, but Barabbas. Now Barabbas was a robber.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 1, 'Then Pilate therefore took Jesus, and scourged him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 2, 'And the soldiers platted a crown of thorns, and put it on his head, and they put on him a purple robe,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 3, 'And said, Hail, King of the Jews! and they smote him with their hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 4, 'Pilate therefore went forth again, and saith unto them, Behold, I bring him forth to you, that ye may know that I find no fault in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 5, 'Then came Jesus forth, wearing the crown of thorns, and the purple robe. And Pilate saith unto them, Behold the man!'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 6, 'When the chief priests therefore and officers saw him, they cried out, saying, Crucify him, crucify him. Pilate saith unto them, Take ye him, and crucify him: for I find no fault in him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 7, 'The Jews answered him, We have a law, and by our law he ought to die, because he made himself the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 8, 'When Pilate therefore heard that saying, he was the more afraid;'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 9, 'And went again into the judgment hall, and saith unto Jesus, Whence art thou? But Jesus gave him no answer.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 10, 'Then saith Pilate unto him, Speakest thou not unto me? knowest thou not that I have power to crucify thee, and have power to release thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 11, 'Jesus answered, Thou couldest have no power at all against me, except it were given thee from above: therefore he that delivered me unto thee hath the greater sin.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 12, 'And from thenceforth Pilate sought to release him: but the Jews cried out, saying, If thou let this man go, thou art not Caesar''s friend: whosoever maketh himself a king speaketh against Caesar.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 13, 'When Pilate therefore heard that saying, he brought Jesus forth, and sat down in the judgment seat in a place that is called the Pavement, but in the Hebrew, Gabbatha.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 14, 'And it was the preparation of the passover, and about the sixth hour: and he saith unto the Jews, Behold your King!'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 15, 'But they cried out, Away with him, away with him, crucify him. Pilate saith unto them, Shall I crucify your King? The chief priests answered, We have no king but Caesar.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 16, 'Then delivered he him therefore unto them to be crucified. And they took Jesus, and led him away.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 17, 'And he bearing his cross went forth into a place called the place of a skull, which is called in the Hebrew Golgotha:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 18, 'Where they crucified him, and two other with him, on either side one, and Jesus in the midst.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 19, 'And Pilate wrote a title, and put it on the cross. And the writing was, JESUS OF NAZARETH THE KING OF THE JEWS.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 20, 'This title then read many of the Jews: for the place where Jesus was crucified was nigh to the city: and it was written in Hebrew, and Greek, and Latin.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 21, 'Then said the chief priests of the Jews to Pilate, Write not, The King of the Jews; but that he said, I am King of the Jews.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 22, 'Pilate answered, What I have written I have written.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 23, 'Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Jesus, took his garments, and made four parts, to every soldier a part; and also his coat: now the coat was without seam, woven from the top throughout.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 24, 'They said therefore among themselves, Let us not rend it, but cast lots for it, whose it shall be: that the scripture might be fulfilled, which saith, They parted my raiment among them, and for my vesture they did cast lots. These things therefore the soldiers did.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 25, 'Now there stood by the cross of Jesus his mother, and his mother''s sister, Mary the wife of Cleophas, and Mary Magdalene.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 26, 'When Jesus therefore saw his mother, and the disciple standing by, whom he loved, he saith unto his mother, Woman, behold thy son!'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 27, 'Then saith he to the disciple, Behold thy mother! And from that hour that disciple took her unto his own home.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 28, 'After this, Jesus knowing that all things were now accomplished, that the scripture might be fulfilled, saith, I thirst.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 29, 'Now there was set a vessel full of vinegar: and they filled a spunge with vinegar, and put it upon hyssop, and put it to his mouth.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 30, 'When Jesus therefore had received the vinegar, he said, It is finished: and he bowed his head, and gave up the ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 31, 'The Jews therefore, because it was the preparation, that the bodies should not remain upon the cross on the sabbath day, (for that sabbath day was an high day,) besought Pilate that their legs might be broken, and that they might be taken away.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 32, 'Then came the soldiers, and brake the legs of the first, and of the other which was crucified with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 33, 'But when they came to Jesus, and saw that he was dead already, they brake not his legs:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 34, 'But one of the soldiers with a spear pierced his side, and forthwith came there out blood and water.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 35, 'And he that saw it bare record, and his record is true: and he knoweth that he saith true, that ye might believe.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 36, 'For these things were done, that the scripture should be fulfilled, A bone of him shall not be broken.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 37, 'And again another scripture saith, They shall look on him whom they pierced.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 38, 'And after this Joseph of Arimathaea, being a disciple of Jesus, but secretly for fear of the Jews, besought Pilate that he might take away the body of Jesus: and Pilate gave him leave. He came therefore, and took the body of Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 39, 'And there came also Nicodemus, which at the first came to Jesus by night, and brought a mixture of myrrh and aloes, about an hundred pound weight.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 40, 'Then took they the body of Jesus, and wound it in linen clothes with the spices, as the manner of the Jews is to bury.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 41, 'Now in the place where he was crucified there was a garden; and in the garden a new sepulchre, wherein was never man yet laid.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 19, 42, 'There laid they Jesus therefore because of the Jews'' preparation day; for the sepulchre was nigh at hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 1, 'The first day of the week cometh Mary Magdalene early, when it was yet dark, unto the sepulchre, and seeth the stone taken away from the sepulchre.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 2, 'Then she runneth, and cometh to Simon Peter, and to the other disciple, whom Jesus loved, and saith unto them, They have taken away the Lord out of the sepulchre, and we know not where they have laid him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 3, 'Peter therefore went forth, and that other disciple, and came to the sepulchre.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 4, 'So they ran both together: and the other disciple did outrun Peter, and came first to the sepulchre.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 5, 'And he stooping down, and looking in, saw the linen clothes lying; yet went he not in.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 6, 'Then cometh Simon Peter following him, and went into the sepulchre, and seeth the linen clothes lie,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 7, 'And the napkin, that was about his head, not lying with the linen clothes, but wrapped together in a place by itself.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 8, 'Then went in also that other disciple, which came first to the sepulchre, and he saw, and believed.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 9, 'For as yet they knew not the scripture, that he must rise again from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 10, 'Then the disciples went away again unto their own home.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 11, 'But Mary stood without at the sepulchre weeping: and as she wept, she stooped down, and looked into the sepulchre,'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 12, 'And seeth two angels in white sitting, the one at the head, and the other at the feet, where the body of Jesus had lain.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 13, 'And they say unto her, Woman, why weepest thou? She saith unto them, Because they have taken away my Lord, and I know not where they have laid him.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 14, 'And when she had thus said, she turned herself back, and saw Jesus standing, and knew not that it was Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 15, 'Jesus saith unto her, Woman, why weepest thou? whom seekest thou? She, supposing him to be the gardener, saith unto him, Sir, if thou have borne him hence, tell me where thou hast laid him, and I will take him away.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 16, 'Jesus saith unto her, Mary. She turned herself, and saith unto him, Rabboni; which is to say, Master.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 17, 'Jesus saith unto her, Touch me not; for I am not yet ascended to my Father: but go to my brethren, and say unto them, I ascend unto my Father, and your Father; and to my God, and your God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 18, 'Mary Magdalene came and told the disciples that she had seen the Lord, and that he had spoken these things unto her.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 19, 'Then the same day at evening, being the first day of the week, when the doors were shut where the disciples were assembled for fear of the Jews, came Jesus and stood in the midst, and saith unto them, Peace be unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 20, 'And when he had so said, he shewed unto them his hands and his side. Then were the disciples glad, when they saw the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 21, 'Then said Jesus to them again, Peace be unto you: as my Father hath sent me, even so send I you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 22, 'And when he had said this, he breathed on them, and saith unto them, Receive ye the Holy Ghost:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 23, 'Whose soever sins ye remit, they are remitted unto them; and whose soever sins ye retain, they are retained.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 24, 'But Thomas, one of the twelve, called Didymus, was not with them when Jesus came.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 25, 'The other disciples therefore said unto him, We have seen the Lord. But he said unto them, Except I shall see in his hands the print of the nails, and put my finger into the print of the nails, and thrust my hand into his side, I will not believe.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 26, 'And after eight days again his disciples were within, and Thomas with them: then came Jesus, the doors being shut, and stood in the midst, and said, Peace be unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 27, 'Then saith he to Thomas, Reach hither thy finger, and behold my hands; and reach hither thy hand, and thrust it into my side: and be not faithless, but believing.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 28, 'And Thomas answered and said unto him, My Lord and my God.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 29, 'Jesus saith unto him, Thomas, because thou hast seen me, thou hast believed: blessed are they that have not seen, and yet have believed.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 30, 'And many other signs truly did Jesus in the presence of his disciples, which are not written in this book:'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 20, 31, 'But these are written, that ye might believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God; and that believing ye might have life through his name.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 1, 'After these things Jesus shewed himself again to the disciples at the sea of Tiberias; and on this wise shewed he himself.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 2, 'There were together Simon Peter, and Thomas called Didymus, and Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, and the sons of Zebedee, and two other of his disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 3, 'Simon Peter saith unto them, I go a fishing. They say unto him, We also go with thee. They went forth, and entered into a ship immediately; and that night they caught nothing.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 4, 'But when the morning was now come, Jesus stood on the shore: but the disciples knew not that it was Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 5, 'Then Jesus saith unto them, Children, have ye any meat? They answered him, No.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 6, 'And he said unto them, Cast the net on the right side of the ship, and ye shall find. They cast therefore, and now they were not able to draw it for the multitude of fishes.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 7, 'Therefore that disciple whom Jesus loved saith unto Peter, It is the Lord. Now when Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he girt his fisher''s coat unto him, (for he was naked,) and did cast himself into the sea.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 8, 'And the other disciples came in a little ship; (for they were not far from land, but as it were two hundred cubits,) dragging the net with fishes.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 9, 'As soon then as they were come to land, they saw a fire of coals there, and fish laid thereon, and bread.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 10, 'Jesus saith unto them, Bring of the fish which ye have now caught.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 11, 'Simon Peter went up, and drew the net to land full of great fishes, an hundred and fifty and three: and for all there were so many, yet was not the net broken.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 12, 'Jesus saith unto them, Come and dine. And none of the disciples durst ask him, Who art thou? knowing that it was the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 13, 'Jesus then cometh, and taketh bread, and giveth them, and fish likewise.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 14, 'This is now the third time that Jesus shewed himself to his disciples, after that he was risen from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 15, 'So when they had dined, Jesus saith to Simon Peter, Simon, son of Jonas, lovest thou me more than these? He saith unto him, Yea, Lord; thou knowest that I love thee. He saith unto him, Feed my lambs.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 16, 'He saith to him again the second time, Simon, son of Jonas, lovest thou me? He saith unto him, Yea, Lord; thou knowest that I love thee. He saith unto him, Feed my sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 17, 'He saith unto him the third time, Simon, son of Jonas, lovest thou me? Peter was grieved because he said unto him the third time, Lovest thou me? And he said unto him, Lord, thou knowest all things; thou knowest that I love thee. Jesus saith unto him, Feed my sheep.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 18, 'Verily, verily, I say unto thee, When thou wast young, thou girdedst thyself, and walkedst whither thou wouldest: but when thou shalt be old, thou shalt stretch forth thy hands, and another shall gird thee, and carry thee whither thou wouldest not.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 19, 'This spake he, signifying by what death he should glorify God. And when he had spoken this, he saith unto him, Follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 20, 'Then Peter, turning about, seeth the disciple whom Jesus loved following; which also leaned on his breast at supper, and said, Lord, which is he that betrayeth thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 21, 'Peter seeing him saith to Jesus, Lord, and what shall this man do?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 22, 'Jesus saith unto him, If I will that he tarry till I come, what is that to thee? follow thou me.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 23, 'Then went this saying abroad among the brethren, that that disciple should not die: yet Jesus said not unto him, He shall not die; but, If I will that he tarry till I come, what is that to thee?'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 24, 'This is the disciple which testifieth of these things, and wrote these things: and we know that his testimony is true.'),
  ('KJV', 'John', 43, 21, 25, 'And there are also many other things which Jesus did, the which, if they should be written every one, I suppose that even the world itself could not contain the books that should be written. Amen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 1, 'The former treatise have I made, O Theophilus, of all that Jesus began both to do and teach,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 2, 'Until the day in which he was taken up, after that he through the Holy Ghost had given commandments unto the apostles whom he had chosen:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 3, 'To whom also he shewed himself alive after his passion by many infallible proofs, being seen of them forty days, and speaking of the things pertaining to the kingdom of God:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 4, 'And, being assembled together with them, commanded them that they should not depart from Jerusalem, but wait for the promise of the Father, which, saith he, ye have heard of me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 5, 'For John truly baptized with water; but ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost not many days hence.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 6, 'When they therefore were come together, they asked of him, saying, Lord, wilt thou at this time restore again the kingdom to Israel?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 7, 'And he said unto them, It is not for you to know the times or the seasons, which the Father hath put in his own power.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 8, 'But ye shall receive power, after that the Holy Ghost is come upon you: and ye shall be witnesses unto me both in Jerusalem, and in all Judaea, and in Samaria, and unto the uttermost part of the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 9, 'And when he had spoken these things, while they beheld, he was taken up; and a cloud received him out of their sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 10, 'And while they looked stedfastly toward heaven as he went up, behold, two men stood by them in white apparel;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 11, 'Which also said, Ye men of Galilee, why stand ye gazing up into heaven? this same Jesus, which is taken up from you into heaven, shall so come in like manner as ye have seen him go into heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 12, 'Then returned they unto Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet, which is from Jerusalem a sabbath day''s journey.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 13, 'And when they were come in, they went up into an upper room, where abode both Peter, and James, and John, and Andrew, Philip, and Thomas, Bartholomew, and Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon Zelotes, and Judas the brother of James.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 14, 'These all continued with one accord in prayer and supplication, with the women, and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with his brethren.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 15, 'And in those days Peter stood up in the midst of the disciples, and said, (the number of names together were about an hundred and twenty,)'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 16, 'Men and brethren, this scripture must needs have been fulfilled, which the Holy Ghost by the mouth of David spake before concerning Judas, which was guide to them that took Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 17, 'For he was numbered with us, and had obtained part of this ministry.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 18, 'Now this man purchased a field with the reward of iniquity; and falling headlong, he burst asunder in the midst, and all his bowels gushed out.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 19, 'And it was known unto all the dwellers at Jerusalem; insomuch as that field is called in their proper tongue, Aceldama, that is to say, The field of blood.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 20, 'For it is written in the book of Psalms, Let his habitation be desolate, and let no man dwell therein: and his bishoprick let another take.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 21, 'Wherefore of these men which have companied with us all the time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 22, 'Beginning from the baptism of John, unto that same day that he was taken up from us, must one be ordained to be a witness with us of his resurrection.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 23, 'And they appointed two, Joseph called Barsabas, who was surnamed Justus, and Matthias.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 24, 'And they prayed, and said, Thou, Lord, which knowest the hearts of all men, shew whether of these two thou hast chosen,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 25, 'That he may take part of this ministry and apostleship, from which Judas by transgression fell, that he might go to his own place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 1, 26, 'And they gave forth their lots; and the lot fell upon Matthias; and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 1, 'And when the day of Pentecost was fully come, they were all with one accord in one place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 2, 'And suddenly there came a sound from heaven as of a rushing mighty wind, and it filled all the house where they were sitting.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 3, 'And there appeared unto them cloven tongues like as of fire, and it sat upon each of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 4, 'And they were all filled with the Holy Ghost, and began to speak with other tongues, as the Spirit gave them utterance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 5, 'And there were dwelling at Jerusalem Jews, devout men, out of every nation under heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 6, 'Now when this was noised abroad, the multitude came together, and were confounded, because that every man heard them speak in his own language.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 7, 'And they were all amazed and marvelled, saying one to another, Behold, are not all these which speak Galilaeans?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 8, 'And how hear we every man in our own tongue, wherein we were born?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 9, 'Parthians, and Medes, and Elamites, and the dwellers in Mesopotamia, and in Judaea, and Cappadocia, in Pontus, and Asia,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 10, 'Phrygia, and Pamphylia, in Egypt, and in the parts of Libya about Cyrene, and strangers of Rome, Jews and proselytes,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 11, 'Cretes and Arabians, we do hear them speak in our tongues the wonderful works of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 12, 'And they were all amazed, and were in doubt, saying one to another, What meaneth this?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 13, 'Others mocking said, These men are full of new wine.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 14, 'But Peter, standing up with the eleven, lifted up his voice, and said unto them, Ye men of Judaea, and all ye that dwell at Jerusalem, be this known unto you, and hearken to my words:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 15, 'For these are not drunken, as ye suppose, seeing it is but the third hour of the day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 16, 'But this is that which was spoken by the prophet Joel;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 17, 'And it shall come to pass in the last days, saith God, I will pour out of my Spirit upon all flesh: and your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, and your young men shall see visions, and your old men shall dream dreams:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 18, 'And on my servants and on my handmaidens I will pour out in those days of my Spirit; and they shall prophesy:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 19, 'And I will shew wonders in heaven above, and signs in the earth beneath; blood, and fire, and vapour of smoke:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 20, 'The sun shall be turned into darkness, and the moon into blood, before that great and notable day of the Lord come:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 21, 'And it shall come to pass, that whosoever shall call on the name of the Lord shall be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 22, 'Ye men of Israel, hear these words; Jesus of Nazareth, a man approved of God among you by miracles and wonders and signs, which God did by him in the midst of you, as ye yourselves also know:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 23, 'Him, being delivered by the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God, ye have taken, and by wicked hands have crucified and slain:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 24, 'Whom God hath raised up, having loosed the pains of death: because it was not possible that he should be holden of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 25, 'For David speaketh concerning him, I foresaw the Lord always before my face, for he is on my right hand, that I should not be moved:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 26, 'Therefore did my heart rejoice, and my tongue was glad; moreover also my flesh shall rest in hope:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 27, 'Because thou wilt not leave my soul in hell, neither wilt thou suffer thine Holy One to see corruption.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 28, 'Thou hast made known to me the ways of life; thou shalt make me full of joy with thy countenance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 29, 'Men and brethren, let me freely speak unto you of the patriarch David, that he is both dead and buried, and his sepulchre is with us unto this day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 30, 'Therefore being a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an oath to him, that of the fruit of his loins, according to the flesh, he would raise up Christ to sit on his throne;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 31, 'He seeing this before spake of the resurrection of Christ, that his soul was not left in hell, neither his flesh did see corruption.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 32, 'This Jesus hath God raised up, whereof we all are witnesses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 33, 'Therefore being by the right hand of God exalted, and having received of the Father the promise of the Holy Ghost, he hath shed forth this, which ye now see and hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 34, 'For David is not ascended into the heavens: but he saith himself, The LORD said unto my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 35, 'Until I make thy foes thy footstool.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 36, 'Therefore let all the house of Israel know assuredly, that God hath made that same Jesus, whom ye have crucified, both Lord and Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 37, 'Now when they heard this, they were pricked in their heart, and said unto Peter and to the rest of the apostles, Men and brethren, what shall we do?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 38, 'Then Peter said unto them, Repent, and be baptized every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ for the remission of sins, and ye shall receive the gift of the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 39, 'For the promise is unto you, and to your children, and to all that are afar off, even as many as the Lord our God shall call.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 40, 'And with many other words did he testify and exhort, saying, Save yourselves from this untoward generation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 41, 'Then they that gladly received his word were baptized: and the same day there were added unto them about three thousand souls.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 42, 'And they continued stedfastly in the apostles'' doctrine and fellowship, and in breaking of bread, and in prayers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 43, 'And fear came upon every soul: and many wonders and signs were done by the apostles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 44, 'And all that believed were together, and had all things common;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 45, 'And sold their possessions and goods, and parted them to all men, as every man had need.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 46, 'And they, continuing daily with one accord in the temple, and breaking bread from house to house, did eat their meat with gladness and singleness of heart,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 2, 47, 'Praising God, and having favour with all the people. And the Lord added to the church daily such as should be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 1, 'Now Peter and John went up together into the temple at the hour of prayer, being the ninth hour.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 2, 'And a certain man lame from his mother''s womb was carried, whom they laid daily at the gate of the temple which is called Beautiful, to ask alms of them that entered into the temple;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 3, 'Who seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple asked an alms.')
insert into control_room_bible (version, book, book_num, chapter, verse, text) values
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 4, 'And Peter, fastening his eyes upon him with John, said, Look on us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 5, 'And he gave heed unto them, expecting to receive something of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 6, 'Then Peter said, Silver and gold have I none; but such as I have give I thee: In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth rise up and walk.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 7, 'And he took him by the right hand, and lifted him up: and immediately his feet and ankle bones received strength.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 8, 'And he leaping up stood, and walked, and entered with them into the temple, walking, and leaping, and praising God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 9, 'And all the people saw him walking and praising God:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 10, 'And they knew that it was he which sat for alms at the Beautiful gate of the temple: and they were filled with wonder and amazement at that which had happened unto him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 11, 'And as the lame man which was healed held Peter and John, all the people ran together unto them in the porch that is called Solomon''s, greatly wondering.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 12, 'And when Peter saw it, he answered unto the people, Ye men of Israel, why marvel ye at this? or why look ye so earnestly on us, as though by our own power or holiness we had made this man to walk?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 13, 'The God of Abraham, and of Isaac, and of Jacob, the God of our fathers, hath glorified his Son Jesus; whom ye delivered up, and denied him in the presence of Pilate, when he was determined to let him go.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 14, 'But ye denied the Holy One and the Just, and desired a murderer to be granted unto you;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 15, 'And killed the Prince of life, whom God hath raised from the dead; whereof we are witnesses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 16, 'And his name through faith in his name hath made this man strong, whom ye see and know: yea, the faith which is by him hath given him this perfect soundness in the presence of you all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 17, 'And now, brethren, I wot that through ignorance ye did it, as did also your rulers.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 18, 'But those things, which God before had shewed by the mouth of all his prophets, that Christ should suffer, he hath so fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 19, 'Repent ye therefore, and be converted, that your sins may be blotted out, when the times of refreshing shall come from the presence of the Lord;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 20, 'And he shall send Jesus Christ, which before was preached unto you:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 21, 'Whom the heaven must receive until the times of restitution of all things, which God hath spoken by the mouth of all his holy prophets since the world began.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 22, 'For Moses truly said unto the fathers, A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you of your brethren, like unto me; him shall ye hear in all things whatsoever he shall say unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 23, 'And it shall come to pass, that every soul, which will not hear that prophet, shall be destroyed from among the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 24, 'Yea, and all the prophets from Samuel and those that follow after, as many as have spoken, have likewise foretold of these days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 25, 'Ye are the children of the prophets, and of the covenant which God made with our fathers, saying unto Abraham, And in thy seed shall all the kindreds of the earth be blessed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 3, 26, 'Unto you first God, having raised up his Son Jesus, sent him to bless you, in turning away every one of you from his iniquities.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 1, 'And as they spake unto the people, the priests, and the captain of the temple, and the Sadducees, came upon them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 2, 'Being grieved that they taught the people, and preached through Jesus the resurrection from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 3, 'And they laid hands on them, and put them in hold unto the next day: for it was now eventide.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 4, 'Howbeit many of them which heard the word believed; and the number of the men was about five thousand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 5, 'And it came to pass on the morrow, that their rulers, and elders, and scribes,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 6, 'And Annas the high priest, and Caiaphas, and John, and Alexander, and as many as were of the kindred of the high priest, were gathered together at Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 7, 'And when they had set them in the midst, they asked, By what power, or by what name, have ye done this?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 8, 'Then Peter, filled with the Holy Ghost, said unto them, Ye rulers of the people, and elders of Israel,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 9, 'If we this day be examined of the good deed done to the impotent man, by what means he is made whole;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 10, 'Be it known unto you all, and to all the people of Israel, that by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom ye crucified, whom God raised from the dead, even by him doth this man stand here before you whole.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 11, 'This is the stone which was set at nought of you builders, which is become the head of the corner.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 12, 'Neither is there salvation in any other: for there is none other name under heaven given among men, whereby we must be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 13, 'Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men, they marvelled; and they took knowledge of them, that they had been with Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 14, 'And beholding the man which was healed standing with them, they could say nothing against it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 15, 'But when they had commanded them to go aside out of the council, they conferred among themselves,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 16, 'Saying, What shall we do to these men? for that indeed a notable miracle hath been done by them is manifest to all them that dwell in Jerusalem; and we cannot deny it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 17, 'But that it spread no further among the people, let us straitly threaten them, that they speak henceforth to no man in this name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 18, 'And they called them, and commanded them not to speak at all nor teach in the name of Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 19, 'But Peter and John answered and said unto them, Whether it be right in the sight of God to hearken unto you more than unto God, judge ye.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 20, 'For we cannot but speak the things which we have seen and heard.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 21, 'So when they had further threatened them, they let them go, finding nothing how they might punish them, because of the people: for all men glorified God for that which was done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 22, 'For the man was above forty years old, on whom this miracle of healing was shewed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 23, 'And being let go, they went to their own company, and reported all that the chief priests and elders had said unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 24, 'And when they heard that, they lifted up their voice to God with one accord, and said, Lord, thou art God, which hast made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all that in them is:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 25, 'Who by the mouth of thy servant David hast said, Why did the heathen rage, and the people imagine vain things?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 26, 'The kings of the earth stood up, and the rulers were gathered together against the Lord, and against his Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 27, 'For of a truth against thy holy child Jesus, whom thou hast anointed, both Herod, and Pontius Pilate, with the Gentiles, and the people of Israel, were gathered together,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 28, 'For to do whatsoever thy hand and thy counsel determined before to be done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 29, 'And now, Lord, behold their threatenings: and grant unto thy servants, that with all boldness they may speak thy word,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 30, 'By stretching forth thine hand to heal; and that signs and wonders may be done by the name of thy holy child Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 31, 'And when they had prayed, the place was shaken where they were assembled together; and they were all filled with the Holy Ghost, and they spake the word of God with boldness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 32, 'And the multitude of them that believed were of one heart and of one soul: neither said any of them that ought of the things which he possessed was his own; but they had all things common.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 33, 'And with great power gave the apostles witness of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus: and great grace was upon them all.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 34, 'Neither was there any among them that lacked: for as many as were possessors of lands or houses sold them, and brought the prices of the things that were sold,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 35, 'And laid them down at the apostles'' feet: and distribution was made unto every man according as he had need.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 36, 'And Joses, who by the apostles was surnamed Barnabas, (which is, being interpreted, The son of consolation,) a Levite, and of the country of Cyprus,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 4, 37, 'Having land, sold it, and brought the money, and laid it at the apostles'' feet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 1, 'But a certain man named Ananias, with Sapphira his wife, sold a possession,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 2, 'And kept back part of the price, his wife also being privy to it, and brought a certain part, and laid it at the apostles'' feet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 3, 'But Peter said, Ananias, why hath Satan filled thine heart to lie to the Holy Ghost, and to keep back part of the price of the land?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 4, 'Whiles it remained, was it not thine own? and after it was sold, was it not in thine own power? why hast thou conceived this thing in thine heart? thou hast not lied unto men, but unto God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 5, 'And Ananias hearing these words fell down, and gave up the ghost: and great fear came on all them that heard these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 6, 'And the young men arose, wound him up, and carried him out, and buried him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 7, 'And it was about the space of three hours after, when his wife, not knowing what was done, came in.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 8, 'And Peter answered unto her, Tell me whether ye sold the land for so much? And she said, Yea, for so much.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 9, 'Then Peter said unto her, How is it that ye have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of the Lord? behold, the feet of them which have buried thy husband are at the door, and shall carry thee out.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 10, 'Then fell she down straightway at his feet, and yielded up the ghost: and the young men came in, and found her dead, and, carrying her forth, buried her by her husband.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 11, 'And great fear came upon all the church, and upon as many as heard these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 12, 'And by the hands of the apostles were many signs and wonders wrought among the people; (and they were all with one accord in Solomon''s porch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 13, 'And of the rest durst no man join himself to them: but the people magnified them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 14, 'And believers were the more added to the Lord, multitudes both of men and women.)'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 15, 'Insomuch that they brought forth the sick into the streets, and laid them on beds and couches, that at the least the shadow of Peter passing by might overshadow some of them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 16, 'There came also a multitude out of the cities round about unto Jerusalem, bringing sick folks, and them which were vexed with unclean spirits: and they were healed every one.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 17, 'Then the high priest rose up, and all they that were with him, (which is the sect of the Sadducees,) and were filled with indignation,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 18, 'And laid their hands on the apostles, and put them in the common prison.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 19, 'But the angel of the Lord by night opened the prison doors, and brought them forth, and said,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 20, 'Go, stand and speak in the temple to the people all the words of this life.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 21, 'And when they heard that, they entered into the temple early in the morning, and taught. But the high priest came, and they that were with him, and called the council together, and all the senate of the children of Israel, and sent to the prison to have them brought.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 22, 'But when the officers came, and found them not in the prison, they returned, and told,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 23, 'Saying, The prison truly found we shut with all safety, and the keepers standing without before the doors: but when we had opened, we found no man within.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 24, 'Now when the high priest and the captain of the temple and the chief priests heard these things, they doubted of them whereunto this would grow.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 25, 'Then came one and told them, saying, Behold, the men whom ye put in prison are standing in the temple, and teaching the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 26, 'Then went the captain with the officers, and brought them without violence: for they feared the people, lest they should have been stoned.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 27, 'And when they had brought them, they set them before the council: and the high priest asked them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 28, 'Saying, Did not we straitly command you that ye should not teach in this name? and, behold, ye have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine, and intend to bring this man''s blood upon us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 29, 'Then Peter and the other apostles answered and said, We ought to obey God rather than men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 30, 'The God of our fathers raised up Jesus, whom ye slew and hanged on a tree.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 31, 'Him hath God exalted with his right hand to be a Prince and a Saviour, for to give repentance to Israel, and forgiveness of sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 32, 'And we are his witnesses of these things; and so is also the Holy Ghost, whom God hath given to them that obey him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 33, 'When they heard that, they were cut to the heart, and took counsel to slay them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 34, 'Then stood there up one in the council, a Pharisee, named Gamaliel, a doctor of the law, had in reputation among all the people, and commanded to put the apostles forth a little space;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 35, 'And said unto them, Ye men of Israel, take heed to yourselves what ye intend to do as touching these men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 36, 'For before these days rose up Theudas, boasting himself to be somebody; to whom a number of men, about four hundred, joined themselves: who was slain; and all, as many as obeyed him, were scattered, and brought to nought.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 37, 'After this man rose up Judas of Galilee in the days of the taxing, and drew away much people after him: he also perished; and all, even as many as obeyed him, were dispersed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 38, 'And now I say unto you, Refrain from these men, and let them alone: for if this counsel or this work be of men, it will come to nought:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 39, 'But if it be of God, ye cannot overthrow it; lest haply ye be found even to fight against God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 40, 'And to him they agreed: and when they had called the apostles, and beaten them, they commanded that they should not speak in the name of Jesus, and let them go.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 41, 'And they departed from the presence of the council, rejoicing that they were counted worthy to suffer shame for his name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 5, 42, 'And daily in the temple, and in every house, they ceased not to teach and preach Jesus Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 1, 'And in those days, when the number of the disciples was multiplied, there arose a murmuring of the Grecians against the Hebrews, because their widows were neglected in the daily ministration.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 2, 'Then the twelve called the multitude of the disciples unto them, and said, It is not reason that we should leave the word of God, and serve tables.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 3, 'Wherefore, brethren, look ye out among you seven men of honest report, full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom, whom we may appoint over this business.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 4, 'But we will give ourselves continually to prayer, and to the ministry of the word.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 5, 'And the saying pleased the whole multitude: and they chose Stephen, a man full of faith and of the Holy Ghost, and Philip, and Prochorus, and Nicanor, and Timon, and Parmenas, and Nicolas a proselyte of Antioch:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 6, 'Whom they set before the apostles: and when they had prayed, they laid their hands on them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 7, 'And the word of God increased; and the number of the disciples multiplied in Jerusalem greatly; and a great company of the priests were obedient to the faith.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 8, 'And Stephen, full of faith and power, did great wonders and miracles among the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 9, 'Then there arose certain of the synagogue, which is called the synagogue of the Libertines, and Cyrenians, and Alexandrians, and of them of Cilicia and of Asia, disputing with Stephen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 10, 'And they were not able to resist the wisdom and the spirit by which he spake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 11, 'Then they suborned men, which said, We have heard him speak blasphemous words against Moses, and against God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 12, 'And they stirred up the people, and the elders, and the scribes, and came upon him, and caught him, and brought him to the council,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 13, 'And set up false witnesses, which said, This man ceaseth not to speak blasphemous words against this holy place, and the law:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 14, 'For we have heard him say, that this Jesus of Nazareth shall destroy this place, and shall change the customs which Moses delivered us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 6, 15, 'And all that sat in the council, looking stedfastly on him, saw his face as it had been the face of an angel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 1, 'Then said the high priest, Are these things so?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 2, 'And he said, Men, brethren, and fathers, hearken; The God of glory appeared unto our father Abraham, when he was in Mesopotamia, before he dwelt in Charran,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 3, 'And said unto him, Get thee out of thy country, and from thy kindred, and come into the land which I shall shew thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 4, 'Then came he out of the land of the Chaldaeans, and dwelt in Charran: and from thence, when his father was dead, he removed him into this land, wherein ye now dwell.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 5, 'And he gave him none inheritance in it, no, not so much as to set his foot on: yet he promised that he would give it to him for a possession, and to his seed after him, when as yet he had no child.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 6, 'And God spake on this wise, That his seed should sojourn in a strange land; and that they should bring them into bondage, and entreat them evil four hundred years.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 7, 'And the nation to whom they shall be in bondage will I judge, said God: and after that shall they come forth, and serve me in this place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 8, 'And he gave him the covenant of circumcision: and so Abraham begat Isaac, and circumcised him the eighth day; and Isaac begat Jacob; and Jacob begat the twelve patriarchs.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 9, 'And the patriarchs, moved with envy, sold Joseph into Egypt: but God was with him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 10, 'And delivered him out of all his afflictions, and gave him favour and wisdom in the sight of Pharaoh king of Egypt; and he made him governor over Egypt and all his house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 11, 'Now there came a dearth over all the land of Egypt and Chanaan, and great affliction: and our fathers found no sustenance.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 12, 'But when Jacob heard that there was corn in Egypt, he sent out our fathers first.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 13, 'And at the second time Joseph was made known to his brethren; and Joseph''s kindred was made known unto Pharaoh.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 14, 'Then sent Joseph, and called his father Jacob to him, and all his kindred, threescore and fifteen souls.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 15, 'So Jacob went down into Egypt, and died, he, and our fathers,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 16, 'And were carried over into Sychem, and laid in the sepulchre that Abraham bought for a sum of money of the sons of Emmor the father of Sychem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 17, 'But when the time of the promise drew nigh, which God had sworn to Abraham, the people grew and multiplied in Egypt,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 18, 'Till another king arose, which knew not Joseph.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 19, 'The same dealt subtilly with our kindred, and evil entreated our fathers, so that they cast out their young children, to the end they might not live.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 20, 'In which time Moses was born, and was exceeding fair, and nourished up in his father''s house three months:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 21, 'And when he was cast out, Pharaoh''s daughter took him up, and nourished him for her own son.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 22, 'And Moses was learned in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and was mighty in words and in deeds.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 23, 'And when he was full forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his brethren the children of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 24, 'And seeing one of them suffer wrong, he defended him, and avenged him that was oppressed, and smote the Egyptian:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 25, 'For he supposed his brethren would have understood how that God by his hand would deliver them: but they understood not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 26, 'And the next day he shewed himself unto them as they strove, and would have set them at one again, saying, Sirs, ye are brethren; why do ye wrong one to another?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 27, 'But he that did his neighbour wrong thrust him away, saying, Who made thee a ruler and a judge over us?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 28, 'Wilt thou kill me, as thou diddest the Egyptian yesterday?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 29, 'Then fled Moses at this saying, and was a stranger in the land of Madian, where he begat two sons.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 30, 'And when forty years were expired, there appeared to him in the wilderness of mount Sina an angel of the Lord in a flame of fire in a bush.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 31, 'When Moses saw it, he wondered at the sight: and as he drew near to behold it, the voice of the Lord came unto him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 32, 'Saying, I am the God of thy fathers, the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob. Then Moses trembled, and durst not behold.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 33, 'Then said the Lord to him, Put off thy shoes from thy feet: for the place where thou standest is holy ground.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 34, 'I have seen, I have seen the affliction of my people which is in Egypt, and I have heard their groaning, and am come down to deliver them. And now come, I will send thee into Egypt.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 35, 'This Moses whom they refused, saying, Who made thee a ruler and a judge? the same did God send to be a ruler and a deliverer by the hand of the angel which appeared to him in the bush.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 36, 'He brought them out, after that he had shewed wonders and signs in the land of Egypt, and in the Red sea, and in the wilderness forty years.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 37, 'This is that Moses, which said unto the children of Israel, A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you of your brethren, like unto me; him shall ye hear.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 38, 'This is he, that was in the church in the wilderness with the angel which spake to him in the mount Sina, and with our fathers: who received the lively oracles to give unto us:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 39, 'To whom our fathers would not obey, but thrust him from them, and in their hearts turned back again into Egypt,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 40, 'Saying unto Aaron, Make us gods to go before us: for as for this Moses, which brought us out of the land of Egypt, we wot not what is become of him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 41, 'And they made a calf in those days, and offered sacrifice unto the idol, and rejoiced in the works of their own hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 42, 'Then God turned, and gave them up to worship the host of heaven; as it is written in the book of the prophets, O ye house of Israel, have ye offered to me slain beasts and sacrifices by the space of forty years in the wilderness?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 43, 'Yea, ye took up the tabernacle of Moloch, and the star of your god Remphan, figures which ye made to worship them: and I will carry you away beyond Babylon.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 44, 'Our fathers had the tabernacle of witness in the wilderness, as he had appointed, speaking unto Moses, that he should make it according to the fashion that he had seen.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 45, 'Which also our fathers that came after brought in with Jesus into the possession of the Gentiles, whom God drave out before the face of our fathers, unto the days of David;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 46, 'Who found favour before God, and desired to find a tabernacle for the God of Jacob.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 47, 'But Solomon built him an house.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 48, 'Howbeit the most High dwelleth not in temples made with hands; as saith the prophet,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 49, 'Heaven is my throne, and earth is my footstool: what house will ye build me? saith the Lord: or what is the place of my rest?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 50, 'Hath not my hand made all these things?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 51, 'Ye stiffnecked and uncircumcised in heart and ears, ye do always resist the Holy Ghost: as your fathers did, so do ye.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 52, 'Which of the prophets have not your fathers persecuted? and they have slain them which shewed before of the coming of the Just One; of whom ye have been now the betrayers and murderers:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 53, 'Who have received the law by the disposition of angels, and have not kept it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 54, 'When they heard these things, they were cut to the heart, and they gnashed on him with their teeth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 55, 'But he, being full of the Holy Ghost, looked up stedfastly into heaven, and saw the glory of God, and Jesus standing on the right hand of God,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 56, 'And said, Behold, I see the heavens opened, and the Son of man standing on the right hand of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 57, 'Then they cried out with a loud voice, and stopped their ears, and ran upon him with one accord,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 58, 'And cast him out of the city, and stoned him: and the witnesses laid down their clothes at a young man''s feet, whose name was Saul.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 59, 'And they stoned Stephen, calling upon God, and saying, Lord Jesus, receive my spirit.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 7, 60, 'And he kneeled down, and cried with a loud voice, Lord, lay not this sin to their charge. And when he had said this, he fell asleep.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 1, 'And Saul was consenting unto his death. And at that time there was a great persecution against the church which was at Jerusalem; and they were all scattered abroad throughout the regions of Judaea and Samaria, except the apostles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 2, 'And devout men carried Stephen to his burial, and made great lamentation over him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 3, 'As for Saul, he made havock of the church, entering into every house, and haling men and women committed them to prison.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 4, 'Therefore they that were scattered abroad went every where preaching the word.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 5, 'Then Philip went down to the city of Samaria, and preached Christ unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 6, 'And the people with one accord gave heed unto those things which Philip spake, hearing and seeing the miracles which he did.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 7, 'For unclean spirits, crying with loud voice, came out of many that were possessed with them: and many taken with palsies, and that were lame, were healed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 8, 'And there was great joy in that city.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 9, 'But there was a certain man, called Simon, which beforetime in the same city used sorcery, and bewitched the people of Samaria, giving out that himself was some great one:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 10, 'To whom they all gave heed, from the least to the greatest, saying, This man is the great power of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 11, 'And to him they had regard, because that of long time he had bewitched them with sorceries.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 12, 'But when they believed Philip preaching the things concerning the kingdom of God, and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 13, 'Then Simon himself believed also: and when he was baptized, he continued with Philip, and wondered, beholding the miracles and signs which were done.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 14, 'Now when the apostles which were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of God, they sent unto them Peter and John:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 15, 'Who, when they were come down, prayed for them, that they might receive the Holy Ghost:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 16, '(For as yet he was fallen upon none of them: only they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.)'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 17, 'Then laid they their hands on them, and they received the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 18, 'And when Simon saw that through laying on of the apostles'' hands the Holy Ghost was given, he offered them money,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 19, 'Saying, Give me also this power, that on whomsoever I lay hands, he may receive the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 20, 'But Peter said unto him, Thy money perish with thee, because thou hast thought that the gift of God may be purchased with money.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 21, 'Thou hast neither part nor lot in this matter: for thy heart is not right in the sight of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 22, 'Repent therefore of this thy wickedness, and pray God, if perhaps the thought of thine heart may be forgiven thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 23, 'For I perceive that thou art in the gall of bitterness, and in the bond of iniquity.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 24, 'Then answered Simon, and said, Pray ye to the Lord for me, that none of these things which ye have spoken come upon me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 25, 'And they, when they had testified and preached the word of the Lord, returned to Jerusalem, and preached the gospel in many villages of the Samaritans.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 26, 'And the angel of the Lord spake unto Philip, saying, Arise, and go toward the south unto the way that goeth down from Jerusalem unto Gaza, which is desert.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 27, 'And he arose and went: and, behold, a man of Ethiopia, an eunuch of great authority under Candace queen of the Ethiopians, who had the charge of all her treasure, and had come to Jerusalem for to worship,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 28, 'Was returning, and sitting in his chariot read Esaias the prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 29, 'Then the Spirit said unto Philip, Go near, and join thyself to this chariot.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 30, 'And Philip ran thither to him, and heard him read the prophet Esaias, and said, Understandest thou what thou readest?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 31, 'And he said, How can I, except some man should guide me? And he desired Philip that he would come up and sit with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 32, 'The place of the scripture which he read was this, He was led as a sheep to the slaughter; and like a lamb dumb before his shearer, so opened he not his mouth:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 33, 'In his humiliation his judgment was taken away: and who shall declare his generation? for his life is taken from the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 34, 'And the eunuch answered Philip, and said, I pray thee, of whom speaketh the prophet this? of himself, or of some other man?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 35, 'Then Philip opened his mouth, and began at the same scripture, and preached unto him Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 36, 'And as they went on their way, they came unto a certain water: and the eunuch said, See, here is water; what doth hinder me to be baptized?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 37, 'And Philip said, If thou believest with all thine heart, thou mayest. And he answered and said, I believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 38, 'And he commanded the chariot to stand still: and they went down both into the water, both Philip and the eunuch; and he baptized him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 39, 'And when they were come up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord caught away Philip, that the eunuch saw him no more: and he went on his way rejoicing.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 8, 40, 'But Philip was found at Azotus: and passing through he preached in all the cities, till he came to Caesarea.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 1, 'And Saul, yet breathing out threatenings and slaughter against the disciples of the Lord, went unto the high priest,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 2, 'And desired of him letters to Damascus to the synagogues, that if he found any of this way, whether they were men or women, he might bring them bound unto Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 3, 'And as he journeyed, he came near Damascus: and suddenly there shined round about him a light from heaven:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 4, 'And he fell to the earth, and heard a voice saying unto him, Saul, Saul, why persecutest thou me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 5, 'And he said, Who art thou, Lord? And the Lord said, I am Jesus whom thou persecutest: it is hard for thee to kick against the pricks.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 6, 'And he trembling and astonished said, Lord, what wilt thou have me to do? And the Lord said unto him, Arise, and go into the city, and it shall be told thee what thou must do.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 7, 'And the men which journeyed with him stood speechless, hearing a voice, but seeing no man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 8, 'And Saul arose from the earth; and when his eyes were opened, he saw no man: but they led him by the hand, and brought him into Damascus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 9, 'And he was three days without sight, and neither did eat nor drink.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 10, 'And there was a certain disciple at Damascus, named Ananias; and to him said the Lord in a vision, Ananias. And he said, Behold, I am here, Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 11, 'And the Lord said unto him, Arise, and go into the street which is called Straight, and enquire in the house of Judas for one called Saul, of Tarsus: for, behold, he prayeth,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 12, 'And hath seen in a vision a man named Ananias coming in, and putting his hand on him, that he might receive his sight.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 13, 'Then Ananias answered, Lord, I have heard by many of this man, how much evil he hath done to thy saints at Jerusalem:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 14, 'And here he hath authority from the chief priests to bind all that call on thy name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 15, 'But the Lord said unto him, Go thy way: for he is a chosen vessel unto me, to bear my name before the Gentiles, and kings, and the children of Israel:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 16, 'For I will shew him how great things he must suffer for my name''s sake.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 17, 'And Ananias went his way, and entered into the house; and putting his hands on him said, Brother Saul, the Lord, even Jesus, that appeared unto thee in the way as thou camest, hath sent me, that thou mightest receive thy sight, and be filled with the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 18, 'And immediately there fell from his eyes as it had been scales: and he received sight forthwith, and arose, and was baptized.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 19, 'And when he had received meat, he was strengthened. Then was Saul certain days with the disciples which were at Damascus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 20, 'And straightway he preached Christ in the synagogues, that he is the Son of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 21, 'But all that heard him were amazed, and said; Is not this he that destroyed them which called on this name in Jerusalem, and came hither for that intent, that he might bring them bound unto the chief priests?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 22, 'But Saul increased the more in strength, and confounded the Jews which dwelt at Damascus, proving that this is very Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 23, 'And after that many days were fulfilled, the Jews took counsel to kill him:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 24, 'But their laying await was known of Saul. And they watched the gates day and night to kill him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 25, 'Then the disciples took him by night, and let him down by the wall in a basket.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 26, 'And when Saul was come to Jerusalem, he assayed to join himself to the disciples: but they were all afraid of him, and believed not that he was a disciple.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 27, 'But Barnabas took him, and brought him to the apostles, and declared unto them how he had seen the Lord in the way, and that he had spoken to him, and how he had preached boldly at Damascus in the name of Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 28, 'And he was with them coming in and going out at Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 29, 'And he spake boldly in the name of the Lord Jesus, and disputed against the Grecians: but they went about to slay him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 30, 'Which when the brethren knew, they brought him down to Caesarea, and sent him forth to Tarsus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 31, 'Then had the churches rest throughout all Judaea and Galilee and Samaria, and were edified; and walking in the fear of the Lord, and in the comfort of the Holy Ghost, were multiplied.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 32, 'And it came to pass, as Peter passed throughout all quarters, he came down also to the saints which dwelt at Lydda.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 33, 'And there he found a certain man named Aeneas, which had kept his bed eight years, and was sick of the palsy.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 34, 'And Peter said unto him, Aeneas, Jesus Christ maketh thee whole: arise, and make thy bed. And he arose immediately.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 35, 'And all that dwelt at Lydda and Saron saw him, and turned to the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 36, 'Now there was at Joppa a certain disciple named Tabitha, which by interpretation is called Dorcas: this woman was full of good works and almsdeeds which she did.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 37, 'And it came to pass in those days, that she was sick, and died: whom when they had washed, they laid her in an upper chamber.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 38, 'And forasmuch as Lydda was nigh to Joppa, and the disciples had heard that Peter was there, they sent unto him two men, desiring him that he would not delay to come to them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 39, 'Then Peter arose and went with them. When he was come, they brought him into the upper chamber: and all the widows stood by him weeping, and shewing the coats and garments which Dorcas made, while she was with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 40, 'But Peter put them all forth, and kneeled down, and prayed; and turning him to the body said, Tabitha, arise. And she opened her eyes: and when she saw Peter, she sat up.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 41, 'And he gave her his hand, and lifted her up, and when he had called the saints and widows, presented her alive.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 42, 'And it was known throughout all Joppa; and many believed in the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 9, 43, 'And it came to pass, that he tarried many days in Joppa with one Simon a tanner.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 1, 'There was a certain man in Caesarea called Cornelius, a centurion of the band called the Italian band,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 2, 'A devout man, and one that feared God with all his house, which gave much alms to the people, and prayed to God alway.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 3, 'He saw in a vision evidently about the ninth hour of the day an angel of God coming in to him, and saying unto him, Cornelius.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 4, 'And when he looked on him, he was afraid, and said, What is it, Lord? And he said unto him, Thy prayers and thine alms are come up for a memorial before God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 5, 'And now send men to Joppa, and call for one Simon, whose surname is Peter:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 6, 'He lodgeth with one Simon a tanner, whose house is by the sea side: he shall tell thee what thou oughtest to do.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 7, 'And when the angel which spake unto Cornelius was departed, he called two of his household servants, and a devout soldier of them that waited on him continually;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 8, 'And when he had declared all these things unto them, he sent them to Joppa.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 9, 'On the morrow, as they went on their journey, and drew nigh unto the city, Peter went up upon the housetop to pray about the sixth hour:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 10, 'And he became very hungry, and would have eaten: but while they made ready, he fell into a trance,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 11, 'And saw heaven opened, and a certain vessel descending unto him, as it had been a great sheet knit at the four corners, and let down to the earth:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 12, 'Wherein were all manner of fourfooted beasts of the earth, and wild beasts, and creeping things, and fowls of the air.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 13, 'And there came a voice to him, Rise, Peter; kill, and eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 14, 'But Peter said, Not so, Lord; for I have never eaten any thing that is common or unclean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 15, 'And the voice spake unto him again the second time, What God hath cleansed, that call not thou common.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 16, 'This was done thrice: and the vessel was received up again into heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 17, 'Now while Peter doubted in himself what this vision which he had seen should mean, behold, the men which were sent from Cornelius had made enquiry for Simon''s house, and stood before the gate,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 18, 'And called, and asked whether Simon, which was surnamed Peter, were lodged there.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 19, 'While Peter thought on the vision, the Spirit said unto him, Behold, three men seek thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 20, 'Arise therefore, and get thee down, and go with them, doubting nothing: for I have sent them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 21, 'Then Peter went down to the men which were sent unto him from Cornelius; and said, Behold, I am he whom ye seek: what is the cause wherefore ye are come?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 22, 'And they said, Cornelius the centurion, a just man, and one that feareth God, and of good report among all the nation of the Jews, was warned from God by an holy angel to send for thee into his house, and to hear words of thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 23, 'Then called he them in, and lodged them. And on the morrow Peter went away with them, and certain brethren from Joppa accompanied him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 24, 'And the morrow after they entered into Caesarea. And Cornelius waited for them, and had called together his kinsmen and near friends.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 25, 'And as Peter was coming in, Cornelius met him, and fell down at his feet, and worshipped him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 26, 'But Peter took him up, saying, Stand up; I myself also am a man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 27, 'And as he talked with him, he went in, and found many that were come together.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 28, 'And he said unto them, Ye know how that it is an unlawful thing for a man that is a Jew to keep company, or come unto one of another nation; but God hath shewed me that I should not call any man common or unclean.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 29, 'Therefore came I unto you without gainsaying, as soon as I was sent for: I ask therefore for what intent ye have sent for me?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 30, 'And Cornelius said, Four days ago I was fasting until this hour; and at the ninth hour I prayed in my house, and, behold, a man stood before me in bright clothing,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 31, 'And said, Cornelius, thy prayer is heard, and thine alms are had in remembrance in the sight of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 32, 'Send therefore to Joppa, and call hither Simon, whose surname is Peter; he is lodged in the house of one Simon a tanner by the sea side: who, when he cometh, shall speak unto thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 33, 'Immediately therefore I sent to thee; and thou hast well done that thou art come. Now therefore are we all here present before God, to hear all things that are commanded thee of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 34, 'Then Peter opened his mouth, and said, Of a truth I perceive that God is no respecter of persons:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 35, 'But in every nation he that feareth him, and worketh righteousness, is accepted with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 36, 'The word which God sent unto the children of Israel, preaching peace by Jesus Christ: (he is Lord of all:)'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 37, 'That word, I say, ye know, which was published throughout all Judaea, and began from Galilee, after the baptism which John preached;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 38, 'How God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Ghost and with power: who went about doing good, and healing all that were oppressed of the devil; for God was with him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 39, 'And we are witnesses of all things which he did both in the land of the Jews, and in Jerusalem; whom they slew and hanged on a tree:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 40, 'Him God raised up the third day, and shewed him openly;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 41, 'Not to all the people, but unto witnesses chosen before of God, even to us, who did eat and drink with him after he rose from the dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 42, 'And he commanded us to preach unto the people, and to testify that it is he which was ordained of God to be the Judge of quick and dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 43, 'To him give all the prophets witness, that through his name whosoever believeth in him shall receive remission of sins.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 44, 'While Peter yet spake these words, the Holy Ghost fell on all them which heard the word.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 45, 'And they of the circumcision which believed were astonished, as many as came with Peter, because that on the Gentiles also was poured out the gift of the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 46, 'For they heard them speak with tongues, and magnify God. Then answered Peter,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 47, 'Can any man forbid water, that these should not be baptized, which have received the Holy Ghost as well as we?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 10, 48, 'And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of the Lord. Then prayed they him to tarry certain days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 1, 'And the apostles and brethren that were in Judaea heard that the Gentiles had also received the word of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 2, 'And when Peter was come up to Jerusalem, they that were of the circumcision contended with him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 3, 'Saying, Thou wentest in to men uncircumcised, and didst eat with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 4, 'But Peter rehearsed the matter from the beginning, and expounded it by order unto them, saying,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 5, 'I was in the city of Joppa praying: and in a trance I saw a vision, A certain vessel descend, as it had been a great sheet, let down from heaven by four corners; and it came even to me:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 6, 'Upon the which when I had fastened mine eyes, I considered, and saw fourfooted beasts of the earth, and wild beasts, and creeping things, and fowls of the air.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 7, 'And I heard a voice saying unto me, Arise, Peter; slay and eat.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 8, 'But I said, Not so, Lord: for nothing common or unclean hath at any time entered into my mouth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 9, 'But the voice answered me again from heaven, What God hath cleansed, that call not thou common.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 10, 'And this was done three times: and all were drawn up again into heaven.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 11, 'And, behold, immediately there were three men already come unto the house where I was, sent from Caesarea unto me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 12, 'And the Spirit bade me go with them, nothing doubting. Moreover these six brethren accompanied me, and we entered into the man''s house:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 13, 'And he shewed us how he had seen an angel in his house, which stood and said unto him, Send men to Joppa, and call for Simon, whose surname is Peter;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 14, 'Who shall tell thee words, whereby thou and all thy house shall be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 15, 'And as I began to speak, the Holy Ghost fell on them, as on us at the beginning.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 16, 'Then remembered I the word of the Lord, how that he said, John indeed baptized with water; but ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 17, 'Forasmuch then as God gave them the like gift as he did unto us, who believed on the Lord Jesus Christ; what was I, that I could withstand God?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 18, 'When they heard these things, they held their peace, and glorified God, saying, Then hath God also to the Gentiles granted repentance unto life.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 19, 'Now they which were scattered abroad upon the persecution that arose about Stephen travelled as far as Phenice, and Cyprus, and Antioch, preaching the word to none but unto the Jews only.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 20, 'And some of them were men of Cyprus and Cyrene, which, when they were come to Antioch, spake unto the Grecians, preaching the Lord Jesus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 21, 'And the hand of the Lord was with them: and a great number believed, and turned unto the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 22, 'Then tidings of these things came unto the ears of the church which was in Jerusalem: and they sent forth Barnabas, that he should go as far as Antioch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 23, 'Who, when he came, and had seen the grace of God, was glad, and exhorted them all, that with purpose of heart they would cleave unto the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 24, 'For he was a good man, and full of the Holy Ghost and of faith: and much people was added unto the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 25, 'Then departed Barnabas to Tarsus, for to seek Saul:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 26, 'And when he had found him, he brought him unto Antioch. And it came to pass, that a whole year they assembled themselves with the church, and taught much people. And the disciples were called Christians first in Antioch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 27, 'And in these days came prophets from Jerusalem unto Antioch.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 28, 'And there stood up one of them named Agabus, and signified by the Spirit that there should be great dearth throughout all the world: which came to pass in the days of Claudius Caesar.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 29, 'Then the disciples, every man according to his ability, determined to send relief unto the brethren which dwelt in Judaea:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 11, 30, 'Which also they did, and sent it to the elders by the hands of Barnabas and Saul.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 1, 'Now about that time Herod the king stretched forth his hands to vex certain of the church.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 2, 'And he killed James the brother of John with the sword.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 3, 'And because he saw it pleased the Jews, he proceeded further to take Peter also. (Then were the days of unleavened bread.)'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 4, 'And when he had apprehended him, he put him in prison, and delivered him to four quaternions of soldiers to keep him; intending after Easter to bring him forth to the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 5, 'Peter therefore was kept in prison: but prayer was made without ceasing of the church unto God for him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 6, 'And when Herod would have brought him forth, the same night Peter was sleeping between two soldiers, bound with two chains: and the keepers before the door kept the prison.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 7, 'And, behold, the angel of the Lord came upon him, and a light shined in the prison: and he smote Peter on the side, and raised him up, saying, Arise up quickly. And his chains fell off from his hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 8, 'And the angel said unto him, Gird thyself, and bind on thy sandals. And so he did. And he saith unto him, Cast thy garment about thee, and follow me.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 9, 'And he went out, and followed him; and wist not that it was true which was done by the angel; but thought he saw a vision.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 10, 'When they were past the first and the second ward, they came unto the iron gate that leadeth unto the city; which opened to them of his own accord: and they went out, and passed on through one street; and forthwith the angel departed from him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 11, 'And when Peter was come to himself, he said, Now I know of a surety, that the Lord hath sent his angel, and hath delivered me out of the hand of Herod, and from all the expectation of the people of the Jews.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 12, 'And when he had considered the thing, he came to the house of Mary the mother of John, whose surname was Mark; where many were gathered together praying.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 13, 'And as Peter knocked at the door of the gate, a damsel came to hearken, named Rhoda.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 14, 'And when she knew Peter''s voice, she opened not the gate for gladness, but ran in, and told how Peter stood before the gate.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 15, 'And they said unto her, Thou art mad. But she constantly affirmed that it was even so. Then said they, It is his angel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 16, 'But Peter continued knocking: and when they had opened the door, and saw him, they were astonished.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 17, 'But he, beckoning unto them with the hand to hold their peace, declared unto them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison. And he said, Go shew these things unto James, and to the brethren. And he departed, and went into another place.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 18, 'Now as soon as it was day, there was no small stir among the soldiers, what was become of Peter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 19, 'And when Herod had sought for him, and found him not, he examined the keepers, and commanded that they should be put to death. And he went down from Judaea to Caesarea, and there abode.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 20, 'And Herod was highly displeased with them of Tyre and Sidon: but they came with one accord to him, and, having made Blastus the king''s chamberlain their friend, desired peace; because their country was nourished by the king''s country.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 21, 'And upon a set day Herod, arrayed in royal apparel, sat upon his throne, and made an oration unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 22, 'And the people gave a shout, saying, It is the voice of a god, and not of a man.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 23, 'And immediately the angel of the Lord smote him, because he gave not God the glory: and he was eaten of worms, and gave up the ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 24, 'But the word of God grew and multiplied.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 12, 25, 'And Barnabas and Saul returned from Jerusalem, when they had fulfilled their ministry, and took with them John, whose surname was Mark.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 1, 'Now there were in the church that was at Antioch certain prophets and teachers; as Barnabas, and Simeon that was called Niger, and Lucius of Cyrene, and Manaen, which had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch, and Saul.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 2, 'As they ministered to the Lord, and fasted, the Holy Ghost said, Separate me Barnabas and Saul for the work whereunto I have called them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 3, 'And when they had fasted and prayed, and laid their hands on them, they sent them away.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 4, 'So they, being sent forth by the Holy Ghost, departed unto Seleucia; and from thence they sailed to Cyprus.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 5, 'And when they were at Salamis, they preached the word of God in the synagogues of the Jews: and they had also John to their minister.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 6, 'And when they had gone through the isle unto Paphos, they found a certain sorcerer, a false prophet, a Jew, whose name was Barjesus:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 7, 'Which was with the deputy of the country, Sergius Paulus, a prudent man; who called for Barnabas and Saul, and desired to hear the word of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 8, 'But Elymas the sorcerer (for so is his name by interpretation) withstood them, seeking to turn away the deputy from the faith.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 9, 'Then Saul, (who also is called Paul,) filled with the Holy Ghost, set his eyes on him,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 10, 'And said, O full of all subtilty and all mischief, thou child of the devil, thou enemy of all righteousness, wilt thou not cease to pervert the right ways of the Lord?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 11, 'And now, behold, the hand of the Lord is upon thee, and thou shalt be blind, not seeing the sun for a season. And immediately there fell on him a mist and a darkness; and he went about seeking some to lead him by the hand.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 12, 'Then the deputy, when he saw what was done, believed, being astonished at the doctrine of the Lord.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 13, 'Now when Paul and his company loosed from Paphos, they came to Perga in Pamphylia: and John departing from them returned to Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 14, 'But when they departed from Perga, they came to Antioch in Pisidia, and went into the synagogue on the sabbath day, and sat down.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 15, 'And after the reading of the law and the prophets the rulers of the synagogue sent unto them, saying, Ye men and brethren, if ye have any word of exhortation for the people, say on.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 16, 'Then Paul stood up, and beckoning with his hand said, Men of Israel, and ye that fear God, give audience.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 17, 'The God of this people of Israel chose our fathers, and exalted the people when they dwelt as strangers in the land of Egypt, and with an high arm brought he them out of it.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 18, 'And about the time of forty years suffered he their manners in the wilderness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 19, 'And when he had destroyed seven nations in the land of Chanaan, he divided their land to them by lot.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 20, 'And after that he gave unto them judges about the space of four hundred and fifty years, until Samuel the prophet.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 21, 'And afterward they desired a king: and God gave unto them Saul the son of Cis, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, by the space of forty years.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 22, 'And when he had removed him, he raised up unto them David to be their king; to whom also he gave testimony, and said, I have found David the son of Jesse, a man after mine own heart, which shall fulfil all my will.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 23, 'Of this man''s seed hath God according to his promise raised unto Israel a Saviour, Jesus:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 24, 'When John had first preached before his coming the baptism of repentance to all the people of Israel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 25, 'And as John fulfilled his course, he said, Whom think ye that I am? I am not he. But, behold, there cometh one after me, whose shoes of his feet I am not worthy to loose.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 26, 'Men and brethren, children of the stock of Abraham, and whosoever among you feareth God, to you is the word of this salvation sent.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 27, 'For they that dwell at Jerusalem, and their rulers, because they knew him not, nor yet the voices of the prophets which are read every sabbath day, they have fulfilled them in condemning him.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 28, 'And though they found no cause of death in him, yet desired they Pilate that he should be slain.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 29, 'And when they had fulfilled all that was written of him, they took him down from the tree, and laid him in a sepulchre.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 30, 'But God raised him from the dead:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 31, 'And he was seen many days of them which came up with him from Galilee to Jerusalem, who are his witnesses unto the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 32, 'And we declare unto you glad tidings, how that the promise which was made unto the fathers,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 33, 'God hath fulfilled the same unto us their children, in that he hath raised up Jesus again; as it is also written in the second psalm, Thou art my Son, this day have I begotten thee.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 34, 'And as concerning that he raised him up from the dead, now no more to return to corruption, he said on this wise, I will give you the sure mercies of David.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 35, 'Wherefore he saith also in another psalm, Thou shalt not suffer thine Holy One to see corruption.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 36, 'For David, after he had served his own generation by the will of God, fell on sleep, and was laid unto his fathers, and saw corruption:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 37, 'But he, whom God raised again, saw no corruption.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 38, 'Be it known unto you therefore, men and brethren, that through this man is preached unto you the forgiveness of sins:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 39, 'And by him all that believe are justified from all things, from which ye could not be justified by the law of Moses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 40, 'Beware therefore, lest that come upon you, which is spoken of in the prophets;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 41, 'Behold, ye despisers, and wonder, and perish: for I work a work in your days, a work which ye shall in no wise believe, though a man declare it unto you.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 42, 'And when the Jews were gone out of the synagogue, the Gentiles besought that these words might be preached to them the next sabbath.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 43, 'Now when the congregation was broken up, many of the Jews and religious proselytes followed Paul and Barnabas: who, speaking to them, persuaded them to continue in the grace of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 44, 'And the next sabbath day came almost the whole city together to hear the word of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 45, 'But when the Jews saw the multitudes, they were filled with envy, and spake against those things which were spoken by Paul, contradicting and blaspheming.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 46, 'Then Paul and Barnabas waxed bold, and said, It was necessary that the word of God should first have been spoken to you: but seeing ye put it from you, and judge yourselves unworthy of everlasting life, lo, we turn to the Gentiles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 47, 'For so hath the Lord commanded us, saying, I have set thee to be a light of the Gentiles, that thou shouldest be for salvation unto the ends of the earth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 48, 'And when the Gentiles heard this, they were glad, and glorified the word of the Lord: and as many as were ordained to eternal life believed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 49, 'And the word of the Lord was published throughout all the region.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 50, 'But the Jews stirred up the devout and honourable women, and the chief men of the city, and raised persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and expelled them out of their coasts.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 51, 'But they shook off the dust of their feet against them, and came unto Iconium.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 13, 52, 'And the disciples were filled with joy, and with the Holy Ghost.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 1, 'And it came to pass in Iconium, that they went both together into the synagogue of the Jews, and so spake, that a great multitude both of the Jews and also of the Greeks believed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 2, 'But the unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles, and made their minds evil affected against the brethren.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 3, 'Long time therefore abode they speaking boldly in the Lord, which gave testimony unto the word of his grace, and granted signs and wonders to be done by their hands.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 4, 'But the multitude of the city was divided: and part held with the Jews, and part with the apostles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 5, 'And when there was an assault made both of the Gentiles, and also of the Jews with their rulers, to use them despitefully, and to stone them,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 6, 'They were ware of it, and fled unto Lystra and Derbe, cities of Lycaonia, and unto the region that lieth round about:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 7, 'And there they preached the gospel.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 8, 'And there sat a certain man at Lystra, impotent in his feet, being a cripple from his mother''s womb, who never had walked:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 9, 'The same heard Paul speak: who stedfastly beholding him, and perceiving that he had faith to be healed,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 10, 'Said with a loud voice, Stand upright on thy feet. And he leaped and walked.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 11, 'And when the people saw what Paul had done, they lifted up their voices, saying in the speech of Lycaonia, The gods are come down to us in the likeness of men.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 12, 'And they called Barnabas, Jupiter; and Paul, Mercurius, because he was the chief speaker.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 13, 'Then the priest of Jupiter, which was before their city, brought oxen and garlands unto the gates, and would have done sacrifice with the people.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 14, 'Which when the apostles, Barnabas and Paul, heard of, they rent their clothes, and ran in among the people, crying out,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 15, 'And saying, Sirs, why do ye these things? We also are men of like passions with you, and preach unto you that ye should turn from these vanities unto the living God, which made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all things that are therein:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 16, 'Who in times past suffered all nations to walk in their own ways.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 17, 'Nevertheless he left not himself without witness, in that he did good, and gave us rain from heaven, and fruitful seasons, filling our hearts with food and gladness.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 18, 'And with these sayings scarce restrained they the people, that they had not done sacrifice unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 19, 'And there came thither certain Jews from Antioch and Iconium, who persuaded the people, and, having stoned Paul, drew him out of the city, supposing he had been dead.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 20, 'Howbeit, as the disciples stood round about him, he rose up, and came into the city: and the next day he departed with Barnabas to Derbe.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 21, 'And when they had preached the gospel to that city, and had taught many, they returned again to Lystra, and to Iconium, and Antioch,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 22, 'Confirming the souls of the disciples, and exhorting them to continue in the faith, and that we must through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 23, 'And when they had ordained them elders in every church, and had prayed with fasting, they commended them to the Lord, on whom they believed.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 24, 'And after they had passed throughout Pisidia, they came to Pamphylia.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 25, 'And when they had preached the word in Perga, they went down into Attalia:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 26, 'And thence sailed to Antioch, from whence they had been recommended to the grace of God for the work which they fulfilled.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 27, 'And when they were come, and had gathered the church together, they rehearsed all that God had done with them, and how he had opened the door of faith unto the Gentiles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 14, 28, 'And there they abode long time with the disciples.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 1, 'And certain men which came down from Judaea taught the brethren, and said, Except ye be circumcised after the manner of Moses, ye cannot be saved.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 2, 'When therefore Paul and Barnabas had no small dissension and disputation with them, they determined that Paul and Barnabas, and certain other of them, should go up to Jerusalem unto the apostles and elders about this question.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 3, 'And being brought on their way by the church, they passed through Phenice and Samaria, declaring the conversion of the Gentiles: and they caused great joy unto all the brethren.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 4, 'And when they were come to Jerusalem, they were received of the church, and of the apostles and elders, and they declared all things that God had done with them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 5, 'But there rose up certain of the sect of the Pharisees which believed, saying, That it was needful to circumcise them, and to command them to keep the law of Moses.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 6, 'And the apostles and elders came together for to consider of this matter.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 7, 'And when there had been much disputing, Peter rose up, and said unto them, Men and brethren, ye know how that a good while ago God made choice among us, that the Gentiles by my mouth should hear the word of the gospel, and believe.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 8, 'And God, which knoweth the hearts, bare them witness, giving them the Holy Ghost, even as he did unto us;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 9, 'And put no difference between us and them, purifying their hearts by faith.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 10, 'Now therefore why tempt ye God, to put a yoke upon the neck of the disciples, which neither our fathers nor we were able to bear?'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 11, 'But we believe that through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ we shall be saved, even as they.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 12, 'Then all the multitude kept silence, and gave audience to Barnabas and Paul, declaring what miracles and wonders God had wrought among the Gentiles by them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 13, 'And after they had held their peace, James answered, saying, Men and brethren, hearken unto me:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 14, 'Simeon hath declared how God at the first did visit the Gentiles, to take out of them a people for his name.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 15, 'And to this agree the words of the prophets; as it is written,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 16, 'After this I will return, and will build again the tabernacle of David, which is fallen down; and I will build again the ruins thereof, and I will set it up:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 17, 'That the residue of men might seek after the Lord, and all the Gentiles, upon whom my name is called, saith the Lord, who doeth all these things.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 18, 'Known unto God are all his works from the beginning of the world.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 19, 'Wherefore my sentence is, that we trouble not them, which from among the Gentiles are turned to God:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 20, 'But that we write unto them, that they abstain from pollutions of idols, and from fornication, and from things strangled, and from blood.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 21, 'For Moses of old time hath in every city them that preach him, being read in the synagogues every sabbath day.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 22, 'Then pleased it the apostles and elders, with the whole church, to send chosen men of their own company to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas; namely, Judas surnamed Barsabas, and Silas, chief men among the brethren:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 23, 'And they wrote letters by them after this manner; The apostles and elders and brethren send greeting unto the brethren which are of the Gentiles in Antioch and Syria and Cilicia:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 24, 'Forasmuch as we have heard, that certain which went out from us have troubled you with words, subverting your souls, saying, Ye must be circumcised, and keep the law: to whom we gave no such commandment:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 25, 'It seemed good unto us, being assembled with one accord, to send chosen men unto you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 26, 'Men that have hazarded their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 27, 'We have sent therefore Judas and Silas, who shall also tell you the same things by mouth.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 28, 'For it seemed good to the Holy Ghost, and to us, to lay upon you no greater burden than these necessary things;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 29, 'That ye abstain from meats offered to idols, and from blood, and from things strangled, and from fornication: from which if ye keep yourselves, ye shall do well. Fare ye well.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 30, 'So when they were dismissed, they came to Antioch: and when they had gathered the multitude together, they delivered the epistle:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 31, 'Which when they had read, they rejoiced for the consolation.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 32, 'And Judas and Silas, being prophets also themselves, exhorted the brethren with many words, and confirmed them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 33, 'And after they had tarried there a space, they were let go in peace from the brethren unto the apostles.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 34, 'Notwithstanding it pleased Silas to abide there still.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 35, 'Paul also and Barnabas continued in Antioch, teaching and preaching the word of the Lord, with many others also.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 36, 'And some days after Paul said unto Barnabas, Let us go again and visit our brethren in every city where we have preached the word of the Lord, and see how they do.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 37, 'And Barnabas determined to take with them John, whose surname was Mark.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 38, 'But Paul thought not good to take him with them, who departed from them from Pamphylia, and went not with them to the work.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 39, 'And the contention was so sharp between them, that they departed asunder one from the other: and so Barnabas took Mark, and sailed unto Cyprus;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 40, 'And Paul chose Silas, and departed, being recommended by the brethren unto the grace of God.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 15, 41, 'And he went through Syria and Cilicia, confirming the churches.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 1, 'Then came he to Derbe and Lystra: and, behold, a certain disciple was there, named Timotheus, the son of a certain woman, which was a Jewess, and believed; but his father was a Greek:'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 2, 'Which was well reported of by the brethren that were at Lystra and Iconium.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 3, 'Him would Paul have to go forth with him; and took and circumcised him because of the Jews which were in those quarters: for they knew all that his father was a Greek.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 4, 'And as they went through the cities, they delivered them the decrees for to keep, that were ordained of the apostles and elders which were at Jerusalem.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 5, 'And so were the churches established in the faith, and increased in number daily.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 6, 'Now when they had gone throughout Phrygia and the region of Galatia, and were forbidden of the Holy Ghost to preach the word in Asia,'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 7, 'After they were come to Mysia, they assayed to go into Bithynia: but the Spirit suffered them not.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 8, 'And they passing by Mysia came down to Troas.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 9, 'And a vision appeared to Paul in the night; There stood a man of Macedonia, and prayed him, saying, Come over into Macedonia, and help us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 10, 'And after he had seen the vision, immediately we endeavoured to go into Macedonia, assuredly gathering that the Lord had called us for to preach the gospel unto them.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 11, 'Therefore loosing from Troas, we came with a straight course to Samothracia, and the next day to Neapolis;'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 12, 'And from thence to Philippi, which is the chief city of that part of Macedonia, and a colony: and we were in that city abiding certain days.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 13, 'And on the sabbath we went out of the city by a river side, where prayer was wont to be made; and we sat down, and spake unto the women which resorted thither.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 14, 'And a certain woman named Lydia, a seller of purple, of the city of Thyatira, which worshipped God, heard us: whose heart the Lord opened, that she attended unto the things which were spoken of Paul.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 15, 'And when she was baptized, and her household, she besought us, saying, If ye have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come into my house, and abide there. And she constrained us.'),
  ('KJV', 'Acts', 44, 16, 16, 'And it came to pass, as we went to prayer, a certain damsel possessed with a spirit of divination met us, which brought her masters much gain by soothsaying:')
